INSERT INTO @tmpJokes (JokeId, Categories, JokeTxt, Attribution, ImageTxt) VALUES
 (1, 'Aging, Good Question!, Jobs, Science', 'If Moses were alive today, the Ten Commandments would be known as the Ten Best Practices, presented in PowerPoint and followed by 40 years of status meetings.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a modern-day Moses in business attire standing at a conference room podium. Behind him is a large screen with a colorful PowerPoint slide titled ''The Ten Best Practices'' featuring bullet points numbered 1 to 10. Moses holds a remote clicker in one hand and looks slightly overwhelmed but professional. Seated around a long table are diverse office workers in typical corporate clothing, looking bored or checking their watches. On the table are laptops, coffee cups, and notepads. A large office clock on the wall shows time passing quickly. In the background, a calendar is visible marking ''Year 1 to Year 40'' with repeated sticky notes labeled ''Status Meeting.'' The overall tone is light and funny, capturing the clash between ancient biblical events and modern corporate culture in a colorful cartoon style.'),
 (2, 'Bad Puns, Good Question!, Science', 'If poison is past it''s expiration date, is it more or less poisonous?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple kitchen with a bright window and a countertop. On the counter, there is a small, colorful bottle labeled ''Poison'' with a big, exaggerated expiration date sticker that looks very old and faded. Next to the bottle, a puzzled cartoon character with a raised eyebrow and a scratch on the head is holding the bottle, looking quizzically at the label. A question bubble above the character reads, ''If poison is past its expiration date, is it more or less poisonous?'' Nearby, a harmless-looking little mouse wearing glasses sits calmly, holding a clipboard with checkmarks, as if evaluating the poison. The style is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the confusion and irony. The background should be simple to keep the focus on the character and the bottle, with bright and cheerful colors to contrast the morbid topic in a funny way.'),
 (3, 'Bad Puns, Good Question!, Science', 'If practice makes perfect, and nobody''s perfect, why practice?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple room with a person sitting at a desk, practicing a skill like playing the piano or painting. The character looks puzzled and slightly frustrated, with a thought bubble above their head showing the phrase ''If practice makes perfect, and nobody''s perfect, why practice?'' Nearby, scattered sheets of music or sketches lie messily on the floor, reinforcing the idea of ongoing practice. The background includes a clock showing time passing and a small motivational poster on the wall humorously crossed out or altered to say something like ''Practice makes perfect?...'' The overall tone is lighthearted and whimsical, with exaggerated facial expressions and gentle, rounded lines typical of a funny cartoon.'),
 (4, 'Bad Puns, Insults, Quotes', 'If Satan ever loses his hair, there will be hell toupee', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a fiery, classic depiction of hell with red and orange flames around. In the center, a devilish character with small horns, red skin, a mischievous grin, and an exaggerated bald spot on his head is looking surprised. Next to him is a floating toupee with little devil horns attached, as if it belongs to him. The toupee is stylized to look like it''s made of flames or fiery hair. The background includes pitchforks stuck in the ground and small flames flickering up. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and simple cartoon lines fostering a comedic vibe rather than anything scary or dark.'),
 (5, 'Aging, Animals, Bad Puns, Science', 'If swimming is good for your shape, then why do the whales look the way they do?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in an ocean environment. In the foreground, a large, plump whale with a friendly, puzzled expression is floating lazily near the water surface. The whale looks round and chubby, clearly not fitting the typical idea of ''good shape.'' Nearby, a slender, fit human swimmer in a classic swimming cap and goggles is actively swimming and looking confusedly at the whale. Around them, a few small fish with exaggerated, toned physiques are swimming energetically, adding contrast. The background should show a sunny sky and gentle waves, keeping a lighthearted and cheerful tone. The style should be colorful and cartoony with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor of the whale''s shape despite swimming being ''good for your shape.'' No text is required in the image, but the scene should clearly communicate the joke''s playful question about swimming and body shape.'),
 (6, 'Facts, Good Question!, Science', 'If the population of China walked past you in single file, the line would never end because of the rate of reproduction.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a long, winding, endless line of people stretching from the foreground far into the distance, curving beyond the horizon. Each person is drawn as a simple, friendly-looking figure to represent the population of China. Near the front of the line, a single surprised or bewildered person is standing, looking sideways at the line. Above the scene, include a playful banner or sign reading ''Single File Line.'' To emphasize the joke about reproduction, small cartoon baby storks or baby figures can be subtly integrated into the crowd, making it clear that the line keeps growing. The overall style should be lighthearted and colorful, ensuring a non-threatening, funny atmosphere that illustrates the concept of an endless line due to continuous population growth.'),
 (7, 'Bad Puns, Shopping Jokes', 'If the shoe fits, buy the other one too.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person standing in front of a shoe store display. The person is trying on one brightly colored sneaker and has a big smile on their face. The display shelf shows a matching empty spot next to the worn shoe, implying the other shoe is waiting to be bought. Around the character are speech bubbles with playful text like ''If the shoe fits...'' and the person thinking ''Better get the other one too!'' The background shows typical shoe store elements like shelves filled with various shoes and a friendly sales clerk giving a thumbs-up. The style should be lighthearted and exaggerated, with the character wearing casual clothes and the shoes being slightly oversized for comedic effect.'),
 (8, 'Bad Puns, Pessimistic, Quotes', 'If there was an award for most pessimistic, I probably wouldn''t even be nominated.', 'Jim Gaffigan', 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a character standing on a small stage at an award ceremony. The character looks unimpressed and somewhat gloomy, wearing semi-formal clothes and holding a microphone with one hand. A large banner overhead says ''Most Pessimistic Award.'' The audience in front of the stage looks enthusiastic and ready to cheer while holding programs and clapping, but the character looks detached and disinterested, as if thinking, ''I probably wouldn''t even be nominated.'' Include a trophy stand next to the character with a quirky, empty pedestal labeled ''Most Pessimistic Award'' to emphasize the joke. The setting is indoors with spotlights and cheerful decorations to contrast with the character’s pessimism. Keep the overall art style light, simple, and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humor without any negative or harsh tones.'),
 (9, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Computers, Engineers', 'If this computer were a horse, I''d have to shoot it!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a frustrated person sitting at a desk with an old, slow-looking computer on it. The computer has exaggerated horse-like features such as ears, a mane, and a tail attached to the monitor and tower. The person is holding a large red toolbox in one hand and looking exasperated, while the computer-horse is sluggish, with sleepy eyes and a patchy mane, maybe with a small thought bubble showing a snail or a loading icon. The background is a simple office or home workspace with a coffee mug and scattered papers. The overall tone is light and comical, emphasizing the computer’s slowness by likening it to a worn-out horse that one might ''shoot'' to put out of its misery, but without any violence shown explicitly—just humorous expressions and body language.'),
 (10, 'Good Question!, Pessimistic, Politics, Quotes', 'If voting changed anything, they''d make it illegal.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused and skeptical voter standing in front of a voting booth. The voter is scratching their head while holding a ballot paper with a big red ''X'' on it. Behind the booth, there''s a large, exaggerated government official or politician sneaking away with a mischievous smirk, holding a rulebook labeled ''Laws'' with a page flipped open to ''Make Voting Illegal.'' In the background, a large sign hangs above the voting area that says, ''Voting Day,'' but it looks slightly crooked or worn out. The style is bright and colorful, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the irony and cynicism of the joke. No violence or aggression, just playful cynicism portrayed in a friendly way.'),
 (11, 'Bad Puns, Did''ya Hear, Pessimistic', 'If we can''t fix it, it ain''t broke.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person casually sitting on a broken, visibly cracked chair with one leg shorter than the others, causing it to wobble heavily. The person appears completely relaxed and unconcerned, perhaps sipping a cup of coffee or reading a newspaper. Nearby, a friend or another person looks puzzled or confused, staring at the chair’s broken leg. The setting is a simple living room with a small side table and a floor lamp. There should be a speech bubble above the relaxed person saying, ''If we can''t fix it, it ain''t broke.'' The overall tone is light and playful, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor of ignoring the problem because it hasn’t been fixed yet. The style should be colorful and cartoonish, with clean lines and a comedic, cheerful vibe.'),
 (12, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Butter, Pessimistic', 'If we removed all the margarine on earth the world would be a much butter place', NULL, 'A lighthearted cartoon scene depicting planet Earth as a giant round buttered toast. The Earth has a smiling face, with continents shaped like chunks of golden butter melting across the surface. Surrounding the Earth are several oversized sticks and tubs of margarine with sad, droopy expressions, looking like they are being pushed away with little cartoon arms. Above the planet, whimsical text or a banner reads: ''A much butter place!'' The background is bright and cheerful with a clear blue sky and a few fluffy clouds. The overall art style should be simple, colorful, and playful to highlight the pun, without any people or complex elements.'),
 (13, 'Aging, Bad Puns, Good Question!, Humor about Gender', 'If women ran the world, there would be no war.  Just a bunch of countries not talking to each other', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two groups of people on opposite sides of a globe. One side shows women with confident, determined expressions, arms crossed or pointing fingers, standing on a cartoon-style colorful country labeled with flags. On the other side, another group of women with crossed arms, backs turned, glaring or giving side-eye looks, clearly not speaking to each other. Between them is a globe emphasizing division, with jagged lines or a crack showing separation. The atmosphere is lighthearted, with exaggerated facial expressions of mild annoyance or stubbornness, no anger or violence. The background is simple with a blue sky and a few peace symbols floating around to contrast the lack of communication with the theme of peace. The artistic style is bright, cartoonish, and playful with clear outlines and exaggerated body language to emphasize the joke’s idea of diplomacy replaced by silent standoffs rather than war.'),
 (14, 'Facts, Humor, Pessimistic, School, Students', 'If you are given an open-book exam, you will forget your book.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a student sitting at a school desk looking puzzled and distressed. On the desk is a large, clearly open textbook labeled ''Exam Book,'' but the student is scratching their head as if confused and has a thought bubble showing an empty bookshelf or a book flying away. Behind the student is a teacher holding a stopwatch and looking amused. The classroom has a blackboard with the words ''Open-Book Exam Today!'' written on it. The overall mood is light and funny, emphasizing the irony that having the book doesn’t help because the student either forgot to bring it or forgot how to use it during the test.'),
 (15, 'Good Question!, Humor, Pessimistic, Quotes', 'If you can smile when things go wrong, you have someone in mind to blame.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person (gender-neutral) standing in a cluttered room where a series of small mishaps have just happened: a spilled cup of coffee on the floor, a broken picture frame hanging crookedly on the wall, and a computer screen displaying an error message. The person is smiling slyly, with one hand behind their back holding a finger pointed subtly as if blaming someone else. In the background, a shadowy silhouette of another character (just an outline with a surprised or worried expression) peeks from around a doorway. The overall atmosphere is light-hearted with exaggerated facial expressions. The style should be clean and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated cartoon proportions to emphasize the humor in calmly smiling despite chaos.'),
 (16, 'Dad, Good Question!, Humor, Quotes', 'If you can''t convince them, confuse them.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in front of an audience, trying to give a serious presentation. The presenter is holding a pointer stick and pointing at a complicated, nonsensical chart filled with jumbled numbers and symbols that don''t make sense. The audience looks bewildered and confused, with some scratching their heads and others with swirling question marks above their heads. The presenter has a sly smile, as if intentionally trying to confuse rather than convince. The setting is a simple conference room or classroom with a whiteboard or projector screen. The overall vibe is light and playful, emphasizing confusion as a tactic.'),
 (17, 'Bad Puns, Dad, Good Question!, Humor', 'If you do something tonight that you''ll regret in the morning---sleep late!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a bedroom early in the morning with a cozy bed in the center. The main character is a person happily sleeping in, snuggled under the covers with a big smile on their face and a relaxed posture. On the bedside table, there''s an alarm clock showing a late morning time (like 11:00 AM). A window reveals bright sunlight streaming in, indicating it''s well past the usual waking hour. To add to the humor, include a small thought bubble above the sleeper with the text: ''Best regret ever!'' The room should have light, cheerful colors and a warm atmosphere to emphasize comfort and relaxation. No other people should be in the scene, and nothing violent or inappropriate. The overall vibe is lighthearted and relatable, emphasizing the joke’s idea that sleeping late is a harmless regret.'),
 (18, 'Dad, Good Question!', 'If you don''t know where you are, you shouldn''t be there.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person standing at a fork in the road with exaggeratedly large, confusing road signs pointing in opposite directions. The person is scratching their head with a puzzled expression. Nearby, a wise old owl perches on a signpost labeled ''You Should Know Where You Are.'' The background is a simple, sunny countryside path with trees and bushes. The style is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors, and the characters have big eyes and expressive faces to emphasize the confusion and humor of the situation.'),
 (19, 'Bad Puns, Dad, Good Question!', 'If you have half as much fun reading these cookies as we had assembling them, then we had twice as much fun as you.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene showing a cheerful group of diverse people sitting around a table cluttered with puzzle pieces shaped like giant fortune cookies. Some people are laughing and fitting puzzle pieces together, while others hold up a finished cookie proudly. On the table, a stack of oversized fortune cookies is visible. Above the group, a large whimsical banner reads: ''Half as much fun reading these as we had assembling them!'' The atmosphere is casual and lighthearted, with playful facial expressions and exaggerated movements to emphasize the fun of assembling the cookies. The background is simple with warm colors and a few scattered confetti pieces to highlight the joyful mood.'),
 (20, 'Facts, Good Question!', 'If you have three quarters, four dimes, and four pennies, you have $1.19.  You also have the largest amount of money in coins without being able to make change for a dollar.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a kitchen table with coins spread out in front of them. The coins include three quarters, four dimes, and four pennies, each clearly visible and labeled. The person has a puzzled, slightly frustrated expression while staring at the coins. A thought bubble above their head shows a dollar bill with a question mark, emphasizing the challenge of making exact change for one dollar. On the table is a small coin jar labeled ''Change Jar'' and a calculator with a confused face emoticon on its screen. The background is a simple, cozy kitchen setting with minimal details so the focus remains on the coins and the person''s expression. The overall style is colorful, cartoonish, and lighthearted to highlight the quirky and tricky nature of the joke without any negativity or violence.'),
 (21, 'Bad Puns, Dad, Humor, Insults', 'If you lend someone $20, and you never see that person again, it was probably worth it.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing two characters in a casual setting, like a small park bench or a street corner. On one side, a person looks slightly annoyed but resigned, holding an empty wallet or a torn twenty-dollar bill with a sad face. On the other side, the second character is happily walking away quickly, looking over their shoulder with a mischievous grin and waving goodbye. Include visual cues like the money clearly shown as borrowed, a speech bubble above the annoyed character saying, ''If you lend someone $20...'' and a thought bubble above the departing character implying they won’t be seen again. Make the style lighthearted and playful, using exaggerated facial expressions and bright, simple colors to emphasize the joke’s humor without any negativity or violence.'),
 (22, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Insults, Pessimistic', 'If you make something idiot proof, they''ll just make a better idiot.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in a simple, colorful style. In the foreground, a person with a confused and somewhat silly facial expression is holding a very basic, oversized instruction manual labeled ''Idiot Proof Device.'' Nearby is a machine or gadget with several big, obvious safety features and warning signs, like large red buttons, locks, and flashing lights, clearly designed to be foolproof. In the background, another person with an exaggerated, goofy look—wearing mismatched clothes and tripping over their own feet—is interacting with the gadget, somehow causing a small harmless accident or mishap (like pressing the wrong button or fumbling the gadget). The setting is a kitchen or a workshop with tools and everyday objects, adding a casual vibe. Above or beside the scene, a comic-style speech bubble shows the phrase ''If you make something idiot proof, they’ll just make a better idiot.'' The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing irony and the humor of human error despite attempts at simplicity.'),
 (23, 'Dad, Good Question!, Humor, Pessimistic', 'If you must choose between two evils, choose the one you''ve never tried before.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two mischievous-looking ''evil'' characters standing side by side, each representing a different evil. One character looks like a classic devil with small horns and a pitchfork, smirking confidently. The other character is a quirky, friendly monster with an exaggerated goofy grin. In the foreground, a cartoon person with a confused but amused expression stands at a forked path or crossroads, scratching their head, looking toward the two evils. The background is light and colorful with simple shapes to keep the mood playful and funny. The signpost between the two evils reads ''Choose Your Evil''. The style should be simple, bold, and colorful with expressive faces to emphasize the joke’s meaning about choosing between two undesirable options but humorously opting for the unfamiliar one.'),
 (24, 'Good Question!, Humor, Pessimistic', 'If you must fall on your face, then do it in bed.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon of a person tripping and about to fall, but instead of falling onto a hard floor, they land face-first onto a cozy, fluffy bed with a big smile on their face. The bedroom is bright and cheerful, with soft pillows and a warm blanket on the bed. The person has exaggerated surprise and relief on their expression as they gently flop onto the bed. Around them, playful details like a startled alarm clock on the nightstand and a small cat watching curiously add to the lighthearted mood. The cartoon style is simple, colorful, and exaggerated for comedic effect, focusing on the safe ''falling on your face'' scenario in bed rather than a painful one.'),
 (25, 'Bad Puns, Engineers, Good Question!', 'If you only have a hammer, you tend to see every problem as a nail.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing in the middle of a room cluttered with various objects representing different problems. The person, looking slightly confused or determined, is holding a large, oversized hammer in both hands. Surrounding them are objects like a computer with a cracked screen, a leaky faucet dripping water, a broken clock showing the wrong time, and a flat tire leaning against a wall. Each object has a little label or symbol hinting at its problem. The person is about to hit one of these non-nail objects with the hammer, implying they''re trying to solve every problem the same way. The style is bright and colorful, with exaggerated expressions and playful details to emphasize the humor and absurdity without any violence or negativity.'),
 (26, 'Animals, Science', 'If you put a raisin in a glass of champagne, it will keep floating to the top and sinking to the bottom.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a tall, elegant champagne glass filled with bubbly champagne. Inside the glass, a single raisin is depicted with animated eyes and tiny arms, looking surprised or dizzy as it repeatedly floats up to the surface and sinks back down. Bubbles surround the raisin, with a few popping at the top of the glass. The background is simple and light to keep focus on the glass and the active raisin. The style is playful and exaggerated, capturing the movement of the raisin going up and down in a loop, creating a fun, lively vibe.'),
 (27, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'If you replace the W with a T in What, Where and When... you get the answer to each of them.', NULL, 'A lighthearted cartoon scene showing three large colorful question words arranged side by side: ''What'', ''Where'', and ''When''. Each word has friendly cartoon eyes and smiling faces. Above them, a large whimsical letter ''W'' is shown being playfully swapped out by a cheerful animated letter ''T'' using cartoon hands or arms. As the letter ''T'' replaces the ''W'' in each word, the resulting transformed words appear below them as humorous answers: ''That'', ''There'', and ''Then'', each with equally cheerful expressions. The background is simple and bright with a few question marks and lightbulbs floating around, symbolizing ideas and solving riddles. The overall style is colorful, fun, and exaggerated in a classic comic strip or children''s book illustration style, aimed at conveying a clever wordplay joke in a non-threatening, happy manner.'),
 (28, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'If you say ''gullible'' really slowly, it sounds like ''oranges''', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene set in a classroom or casual setting where a person is whispering something to a friend. The whispering person has a mischievous grin and is leaning close to the other person''s ear. The friend looks puzzled with wide eyes and a slightly open mouth, trying to understand what is being said. Around them, small floating speech bubbles show the word ''gullible'' written very slowly and stretched out, and another bubble next to it shows the word ''oranges'' to visually represent the joke. The background is simple and cheerful, with a few playful details like a clock on the wall and a small plant or poster, emphasizing a lighthearted, playful atmosphere. The expressions and body language should be exaggerated and cartoonish to underline the joke''s silly and funny nature.'),
 (29, 'Bad Puns, Jobs', 'If you see me talking to myself, just move along. I''m self-employed and having a staff meeting.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in front of a mirror, talking to their own reflection as if holding a serious meeting. The person is dressed casually, with arms slightly raised in a talking gesture, while their reflection looks attentive and engaged. Around them, include simple office-like items — a small desk with a coffee mug labeled ''CEO'', a notepad, and maybe a tiny nameplate that says ''Staff Meeting''. The background is a cozy home office or living room to emphasize a self-employed setting. The style should be lighthearted and fun, with exaggerated facial expressions showing the person earnestly talking and the reflection ''listening''. No other people are in the scene, highlighting the joke''s punchline about talking to oneself as a staff meeting.'),
 (30, 'Bad Puns, Shopping Jokes', 'If you see someone shoplifting an iPhone, are you an iWitness?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a brightly colored, modern electronics store. In the foreground, a person with wide eyes and a surprised expression is pointing at another person who is slyly slipping an iPhone into their jacket pocket. Above them, a big, bold comic-style caption reads ''iWitness?'' with a question mark. The store shelves are lined with obvious tech gadgets like smartphones, tablets, and headphones. Other shoppers in the background are casually browsing or looking amused. The style should be lighthearted with exaggerated facial expressions and a clear focus on the iPhone and the witnesses'' reaction, emphasizing the pun with a playful and friendly vibe without any threat or aggression.'),
 (31, 'Good Question!', 'If you take life too seriously, it ceases to be amusing.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person dressed in formal business attire sitting rigidly at a desk with a large, serious expression. The person is surrounded by stacks of paperwork, a computer, and a clock showing the passing of time. Hanging on the wall is a framed motivational poster that reads, ''Life is Serious Business!'' In contrast, next to the desk, there''s a small colorful clown juggling or a playful puppy with a silly hat, symbolizing amusement and fun. The overall tone is lighthearted, with exaggerated expressions on the serious character’s face to show stiffness and the playful elements standing out as bright and inviting. The style is simple, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the contrast between seriousness and amusement without any threatening or sensitive content.'),
 (32, 'Good Question!, Quotes', 'If you tell the truth, you don''t have to remember anything.', NULL, 'A simple humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a desk with a thought bubble above their head. Inside the bubble, there are two contrasting images: on one side, a tangled, complicated web of different storylines symbolizing lies and confusion, with question marks and sticky notes; on the other side, a clear, straight path labeled ''Truth'' leading to a relaxed, smiling brain wearing glasses, indicating ease and clarity. The person at the desk looks relaxed and confident, smiling as they point at the clear path in the thought bubble. The background is minimal, focusing attention on the thought bubble and the character''s expression, with light pastel colors to keep it friendly and playful.'),
 (33, 'Good Question!', 'If you think education is expensive, then try ignorance.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters in a simple classroom setting. On the left, a confident, well-dressed person is holding a large, shiny diploma or a big textbook labeled ''Education'' with dollar signs on it, looking proud but slightly stressed by the cost. On the right, a confused-looking character is standing next to a huge pile of bills labeled ''Ignorance Costs,'' looking overwhelmed and worried, with cartoonish sweat drops flying off their head. Between them, a small price tag hovers in the air reading ''Try Ignorance.'' The background can include a chalkboard with a math problem or alphabet letters, and a small piggy bank on a desk with coins scattered around. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the joke''s point about the cost of ignorance versus education.'),
 (34, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'If you think nobody cares about you, try missing a couple of payments.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy living room. In the center, show a person sitting on a couch looking sad and lonely, with a thought bubble above their head containing a small ghostly figure symbolizing ''nobody cares.'' Next to the couch, place a mailbox or a small stack of overdue payment bills clearly marked ''PAST DUE'' with big, bold letters. From the mailbox or bills, depict tiny, angry cartoon character-versions of the bills or a stern-looking creditor figure glaring at the person threateningly but comically. Add exaggerated facial expressions showing the person''s surprised or worried reaction as these ''billing characters'' loom over them. The style should be lighthearted, with bright colors and simple lines to emphasize the joke’s punchline without appearing harsh. Include details like a clock on the wall to imply time passing and a simple background to keep the focus on the interaction between the person, the ''nobody cares'' ghostly figure, and the payment bills.'),
 (35, 'Good Question!, Humor, Jobs', 'If you think talk is cheap, try hiring a lawyer.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a lawyer''s office desk looking shocked or surprised while holding a very large invoice or bill marked ''Legal Fees.'' The lawyer, dressed in a suit with a confident smile, is pointing at the bill. Around them, scattered papers, a clock showing time passing quickly, and a speech bubble from the person saying ''Talk is cheap? Try hiring a lawyer!'' make the joke clear. The scene should be bright and colorful with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the punchline, with no aggressive or negative vibes.'),
 (36, 'Word Play', 'If you think the way to a man''s heart is through his stomach you''re aiming too high.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a man standing with a slightly puzzled and worried expression while holding a large heart-shaped target above his head. Below him, a small plate of food (like a hamburger or a slice of pizza) lies on the ground looking tiny and insignificant compared to the big red heart target. Around the man, arrows aimed at the heart target are flying wildly but missing completely, some hitting the plate on the floor. The background is simple and cheerful, with light pastel colors. The scene visually represents the saying "the way to a man''s heart is through his stomach" but highlights the joke by showing the heart being set much higher than the plate of food, emphasizing the idea that aiming at the stomach (food) is aiming too high. The cartoon style is exaggerated and playful with clean lines and expressive faces, making it clear that this is a light-hearted pun.'),
 (37, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'If you want the rainbow, you gotta put up with the rain.', NULL, 'A cheerful cartoon scene showing a rainbow brightly arcing across a partly cloudy sky. In the foreground, a happy character holding a large colorful umbrella is standing in the rain with big raindrops falling around. The character looks content and is smiling, enjoying the rain while looking up at the rainbow. There are simple cartoon clouds releasing rain, and sunlight breaking through to create the rainbow. The style is lighthearted and humorous, with soft colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the positive attitude toward enduring rain for the reward of a rainbow.'),
 (38, 'Humor, Science', 'If you yelled for 8 years, 7 months and 6 days, you will have produced enough sound energy to heat one cup of coffee.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a tired, cartoonish person standing in a cozy kitchen. The person looks exhausted, with messy hair and cheeks puffed out as if they''ve been yelling non-stop for a very long time. Surround them with speech bubbles filled with sound waves or exclamation marks to represent yelling. Nearby on a counter or table, place a steaming cup of coffee with visible rising steam. To emphasize the time span, include a large calendar or clock in the background showing the passage of "8 years, 7 months, and 6 days." The kitchen environment should be light-hearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions to add humor. The overall tone is funny and slightly absurd, highlighting the idea that yelling for such a long time could generate enough energy to heat a cup of coffee.'),
 (39, 'Humor, Jobs', 'If your boss calls tomorrow, do you want me to find out his name?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple office environment. In the foreground, a casual employee is on the phone with a wide-eyed, surprised expression. The employee is holding a smartphone to their ear with one hand while the other hand gestures as if asking a question. Nearby, a coworker leans in, smirking mischievously, as if they just delivered the punchline. The office background includes a desk with scattered papers, a computer monitor, and a coffee mug. A calendar on the wall shows the day marked as ''Tomorrow.'' The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the awkwardness of the question about the boss’s name in a funny, non-threatening way. The characters are drawn with exaggerated expressions and rounded features to enhance the comedic effect.'),
 (40, 'Animals, Good Question!, Humor', 'If your not the lead sled dog, the scenery never changes...', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a team of sled dogs harnessed together, pulling a sled across a snowy landscape. At the front is the lead sled dog, looking proud and happy, facing forward and clearly enjoying the view of the changing scenery—a mix of snowy mountains, trees, and a rising sun. Behind the lead dog are the other sled dogs, looking bored, tired, or annoyed, because they see only the backs of the dogs in front and the same unchanging white snow and sled runners. The background should emphasize the contrast between the exciting view for the lead dog and the monotonous, unchanging view seen by the other dogs. Include details like fur hats or scarves on the dogs for extra humor, and make the dogs expressive with big eyes and exaggerated facial expressions. The overall style should be bright, colorful, and cartoonish, highlighting the joke about perspective and effort in a playful, family-friendly manner.'),
 (41, 'Humor, Word Play', 'If you''re ever attached by a group of clowns, go for the juggler', NULL, 'Draw a colorful, humorous cartoon scene featuring a group of clowns standing together, looking mischievous and somewhat silly. In the foreground, show a slightly surprised person (with wide eyes) encountering the clowns. Among the clowns, highlight one juggling bright, bouncing balls or clubs. The setting is cheerful and circus-themed with balloons, juggling pins scattered on the ground, and a big red nose on each clown. The person in the scene is preparing to ''go for the juggler'' by pointing at or stepping toward the juggling clown with a confident but playful expression. The style is lighthearted and whimsical, focusing on exaggerated clown costumes, big shoes, colorful wigs, and face paint to emphasize the joke’s playful tone. No violence is shown, just an amusing encounter full of lively energy.'),
 (42, 'Humor, Science, Word Play', 'If you''re not part of the solution, you''re part of the precipitate.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple chemistry lab. In the foreground, a scientist character wearing a white lab coat and safety goggles looks slightly puzzled while holding a test tube with bubbling liquid. On the lab table in front of them, there is a clear glass beaker labeled ''Solution'' containing a blue liquid, sparkling and looking active. Next to it is a small pile of solid, grainy material labeled ''Precipitate'' with tiny particles clumping together. Above the scene floats a comic-style speech bubble with the joke text: ''If you''re not part of the solution, you''re part of the precipitate.'' The background has typical lab elements like shelves with colorful chemicals and periodic table posters, drawn in bright, cheerful cartoon style to emphasize the pun and lightheartedness of the joke.'),
 (43, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'If you''re sitting in public and a stranger takes the seat next to you, just stare straight ahead and say, ''Did you bring the money?''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a public park bench or in a busy waiting area, like a bus stop. The main character, a casually dressed person with a slightly confused but wary expression, is sitting on the bench looking straight ahead with a deadpan stare. A stranger, who looks like an ordinary passerby, is just sitting down right next to them, with a puzzled and slightly alarmed look. The main character’s mouth is open as if they have just said, ''Did you bring the money?'' The background shows subtle details like other benches, trees or a bus sign to emphasize the public setting. The style should be bright, simple, and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the awkwardness and surprise of the moment, making the humor clear without any aggressive or negative vibes.'),
 (44, 'Humor, Quotes', 'Ignorance is a lack of knowledge. Stupidity is ignorance with pride.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters side by side. On the left, a person looks confused and clueless, scratching their head with question marks floating above them, representing ignorance as a lack of knowledge. On the right, another person looks overly confident or smug, with their chest puffed out proudly and a big, goofy grin, representing stupidity as ignorance with pride. Both characters are in a simple office or classroom setting with a whiteboard behind them that reads the quote: ''Ignorance is a lack of knowledge. Stupidity is ignorance with pride.'' The style is lighthearted and exaggerated, emphasizing the difference in attitudes between the two characters without any hostility or negativity. Include bright, cheerful colors and cartoonish expressions to keep the tone funny and approachable.'),
 (45, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Ignorance is when you don''t know anything and somebody finds it out.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a simple classroom or living room setting. In the center, a character with a confused, clueless expression is shrugging their shoulders. Around them are floating question marks and empty thought bubbles to emphasize ignorance. Nearby, another character is holding a magnifying glass, leaning in with a curious and amused expression as if they have just discovered the clueless person''s ignorance. Add a subtle, lightbulb-shaped sign above the discoverer''s head to indicate the moment of realization. The style is playful and exaggerated, with bright colors and rounded shapes to keep the tone light and funny, no detail should be harsh or negative.'),
 (46, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'I''m afraid of elevators. I''ll be taking steps to avoid them.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a nervous-looking person standing next to an elevator in a building hallway. The elevator doors are open, revealing a shiny interior with buttons. The person is visibly hesitant with wide eyes and a hand raised as if saying no. Next to them, a cute staircase is personified with a friendly, inviting smile and little feet, waving them over to take the stairs instead. Above the scene, a speech bubble coming from the person says, "I''ll be taking steps to avoid them." The hallway is bright and simple, with clear elevator signs and a few floor indicators. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions on the character and the friendly staircase to emphasize the pun on ''taking steps.'' No dark or intense elements.'),
 (47, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'I''m an incorrigible punster -- so don''t incorrige me!', NULL, 'A cheerful cartoon scene featuring a quirky character standing confidently in the center. The character is holding a large, colorful dictionary labeled ''Puns & Wordplay'' in one hand, while with the other hand they make a playful ''stop'' gesture. The character wears round glasses and a big smile, emphasizing their love for puns. Around them are several floating word bubbles containing playful pun words and small doodles, like a broken pencil labeled ''incorrigible'' and a crossed-out word ''incorrige'' with a red X. The background is simple with bright colors, perhaps a classroom or library setting, adding to the linguistic vibe. The overall tone is lighthearted and humorous with exaggerated cartoon expressions that convey the character''s passion for puns and wordplay in a fun, non-threatening way.'),
 (48, 'Humor', 'I''m as confused as a baby in a topless bar.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a very cute, wide-eyed baby sitting in the middle of a colorful, lively topless bar. The baby looks utterly puzzled with raised eyebrows and a small open mouth, clearly overwhelmed. Around the baby, cheerful adults are dancing and socializing, some holding drinks, but the bar is cartoonish and light-hearted with decorations like neon signs, bar stools, and a jukebox in the background. The lighting is playful, with exaggerated expressions on the adults to highlight the baby''s confusion. The baby could be wearing a simple diaper and maybe a pacifier hanging from its neck, emphasizing innocence and contrast with the bar setting.'),
 (49, 'Word Play', 'I''m going to try on my reversible jacket now and see how it turns out', NULL, 'Cartoon-style image of a person standing in front of a full-length mirror in a brightly lit bedroom. The person is halfway through putting on a large, comically oversized reversible jacket, with one side already on and the other side inside out but clearly visible. They have a puzzled and curious expression as they try to see how the jacket looks. The jacket should appear exaggerated with big reversible zippers and contrasting colors or patterns on each side, making it obvious it can be flipped inside out. The room includes simple furniture like a chair with clothes on it, a small plant, and a poster on the wall to add life, but the focus remains on the person and the jacket. The style should be lighthearted and humorous, emphasizing their playful experimentation with the jacket.'),
 (50, 'Humor, Word Play', 'I''m immortal - so far.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a cheerful ghost standing confidently in the middle of a simple, bright background. The ghost has a friendly smile and thumbs up, wearing a casual ''I''m Immortal'' T-shirt. Around the ghost are little cartoon-style hourglasses and calendar pages fluttering away, indicating the passage of time. A small tombstone with the word ''So Far'' humorously written on it is placed next to the ghost, emphasizing the joke’s cautious optimism. The style is light, clean, and colorful, evoking a playful and humorous atmosphere without any darkness or spookiness.'),
 (51, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'I''m in shape ... round''s a shape isn''t it?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person looking into a mirror in a brightly lit bathroom. The person has a cheerful, slightly cheeky expression and a noticeably round body shape. They are standing with hands on hips, posing proudly. The mirror shows a reflection with the same round shape, emphasizing the joke that round is a shape too. Around the character, simple bathroom details like a sink, a towel hanging on a rack, and a small plant on the windowsill add context. The style is light-hearted and playful, with exaggerated roundness to emphasize the humor.'),
 (52, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'I''m making a list of reasons to move to Switzerland. The flag is a big plus.', NULL, 'A cheerful cartoon scene showing a person standing next to a large Swiss flag mounted on a flagpole. The person is holding a clipboard and pen, looking happy and thoughtful. The Swiss flag is bright red with a big white plus sign in the center. Around the person are small signs or notes floating in the air with funny reasons to move to Switzerland, with the largest and most prominent note showing a big white plus symbol emphasizing the pun. The background is a simple outdoor setting with green grass and a clear blue sky, giving a lighthearted, positive feel. The style is colorful, friendly, and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions on the person to enhance the humor of the ''big plus'' joke, without any complex details or distractions.'),
 (53, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'I''m most efficient when nobody is looking.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting at a cluttered desk with papers, a laptop, and a coffee cup. The individual is wearing casual clothes and has a sly, mischievous grin while stealthily typing or working. Behind them, a large window shows an empty room with a ''No Entry'' sign or a ''Help Wanted'' poster to emphasize solitude. In the background, a clock shows normal work hours to imply they''re being productive only when unobserved. The style should be lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the exaggerated expression of secret efficiency without showing anyone else in the room.'),
 (54, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'I''m not a complete idiot, some parts are missing!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing with a goofy, confused expression on their face. Their body is drawn like a simple puzzle with missing pieces—some of the head and torso parts are obviously absent, creating gaps that float nearby. The person wears casual clothes and has exaggerated, wide eyes and a big, silly grin that suggests they are playfully acknowledging their ''incomplete'' state. Surrounding them are small labels or cartoonish tool icons like a wrench, screwdriver, and question marks, indicating the missing parts. The background is simple and cheerful to keep the focus on the character and their missing puzzle pieces. The overall tone is lighthearted and comical, suitable for a family-friendly cartoon strip or joke illustration.'),
 (55, 'Humor, Insults', 'I''m not being rude. You''re just insignificant.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters standing face-to-face. The first character looks calm and polite, with a slight, innocent smile, raising one hand in a gentle, reassuring gesture. The second character appears surprised and slightly offended, eyes wide and mouth open mid-reaction. The setting is simple, with a plain background to keep focus on the interaction. Above the calm character is a speech bubble that reads, "I''m not being rude. You''re just insignificant." The style should be lighthearted and exaggerated, with expressive facial features to highlight the humor without being mean-spirited. No violent or aggressive body language; the mood is playful sarcasm.'),
 (56, 'Humor, Word Play', 'I''m not breaking the rules - I''m just testing their elasticity.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person in casual clothes stretching a large rubber band labeled ''rules'' between their hands. The person has a playful grin and exaggeratedly stretched arms, with the rubber band extending and twisting in a way that looks elastic and flexible. Around them is a setting like an office or classroom with a few simple desks and chairs, and a small stack of rulebooks or a sign that says ''Rules'' nearby. The background is light and simple, focusing on the stretchy rubber band and the person''s animated effort to stretch it. The overall tone is lighthearted and whimsical, emphasizing the idea of flexible rule-breaking without any confrontation.'),
 (57, 'Humor, Word Play', 'I''m not in good enough shape to exercise.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person, slightly out of shape, sitting on a couch surrounded by various exercise equipment like dumbbells, a yoga mat, and a jump rope. The person looks tired and is holding a remote control in one hand and a bag of chips in the other. A thought bubble above their head shows a tired, sweaty version of themselves struggling to lift a weight, emphasizing their lack of motivation or energy to exercise. The room is cozy with a TV in front, displaying a fitness workout program that the person clearly isn''t engaging with. The overall tone is lighthearted and relatable, with exaggerated expressions to highlight the joke about not being in ''good enough shape'' to exercise.'),
 (58, 'Humor, Word Play', 'I''m not indecisive, am I?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing in front of two open doors, both looking identical and equally appealing. The person has a puzzled expression, scratching their head, clearly unsure which door to choose. Above their head, two thought bubbles show conflicting ideas: one with a question mark and the other with an exclamation mark. The background is simple, perhaps an office or hallway setting, to emphasize the indecision. The style is light and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions and bright colors to highlight the comedic confusion.'),
 (59, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'I''m not loafing. I work so fast I''m always finished.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a relaxed, laid-back loaf of bread with a small, comical face, sitting comfortably on a tiny office chair behind a desk cluttered with papers. The loaf is leaning back with its arms behind its head, smiling confidently. A clock on the wall shows time passing quickly. Nearby, a tired-looking human coworker is frantically working, with sweat drops flying off their head. The loaf of bread has a small nameplate on the desk that says ''Employee of the Month.'' The overall style is lighthearted and exaggerated, capturing the pun that the loaf is not ''loafing'' (idling) but instead is so fast that they finish work instantly.'),
 (60, 'Good Question!, Word Play', 'I''m not sure why the call child birth delivery... shouldn''t it be called takeout?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a cozy, brightly colored hospital room. In the center, a pregnant woman lies in a hospital bed, looking amused and holding a takeout menu in one hand while her other hand rests on her belly. Next to the bed, a cheerful nurse or doctor holds a large takeout food container with a newborn baby peeking out, wrapped in a tiny blanket like a ''delivered order.'' Above them, a big speech bubble from the woman says, "Shouldn''t childbirth be called takeout?" In the background, typical hospital details like an IV stand, heart monitor, and baby crib are visible. The overall mood is light, funny, and playful, with exaggerated cartoonish expressions and bright colors to emphasize the joke about childbirth resembling a food takeout experience.'),
 (61, 'Humor, Word Play', 'I''m not unemployed. I''m a consultant.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a casually dressed person sitting at a small desk in a messy home office or living room. They have a relaxed, slightly smug expression while typing on a laptop, with a coffee mug next to them labeled ''World''s Best Consultant.'' Around them, scattered papers and a calendar marked with sparse appointments suggest a lack of actual work. The room includes a couch with a few video game controllers and a TV in the background, emphasizing a laid-back atmosphere. A speech bubble above the person reads, "I''m not unemployed. I''m a consultant." The overall style should be lighthearted and comical, using bright colors and exaggerated expressions to highlight the irony of calling unemployment "consulting." No stressful or serious elements, just a playful take on the phrase.'),
 (62, 'Humor, Word Play', 'I''m out of my mind, but please leave a message.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a cheerful, slightly disheveled cartoon brain character standing next to a classic office answering machine. The brain has wide, friendly eyes and a goofy smile. Beside it, there''s a phone on a desk with a note that says ''Please leave a message.'' The background is a simple, bright office setting with a calendar and a small potted plant on the desk. The brain character looks as if it has just stepped away, leaving a humorous ''message'' sign with an empty speech bubble above it. The style should be lighthearted and whimsical, with bold outlines and vibrant colors to emphasize the silly, playful nature of the phrase ''I''m out of my mind, but please leave a message.'''),
 (63, 'Humor, Insults', 'I''m really easy easy to get along with, once you people learn to worship me.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a confident person standing proudly on a small pedestal or stage, with a bright spotlight shining down on them. The person is dressed in casual, slightly exaggerated ‘royal’ attire—like a crown slightly askew and a flowing cape—striking a boastful pose with arms crossed and a smug smile. Around them, a small group of diverse people stand looking puzzled or slightly annoyed, glancing sideways or whispering to each other, clearly unsure about the person’s demanding attitude. The background is simple, maybe a plain wall or an office breakroom setting to keep the focus on the characters. The mood is lighthearted and playful, with cartoonish, exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke''s ironic tone about wanting to be ‘worshipped’ to get along with someone.'),
 (64, 'Humor, Life', 'I''m trying to hide from reality but it always seems to find me.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a person hiding behind a small tree or a big bush in a park or backyard. The person looks comically anxious or worried, peeking out cautiously with wide eyes. Nearby, a tall, looming figure labeled ''Reality'' is casually strolling toward them with a friendly but inevitable expression, as if it’s about to gently tap the person on the shoulder. The figure can be drawn like a large, shadowy character wearing casual clothes and a small briefcase, symbolizing life responsibilities. The background is simple and cheerful, with a few clouds and birds to keep a lighthearted tone. The overall style is colorful and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor of trying to hide but being found anyway.'),
 (65, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'I''m waiting for the Mothership. What are you waiting for?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing outside at night, looking up at the starry sky with an expectant expression. The person is casually dressed and has one hand shading their eyes, as if scanning the heavens. In the sky, a classic flying saucer-style UFO—silver and slightly glowing—is descending with a beam of light shining down. The background includes a simple landscape of rolling hills or a backyard with a few trees and maybe a fence. The mood is light-hearted and quirky, with exaggerated, cartoonish features for the character and the spaceship to emphasize the joke’s playful tone.'),
 (66, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'Imagine this: A Jello sandwich. Toasted.', NULL, 'A colorful and playful cartoon scene showing a sandwich on a simple white plate. The sandwich is made with two slices of toasted bread, but instead of typical fillings, there is a bright, shiny, translucent red Jello layer in between the slices. The bread slices have exaggerated toasted textures with small, cute steam lines rising to suggest it''s freshly toasted. The Jello looks wobbly and glossy, almost jiggling. Next to the plate is a cheerful fork and knife, both with friendly, smiling faces. The background is a simple kitchen table with a checkered tablecloth, and soft pastel colors keep the tone light and humorous. The overall style is cartoonish and exaggerated, emphasizing the absurdity and silliness of a toasted Jello sandwich.'),
 (67, 'Animals, Humor', 'Impeccable: the ability to avoid being bitten by chickens.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a nervous person standing in the middle of a small farmyard filled with chickens. The person is wearing bright clothes and has wide eyes, leaning back slightly with arms raised defensively to avoid the flapping wings and snapping beaks of several angry chickens lunging towards them. The chickens look comically aggressive with exaggerated expressions, some mid-bite or peck, while one chicken is actually in mid-air as if about to attack. In the background, there is a rustic wooden fence, a small barn, and some scattered eggs on the ground. Above the person’s head is a comic-style thought bubble that says “Impeccable: the ability to avoid being bitten by chickens.” The overall style is colorful and lighthearted with exaggerated cartoon features to emphasize the humor of avoiding chicken bites like a special skill.'),
 (68, 'Humor, Jobs', 'Improve mail delivery -- mail the postal workers their pay.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing a mailroom with a group of cheerful postal workers. In the foreground, one postal worker is handing an oversized envelope labeled ''Paycheck'' to another worker who looks surprised and delighted. Around them, there are mailbags, letters, and parcels scattered about, emphasizing the mail delivery theme. On the wall behind them, a sign reads ''Improve Mail Delivery!'' with a smaller note underneath saying ''Mail the postal workers their pay.'' Everyone is depicted with exaggerated, friendly expressions to add a light-hearted, comedic tone. The style is simple and playful, suitable for a fun, workplace-related joke without any negative or stressful elements.'),
 (69, 'Facts, Humor, Science', 'In 10 minutes, a hurricane releases more energy than all the world''s nuclear weapons combined.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a giant, swirling hurricane cloud taking up most of the frame, with exaggerated wind spirals and raindrops flying wildly. Below the hurricane, a cartoon Earth is looking startled with wide eyes and sweat drops to emphasize the massive power. Around the Earth, several colorful, cartoon-style nuclear bombs with little arms and worried expressions stand side by side, looking dwarfed and intimidated by the hurricane. To add a lighthearted touch, include a small scoreboard or meter labeled ''Energy Output'' next to the hurricane, glowing very high, while the bombs'' meter is barely moving. The background should be bright and simple, focusing attention on the contrast between the huge natural storm and the tiny nuclear weapons. The style is playful and exaggerated, with no scary or violent details, to keep it funny and informative.'),
 (70, 'Humor, Pessimistic', 'In a million years, it won''t make any difference.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing next to a giant, ancient-looking hourglass filled with tiny grains of sand. The person has a clueless or indifferent expression, shrugging their shoulders with palms up. Around them is a vast landscape that looks unchanged through different eras: a dinosaur faintly visible in the background, a futuristic city poking up on the horizon, and a stone age campfire to one side. The hourglass stands prominently in the center, exaggerated in size to emphasize the passage of an enormous amount of time. The overall tone is lighthearted and whimsical, with bright colors and exaggerated cartoon-style features to emphasize the joke’s irony about time making no difference.'),
 (71, 'Humor, Life, Pessimistic', 'In a society of victims, nothing is anybody''s fault.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a courtroom without a judge or jury. Instead of people, there are exaggerated personifications of ''Victim'' characters scattered around, each looking overly dramatic with big, sad eyes and theatrical poses. The courtroom sign above reads ''Blame Court''. There are speech bubbles above the characters saying things like ''It''s not my fault!'' and ''Who could be to blame?'' In the center, there’s an empty spotlight or podium with a large question mark hovering above it, symbolizing no one is taking responsibility. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated with bright colors, clear outlines, and comical expressions to emphasize the irony of the situation. The background can include typical courtroom features like benches, a judge''s stand without anyone sitting, and scales of justice hanging crookedly, to reinforce the setting humorously.'),
 (72, 'Animals, Good Question!, History Humor', 'In ancient Egypt, priests plucked EVERY hair from their bodies, including their eyebrows and eyelashes.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in ancient Egypt, showcasing two Egyptian priests standing outside a large stone temple adorned with hieroglyphics and pyramids in the background. The priests are completely hairless from head to toe: no hair on their scalp, eyebrows, eyelashes, or body. One priest is humorously holding an ancient, oversized feather duster and a few tiny eyebrow tweezers, looking proud while examining his smooth, bald skin. The other priest squints humorously, trying to blink without eyelashes, with a slight exaggerated expression. Nearby, a basket filled with plucked hairs piled up high adds to the comic effect. The sky is bright blue with a blazing sun to emphasize the idea of hairless skin under the hot desert sun. The style should be lighthearted, colorful, and exaggerated, with bold outlines and facial expressions emphasizing the absurdity of being entirely hairless, especially the missing eyelashes and eyebrows which are usually subtle. The scene should avoid anything scary or unpleasant, focusing on the funny, odd historical fact in a playful way.'),
 (73, 'Humor, Life', 'In any household, junk accumulates to fill the storage space available.', NULL, 'Create a humorous cartoon scene set inside a cluttered house storage room or attic. The room is small and cramped with boxes, old furniture, bags, and odd household items stacked neatly but overflowing to completely fill every inch of the available shelf space, floor, and even spilling into the doorway. A confused or mildly exasperated person (gender-neutral, casual clothes) stands in the middle holding a measuring tape or ruler, looking at the jam-packed shelves with wide eyes or a raised eyebrow. Include a calendar or a clock on the wall to subtly imply the passage of time. The humor comes from showing the junk precisely filling all possible storage spots perfectly, as if the clutter magically expanded to fit the room exactly. The overall style should be colorful and exaggerated in a lighthearted, cartoonish way to emphasize the chaos without making it messy or unpleasant.'),
 (74, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'In case of doubt, make it sound convincing.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a person standing confidently at a podium or in a casual setting, speaking to an audience or another character. The speaker is gesturing with one hand, wearing a slightly mischievous smile, as if giving advice. Above or next to the person is a speech bubble containing the phrase, ''In case of doubt, make it sound convincing.'' The background is simple and uncluttered, maybe with a few question marks floating around to represent doubt. The audience or the other character looks uncertain or confused, emphasizing the humorous idea of bluffing one''s way through uncertainty. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to enhance the comedic tone.'),
 (75, 'Good Question!, Humor, Workplace', 'In case of fire, flee with the same reckless abandon that occurs each day at quitting time.', NULL, 'A busy office scene at quitting time depicted in a humorous cartoon style. Show a group of employees rushing out of the office door all at once with exaggerated expressions of excitement and urgency. Some people are half-running, others are leaping over desks or knocking over chairs. Papers and coffee mugs fly in the air to emphasize chaos. Near the door, a fire alarm is ringing with bright red lights flashing, and smoke is starting to appear coming from a small, harmless-looking fire in a trash bin. The scene should capture the similarity between the frantic quitting-time rush and an emergency fire escape, with an amusing and lighthearted tone. Include typical office elements like desks, computers, swivel chairs, and water coolers to set the workplace context.'),
 (76, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'In Cleveland, Ohio, it''s illegal to catch mice without a hunting license.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon set outside a modest house in Cleveland, Ohio. Center the image on a nervous, slightly confused cartoon mouse wearing tiny glasses and holding a small sign that says ''Looking for a job.'' Nearby is a human character dressed like a hunter, complete with a big hunting hat, camouflage jacket, and a large hunting rifle slung over their shoulder. The hunter is solemnly holding up a piece of paper labeled ''Hunting License'' and pointing toward the mouse as if explaining the law. Behind them, a city sign reads ''Welcome to Cleveland, Ohio.'' Maybe include a whimsical courthouse building in the background with a banner saying ''Strict Mouse Hunting Laws.'' The overall style is playful and colorful with exaggerated expressions to highlight the absurdity of needing a license to catch mice.'),
 (77, 'Facts, Humor, Pop Culture', 'In every episode of Seinfeld there is a Superman somewhere.', NULL, 'A colorful, lighthearted cartoon scene showing Jerry Seinfeld sitting on a sofa in a typical 1990s-style NYC apartment living room. Around him, multiple small Superman figures are hidden in various amusing spots: one perched on the bookshelf, another flying past the window, and one tucked in a cereal box on the kitchen counter nearby. The TV screen shows the Seinfeld logo, and there''s a speech bubble above Jerry''s head saying, ''Did you notice Superman?'' The background should include typical Seinfeld props like a red couch, a coffee table with magazines, and a lamp. The style should be simple and exaggerated for comedic effect, emphasizing the fun of spotting Superman references in every episode, with bright colors and smiling characters, no violence or anything inappropriate.'),
 (78, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'In general, people who have the most birthdays live the longest.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring an elderly person with a big, joyful smile surrounded by a large pile of birthday cakes stacked high like a tower. The person wears party hats of different colors and holds a calendar showing many marked birthdays. Around them, colorful balloons float, and confetti fills the air. The background could be a simple party room with a banner that reads "Happy Birthday!" emphasizing the idea of celebrating numerous birthdays. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated to enhance the humor of ''having the most birthdays means living the longest.'''),
 (79, 'Good Question!, Science', 'In reality, everything is less than zero. It just depends where your zero is.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing on a large number line spread out on the ground. The person looks puzzled or contemplative, scratching their head, while pointing at the zero point on the line. Around them, there are other numbers, both positive and negative, depicted as big colorful digits stretching to the left and right. In the background, a whimsical thought bubble shows two scenarios: one where zero is at sea level with negative numbers below and positive numbers above, and another where zero is set higher on a mountain, so everything below is less than zero. The style is lighthearted and fun, with exaggerated expressions and clear labeling on the number line to emphasize the concept that "everything is less than zero depending on where your zero is." The scene should feel educational yet silly, like a visual pun playing on perspective and relative positions on a line.'),
 (80, 'Animals, Facts, History Humor', 'In the last 4000 years, no new animals have been domesticated.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing an ancient timeline stretching left to right with a caveman on the far left trying to domesticate various wild animals like a mammoth and a saber-toothed tiger, looking hopeful. Moving right along the timeline, there are early civilizations with people attempting to domesticate animals such as wolves and wild cats, all failing or giving up. Finally, on the far right labeled ''Modern Day,'' a frustrated person in contemporary clothes is looking at a computer screen displaying a ''No new animals domesticated in 4000 years'' headline. Around them are familiar domesticated animals like dogs, cats, cows, horses, and chickens happily lounging. The tone is light and funny, with exaggerated facial expressions and clear indication that domestication attempts have stopped long ago. The background features a simple environment with trees, houses, and time markers indicating the passage of thousands of years. Overall, the cartoon style is colorful and playful with big eyes and round shapes for characters and animals to enhance humor.'),
 (81, 'Humor, Word Play', 'In the US we call it an elevator, but in the UK they call it a lift. I guess we''re all just raised differently.', NULL, 'A lighthearted, colorful cartoon set in the middle of a city street with an elevator and a lift next to each other. The elevator is a typical American-style elevator with shiny metal doors and buttons visible inside, labeled ''Elevator.'' The lift is a classic British-style red telephone booth turned into a lift, with the word ''Lift'' on the top sign. Two characters stand in front of each: an American person on the elevator side wearing casual clothes with a friendly smile, and a British person on the lift side wearing a bowler hat and holding a teacup with a smirk. Above them is a speech bubble from each, one saying, ''In the US we call it an elevator,'' and the other, ''In the UK they call it a lift.'' The background includes subtle landmarks like a small American flag and Big Ben for the UK to clarify the location humorously. The overall style is a cheerful, simple cartoon emphasizing cultural differences with a friendly tone.'),
 (417, 'Animals, Camping, Good Question!', 'Yo momma''s so fat the bears have to hide their food from her when she goes camping.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon set in a forest campsite. In the center, a large, friendly-looking woman with a big smile and casual camping clothes (like a flannel shirt and hiking boots) stands near a picnic table overflowing with food. Around her, three bears peek out from behind trees and bushes, looking both cautious and mischievous as they hide various foods like jars of honey, sandwiches, and picnic baskets from her. The scene includes typical camping elements like a tent, a campfire with a pot hanging over it, pine trees, and a bright blue sky. The overall tone is light, playful, and exaggerated to emphasize the joke, with the bears clearly acting as if they are hiding their stash from the woman rather than threatening her.'),
 (82, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'In the words of the great philosopher and handyman Red Green:  ''...and remember, if the girls don''t find you handsome, at least let them find you handy''.', NULL, 'A cheerful, humorous cartoon scene featuring a middle-aged man resembling a handyman dressed in a red flannel shirt, worn jeans, and a tool belt packed with typical tools like a hammer, screwdriver, and wrench. He wears a baseball cap slightly askew and has an endearing, slightly goofy grin. The man is in a cozy workshop with wooden shelves holding tools and bits of hardware, including a saw and nails. A speech bubble above him shows the quote: ''...and remember, if the girls don''t find you handsome, at least let them find you handy.'' Nearby, two smiling women glance approvingly at his handiwork, which is a slightly crooked but charmingly built birdhouse on a workbench. The scene has bright colors with a warm, inviting atmosphere. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish, emphasizing humor and relatability without any offensive content.'),
 (83, 'Humor, Language, Word Play', 'In which level of metalanguage are you now speaking?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a desk looking confused, surrounded by floating speech bubbles filled with words inside other words, like a series of nested boxes or Russian dolls illustrating layers of language. The person is scratching their head, with question marks above them. In front of the person, there''s a computer screen displaying a chat window or text conversation with increasingly complex overlapping dialogue bubbles, each labeled ''metalanguage level 1,'' ''metalanguage level 2,'' etc. The setting is a casual office or home workspace with a coffee mug and books titled ''Linguistics'' and ''Language Theory'' scattered on the desk. The color palette is bright and cheerful, enhancing the lighthearted, intellectual humor of the scene.'),
 (84, 'Humor, Science, Word Play', 'Inanimate objects are classified scientifically into three major catergories:', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a classroom or laboratory setting with a cheerful professor or scientist standing beside a large, old-fashioned chalkboard. On the chalkboard, the title reads: ''Classification of Inanimate Objects.'' Below this, there are three large cartoon drawings of everyday objects arranged in three columns. The objects are exaggerated and lively-looking: a grumpy old clock with arms crossing, a dumbfounded toaster with a popping slice of bread, and a confused rubber duck sitting on a lab table. The scientist, wearing a lab coat and glasses, is pointing at the objects with a big smile, as if explaining their scientific categories, while a group of amused students or other scientists watch, some taking notes and others chuckling. The whole scene has bright colors and exaggerated cartoon features to emphasize the joke''s playful tone. The setting should be light and funny, with no text beyond the chalkboard heading and simple arrows/labels pointing to the objects to hint at their ''classification.'' The overall mood is educational parody with a silly twist.'),
 (85, 'Bad Puns, Workplace', 'Incontinence Hotline ... Can you hold, please?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a customer service phone operator sitting at a desk wearing a headset. There is a big, bright sign above the operator reading ''Incontinence Hotline''. The operator looks slightly confused but polite. In the foreground, a speech bubble comes from an unseen caller who says, ''Can you hold, please?'' The scene should include a ringing phone on the desk, a small clock on the wall to imply waiting, and some light-hearted office details such as a coffee mug and a notepad. The style is simple and playful with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the joke''s pun on ''hold.'' The background is a cheerful, non-distracting office space with muted colors to keep the focus on the characters and the humorous text.'),
 (86, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Indecision is the key to flexibility.', NULL, 'A simple cartoon scene featuring a person standing at a crossroads with multiple signposts pointing in different directions. The person looks confused, scratching their head with a puzzled expression. Around them, several transparent thought bubbles show the person imagining different possible paths, each with humorous elements like a relaxing beach, a mountain hike, a cityscape, and a quiet home. In the background, a large key labeled ''Flexibility'' floats above the crossroads, glowing softly. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the theme of indecision leading to adaptability.'),
 (87, 'Humor, Science, Word Play', 'Infinity is far out.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon of a cosmic scene where a cool, laid-back infinity symbol (∞) is floating in space wearing retro sunglasses and a relaxed smile, surrounded by stars and planets. The infinity sign is depicted as a character with arms and legs, one arm casually pointing outward as if saying ''far out,'' and a speech bubble above it saying ''Infinity is far out.'' The background should have vibrant colors with whimsical stars and a swirling galaxy to emphasize the ''far out'' space vibe. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated for comedic effect, suitable for a fun science or math-themed cartoon.'),
 (88, 'Humor, Life, Parenting', 'Insanity is hereditary. You get it from your kids.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a tired-looking parent sitting on a couch with messy hair and dark circles under their eyes. Around them are three energetic children causing chaos: one child is jumping on the couch, another is drawing on the wall, and the third is yelling with a toy drum. The parent holds a cup of coffee, looking overwhelmed but resigned, with a speech bubble above reading, ''Insanity is hereditary. You get it from your kids.'' The room is messy with scattered toys, spilled juice, and a small family photo on a side table showing the same parent and kids all smiling peacefully, contrasting the current chaos. The overall art style is lighthearted, colorful, and exaggerated to enhance the humor without any negativity or violence.'),
 (89, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Life', 'Insomnia isn''t anything to lose sleep over.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person lying in bed wide awake at night, eyes wide open and staring at the ceiling. The clock on the bedside table clearly shows it is past midnight. The room is dimly lit by a small lamp, with a window showing a dark night sky with a crescent moon and stars. The person looks tired but is trying to stay optimistic, perhaps with a subtle smile or a raised eyebrow. Above them, a thought bubble contains the text: ''Insomnia isn''t anything to lose sleep over.'' The overall style is lighthearted and exaggerated, emphasizing the irony of the statement. The setting should clearly convey nighttime bedtime frustration but in a gentle, comical way without serious distress or anxiety.'),
 (90, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'Instant idiot: just add alcohol.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a simple kitchen counter with a large, clear glass labeled ''Instant Idiot Mix'' filled with a bubbly liquid. Next to the glass is a bottle of alcohol with a cheerful, exaggerated label, like ''Funny Juice'' or ''Alcohol''. Above the glass is a sparkling sign or a comic-style bubble that reads ''Just Add Alcohol!'' In the background, a surprised cartoon character with exaggerated wide eyes and a goofy grin is looking at the glass, as if startled by the sudden transformation after adding alcohol. The overall vibe is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke''s punchline.'),
 (91, 'Good Question!, Philosophy', 'Integrity has no need for rules.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cartoon character standing confidently with a bright, glowing aura labeled ''Integrity'' around them. The character is in a simple room with a large, old-fashioned book titled ''Rules'' sitting closed on a table nearby. The character is ignoring the book, perhaps with a relaxed smile or a knowing wink. You can show a few floating symbols representing rules (like stop signs, lines, or do-not symbols) around the book, but they are comically deflated or floating away. The background should be light and cheerful with simple geometric shapes and pastel colors to keep it lighthearted and funny, emphasizing the idea that the character doesn’t need these symbols or rules to guide them. The style should be cartoonish with exaggerated expressions and clean lines to highlight the humor in the phrase ''Integrity has no need for rules.'''),
 (92, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Intentionally losing a game of rock paper scissors is just as hard as trying to win', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two friends sitting across from each other at a small table, playing rock paper scissors. One player has a conflicted, exaggerated facial expression, scratching their head and hesitating with a hand hovering mid-gesture, as if struggling to intentionally lose. The other player is confidently showing a ''rock'' hand sign with a sly, knowing smile. Above them, a playful floating thought bubble shows a cartoon rock, paper, and scissors with tiny sweat drops, emphasizing the difficulty of the task. The background is simple with cheerful, bright colors to keep the tone light and funny. Both characters are drawn in a friendly, exaggerated cartoon style with big eyes and expressive faces to show the internal struggle humorously.'),
 (93, 'Humor, Pop Culture', 'Internationally, Baywatch is the most popular TV show in history.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at a sunny, busy beach with golden sand and bright blue water. In the foreground, a group of lifeguards wearing classic red Baywatch swimsuits and holding rescue buoys are standing proudly on the shore. They have big, exaggerated smiles and confident poses as if they are celebrities. Around them, tourists from various countries are excitedly taking photos, holding international flags, and wearing T-shirts with worldwide landmarks like the Eiffel Tower and the Statue of Liberty. A large television screen on the beach plays the Baywatch show, with oversized ON AIR-style text above it. The sign reads: ''Internationally, Baywatch is the most popular TV show in history.'' Palm trees, beach umbrellas, and seagulls add to the lively, fun seaside atmosphere. The overall tone is bright, cheerful, and clearly pokes fun at the global fame of the show in a lighthearted, cartoonish style.'),
 (94, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Invest in the Miracle Chair Company today!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a bright, cheerful office or living room with a large, luxurious, and obviously comfortable armchair in the center, gleaming as if it''s magical. The chair has sparkles or stars around it to emphasize the ''miracle'' aspect. A person standing nearby, dressed in business casual, is holding a briefcase labeled ''Investments'' and looking excitedly at the chair as if plotting to invest in the company. A small sign next to the chair reads ''Miracle Chair Co.'' in bold, playful letters. The background includes charts or posters that humorously suggest huge growth or profits, but with exaggerated, funny graphics like upward arrows shaped like couches. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions and bright colors to convey optimism and humor related to the idea of investing in a miraculous chair product.'),
 (95, 'Animals, Humor, Science', 'Ironic isn''t it, that the tortoise has a drag factor of 0.03.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a tortoise slowly crawling along a racetrack. The tortoise looks calm and slightly smug, wearing oversized sporty sunglasses. Above the track is a caption or scoreboard showing ''Drag Factor: 0.03'' in bold, playful lettering. The racetrack should visually emphasize speed with aerodynamic lines and a finish line in the distance, contrasting with the tortoise''s slow, steady pace. Nearby, a sleek racing car or motorcycle zooms past, leaving exaggerated motion lines and faint dust clouds, highlighting the irony of the tortoise''s very low drag value despite its slow speed. The background is bright and simple with a few clouds and a sun smiling down, adding to the lighthearted, cartoonish style. Overall, the style should be colorful, cartoony, and non-violent, highlighting the funny contradiction between drag factor (a physics term related to speed) and the tortoise''s famously slow movement.'),
 (96, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Word Play', 'Is that a boy ant or girl ant? How do you tell? Put it in water. If it sinks, it''s a girl ant. If it floats, it''s boy-ant.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing two large ants standing next to a small, clear glass filled with water on a simple table. One ant looks curious and is pointing at the glass, while the other ant appears nervous or worried. The glass contains one ant sinking to the bottom, labeled ''girl ant,'' and another ant floating on top of the water surface, labeled ''boy-ant'' as a pun. The background is simple and bright with a few green leaves and a blue sky visible, emphasizing a lighthearted mood. The ants have big expressive eyes and exaggerated facial expressions, highlighting the joke. Include a small speech bubble near the curious ant that says, ''Is that a boy ant or girl ant? How do you tell? Put it in water!'''),
 (97, 'Humor, Life', 'It doesn''t matter how many times you fall off the horse, what matters is how fast you get back on it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person dressed in casual horseback riding attire who has just fallen off a horse. The rider is lying on the ground with a surprised but determined expression, looking up at a horse standing nearby patiently. The horse looks calm and slightly amused, with a subtle smile. The background is a simple outdoor setting with green grass, a few scattered flowers, and a blue sky with a couple of fluffy clouds. Next to the fallen rider, a stopwatch or timer is shown, emphasizing the importance of speed in getting back on. The overall art style is light-hearted and exaggerated, with vibrant colors and clear facial expressions to convey humor and encouragement.'),
 (98, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'It got a new pair of gloves today, but they were both ''lefts''. On one hand, that''s great, but on the other hand, it''s not right.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful cartoon glove character with a smiling face on its palm. The glove character is holding up two gloves, both shaped as left-hand gloves, one in each hand. The setting is a simple glove store with a shelf behind displaying various gloves. The glove character has exaggerated cartoon eyes looking confused and amused at holding two left gloves. A speech bubble above the character says: "On one hand, that''s great, but on the other hand, it''s not right." The style is light and colorful, with the emphasis on the visual pun of two left gloves and the glove character''s expression reflecting the joke''s play on words about hands and being ''not right''.'),
 (99, 'Animals, Humor, Science', 'It has just been discovered that research causes cancer in rats.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a scientific research laboratory. In the center, a slightly confused cartoon rat wearing tiny glasses and a lab coat stands next to a large, old-fashioned microscope. Around the rat are various scientific equipment like test tubes, beakers bubbling with colorful liquids, and charts on the wall showing graphs and mouse silhouettes. The rat is holding a clipboard and looking curiously at a sign on the wall that reads, ''Research Causes Cancer.'' Other lab rats peek out from behind equipment, some looking worried, others bemused. The room has a lighthearted, playful vibe with exaggerated expressions on the rats to emphasize the joke''s irony that research itself is causing cancer in rats, not the usual expectation that research is trying to prevent disease. The style is bright, colorful, and cartoonish, suitable for a family-friendly humorous panel.'),
 (100, 'Humor, Science', 'It has recently been discovered that research causes cancer in rats.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a cluttered laboratory filled with typical research equipment: microscopes, beakers, test tubes, charts, and a whiteboard with complicated formulas. In the foreground, a cute, slightly confused cartoon rat wearing tiny glasses is holding a small research paper titled ''Cancer Studies''. The rat is surrounded by scientists wearing white lab coats, who are intently observing it and taking notes. In the background, there is a poster on the wall that reads ''Warning: Research Causes Cancer in Rats'' with a humorous emphasis. The overall tone is lighthearted and funny, with exaggerated facial expressions on both the rat and the scientists to emphasize the irony of research causing cancer in the very subject being studied. The style is colorful, simple, and consistent with a classic cartoon comic strip look, with rounded shapes and expressive eyes on the characters to enhance humor and approachability.'),
 (101, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'It is better to die on your feet than to live on your knees.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene with a character standing tall and proud on two upright legs, looking confident and heroic. Opposite them, show a comical character exaggeratedly living on their knees, perhaps wearing slippers and looking a bit lazy or timid. The scene should be simple, with a plain background and no violent or negative elements. Add a small speech bubble near the standing character with the quote: ''Better to die on your feet than live on your knees.'' The overall style should be lighthearted and fun, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the contrast between standing tall and living on knees.'),
 (102, 'Humor, Philosophy, Quotes', 'It is better to keep your mouth shut and have people think you are a fool, than to open it and remove all doubt.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting quietly on a park bench with a calm and thoughtful expression. Their mouth is gently closed, and a light bulb above their head glows softly to indicate a clever idea or thought. Nearby, a small group of people are whispering and looking puzzled, as if unsure about the quiet person''s intelligence. To the right, the same person is shown in a separate circular inset, now with their mouth wide open, animatedly speaking, and exaggeratedly silly expressions that confuse the onlookers, who now laugh or raise their eyebrows in amusement. The background is a simple park with a few trees, bushes, and a clear sky, drawn with vibrant colors to keep the cartoon light and friendly. The whole image plays on the contrast between silence implying mystery and speaking revealing foolishness in a comedic way, without any negativity or harshness.'),
 (103, 'Good Question!, Philosophy', 'It is better to light a candle than to curse the darkness.', NULL, 'A bright and simple cartoon scene featuring a person standing in a small dark room with a gloomy atmosphere. The person is holding a lit candle that casts a warm, glowing light around them, pushing back the surrounding darkness which looks like creeping shadows or a black mist retreating. The person has a calm, hopeful expression and wears casual, approachable clothing. In one corner of the room, there is an unlit candle lying on the floor, symbolizing missed chances. The cartoon style should be colorful but not overly detailed, with exaggerated light contrast between the candle''s glow and the darkness, emphasizing the hopeful message. The background is minimal and uncluttered to keep the focus on the candle and the darkness. A faint smiling face could be imagined in the candle’s flame for an added touch of warmth and humor.'),
 (104, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'It is easier to fight for one''s principles than to live up to them.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing proudly on a soapbox or small pedestal labeled ''Principles,'' holding a megaphone and passionately speaking to a small audience. The speaker looks confident, with an exaggerated determined expression. Next to them, show the same person struggling to carry a large, heavy sack labeled ''Living Up to Principles,'' visibly exhausted and sweating, trying to move forward. The setting is a simple park or street corner, with a few amused or confused onlookers observing both versions of the person. Use bright colors and caricature-style features to emphasize the contrast between the ease of fighting for principles versus the difficulty of living them. Avoid any violent, sexual, or political imagery; focus on the humorous struggle and irony of the situation.'),
 (105, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'It is not enough to succeed; others must fail.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set in a corporate office. In the foreground, a confident-looking character stands on a podium labeled ''Success'' with a big trophy in hand and a wide grin. In the background, several other characters wearing business attire look dejected, sitting or slumped over desks with papers scattered around, showing clear signs of failure. Above them, a thought bubble from the main character shows a sneaky smirk with the phrase ''It is not enough to succeed; others must fail.'' The office should have typical items like a water cooler, computer monitors, a clock on the wall, and motivational posters, but one of the posters ironically says ''Teamwork makes the dream work.'' The style is colorful, simple, and exaggerated for comic effect, with expressive facial features to highlight the competitive and slightly mean-spirited tone of the joke without violence or negativity.'),
 (106, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'It is now beyond any doubt that cigarettes are the biggest cause of statistics.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple office environment with a quirky, slightly stressed middle-aged statistician sitting at a cluttered desk filled with papers, charts, and a large cup of coffee. He is holding a lit cigarette with an exaggerated long trail of smoke curling above him. Nearby, a large graph or pie chart on a whiteboard or computer screen behind him shows a rising curve labeled ''Statistics''. Floating humorously in the smoke are tiny numbers and percentages swirling around, as if the cigarette smoke itself is generating data points. The statistician wears glasses, has a somewhat bewildered expression, and a thought bubble above his head reads ''Cigarettes cause statistics... literally!''. The style is colorful, cartoonish, and lighthearted with no harsh details or negativity. The office is simple, with a potted plant, an overflowing ashtray on the desk, and a calendar on the wall pointing to a generic date.'),
 (107, 'Good Question!, Life', 'It is the climbing of the mountain that makes the view from the top so breathtaking.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful hiker standing at the peak of a tall mountain. The hiker is wearing classic climbing gear: a bright colored jacket, a backpack, and hiking boots. The background features a panoramic view of distant snow-capped mountains and a clear blue sky with a shining sun. The hiker is catching their breath, looking slightly exhausted but happy, with a big smile. Nearby, there is a signpost that reads ''Mount Breathtaking Peak.'' A playful detail could be a pair of binoculars hanging off their neck and some small clouds drifting below the mountain peak to exaggerate the height. The overall style is lighthearted and colorful, emphasizing the triumph and joy of the climb without any complex or serious elements.'),
 (108, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'It may be that your sole purpose in life is simply to serve as a warning to others.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing on a small pedestal labeled ''Warning.'' The person looks awkward and sheepish, rubbing the back of their neck nervously. Around the pedestal are several other people pointing and whispering, looking surprised or amused. In the background, a large, colorful warning sign with exclamation marks and bold letters saying ''BEWARE!'' floats above. The setting is a simple park or city square with a few trees and benches, emphasizing that this is an ordinary place where the ''warning'' person stands out humorously as a living cautionary example.'),
 (109, 'Animals, Facts, Sports Humor', 'It takes 3,000 cows to supply the NFL with enough leather for a year''s supply of footballs.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a huge group of cows in a green field stretching far into the background. In the foreground, one cow is looking confused or surprised, perhaps scratching its head. Nearby, a large conveyor belt is transporting a pile of footballs labeled ''NFL Footballs.'' A factory building in the background has giant football logos and leather hides hanging on racks visible through windows. The sky is bright and sunny. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated cartoon styles and smiling cows, emphasizing the connection between cows and football manufacturing without showing anything distressing or violent.'),
 (110, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'It works better when you turn the brightness up.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a dimly lit room showing a person squinting at a very old, tiny, rudimentary light bulb dangling from the ceiling with a hand crank. The person, looking confused and slightly frustrated, is reaching to turn up a large, ridiculous, oversized brightness dial labeled ''Brightness'' that is humorously attached to the bulb socket. The background is shadowy, with exaggerated dark corners to emphasize the low light. The character''s facial expression should be cartoonish and exaggerated for humor. Nearby, a small table lamp with a big glowing bulb is off to the side, contrasting with the tiny bulb struggling to illuminate the room. The overall tone is light and funny, emphasizing the playful misunderstanding of why turning brightness up would help.'),
 (111, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'It''s always darkest before dawn. So if you''re going to steal your neighbor''s newspaper, that''s the time to do it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a quiet suburban neighborhood at night, just before dawn. The sky is dark with a few stars, and a faint hint of early morning light is starting to appear on the horizon. In the foreground, a sneaky-looking cartoon character, wearing a striped burglar outfit and a black eye mask, tiptoes exaggeratedly toward a front lawn. The character is reaching out to grab a rolled-up newspaper from a typical residential mailbox or placed on a doorstep. Nearby, a friendly dog watches but looks more confused or curious than alarmed. The houses in the background have some lit windows, and a streetlamp casts a soft glow. The scene conveys the joke’s punchline in a lighthearted and playful manner without any menace.'),
 (112, 'Humor, Life', 'It''s best to start each day with a nap.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a cozy bedroom in the morning. The room has soft sunlight streaming through a window with curtains slightly fluttering. A person, wearing pajamas and a sleep mask pushed up on their forehead, is comfortably snuggled in a big, fluffy bed with a huge pillow. Their bedside table has an alarm clock showing an early hour, but the person is blissfully napping with a content smile. Nearby, a cup of coffee is untouched and steam is gently rising from it. The scene should emphasize relaxation and humor, with warm colors and exaggerated, cute features to highlight the joke about starting the day with a nap rather than morning activity. Include a small, playful cat curled up at the foot of the bed, also napping.'),
 (113, 'Humor, Life, Shopping Jokes', 'It''s easy to identify people who can''t count to ten. They''re always in front of you at the express checkout line.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene set in a supermarket checkout area. In the foreground, there is an express checkout lane clearly marked with a bright sign that reads ''Express Checkout: 10 Items or Less.'' In front of this lane, a cheerful cashier is scanning items. Standing just ahead of the line is a customer with a shopping cart overflowing with dozens of items, looking somewhat clueless or sheepish. Behind this customer, a frustrated or amused person waits with only a few items. The background includes other shoppers and grocery store shelves. The scene should be colorful and exaggerated in a humorous way, emphasizing the irony of the person who can’t count to ten blocking the express lane. The expressions on the characters'' faces and the visible quantity of items in the cart help deliver the punchline visually.'),
 (114, 'Humor, Word Play', 'It''s good to keep an open mind - just don''t let your brains fall out.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a friendly-looking human head with the top of the skull opened like a hinged lid, tilted back as if ''open,'' revealing a few humorous, slightly exaggerated brains inside. The brains look surprised or alarmed, some depicted as trying not to fall out, with little cartoon hands holding on or grabbing the edge. The head wears glasses and has a gentle smile, capturing the idea of ''keeping an open mind'' literally. The background is simple, pastel-colored, with maybe a small floating speech bubble above the head saying, ''Keep your brains inside!'' The overall tone is light and funny, with simple line art and bright colors to emphasize the pun without any violence or negativity.'),
 (115, 'Humor, Life', 'It''s lonely at the top, but you eat better.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a mountain peak with a content, slightly plump character sitting at the very top eating a lavish feast—like a huge turkey leg, a bowl of fruits, and a cake—all on a fancy picnic blanket. The character wears a simple crown or laurel wreath symbolizing ''being at the top.'' Below the mountain, at the base, a sad and scruffy climber or hiker looks up with an empty plate and a forlorn expression. The background includes a bright sunny sky, a few fluffy clouds, and a trail winding up the mountain. The overall feel is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the contrast between loneliness at the top and the abundance of food there.'),
 (116, 'Good Question!, Humor, Philosophy', 'It''s never too late to be early.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person with a big, cheerful smile standing confidently in front of a large, old-fashioned clock that shows an early hour, like 7:00 AM. The person is dressed casually with a sense of pride, maybe wearing a wristwatch as well. Surrounding the character, there''s a subtle background showing a sunrise to reinforce the idea of ''early''. Nearby, a calendar on the wall shows a page being flipped backward or a date in the past, symbolizing ''never too late''. The style is colorful and playful, with exaggerated expressions emphasizing the upbeat and optimistic mood of the phrase. The overall tone is lighthearted and motivational, without any complex background elements, focusing on the character and the clock as central objects.'),
 (117, 'Humor, Life', 'It''s not as easy as people think to get a parking ticket - first you have to find somewhere to park.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set in a busy urban street lined with parallel parking spots. A frustrated driver, exaggeratedly scratching their head or looking confused, is standing next to an overfilled parking lot sign. Multiple cars are cramped together, some double-parked or awkwardly squeezed in. Show a clearly visible parking meter with a ticket stuck to a windshield of one car, but instead of focusing on the fine, emphasize the scarcity of empty spots. Include a street sign reading ''No Parking'' or ''Full Parking'' nearby for context. The overall mood should be light-hearted and comical, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions illustrating the irony that getting a parking ticket requires actually finding a parking space first. Avoid any aggressive or negative portrayal of tickets or enforcement officers.'),
 (118, 'Good Question!, Humor, Philosophy', 'It''s not reality that''s important, but how you perceive things.', NULL, 'Draw a whimsical cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person standing in front of two windows. Through the left window, depict a plain, gray rainy day with a frown on the person''s face. Through the right window, show a bright, sunny park with flowers, children playing, and a rainbow, with the person smiling brightly there. The person is holding a large magnifying glass up to the right window, symbolizing ''perception.'' Above their head, floating like a thought bubble, is a small, colorful brain with sparkles around it, emphasizing the idea of mental perspective. The overall style should be light and humorous with exaggerated expressions and bright colors for the positive scene, and duller, muted colors for the negative side. Add a small sign on a wall behind the person that reads: ''Perception is everything,'' to reinforce the joke''s message in a playful way.'),
 (119, 'Humor, Life', 'It''s not the waiting, it''s the time between now and then that concerns me!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person anxiously sitting on a park bench, repeatedly checking a large wristwatch with an exaggerated worried expression. Around them, time is visually represented by several floating clocks showing different times and calendars fluttering in the wind. The background is a simple park setting with a tree, a couple of birds looking curiously at the person, and a distant horizon suggesting a long wait ahead. The style is colorful and lighthearted, with playful exaggeration in the character''s expression and body language to emphasize impatience and concern about the time passing rather than the actual waiting moment.'),
 (120, 'Animals, Humor, Word Play', 'It''s possible to lead a cow upstairs...but not downstairs.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a frustrated farmer standing at the top of a staircase inside a rustic farmhouse. The farmer, wearing overalls and a straw hat, is gently trying to guide a large, bewildered cow onto the stairs going up. The staircase is narrow with a simple wooden banister. The cow''s hooves are awkwardly positioned halfway up the stairs, looking confused. Below the stairs is a sign that says ''Downstairs? No way!'' with a little arrow pointing down. The overall scene is lighthearted and silly, emphasizing the cow''s clumsiness with stairs. Background elements include a farmhouse kitchen visible through a doorway, with rustic farming tools hung on the wall. The art style is cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions on both the farmer and the cow to highlight the humor in the impossibility of leading the cow down the stairs.'),
 (121, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'It''s pretty hard to tell what does bring happiness; poverty and wealth have both failed.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters sitting on opposite sides of a seesaw. One character is dressed in ragged clothes, holding a small pile of coins, looking confused but hopeful. The other character is wearing a fancy suit with a big bag of money, also looking puzzled and a bit frustrated. Above them, a whimsical thought cloud contains a simple smiley face symbol representing happiness, but it is floating just out of reach. The background is a sunny park with colorful trees, and some birds perched on the seesaw, adding to the lighthearted mood. The overall style is bright, cheerful, and exaggerated, with friendly expressions on both characters emphasizing the joke that neither poverty nor wealth clearly brings happiness.'),
 (122, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'It''s sweet to be remembered, but it''s often cheaper to be forgotten.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing two characters at a birthday party. One character is holding a gift and smiling happily, surrounded by brightly colored balloons and a ''Happy Birthday'' banner. The other character stands off to the side looking a bit puzzled or blank, symbolizing being forgotten. Nearby is a table with a modest cake and a donation jar labeled ''Forget-Me-Not Fund'' with only a few coins inside, emphasizing the idea that being remembered often comes at a cost, while being forgotten might be ''cheaper.'' The setting is lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions to highlight the humorous contrast between being sweetly remembered and the cost associated with it, all in a clean and friendly cartoon style.'),
 (123, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'It''s the little things that count.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a large human hand with a tiny, comically small object being handed over between thumb and forefinger. The tiny object could be a miniature gift box, a tiny coin, or a small flower, emphasizing the phrase ''little things.'' The setting is simple, with a neutral background to keep focus on the hand and the tiny item. The hand is exaggerated in size compared to the small object to highlight the contrast. The style should be bright and cheerful, with exaggerated features to make the scene playful and funny, capturing the pun on ''small things'' mattering.'),
 (124, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'It''s the start of a brand new day, and I''m off like a herd of turtles.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a bright, cheerful morning with a shining sun and a few fluffy clouds. In the foreground, a group of turtles is slowly moving away from the viewer, all looking determined but clearly slow-paced. They are arranged somewhat like a herd of animals running off, but their tiny legs and turtle shells emphasize their sluggishness. Nearby, a human figure (only partially visible from the waist down) is starting to walk or jog with energetic movement, contrasting with the slow turtles. The background can include a simple grassy field or a quiet suburban street to keep it light and funny. The overall style is colorful, playful, and exaggerated to emphasize the irony of a ''herd'' of naturally slow turtles setting off at the start of the day.'),
 (125, 'Humor, Motivational, Philosophy', 'It''s your attitude, not your aptitude, that determines your altitude in life.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a whimsical simple mountain landscape. In the foreground, a cheerful character wearing a business suit and a pilot''s hat is standing on a stack of large books labeled ''Attitude'' and ''Aptitude.'' The character is smiling confidently with arms raised as if ready to take off. Above the character, a cartoon airplane shaped like an upward arrow is soaring upward into the sky labeled ''Altitude.'' The sky is bright with a few fluffy clouds and a sun shining. Around the character, small motivational signs or symbols like smiley faces and light bulbs float to emphasize positive attitude, while the book labeled ''Aptitude'' looks a bit dusty and less colorful. The style should be playful and colorful, using exaggerated expressions and simple shapes to create a humorous and uplifting vibe.'),
 (126, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Life', 'I''ve been on a diet for two weeks and all I''ve lost is two weeks.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing on a scale, looking confused and slightly disappointed. The scale''s screen or dial clearly shows ''0 lbs'' or no weight change. Around them, a calendar on the wall displays two weeks marked off, perhaps with red circles or Xs. The person might be holding a salad bowl or a water bottle to hint they''re trying to diet. Their posture and facial expression should convey the irony that despite dieting for two weeks, they''ve lost nothing but time. The setting is simple, like a bathroom or kitchen corner, with humorous details such as an uneaten cake or a fast food wrapper tossed aside nearby, emphasizing the struggle. The art style should be colorful and cartoony, with exaggerated expressions to enhance the joke''s punchline.'),
 (127, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Science', 'I''ve been reading a sci-fi book about anti-gravity -- I can''t put it down!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting comfortably in a cozy armchair, deeply engrossed in a book titled ''Anti-Gravity Sci-Fi.'' The person has a delighted expression, eyes wide with fascination. The twist is that the person and the armchair are both gently floating slightly above the ground, emphasizing the anti-gravity theme. Around them, several small objects, like a floating cup of coffee, a book, and a pair of glasses, are also hovering mid-air, adding to the lighthearted, weightless atmosphere. The background is a simple living room setting with a window showing stars and a spaceship silhouette outside, hinting at the sci-fi context. The drawing style is playful and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions and soft, rounded lines to keep it friendly and funny.'),
 (128, 'Food Humor, Pop Culture', 'I''ve been seduced by the chocolate side of the Force.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene inspired by a Star Wars theme but with a funny twist. In the middle, depict a smiling person wearing a Jedi robe with a chocolate bar in one hand instead of a lightsaber. Around them, have faint glowing chocolate-themed ‘Force’ effects, like swirling pieces of chocolate or cocoa bean shapes instead of light. Include a small, cute, and confused-looking droid beside the person looking at the chocolate bar. The background should resemble a Star Wars-style starship interior but also incorporate chocolate-themed elements like chocolate bars and cocoa pods on shelves or floating in the air. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, blending sci-fi with dessert humor, in a colorful, cartoon style with exaggerated expressions and clear references to both Star Wars and chocolate cravings.'),
 (129, 'Humor, Language, Workplace', 'Jargon is used as a means of succeeding by not simplifying.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in an office meeting room where a confident businessperson stands at a presentation board filled with complex, confusing jargon-filled charts and graphs. The presenter is smiling smugly, pointing at the overly complicated text that clearly doesn''t simplify anything, while the audience around the table looks baffled, scratching their heads or exchanging confused glances. Include exaggerated thought bubbles above the listeners showing question marks and swirling lines to emphasize confusion. The overall style should be light-hearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humorous contrast between the complicated jargon and the struggling audience.'),
 (130, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Jaywalker: A person who walks when you are driving.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon street scene with a frustrated driver sitting in a small car at a red traffic light. The driver wears a puzzled or annoyed expression, clearly staring at a pedestrian confidently crossing the street outside the crosswalk, without paying attention to the traffic signals. The pedestrian is happily walking right in front of the car with a casual, oblivious smile. Include a traffic light showing red and a visible street sign or mark indicating a crosswalk nearby, to emphasize the jaywalking aspect. Add a cityscape background with simple buildings and other pedestrians waiting politely on the sidewalk. The style should be bright and colorful with exaggerated expressions to bring out the humor of a driver internally labeling the pedestrian as a "jaywalker" because they’re walking when the driver wants to go.'),
 (131, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'Jealousy is all the fun you think they have.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters standing side by side. One character is looking at the other with a greenish tint to their face and exaggeratedly large eyes filled with envy, possibly with tiny cartoon steam puffs or scribbles above their head to show jealousy. The other character is smiling widely and appears to be enjoying a fun activity, like eating a large ice cream cone or playing a party horn, surrounded by confetti to suggest they''re having a great time. The background is simple and cheerful, like a bright park or a casual party setting with balloons or streamers. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with rounded features and expressive faces to emphasize the humor and emotion without any violence or negativity.'),
 (132, 'Bad Puns, Cooking Humor, Life', 'Jim''s bachelor cooking tip #2: If you put food in a Tupperware container and put it in the dishwasher, you can cook the food while you do the dishes!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a messy bachelor apartment kitchen. Center the image on a grinning young man named Jim, wearing a casual T-shirt and apron, standing proudly next to an open dishwasher. Inside the dishwasher, instead of dishes, there''s a transparent Tupperware container with visible, cartoon-style food inside (like pasta or a sandwich). Steam is rising from the container to show cooking in progress. Around the kitchen, include typical bachelor mess: a few empty pizza boxes, dirty dishes piled up nearby, and a sink full of soapy water. The background should feature a simple tiled wall and a kitchen counter with a coffee mug and a dirty sponge. The style is colorful, lighthearted, and exaggerated for comic effect, emphasizing Jim''s proud yet lazy cooking hack. No people besides Jim, no violence or complex detail needed; just a clean, funny snapshot of his quirky life hack.'),
 (133, 'Humor, Jobs, Life', 'JOB: A state of employment everyone wants but few look forward to on a Monday morning.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a typical office on a Monday morning. The focus is a tired-looking worker sitting at a cluttered desk with a computer, coffee mug, and piles of paperwork. The worker has disheveled hair, half-closed eyes, and a slightly slouched posture, clearly not enthusiastic about starting the day. In the background, a large wall clock shows early morning time. Nearby, a motivational poster ironically reads ''Love Your Job!'' The office environment should have cubicles, fluorescent lights, and a window with a dreary sky outside. A small calendar on the desk prominently displays Monday. The overall style should be light, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the worker’s Monday morning dread and the contradictory desire versus reluctance about having a job.'),
 (134, 'History Humor, Word Play', 'Joseph Stalin''s grave was a Communist Plot.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cemetery featuring a simple gravestone labeled ''Joseph Stalin.'' Surrounding the grave are classic communist symbols like a red hammer and sickle flag planted in the ground. In front of the grave, a small group of burly, stereotypical Soviet-style cartoon characters (wearing ushankas and military coats) are gathered, some whispering and looking conspiratorial. The gravestone itself has a subtle cartoonish glow or aura, implying it''s part of a literal ''Communist Plot.'' The background shows some trees and a quaint fence, with lighthearted, exaggerated expressions on the characters to emphasize the joke without menace. The overall tone is playful and satirical, with bright colors, simple lines, and exaggerated features to enhance the comedic effect without depicting anything violent or serious.'),
 (135, 'Humor, Motivational', 'Just close your eyes, fall asleep. Next time you open your eyes you''ll be in your future!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person lying in bed with their eyes closed, snuggled under a blanket. Above their head is a thought bubble depicting two panels: the first panel shows the person peacefully sleeping with ''Zzz'' symbols; the second panel shows the same person waking up, but in a funny future scenario—perhaps wearing futuristic clothes, surrounded by flying gadgets or robots, or standing next to a calendar labeled with a future year. The bedroom should look cozy and simple, with a nightstand holding an alarm clock and a lamp. The overall style should be lighthearted and whimsical, with exaggerated expressions of calm sleep and surprise or curiosity upon waking. The colors should be bright and cheerful to emphasize optimism and humor about the concept of ''sleeping into the future.'''),
 (136, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'Keep America beautiful. Swallow your beer cans.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing proudly with a big, exaggerated smile and bulging cheeks as if they just swallowed something large. Around them, several empty beer cans trail behind on the ground, some crushed and others whole. The setting is a sunny outdoor park or backyard with a "Keep America Beautiful" sign prominently displayed in the background. The character is wearing casual clothes and holding an empty empty-handed, implying they''ve "swallowed" the cans instead of throwing them away. Include lighthearted details like a recycling bin nearby looking confused or surprised. The overall tone is playful and silly, emphasizing the absurdity of literally swallowing beer cans to keep the environment clean. No violence or any unpleasant imagery.'),
 (137, 'Mental Health Humor, Word Play', 'Kiss me twice. I''m schizophrenic.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene shows two identical cartoon characters standing very close to each other. Both look exactly alike, with the same hairstyle, clothes, and facial expressions. One character leans forward puckering lips, ready to give a kiss, while the other character, slightly behind but mirrored, also leans in with puckered lips. Above them is a speech bubble from one character saying, ''Kiss me twice. I''m schizophrenic.'' The background is simple and cheerful, maybe a park bench or neutral interior to keep focus on the characters and the punchline. The style is light and playful, emphasizing the idea of two versions of the same person interacting in a funny way without anything scary or overly serious.'),
 (138, 'Star Wars, Word Play', 'Klingon Wessel Destroyed, Keptin.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a simple spaceship bridge styled like a classic sci-fi starship. In the center, a cartoonish Klingon captain with exaggerated forehead ridges and a proud mustache stands perplexed, looking at a large computer console screen. The screen displays a big red flashing message: ''Wessel Destroyed, Keptin.'' Nearby, a messed-up spelling correction bubble pops up over the console saying, ''Wessel? You mean vessel!'' The captain looks both annoyed and confused, scratching his head. Around him, typical starship controls and blinking lights add to the sci-fi atmosphere. The style is colorful, lighthearted, and exaggerated, emphasizing the joke about Klingon English pronunciation and spelling mistakes in a playful manner.'),
 (139, 'Food Humor, Humor, Word Play', 'LACTOMANGULATION (lak to man gyu lay'' shun) v. Manhandling the ''open here'' spout on a milk container so badly that one has to resort to the illegal side.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a brightly lit kitchen. Central focus is a frustrated person holding a milk carton with multiple taped-up tears and crumpled sections around the official ''open here'' spout. The person''s facial expression is exaggeratedly annoyed and tired, with one hand clutching the damaged spout while the other hand awkwardly peeks under a non-official, taped-up side of the carton clearly marked with a small ''illegal side'' label or sticker. Nearby on the counter, a glass of milk is half-filled, showing the ongoing effort to get milk out. In the background, a clock and simple kitchen elements like a fridge and countertop accessories complete the setting. The overall style is colorful, cartoonish, and playful to emphasize the silly struggle of manhandling a stubborn milk carton.'),
 (140, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Life', 'Last night I thought I was going to die and my whole life flashed before me. It was awful. I hate re-runs.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person lying awake in bed at night with wide, alarmed eyes staring at the ceiling. Above their head is a thought bubble filled with a series of TV screens all showing repetitive scenes of the person''s daily life, as if their entire life is playing like dull reruns on TV. The room should be simple, with a bedside lamp casting a soft yellow light. The facial expression should convey frustration and disbelief. The TV screens in the thought bubble can include funny, exaggerated scenes such as the person brushing their teeth, spilling coffee, and sitting at a desk looking bored, repeated multiple times to emphasize the ''rerun'' concept. Style should be light, colorful, and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions for comedic effect.'),
 (141, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Science', 'Last week a hypnotist convinced me that I was a soft, malleable metal with an atomic number of 82. I''m easily lead.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting in a comfy chair with a hypnotist standing nearby. The hypnotist is wearing classic hypnotist attire—perhaps a suit with a bow tie and holding a swinging pocket watch. The person in the chair has dazed, dreamy eyes and a goofy smile, clearly under hypnosis. Above their head is a thought bubble containing the image of a soft, shiny, gold bar labeled with the atomic number ''82'' and some little waves or wrinkles to emphasize it''s malleable. The background is simple, maybe a cozy room with a few framed certificates on the wall and a small table with a spilled glass of water. The overall style is bright and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions and rounded shapes, focusing on the pun about lead acting like gold (soft malleable metal), making the joke visually clear and lighthearted.'),
 (142, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Lately I''ve found that every time I want to rest on my laurels, I need wider laurels.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person reclining comfortably on a small laurel wreath acting like a recliner chair. The person looks relaxed but slightly cramped and is reaching out to a much larger laurel wreath nearby, shaped like a bigger recliner chair, illustrating the idea of needing more space to rest. The setting is light and playful, with perhaps a few trophies or medals on a nearby shelf to reinforce the concept of ''resting on laurels'' as resting on past achievements. The overall style is colorful and simple, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor of wanting bigger laurel wreaths to rest on.'),
 (143, 'Humor, Life', 'Laugh alone and the world thinks you''re an idiot.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a single person in the center, sitting on a park bench or at a café table. The person is laughing heartily all alone, maybe with their head thrown back and eyes closed in amusement. Around them, several other people nearby are looking at them with puzzled, confused, or slightly judgmental expressions, with some whispering to one another or raising eyebrows. The setting is light and casual, with a sunny day and simple background such as trees, a lamppost, or café chairs to keep it relatable. A visible thought bubble above the laughing person shows a little cartoon world to symbolize ''the world thinks.'' The overall tone is playful and lighthearted, emphasizing the social awkwardness of laughing alone in public without any indication of the person being self-conscious or lonely.'),
 (144, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'Laugh and you''ll burn up three and a half calories. No joke.', NULL, 'A lighthearted and cheerful cartoon scene showing a person sitting on a couch watching TV or holding a phone, laughing heartily. The character is mid-laugh with eyes closed and mouth wide open, with a cartoonish sweat drop or small puff of smoke rising from them to humorously indicate ''burning calories.'' Around the character, little calorie symbols (like tiny flames shaped like calories) float up playfully. The background is cozy and simple, such as a living room with a coffee table and a plant, emphasizing a relaxed atmosphere. The overall style is colorful, friendly, and whimsical to highlight the fun idea that laughter burns calories.'),
 (145, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Laugh, and the world laughs with you. Snore and you sleep alone.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two contrasting panels side by side. On the left panel, a cheerful character is laughing joyfully, surrounded by a crowd of smiling, laughing people who are all enjoying the moment together outdoors in a bright, sunny park. Everyone looks friendly and happy. On the right panel, the same character is lying in bed at night, snoring loudly with exaggerated Z’s floating above their head. The room is dimly lit by a small bedside lamp. Nearby, a partner or roommate is wide awake, looking annoyed and covering their ears with a pillow, highlighting the loneliness caused by snoring. The style is lighthearted and playful with expressive facial features and bold colors, emphasizing the humorous contrast between shared laughter and isolated snoring.'),
 (146, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'Laundry machines have a secret chamber where they hide single socks.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a typical laundry room with a washing machine and a dryer. The washing machine is slightly open, revealing a small hidden secret chamber inside, glowing softly with a few lonely single socks lounging around on tiny armchairs, sipping soda or playing cards. Some socks have funny facial expressions displaying boredom or mischief. Around the machines, piles of matching folded socks sit neatly, while one sock appears puzzled looking toward the secret chamber. The setting is bright, colorful, and playful with exaggerated cartoon features to emphasize the whimsical idea of socks having a secret hiding spot inside the machine.'),
 (147, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Law of Probability Dispersal: Whatever it is that hits the fan will not be evenly distributed', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a classic fan mounted on a table blowing air. In front of the fan, a large pile of various messy items (representing ''whatever hits the fan'') like mud, papers, paint splatters, and a pie are flying toward the fan. Instead of being evenly spread behind the fan, the mess is scattered wildly and unevenly—one corner has a huge splatter on the wall, another patch on the floor, and some dripping on a nearby character’s surprised face. The character, cartoonishly wide-eyed and wearing casual clothes, is ducking or trying to shield themselves with a newspaper. The background is simple, focusing on the fan, the flying mess, and the uneven splatter patterns to emphasize the joke. The overall style is light, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize humor without any mess being scary or dirty—just silly and exaggerated splats and drips.'),
 (148, 'Lawyer Humor, Politics, Workplace', 'LAWYER: A professional advocate hired to bend the law on behalf of a paying client; for this reason considered the most suitable background for entry into politics.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a lawyer standing confidently in a courtroom. The lawyer is dressed in a suit with a briefcase labeled ''Law Books'' and is smiling slyly. Behind the lawyer, there is a scale of justice that is noticeably tipped heavily to one side, humorously implying imbalance. In the background, a large open door labeled ''Politics'' is shown with a red carpet leading from the courtroom to the door. A few shadowy figures dressed in suits stand near the door, welcoming the lawyer with outstretched hands. The courtroom has typical elements like judge''s bench, witness stand, and spectators, but exaggerated and whimsical in style for comedic effect. The overall mood is light, playful, and ironic, emphasizing the joke’s commentary on lawyers often entering politics because of their skill at ''bending the law.'''),
 (149, 'Humor, Parenting', 'Learn from your parents'' mistakes - use birth control!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a teenager sitting with a thoughtful expression while looking at a family photo album. In the album, the images of quirky-looking parents are exaggerated with comical features, such as glasses slipping down the nose and slightly disheveled hairstyles. Next to the teen is a large, clearly labeled pack of birth control pills, highlighted with a glowing aura to emphasize its importance. The background is a cozy living room with a framed picture on the wall that says ''Learn from your parents!'' The overall tone is lighthearted and cheeky, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to enhance the joke''s playful warning.'),
 (150, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'Lefties have rights too.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters: one is a left-handed person happily writing with a giant pen using their left hand, while a smiling, anthropomorphic right hand stands beside them holding a small protest sign that reads ''Rights!'' Above them, a playful banner says ''Lefties have rights too!'' The background is simple and cheerful, with bright colors and a classroom or office setting. The characters should have exaggerated expressions to emphasize humor and friendliness, making it clear that it''s a lighthearted take on left-handedness and rights. No violence or negativity; just a fun, upbeat vibe focused on the pun.'),
 (151, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Legalize mental telepathy? I knew you were going to say that.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing two people facing each other in a casual setting, such as a park bench or coffee shop. One person says the phrase, ''Legalize mental telepathy?'' with an inquisitive look, as if proposing a new idea. The other person immediately replies with a knowing smile and hand raised in acknowledgment, responding, ''I knew you were going to say that.'' To emphasize the telepathy joke, small playful wavy lines or a faint glowing outline could be drawn between their heads, suggesting communication without words. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions portraying surprise and amusement. The background is simple but cheerful, with minimal details so the focus remains on the interaction between the two characters.'),
 (152, 'Good Question!, History Humor', 'Leonardo da Vinci invented the scissors.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Leonardo da Vinci in a Renaissance workshop filled with sketches and inventions. Leonardo, wearing typical Renaissance clothes and a beret, is holding a pair of old-fashioned scissors with a proud smile. The scissors should look slightly exaggerated with large, ornate handles made of wood or metal. Around him on a wooden table are papers with rough sketches of scissors and other famous da Vinci inventions like the flying machine. The background could include shelves with tools, gears, and scrolls to emphasize the inventor''s workspace. The style should be lighthearted and colorful, with a playful mood to match the joke''s tongue-in-cheek claim.'),
 (153, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'Let a fool hold his tongue and he will pass for a sage.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters sitting on a park bench. One character is a cheerful, naive-looking person with wide eyes and a big smile, clearly a fool, holding his own tongue gently with both hands as if to keep it from speaking. The other character is an older, wise figure, perhaps an elderly person with glasses, a long beard, and a thoughtful expression, nodding approvingly at the fool''s silence. Around them, there are speech bubbles with silly nonsense from the fool when he speaks, but now the bubbles are empty to indicate silence. The background is simple, with trees and a sunny sky. The setting is lighthearted and colorful, emphasizing the humor of the situation where silence makes the fool appear wise.'),
 (154, 'Bad Puns, Camping', 'Let sleeping bags lie.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set outdoors at a campsite. In the foreground, a couple of brightly colored sleeping bags lie on the grass, looking slightly puffed up as if they are ''sleeping'' creatures. Nearby, a camper character tiptoes carefully past them with wide eyes and a finger held up to their lips, signaling to be quiet. The background includes a simple tent, a campfire with small flames but no smoke, and a few trees under a clear night sky with twinkling stars. The overall tone is light and playful, emphasizing the pun on ''Let sleeping bags lie,'' visually representing the idea that the sleeping bags are left undisturbed, with the camper humorously treating them as if they were alive and sleeping. Draw everything in bright, cartoonish colors with exaggerated expressions to enhance the joke''s charm and make the scene whimsical and inviting.'),
 (155, 'Computers, Humor, Philosophy', 'Life after death? Is that like terminate and stay resident?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a computer-themed afterlife. The background resembles a whimsical, glowing circuit board with soft pastel colors. In the center, a friendly ghost with a slight pixelated or digital appearance floats, looking puzzled and scratching its chin. Next to the ghost, a classic old computer with a monitor displaying a message box that reads "Terminate and Stay Resident?" A thought bubble from the ghost shows the words "Life after death?" Above this setup, a playful sign reads "Afterlife Operating System." Scattered around are lighthearted computer elements like floppy disks, a mouse, and a keyboard, all with cute faces. The overall tone is cartoonish and fun, emphasizing the pun on computer terminology and the concept of life after death, without any scary or dark elements.'),
 (156, 'Humor, Philosophy, Word Play', 'Life is like an analogy.', NULL, 'Draw a light-hearted cartoon scene featuring a cheerful, slightly confused character standing at a blackboard or flip chart. The blackboard or chart has the phrase ''Life is like an analogy'' written prominently. The character, a simple stick-figure or cartoon person with exaggerated puzzled eyebrows and a playful smile, is holding a pointer stick or chalk, as if explaining the phrase. Around the character, include whimsical thought bubbles illustrating confusing but related items—for example, a clock, a fruit, a puzzle piece, and a question mark—to visually show the abstract and humorous concept of comparing life to an analogy. The style should be colorful, simple, and playful, evoking a light, philosophical humor without any complexity or negativity.'),
 (157, 'Humor, Life', 'Life is too short to waste time matching socks.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person standing in front of an open laundry basket overflowing with colorful, mismatched socks. The person, wearing casual home clothes, has a relaxed, carefree expression and is tossing one sock over their shoulder. Around them, socks of various bright colors and patterns are scattered on the floor and some even float in the air, emphasizing the chaotic mismatch. The background is a cozy, simple laundry room with a washing machine and a clothesline. The overall mood is lighthearted and playful, highlighting the theme of not stressing over matching socks and enjoying life.'),
 (158, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'Life is uncertain. Eat dessert first.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful person sitting at a dining table with a fancy dinner setting (silverware, plate, napkin), but instead of the main course, the person is eagerly eating a big, colorful, delicious-looking dessert, like a slice of cake with bright icing and a cherry on top. The person has a wide smile and looks very satisfied. In the background, there is a clock showing time passing quickly, and a thought bubble above the person’s head with the words "Life is uncertain. Eat dessert first." The setting is cozy, with warm lighting and perhaps a window showing a sunny day outside to add a positive vibe. The cartoon style should be lighthearted, simple, and whimsical, and the scene emphasizes the playful idea of prioritizing dessert over the main meal in life.'),
 (159, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'Life isn''t fair, but neither is death.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing in front of a large, old-fashioned balance scale outdoors. On one side of the scale is a smiling, happy sun labeled ''Life,'' which is clearly lighter and higher up. On the other side is a grumpy-looking, dark cloud labeled ''Death,'' weighing heavier and lower. The person stands in the middle, wearing casual clothes, shrugging with an amused but resigned expression. Around the person are simple background elements like grass, a tree, and a few flowers to create a peaceful park-like setting. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the unfairness yet acceptance of both concepts.'),
 (160, 'Humor, Philosophy, Programming', 'Life would be so much easier if we could just look at the source code.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting comfortably at a desk with a big, exaggerated computer monitor in front of them. The monitor displays complex, colorful, and tangled lines of code, with some humorous snippets like function names: lifeProblems(), happiness(), and love(). The person has a curious and slightly puzzled expression, scratching their head as if wishing they could understand the code of life. Around them, everyday objects like a coffee mug, a calendar marked with chaotic events, and a thought bubble showing a simplified, happy life flowchart add to the scene. The background is a cozy home office with playful details such as post-it notes saying ''If only...'' and ''debug life()''. The style is cheerful, cartoonish, with bright colors and exaggerated features to emphasize humor and relatability without any violent or controversial content.'),
 (161, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Living on Earth is expensive, but it does include a free trip around the sun.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a smiling, cartoon-style Earth character wearing sunglasses and holding a suitcase labeled ''Life Journey.'' The Earth is standing on a small patch of grass, with a price tag hanging from its side showing a high cost in dollars. Beside the Earth, a friendly, cartoon Sun wearing a cheerful face and a sunhat is orbiting around the Earth, depicted by a dotted circular path with arrows indicating the orbit. Above the scene, include a playful banner that reads ''Living on Earth is expensive...'' and below, a caption reading ''...but it does include a free trip around the sun.'' The overall style should be bright, colorful, and lighthearted, emphasizing humor without any people or complex backgrounds, focusing on the personified Earth and Sun as main characters.'),
 (162, 'Math Humor, Word Play', 'Long computations that yield zero are probably all for naught.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cluttered home office or study room filled with math books, papers, and a computer on a desk. A person with a puzzled or slightly frustrated expression is sitting at the desk, staring at a long scroll of printed calculations that curl all the way to the floor. The scroll ends with a giant zero circled in red. On the wall behind the person, whimsical mathematical symbols and formulas float in thought bubbles, emphasizing complex math work. The person’s hand is raised in a shrugging gesture, conveying the meaning of ''all for naught.'' The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to enhance the comedic effect of the futile long calculation resulting in zero.'),
 (163, 'Humor, Workplace', 'Look deeeeep into the monitor..... you''re getting sleeeeeeeeepy.  As usual.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a tired person sitting at a desk staring at a computer monitor. The monitor screen should have exaggerated, hypnotic swirling spirals or concentric circles glowing softly in blue and purple hues. The person has droopy eyelids starting to close, a slight yawn, and a sleepy expression. Around the desk are typical office items like a coffee mug labeled ''Need Coffee,'' scattered papers, and a desk lamp dimly lit. The room looks dim to emphasize late-night fatigue. The caption near the monitor reads in a wavy font: ''Look deeeeep into the monitor..... you''re getting sleeeeeeeeepy. As usual.'' The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated sleepy features and whimsical colors to enhance the humor of feeling tired from screen time without any threat or negativity.'),
 (164, 'Humor, Pop Culture, Star Wars', 'Look! There''s a Klingon vessel, Mr. Chekov!', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set on the bridge of the Starship Enterprise from Star Trek. In the foreground, a surprised and slightly confused Russian crewmember, Mr. Chekov, wearing a classic Starfleet uniform with a distinctive golden shirt, points excitedly out a large curved window. Outside the window, visible in space, is a brightly colored Klingon bird-of-prey spaceship with exaggerated, cartoonish features such as large wings, sharp angles, and menacing eyes on its hull to make it look funny rather than threatening. The setting should look like a sci-fi spaceship interior with control panels, blinking lights, and futuristic screens in the background. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, capturing the moment of Mr. Chekov excitedly announcing the Klingon vessel to his crewmates, but with a smile or smirk from nearby characters to imply the joke is appreciated. The style is simple, colorful, and exaggerates facial expressions for comedic effect.'),
 (165, 'Humor, Word Play', 'LOOTING: A public shopping spree generously sponsored by local merchants in the wake of a riot.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a chaotic outdoor street market just after a riot. Local shop owners stand bewildered behind their colorful storefronts with ''Sale'' signs, scratching their heads or shrugging. In front of the shops, groups of cartoonish cartoon people excitedly dash around grabbing merchandise off shelves and from displays, holding shopping bags overflowing with goods. Some shoppers look gleeful and others confused, as if mistaking looting for a public shopping spree. Smoke and broken windows in the background suggest recent unrest, but the atmosphere remains lighthearted with exaggerated expressions. Bright colors, exaggerated motion lines, and comical facial expressions emphasize the joke’s ironic tone about looting being a ‘shopping spree sponsored by local merchants.’ No one appears angry or violent; instead, everyone is caught in comedic disbelief or merriment.'),
 (166, 'Humor, Life', 'Lord give me patience......but hurry!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person kneeling with clasped hands in a classic prayer pose, eyes closed, and a slightly impatient expression on their face. Above their head, a speech bubble reads, "Lord give me patience......but hurry!" The setting is simple, like a cozy living room with a small table nearby holding a clock with its hands spinning fast, emphasizing the urgency. The person’s exaggerated facial expression, with raised eyebrows and a slightly open mouth, conveys a mix of earnestness and impatience. The overall style is clean, bright, and lighthearted with rounded lines and soft colors, emphasizing the comedic and relatable tone of the joke without any religious symbols or darker tones.'),
 (167, 'Bad Puns, Math Humor', 'Lottery: A tax on people who are bad at math.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing at a lottery ticket booth looking confused while holding multiple lottery tickets and a calculator. The person has a puzzled expression, scratching their head as they try to add up the odds or costs. The lottery booth is colorful with flashing signs saying ''Lottery'' and ''Win Big!''. Nearby, a friendly cashier behind the counter smiles knowingly. The background is simple, maybe a few people walking by, with some dollar bills fluttering away in the wind to symbolize money lost. The overall mood is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the idea that playing the lottery is a kind of math challenge that most fail.'),
 (168, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'LOTTERY: The equivalent of betting that the next pope will be from Duluth, or that the parrot in the pet store window speaks Flemish.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in front of a lottery ticket counter looking confused and skeptical. Behind the counter, there is a colorful lottery poster featuring wildly unlikely predictions, such as a map pinpointing Duluth with a pope''s hat on it, and a bright pet store window with a cartoonish parrot wearing a little Flemish hat and speech bubble showing gibberish representing Flemish language. The customer holds a lottery ticket marked with question marks and raised eyebrows, emphasizing disbelief. The environment is light and playful with exaggerated facial expressions and a whimsical style, using vibrant colors and simple line art to enhance the joke''s absurdity.'),
 (169, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Love is blind. And when you get married you get your eyesight back.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene shows a happy couple standing side by side. The husband is wearing thick, comically oversized glasses with lenses fogged up, looking surprised but relieved. The wife is playfully holding a giant pair of binoculars aimed at him. Above them is a heart-shaped speech bubble or banner with the phrase, “Love is blind. And when you get married you get your eyesight back.” The background is a simple cozy home setting with a window showing a sunny day outside. The couple''s expressions are lighthearted and exaggerated to emphasize the joke’s irony. The style is colorful, cheerful, and clearly cartoonish with soft outlines and exaggerated facial features to enhance the humor.'),
 (170, 'Humor, Life, Motivational', 'Love like you''ve never been hurt, dance like nobody is watching, sing like nobody is listening and live like heaven on earth.', NULL, 'A cheerful cartoon scene set in a bright, open meadow under a sunny sky with fluffy clouds. In the center, a joyful person is dancing freely with eyes closed and a big smile, wearing casual, colorful clothes. Around them, musical notes float in the air to show singing, while a small audience of diverse cartoon characters (animals and people) nearby look either playfully distracted or genuinely happy but not directly watching the dancer. In the background, a peaceful idyllic landscape with a few birds flying and flowers blooming suggests a ''heaven on earth'' vibe. The overall mood is lighthearted, carefree, and uplifting, with soft pastel colors and exaggerated happy expressions for humor and positivity.'),
 (171, 'Love Humor, Marriage Humor, Word Play', 'Love may be blind, but marriage is a real eye-opener.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a newlywed couple standing side by side. The wife looks lovingly at her husband with heart-shaped eyes and a dreamy smile, symbolizing ''love may be blind.'' The husband wears very thick, oversized eyeglasses with exaggeratedly wide-open eyes, glasses slipping down his nose to highlight ''marriage is a real eye-opener.'' Around them, wedding decorations like balloons, flowers, and a ''Just Married'' sign. The background is cheerful but includes subtle details like a messy pile of bills or a misbehaving pet to gently hint at marriage realities. Both characters are drawn in a lighthearted and playful style with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the joke. Bright colors and simple lines keep the tone fun and friendly.'),
 (172, 'Facts, Food Humor', 'M&M''s stands for the last names of Forrest Mars, Sr., the candymaker, and his associate Bruce Murrie.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing two characters representing Forrest Mars, Sr. and Bruce Murrie standing side by side in a candy factory. Forrest Mars, Sr. is depicted as a friendly businessman in a suit with a lab coat over it, holding a giant, colorful M&M candy. Bruce Murrie, wearing a bow tie and suspenders, is smiling and holding another large M&M. Between them, a big sign reads ''M&M’s'' with the ampersand symbol styled as a candy. Around them are whimsical candy-making machines that are producing colorful M&Ms dropping into bags labeled ''Chocolate Candies.'' The background shows a bright factory setting with cartoon-style candy jars, conveyor belts, and candy decorations such as chocolate bars and peanuts to emphasize the candy theme. The style is bright, cheerful, and exaggerated for humor, with playful expressions on both men as if proudly presenting their candy creation. No complex details or people in distress; the mood is light and educational-humorous.'),
 (173, 'Love Humor, Marriage Humor, Word Play', 'Make love, not war; get married and do both!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful couple standing side by side. The couple is in wedding attire: the bride wearing a flowing white dress and the groom in a tuxedo. Above them, a playful banner reads ''Make Love, Not War.'' Surrounding the couple are whimsical symbols combining love and conflict imagery in a lighthearted way: hearts floating around the couple, but also small cartoonish peace signs and tiny, harmless cartoon bombs with smiley faces. The husband is holding a bouquet of flowers in one hand and a tiny white flag in the other. The background is bright and colorful, with a simple outdoor garden wedding setup featuring a decorated arch. Include subtle humorous cues like the bride giving a playful smirk and the groom looking slightly surprised, hinting at the joke''s punchline about marriage involving a mix of love and conflict in a fun, non-offensive way. The style should be cartoonish and cheerful with exaggerated expressions to emphasize humor.'),
 (174, 'Humor, Life, Traffic Jokes', 'Making eye contact with another driver revokes your right of way.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at a busy intersection with two cars stopped opposite each other. The drivers, a man in one car and a woman in the other, are exaggeratedly making intense eye contact through their windshields, each looking suspicious and determined. Small sweat drops or cartoonish tense expression lines emphasize their serious stares. Above their heads, a cartoonish ''Right of Way'' sign with a red crossed circle symbol appears, indicating it''s been ''revoked.'' Around the cars, other vehicles wait impatiently, with one driver tapping the steering wheel or honking lightly in frustration. The background shows typical street elements like traffic lights and crosswalks, but the focus remains on the staring drivers and the humorous moment of silent negotiation over who proceeds first. The style should be light, colorful, and playful, capturing the funny awkwardness of the situation without any aggression.'),
 (175, 'Humor, Jobs, Word Play', 'Manual Writer''s Creed:  Garbage in, gospel out.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a person sitting at a cluttered desk labeled ‘Manual Writer.’ The person looks frustrated but diligent, wearing glasses and holding a pen over a large open manual or instruction book. Around them are piles of crumpled papers and garbage bins overflowing with trash. In the background, there''s a whiteboard or poster with the phrase: ''Garbage in, gospel out'' written in bold, playful letters. The scene should show a mix of seriousness and silliness, with exaggerated facial expressions and cartoonish mess to emphasize the idea that poor input leads to blindly accepted output. Include small humorous details like spilled coffee and a clock showing late hours to capture the writer’s ongoing struggle.'),
 (176, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'Many are called, few are chosen. Fewer still get to do the choosing.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a celestial or mystical environment. In the foreground, a large group of diverse, eager people stand with hopeful expressions, looking up toward a glowing heavenly figure or figure on a throne symbolizing ''the chooser.'' This figure is depicted with a thoughtful or slightly overwhelmed expression, holding a golden clipboard or a list labeled ''Chosen List.'' Around this figure are a handful of individuals standing confidently or celebrating, wearing little stars or badges that say ''Chosen.'' The background has soft clouds, beams of light, and maybe faint outlines of other groups waiting for their turn, emphasizing the idea of many being called, fewer chosen, and even fewer choosing. The style should be lighthearted and exaggerated to emphasize the humor and hierarchy, with cartoonish expressions and gentle colors suitable for all ages. No violent or political imagery.'),
 (177, 'Humor, Life, Workplace', 'Many people quit looking for work when they find a job.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a busy job seeker in casual clothes holding a large magnifying glass, looking intensely at a ''Help Wanted'' sign on a shop window. Behind them, another character wearing work clothes is cheerfully walking away from a cluster of job listings with a briefcase in hand, smiling and waving goodbye to the hunting phase. The background includes a city street with other shops and a few puzzled pedestrians watching the worker leave the hunt behind. The style is light and playful with exaggerated expressions highlighting the contrast between searching and having a job.'),
 (178, 'Marriage Humor, Word Play', 'Marriage is a democracy -- one woman, one vote.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a husband and wife sitting at a small table that looks like a voting booth with a ballot box labeled ''Marriage Elections.'' The wife is smiling confidently and holding a single large ballot paper or a big checkmark, while the husband looks slightly puzzled or resigned with a small voting slip or empty hand. The setting is a cozy living room with a picture frame on the wall that shows a heart or wedding ring symbol. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated, with bright colors and cheerful expressions to emphasize the joke that in marriage, the wife has the decisive or sole vote.'),
 (179, 'Humor, Math Humor', 'MATH ANXIETY: An intense lifelong fear of two trains approaching each other at speeds of 60 and 80 mph.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two trains on the same track heading directly towards each other. One train is labeled ''60 mph'' and is colored blue, the other labeled ''80 mph'' and is red. Both trains have exaggerated scared facial expressions with wide eyes and sweat drops on their faces. In the middle between the trains, a cartoon person stands with a frightened expression, clutching a math book titled ''Math Anxiety.'' The background is a simple countryside with railroad tracks continuing into the distance and a few trees. The overall mood should be lighthearted and funny, emphasizing the ''fear'' element with cartoon-style over-the-top emotions and a math-related twist, without any violence or danger depicted explicitly.'),
 (180, 'Bad Puns, Math Humor', 'Math illiteracy affects eight of every five people.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a group of five people standing together. Above them, a large, comically exaggerated math equation floats in the air reading ''8 of every 5 people.'' The characters look confused and puzzled, scratching their heads or staring at the equation with exaggerated expressions. Some have question marks or little swirling lines above their heads to represent confusion. The background is a simple classroom or casual setting with a chalkboard showing random numbers and symbols faintly. The style is lighthearted, with bright colors and exaggerated facial features to emphasize the joke about math illiteracy and the absurdity of the fraction.'),
 (181, 'Humor, Philosophy, Science', 'Maybe oxygen is a very lethal poison that just takes 75-100 years to work', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a playful personified oxygen molecule wearing a mischievous grin, holding a small hourglass dripping sand slowly. The oxygen molecule stands next to an elderly smiling human cartoon character sitting in a rocking chair, wearing comfy clothes and glasses, looking relaxed and unaware. Around them are subtle symbols of aging, like a birthday cake with many candles and a calendar showing many years passing. The setting is bright and cheerful, maybe in a cozy living room or a park bench, emphasizing the long timespan. The style is light, colorful, and whimsical with exaggerated expressions to highlight the joke that oxygen is a slow-acting poison.'),
 (182, 'Good Question!, Life, Philosophy', 'Measuring wealth: count the things that you have for which you would not accept money.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful person standing next to a large, overflowing treasure chest filled not only with traditional riches like gold coins and jewels but also with everyday meaningful items. The person is holding up a photo album, a pet cat sitting beside them, a family portrait, and a blooming flower, all sparkling or glowing slightly to highlight their value. Around the chest, various objects like a handmade gift, a favorite book, and a pair of worn-out but treasured shoes are visible. The background is bright and whimsical, with floating dollar signs crossed out or with a red ''no'' symbol over them, emphasizing that these items can''t be bought. The overall tone is lighthearted and warm, celebrating sentimental value over money in a playful cartoon style.'),
 (183, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'Meditation is not what you think.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a person sitting cross-legged in a typical meditation pose on a cushion in a peaceful, minimalistic room. Instead of looking calm and serene, the person''s face shows surprise or confusion with wide eyes and raised eyebrows. Above their head is a thought bubble depicting a chaotic jumble of random funny images like dancing cats, flying toasters, and question marks, illustrating how their mind is not at peace as they might expect during meditation. The background includes simple elements like a small indoor plant, a window with sunlight streaming in, and a small clock showing the passage of time. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the contrast between the ideal of meditation and the reality of a busy, distracted mind.'),
 (184, 'Humor, Programming', 'Meets quality standards:  Compiles without errors.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon shows a computer programmer sitting at a desk cluttered with typical coding paraphernalia: multiple computer monitors displaying lines of colorful code, a keyboard, a coffee mug labeled ''Code Fuel,'' and sticky notes on the desk and monitor. The programmer is smiling proudly with a speech bubble that says, ''Meets quality standards: Compiles without errors.'' Around the desk, there are small cartoon-style celebratory elements like confetti or little stars to emphasize the joy of a successful compile. The background is a simple office or home workspace with minimal details to keep the focus on the programmer and the code. The overall mood is light-hearted and playful, highlighting the satisfaction programmers feel when their code compiles error-free.'),
 (185, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'Memories are a gift for the mind to open.', NULL, 'A whimsical cartoon scene showing a cheerful person standing in front of a giant, ornate gift box labeled ''Memories.'' The box is partly open, and instead of typical presents inside, glowing, colorful brain-shaped items float out like magical sparks. The background is bright and cheerful, with soft clouds and sparkles emanating from the open gift box. The person has a delighted, surprised expression as they reach out to catch one of the glowing brain souvenirs. Around them, faint, playful illustrations of past happy moments (like a small heart, a smiling sun, or a simple family stick figure) float gently nearby, emphasizing warmth and nostalgia. The style is light-hearted, cartoonish, and inviting, with exaggerated features and vibrant colors to emphasize the whimsical nature of the metaphor.'),
 (186, 'Humor, Philosophy, Science', 'Men love to wonder, and that is the seed of science.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a group of men gathered around a large plant pot labeled ''Science.'' From the pot, a whimsical seedling with exaggerated light bulbs as leaves is sprouting, symbolizing ideas and knowledge growing. The men have curious and thoughtful expressions, some stroking their chins or pointing at the seedling. The background is simple, with a lab table holding beakers and books titled ''Wonder'' and ''Curiosity.'' The overall style is light-hearted and colorful, emphasizing the connection between wonder and the birth of science without being serious or technical.'),
 (187, 'Humor, Word Play', 'METHYLPHOBIA: n. The fear that you are going to have to pay the one cent you over-pumped at the self-service station.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene at a busy self-service gas station. In the foreground, a nervous-looking person stands next to a gas pump with a wide-eyed expression of anxiety. The gas hose is still hooked to the car, and a small digital meter on the pump shows a price ending with an extra 1 cent. Behind the character is a thought bubble displaying a tiny, scary-looking, but funny cartoon monster labeled ''Methylphobia'' with a worried expression holding a tiny coin. Include the gas station surroundings with signs that say ''Self-Service'' and a price board showing gas prices. The overall tone is light-hearted and comical, with exaggerated facial expressions and a bright color palette to convey the silly fear of having to pay an extra cent at the pump.'),
 (188, 'Facts, Humor, Workplace', 'Michael Jordan has more money from Nike annually than all of the Nike factory workers in Malaysia combined.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Michael Jordan in a flashy basketball jersey holding a large bag overflowing with money marked with dollar signs. He is standing happily next to a huge, mountain-like pile of money. Nearby, a small group of factory workers from Malaysia, wearing simple work clothes and caps, look up at Jordan''s pile with surprised expressions. The factory workers are standing in front of a large factory building with the Nike swoosh logo prominently displayed on it. The setting is bright and cheerful, with exaggerated cartoon features and expressions emphasizing the disparity in earnings. The scene uses bright colors and caricature style to keep it light and funny.'),
 (189, 'Bad Puns, Pop Culture', 'Might as well be frank, Monsieur. It would take a miracle to get you out of Casablanca.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters in 1940s-style attire to evoke the classic movie Casablanca setting. One character is dressed as a French waiter or a suave gentleman (labeled ''Monsieur''), who looks stubbornly seated inside a cozy, dimly lit cafe reminiscent of Rick''s Café Américain. The other character, a friend or fellow patron, is standing nearby with a playful smirk, holding a plate with a frankfurter sausage on it, making a pun on the name ''frank''. The background includes classic 1940s decor—wooden tables, a vintage jukebox, and an old-fashioned clock showing late evening. A window shows a dimly lit street outside, hinting that ''getting out of Casablanca'' would be difficult. The expressions convey witty banter: the standing character is amused while ''Monsieur'' looks resigned or cheeky. The overall style is light and friendly with bold outlines and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the pun humor.'),
 (190, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'Modesty is a vastly overrated virtue.', NULL, 'A humorous, colorful cartoon scene showing a confident person standing proudly on a small podium labeled ''Most Modest Award.'' The person is smiling broadly with their chest puffed up and arms folded proudly. Around their feet, there are several discarded modesty-related items like a folded shirt labeled ''Modesty'' or a book lying open titled ''How to Be Modest''. In the background, a few cartoonish onlookers have puzzled or skeptical expressions, scratching their heads or whispering to each other. The setting is light and playful with simple, rounded shapes and bright colors to emphasize the joke about modesty being overrated without any aggressive or negative tones.'),
 (191, 'Humor, Life', 'Monday is a terrible way to spend 1/7 of your life.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at an office desk looking tired and miserable with a calendar prominently displayed that shows Monday circled in red. The background is an exaggeratedly gloomy Monday morning office setting with a clock showing early morning time, a coffee mug labeled ''Survival Juice'', and a stack of paperwork towering over the person. On the wall behind, a large poster humorously displays ''1/7 of life spent here!'' with a sad face emoji. The person slouches in their chair, wearing messy hair and wrinkled clothes, clearly dreading the start of the week. The overall tone is lighthearted and slightly exaggerated to emphasize the universal dread of Mondays.'),
 (192, 'Humor, Life', 'Money can''t buy happiness...But it sure makes misery easier to live with.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting on a simple wooden bench looking somewhat gloomy or stressed. The setting is a park with green grass and a few trees in the background. Next to the person on the bench is a big, overflowing bag labeled with a dollar sign ($), brimming with money such as cash and coins spilling out slightly. The person is holding a cup of coffee in one hand, with a small smile suggesting a slight comfort despite the misery. Above the scene, a thought bubble shows a happy face crossed out and replaced with a money bag, indicating the conflict between happiness and money. The colors should be bright and cheerful to contrast the person''s mixed emotions, and the overall style is lighthearted with exaggerated cartoon expressions emphasizing irony rather than sadness or despair.'),
 (193, 'Bad Puns, Money Humor', 'Money talks. The last thing I heard it say was ''Goodbye''.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing next to an open wallet that is empty. The wallet has eyes and a mouth, animated like a talking character, and it is waving goodbye with a little hand. The person looks surprised and sad, scratching their head or shrugging with a comic expression. Around them are scattered coins and bills flying away into the distance, as if the money is literally saying ''Goodbye'' and walking away. The background is simple, with maybe a city park bench or a kitchen table to set an everyday scene. The style should be light-hearted and playful, with bold lines and bright colors typical of a cartoon comic strip.'),
 (194, 'Life, Money Humor, Philosophy', 'Money wouldn''t be so important if everybody didn''t want some.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a diverse group of cartoon characters standing in a queue, all reaching eagerly toward a large, shiny coin or stack of bills floating just out of reach in the air. The coin is exaggerated in size and glowing to emphasize its importance. Characters vary in appearance; some look desperate, others greedy or hopeful, with comical exaggerated expressions like wide eyes and extended hands. In the background, a sign reads ''Money Here!'' with an arrow pointing toward the coin. The overall mood is lighthearted, with bright colors and playful details, such as one character holding an empty wallet and another counting coins with a puzzled look. The scene captures the universal idea that money is coveted by everyone because everyone wants some.'),
 (195, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'Morfy''s law - Enythink thit ken go rong willl.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a quirky, slightly disheveled scientist character standing next to a whiteboard or chalkboard. On the board is a large, hand-drawn text that humorously misspells Murphy''s Law as ''Morfy''s law - Enythink thit ken go rong willl.'' The scientist scratches their head, looking puzzled but amused at the misspelling. Nearby, objects are scattered in mild disarray: a tipped-over coffee mug, scattered papers with more funny spelling errors, and a broken gadget emitting a small puff of smoke to emphasize things going wrong. The overall tone is light and playful, with exaggerated expressions and bright colors to enhance the comedic effect of Murphy''s Law inevitably leading to errors, especially with spelling. The background is a simple lab or office setting with a few humorous details like a poster labeled “Law of Murphy” slightly peeling from the wall, and a small mischievous cat knocking over a plant in the corner, embodying chaos.'),
 (196, 'Food Humor, Humor', 'Most people eat as though they were fattening themselves for market.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a chubby person sitting at a dining table loaded with an exaggeratedly large feast: giant turkeys, mountains of mashed potatoes, oversized pies, and endless desserts. The person eagerly shovels food onto their plate with a satisfied grin, eyes gleaming with anticipation. In the background, a humorous twist shows a friendly-looking farmer wearing overalls and a straw hat, holding a clipboard and checking off the person''s name as if they were livestock being fattened for a market. The setting is warm and cozy, with a kitchen or dining room vibe, using bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke’s playful comparison of overeating to preparing animals for sale. No violence, just lighthearted and cartoonishly absurd imagery.'),
 (197, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'Most people have photographic memories, some just don''t have any film.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside an old-fashioned photo studio with a photographer dressed in vintage clothes holding a large, classic box camera mounted on a tripod. In front of the camera stands a confused person with a blank expression, holding an empty photo film cartridge. Around them, framed pictures of various people with perfectly clear, colorful photos hang on the studio walls, labeled ''Photographic Memory.'' The empty film cartridge in the person''s hand is humorously oversized, with a label reading ''No Film.'' The background should be lightly detailed to highlight the studio setting, with props like old photo albums and camera equipment. The art style should be bright, friendly, and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke''s pun about memory and photographic film without any violent or inappropriate elements.'),
 (198, 'Animals, Word Play', 'Most people think that T-rex can''t clap because they have short arms, but really they can''t clap because they are dead.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a friendly T-rex skeleton standing upright in a museum or prehistoric setting. The skeleton has tiny, short arms extended slightly forward but clearly too small to clap. Around the T-rex are a few curious cartoon characters or children looking up at it with puzzled expressions. Above or beside the skeleton is a playful speech bubble or a sign that says, ''Most people think T-rex can’t clap because of short arms, but really it’s because they’re dead!'' The background could show dinosaur bones or fossils in display cases. The overall tone should be light-hearted and comical, emphasizing the irony in the joke without any dark or scary elements.'),
 (199, 'Humor, Science', 'Mr. Interesting says: Imagine if water were magnetic! Drink some and walk through a strong magnetic field...', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene showing a quirky character labeled ''Mr. Interesting'' wearing a bright ''Mr. Interesting'' name tag, holding up a glass of water with a curious and mischievous smile. Around him, there’s a playful, visible magnetic field illustrated by large, wavy red and blue magnetic lines or waves emanating from a giant magnet shaped like a horseshoe. The magnet is positioned nearby, and the character is shown slightly lifting off the ground or being pulled towards the magnet as if the water inside him is magnetic. The setting is a simple lab or science classroom with a chalkboard in the background featuring a simple drawing of a magnet and water molecules. The overall style is lighthearted, colorful, and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the absurdity of magnetic water manipulation. The scene should evoke a fun “what-if” science vibe with humor and imagination clearly conveyed.'),
 (200, 'Humor, Insults, Word Play', 'MUGGER: A benevolent citizen of the streets who frequently spares the lives of total strangers in exchange for any cash and valuables in their possession.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a busy city street corner. The central figure is a cartoon mugger who looks surprisingly friendly and kind, wearing casual clothes but with a big goofy smile. Instead of a threatening pose, the mugger is holding out an open palm kindly or tipping an imaginary hat. Around him, surprised pedestrians are handing over their wallets, watches, and jewelry cheerfully with relieved or amused expressions. The background shows urban details like street lamps, a trash can, and a few passersby looking shocked yet unafraid. Above the scene, a playful sign or thought bubble reads: ''Benevolent citizen of the streets'' in a whimsical font. The style should be bright, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the ironic contrast between typical mugger expectations and this funny portrayal.'),
 (201, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'Murphy''s Law is recursive. Washing your car to make it rain doesn''t work.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a frustrated person standing next to a shiny, freshly washed car with soap suds dripping off. The person holds a garden hose and looks up at dark, menacing rain clouds forming directly overhead. The rain clouds have a comical, sly facial expression, as if they are mocking the person. In the background, a calendar or sign displays ''Murphy''s Law: Things go wrong, recursively.'' The setting is a suburban driveway with a lawn and maybe a cheerful sun trying to peek out behind the clouds. Add subtle details like water puddles on the ground reflecting the sky and a small weather vane spinning in confusion. The overall tone is lighthearted and silly, emphasizing the irony that trying to wash the car causes the rain to start, but the rain doesn''t help the situation—playing on the idea of recursion and Murphy''s Law.'),
 (202, 'Good Question!, Word Play', 'My book on the history of clocks just arrived. It''s about time.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person holding a freshly delivered book titled ''The History of Clocks.'' The person should be smiling widely and giving a thumbs-up gesture. In the background, show an exaggeratedly large, old-fashioned grandfather clock and a modern digital clock on the wall to emphasize the theme of time. Include a delivery box on the floor beside the person with a shipping label reading ''Just arrived.'' Add light rays or sparkles around the book to highlight it as special or long-awaited. The style should be bright and playful with simple lines and exaggerated expressions to enhance the joke''s pun on ''about time.'' Avoid any violent or sensitive content, focusing on a warm and funny atmosphere.'),
 (203, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'My buddy can''t afford to pay his water bill, so I sent him a ''Get Well Soon'' card', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing two friends in a living room. One friend looks worried, holding a water bill with a big red ''PAST DUE'' stamp on it. The other friend is cheerfully handing over a comical ''Get Well Soon'' card with a smiling water droplet character on the front. Include a kitchen sink or a dripping faucet in the background to emphasize the water theme. The setting is light and playful with exaggerated facial expressions to enhance the joke, capturing the irony of sending a ''Get Well Soon'' card for a water bill problem.'),
 (204, 'Animals, Humor, Word Play', 'My dog ate a bag of Scrabble tiles. Took him to the vet. No word yet.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a veterinarian''s office. In the foreground, a worried owner stands next to an anxious-looking dog sitting on the exam table. The dog looks slightly sheepish with a few Scrabble tiles stuck out of its mouth. Scattered on the floor near the table are colorful Scrabble tiles with letters clearly visible. The vet, wearing a white coat and stethoscope, bends over the table reviewing a clipboard with a puzzled expression. A wall clock shows time passing to emphasize the ''waiting'' element of the joke. The background includes typical vet office details like animal posters, a scale, and a small reception desk to create a comforting yet professional atmosphere. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions to capture the humor and confusion from the situation. No violence or negativity—just whimsical and funny.'),
 (205, 'Animals, Bad Puns', 'My dog has no legs, nobody likes him. He can''t even stand himself', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a sad-looking dog with no legs sitting on the ground. The dog appears to be glancing downwards, conveying a feeling of self-pity. Nearby, a few other cartoon dogs with legs are walking away or looking uninterested, illustrating that nobody likes him. A speech bubble above the legless dog reads, "I can''t even stand myself," emphasizing the pun. The background is a simple park with green grass and a few trees, keeping the focus on the dog and the play on words. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish to keep the mood funny, not depressing.'),
 (206, 'Animals, Word Play', 'My father has the heart of a lion, and a lifetime ban from the zoo.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful middle-aged man with a big smile standing outside a zoo entrance. The man is holding a certificate or piece of paper labeled ''Lifetime Ban Notice'' with a cartoon lion behind a fence in the background. The lion looks mildly amused or indifferent. The zoo gate has a sign that says ''Zoo Entrance'' and another sign next to the man saying ''No Entry for This Visitor.'' Around the man, add subtle comical elements like a few broken tree branches or a knocked over trash can hinting at prior mischief. Use bright, playful colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize humor and lightheartedness.'),
 (207, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'My favorite genre of movie is ''someone coughs up blood into a napkin and doesn''t tell anyone''.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a cozy movie theater. The foreground shows a person seated in a movie chair, looking suspicious and nervous, holding a napkin with visible red spots on it. Around them, other moviegoers are glancing over with puzzled or suspicious expressions. The background shows a typical movie theater setting with a large screen, dim lights, and rows of seats. A faint silhouette of someone on screen is coughing dramatically but everyone in the room looks uncomfortable and whispering to each other. The style should be lighthearted and exaggerated, with expressive faces and clear focus on the awkwardness created by the secretive napkin incident.'),
 (208, 'Pop Culture, Word Play', 'My favorite movie is Robin Williams, without a doubt, is Mrs. Fire', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting comfortably in a movie theater with popcorn, watching a movie. On the movie screen, instead of a movie title or scene, the words ''Mrs. Fire'' are displayed prominently. The person looks confused or amused, scratching their head as if mishearing or misunderstanding the movie title. Around the person, add subtle visual hints referencing Robin Williams, such as a stand-up microphone or a cartoonish mask resembling his face on a poster nearby, to connect the name ''Robin Williams'' with the joke. The theater is cozy with rows of seats and a classic movie screen, emphasizing the movie-watching setting in a light, funny way. The style should be colorful, exaggerated, and cartoonish, with expressive facial features and playful details that highlight the confusion in the joke without any harsh or negative themes.'),
 (209, 'Humor, Word Play', 'My friend David had his ID stolen recently. Now we just call him Dave.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two male friends standing together outside. One friend, looking slightly smug and wearing casual clothes, is pointing at the other who looks confused and slightly annoyed. The annoyed friend is holding an empty wallet with a visible ''ID Missing'' label on it. Above them is a small floating caption showing a torn or disappearing ID card icon. The environment is simple, maybe a park or street background with light colors to keep it bright and funny. The style should be playful and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions emphasizing the joke about the stolen ID and the nickname change from ''David'' to ''Dave.'' No violence or negativity, just light-hearted and witty banter vibes.'),
 (210, 'Humor, Word Play', 'My friend Rick has CDO - it''s just like OCD but it''s in alphabetical order', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a person named Rick standing proudly next to a large clipboard or poster. On the clipboard, the letters ''CDO'' are neatly written in perfect alphabetical order, with the letters ''OCD'' jumbled or crossed out nearby. Rick should have a cheerful, slightly nerdy expression, wearing casual clothes with maybe glasses. Around him, include little visual hints of neatness and order: perfectly stacked books, color-coded folders, or labeled jars arranged alphabetically on shelves. The style should be bright, clean, and light-hearted, emphasizing neatness and the joke about OCD being alphabetized.'),
 (211, 'Animals, Dark Humor', 'My friends dog died the other day so I got her an identical one to make her feel better, although I''m not sure what she''s gonna do with two dead dogs', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing with a slightly confused or awkward expression, holding two identical dogs who are cartoonishly portrayed as clearly ''dead'' in a funny, non-offensive way (e.g., stiff limbs, X eyes, a small cloud above their heads indicating being lifeless, or little ''zzz'' symbols). The background is a simple domestic setting, like a living room with a couch and a picture of a happy dog on the wall. The person you see is trying to comfort a friend, who stands nearby looking surprised or bewildered at holding two identical lifeless dogs. The overall style is light, colorful, and exaggerated to enhance the comedic effect without anything dark or upsetting.'),
 (212, 'Bathroom Humor, Word Play', 'My grandson laughs when I tell bathroom jokes. Poop jokes aren''t my favorite kind of joke, but they are a solid #2.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in a cozy living room where a cheerful elderly grandfather is sitting on an armchair with a big smile, telling a joke. Nearby, his young grandson is laughing heartily, clutching his stomach. On a small coffee table between them is a comically oversized book titled ''Bathroom Jokes.'' The background shows a bathroom door with a visible number ''2'' on it, subtly referencing the joke''s punchline. A roll of toilet paper, a rubber duck, and a plunger are playfully placed around the room, adding to the bathroom humor. The art style is bright, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the jovial mood and the silly nature of the joke, suitable for all ages and free from any violence or sensitive content.'),
 (213, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Word Play', 'My horse will not come out of her stable after dark. She''s becoming a night mare.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at dusk or nighttime outside a stable. The stable is wooden with an open door showing a cozy interior. Just inside the doorway, a horse looks tired or sleepy with droopy eyes, half-lidded, and maybe wearing a cute little sleeping cap. Outside the stable, moonlight shines softly, casting shadows. Above the stable, floating in the air as a ghostly figure, is a playful, friendly-looking nightmare—depicted as a small, cartoonish horse with wings and a goofy grin, representing the pun on "nightmare." The main horse looks reluctant to leave the stable, clearly preferring the safety inside. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, emphasizing the pun without anything scary or threatening.'),
 (214, 'Good Question!, Humor, Life', 'My life has a superb cast, but I can''t figure out the plot.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a person standing center stage like an actor in a theater. Around them are various caricatured figures representing their ''cast'' — friends, family, coworkers — all dressed in colorful, exaggerated costumes to highlight their distinctive personality traits. The person looks puzzled, scratching their head, holding a large, open script or plot outline that''s completely blank or filled with random question marks. The background suggests a whimsical stage setting with curtains, spotlights, and a cluttered director’s chair nearby. The overall vibe is lighthearted and playful, with speech bubbles or signs that say things like ''Great cast!'' and ''Where''s the plot?''. The characters and setting are drawn in a lively, cartoon style with exaggerated expressions to emphasize confusion mixed with amusement.'),
 (215, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'My luck is like a bald guy who just won a comb.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful bald man holding a shiny new comb in one hand. The man should be standing in the center with an excited expression, but clearly, he has no hair on his head to use the comb on. Maybe add little sparkle effects around the comb to emphasize its newness. Surround the man with a few exaggerated unlucky symbols, like a broken mirror, a black cat crossing behind him, or a spilled salt shaker on the ground, to reinforce the idea of bad luck despite the ''win.'' The overall style should be lighthearted and colorful, with a clear focus on the contrast between the baldness and the useless comb prize. The background can be simple, like a lottery or game show stage with a banner that says ''Lucky Prize!'''),
 (216, 'Humor, Mechanics, Steven Wright, Word Play', 'My mechanic told me, ''I couldn''t repair your brakes, so I made your horn louder.''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in a small auto repair shop. In the foreground, a cheerful mechanic wearing a work jumpsuit and a name tag is speaking with a customer standing beside a car. The customer looks both surprised and amused. The car has a visible extra-large, comically loud horn attached to the front bumper, maybe painted bright red with sound waves drawn coming out of it to show it''s booming. The brake area of the car is either visibly broken or has a small ''Out of Order'' sign on it. The background shows typical garage elements: toolboxes, tires, and a lift. The overall style is lighthearted and exaggerated, with bright colors and expressive characters to emphasize the joke.'),
 (217, 'Humor, Mental Health Humor, Word Play', 'My memory is so bad.. (how bad is it?) How bad is what?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters having a conversation. Character A looks confused and scratches their head, with a puzzled expression and a thought bubble showing a jumbled mess of symbols or question marks to represent forgetfulness. Character B stands nearby, leaning in slightly with an inquisitive face and raised eyebrows. The background is a simple indoor setting, such as a living room with a couch and a small table. Above Character A, the speech bubble reads, ''My memory is so bad...''. Character B''s speech bubble responds, ''(how bad is it?)''. The punchline is delivered with Character A looking baffled, having an empty or very confused speech bubble, and Character B asks in a final speech bubble, ''How bad is what?''. The overall style is colorful and playful with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize confusion and forgetfulness. This cartoon should be lighthearted and family-friendly, visually emphasizing the comic misunderstanding caused by bad memory.'),
 (218, 'Humor, Life', 'My mind''s made up . . . don''t confuse me with facts.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cartoon character standing stubbornly with arms crossed and a determined, slightly annoyed expression. Their eyebrows are furrowed and mouth is set in a firm line. Around their head are thought bubbles with scribbled question marks and simple symbols representing confusion or contradiction, like a light bulb with a big red ''X'' over it, or question marks. In the background, a friendly cartoon figure labeled ''Facts'' is holding out an open book or paper towards the main character, trying to get their attention. The scene is lighthearted and colorful, using soft lines and exaggerated facial expressions to show the clash between stubbornness and reason without any hostility. The setting can be simple, like a plain room or outdoor park, making the characters and their interaction the focus. The overall tone is playful, illustrating the mental image of someone refusing to change their mind despite clear evidence or logic presented to them.'),
 (219, 'Humor, Philosophy, Word Play', 'My opinions may change, but not the fact that I am right.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a confident person standing on a small stage or platform with their arms crossed and a smug smile. The person is surrounded by floating speech bubbles showing changing opinions, like a thumbs up, a question mark, a lightbulb, and a shrug emoji, illustrating the idea of shifting viewpoints. Despite the changing speech bubbles, a large bold sign behind or above them reads clearly, ''I AM RIGHT.'' The setting should look lighthearted and colorful, avoiding any negativity, with a few laughing or puzzled audience characters watching the person. The style is simple and exaggerated, with big expressive eyes and playful lines to emphasize the humor in stubborn self-assurance despite changing opinions.'),
 (220, 'Humor, Word Play', 'My reality check just bounced.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing at a bank teller''s window looking surprised and slightly confused. The person holds out a large, oversized check labeled ''Reality Check'' in bright, bold letters. The bank teller behind the counter has raised eyebrows and holds up a rubber stamp marked ''Bounced,'' stamping it across the check. Around them, the bank environment is cheerful and exaggeratedly colorful, with a sign that says ''Reality Bank.'' Include small humorous details like a wall poster offering ''Loans for Dreams'' and a tiny calendar showing the date. The person’s expression and body language should convey disbelief and irony, emphasizing the joke about a ''reality check'' literally bouncing like a bad bank check.'),
 (221, 'Animals, Word Play', 'My sea sickness comes in waves.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene on a small boat in the ocean during the day. The boat is gently rocking on stylized cartoon waves that look like large rolling blue waves with white foam tops. A person on the boat looks queasy, holding their stomach with one hand and gripping the boat''s railing with the other. Their face is a bit greenish and shows discomfort but good-spirited humor. Around the boat, the waves are exaggerated, clearly emphasizing the motion. The background features a bright blue sky with a happily smiling sun and a couple of seagulls flying. The overall tone is light-hearted and playful with exaggerated, simple shapes and bright colors to emphasize humor.'),
 (222, 'Humor, Psychology Humor, Word Play', 'My superiority complex is better than your superiority complex.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two quirky characters standing face-to-face, both with exaggerated confident expressions and puffed-up chests. Each character wears a t-shirt with the phrase ''Superiority Complex'' printed on it. Above their heads are speech bubbles: one says, ''My superiority complex is better than yours!'' The background is simple and colorful, emphasizing the playful rivalry. One character might be slightly taller or wearing glasses to add contrast, and both have comically smug smiles. The scene should be lighthearted and playful, with cartoon-style bold outlines and vibrant colors, capturing the ironic and self-contradictory tone of the joke.'),
 (223, 'Humor, Psychology Humor', 'My therapist says I have trouble expressing emotions.  I can''t say I''m surprised.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring a person sitting on a comfy armchair in a therapist''s office. The person looks slightly awkward or uncomfortable, with a blank or deadpan facial expression, mouth closed as if unable to speak. Across from them, a friendly therapist sits with a clipboard and glasses, leaning slightly forward as if listening carefully, wearing a calm expression. The setting includes a framed diploma on the wall, a small potted plant, and a box of tissues on a side table. The scene should visually emphasize the difficulty of expressing emotions: the patient appears silent and unexpressive, while the therapist shows understanding. A speech bubble from the therapist reads, "You have trouble expressing emotions," and a second smaller speech bubble near the patient reads, "I can''t say I''m surprised." The overall style should be lighthearted and cartoonish with clean lines and bright colors, creating a relatable and funny mental image of therapy and emotional expression struggles without seriousness or gloominess.'),
 (224, 'Humor, Programming, Word Play', 'My unix programmer got sick. It was a case of grep throat.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a Unix programmer sitting at a desk cluttered with computer screens displaying code and command lines. The programmer looks unwell, with a red, irritated throat and a sad expression, possibly holding a thermometer or a cup of tea. A speech bubble or sign near the programmer says ''grep throat'' in a playful font. Around the desk, include visual puns: maybe a magnifying glass highlighting the word ''throat'' on a monitor, referencing the ''grep'' command used to search text. The overall style should be lighthearted and colorful, with computer and programming elements clearly visible, emphasizing the joke about a Unix-specific ''sore throat''. Avoid any harsh or graphic imagery; keep it simple, cute, and geeky in style.'),
 (225, 'Humor, Marriage Humor, Word Play', 'My wife and I always argued about which way to hang the toilet paper, so our therapist suggested we try it the other persons way for a week. You know... roll reversal.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a bathroom where a man and a woman stand near a toilet paper holder, each looking at the toilet paper roll with exaggerated facial expressions of mild confusion and surprise. The toilet paper roll is hanging in the ''wrong'' direction from each person''s perspective — one side showing the paper coming over the top, and the other side under the bottom. The bathroom has a simple playful design with a small framed picture on the wall, a plant on a shelf, and a typical toilet. Nearby, a cheerful therapist, holding a clipboard, is smiling and pointing toward the toilet paper roll, symbolizing the suggestion of ''roll reversal.'' The couple seems to be reacting to the therapist''s advice on resolving their argument in a lighthearted way. The overall style is bright, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the humor in the everyday domestic disagreement about toilet paper orientation without any harsh emotions or conflict.'),
 (226, 'Marriage Humor, Word Play', 'My wife and I had a big argument about which is the best vowel. I won.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon depicting a husband and wife standing in a brightly colored living room. The husband is smiling confidently, holding up a large letter ''I'' like a trophy, symbolizing his ''win'' in the argument about the best vowel. The wife looks slightly annoyed or surprised, with her arms crossed. Around them are playful visual hints emphasizing vowels: floating large colorful letters A, E, I, O, and U in the background. The scene is lighthearted and fun, with simple, friendly cartoonish characters and no harsh expressions. The atmosphere conveys a playful debate rather than a serious fight.'),
 (227, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Word Play', 'My wife asked me is I''d seen the dog bowl. I said I didn''t know he bowled', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy kitchen. A man stands confused with a raised eyebrow and a slight smile, looking towards his wife who is holding an empty dog bowl in one hand and pointing at it. Nearby, a friendly dog wearing a bowling ball patterned collar looks up innocently. In the background, a few bowling pins and a brightly colored bowling ball sit beside the dog’s feeding area as a playful nod to the pun. The kitchen is warm and inviting, with typical elements like a countertop, a bowl rack, and a small rug. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated to emphasize the joke’s wordplay between ''dog bowl'' and ''bowled.'''),
 (228, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'My wife asked me to put ketchup on the shopping list. Now I can''t read any of it', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in a cozy kitchen. A man stands near a refrigerator with a confused and frustrated expression, holding a shopping list that is completely covered in bright red ketchup, making the writing illegible. Next to him, his wife looks amused or slightly exasperated, arms crossed or hands on hips. The kitchen counter features typical items like a bottle of ketchup clearly visible, a loaf of bread, and a grocery bag. The scene should be colorful and lighthearted, with exaggerated facial expressions and simple, cartoon-style drawing. The ketchup should be dripping and smeared all over the paper so the list is comically unreadable.'),
 (229, 'Humor, Life, Marriage Humor', 'My wife isn''t talking to me. The funny part is - she thinks she''s punishing me!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a husband and wife in a living room. The wife is sitting comfortably on a couch with her arms crossed and a slight smirk, clearly silent but feeling victorious. The husband stands nearby looking confused and slightly worried, scratching his head or shrugging with a puzzled expression. Show a small comic bubble above the wife''s head with a light bulb to indicate she thinks she''s clever, and a small speech bubble near the husband with a question mark to show his confusion. Around them, objects like a TV, a coffee table with a remote and a cup, and light colors add a cozy home atmosphere. The style is simple and friendly, emphasizing the humor in the silent ''punishment.'' No aggressive or violent imagery, just a funny domestic scenario.'),
 (230, 'Humor', 'My wife just opened the car door for me. Would''ve been a nice gesture if we hadn''t been going 70mph', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a car speeding down a road at about 70 mph with exaggerated motion lines and a speedometer visible inside the car showing the speed. The wife is outside the car on the passenger side, leaning into the open car door with a polite, cheerful smile, as if she just opened the door for her husband. The husband is inside the car, looking surprised and wide-eyed, holding the steering wheel tightly. The scene should be lighthearted and funny, highlighting the absurdity of opening a car door at high speed. The background could be a simple roadside with a few trees or a stretch of highway to emphasize motion. No one should appear hurt or in danger, and the artwork should be cartoonish and playful, avoiding anything violent or serious.'),
 (231, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'My wife told me to stop impersonating a flamingo. I had to put my foot down.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene featuring a man standing on one leg, imitating a flamingo. He looks determined but slightly comical, with a goofy smile. His raised foot is firmly planted on the ground below him like he’s ''putting his foot down.'' Nearby, a woman (his wife) stands with her arms crossed, giving him a mock-serious or slightly annoyed look. In the background, a couple of flamingos wade in a pond, looking confused or amused by the man’s attempt. The setting is a bright, simple backyard or park area with grass and a few trees. The style is humorous and exaggerated, with bright colors and rounded shapes to emphasize the playful mood.'),
 (232, 'Humor, Pop Culture', 'National Enquirer headline we''ll never see:  Elvis Is Dead', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene showing a front page of a tabloid newspaper displayed on a newsstand with the headline ''Elvis Is Dead''. The newspaper has exaggerated, flashy fonts and eye-catching colors typical of sensational tabloids. Surrounding the newsstand are caricatured people reacting with surprise and confusion—two elderly fans wearing Elvis-style sunglasses and leather jackets, a reporter looking shocked, and a bystander with a raised eyebrow. In the background, there’s a subtle ghostly silhouette or shadow of Elvis Presley with his iconic hairstyle and sideburns, giving a playful nod to the joke’s implication that such a headline would never be printed. The overall tone is lighthearted and humorous, drawn in a classic comic strip style with bright colors and exaggerated expressions.'),
 (233, 'Humor, Money Humor, Word Play', 'NEGOTIATING: The art of persuading your opponent to take the nice shiny copper penny and give you the wrinkled old paper money.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters at a negotiation table. One character is enthusiastically holding out a bright, shiny copper penny with a big smile, while the other looks skeptical, holding crumpled, wrinkled paper money (like old dollar bills) in their hand. The setting is simple, with a plain table between them, a small stack of coins on one side, and worn-out paper money on the other. Both characters have exaggerated expressions: the penny-holder looks persuasive and hopeful, the paper-holder looks unsure and wary. The background is minimalistic to focus on the exchange, perhaps with a small sign above the table that says “Negotiations”. The style should be lighthearted and playful, like a typical cartoon strip with bold lines and bright colors to emphasize the humor in the situation.'),
 (234, 'Humor, Word Play', 'NEONPHANCY (ne on'' fan see) n. A fluorescent light bulb struggling to come to life.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a single fluorescent light bulb mounted on a ceiling fixture. The bulb has a face with exaggerated sleepy eyes and a slightly frowning mouth, as if it is struggling to wake up. Tiny sweat droplets can be added around its ''forehead'' to emphasize effort. The bulb glows faintly with dim bluish neon light, flickering intermittently. Around the bulb, whimsical squiggly lines and subtle spark effects illustrate the struggling to come to life. Below, a room with a cozy interior and a person staring up at the bulb in mild frustration or confusion, scratching their head. The overall style is light-hearted and cartoonish, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to convey the humorous concept of a bulb ''waking up'' like a groggy human. No violent or offensive elements, just playful and fun.'),
 (235, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Nerves of steel, Body of iron, Brain of stone.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a superhero character striking a triumphant pose. The superhero is wearing a shiny metallic suit made partly of steel and iron, emphasizing the ''nerves of steel'' and ''body of iron''. Their expression looks dazed or confused, with a comically oversized stone for a brain visible through a transparent helmet or open head section, illustrating ''brain of stone''. The background is simple and bright, with comic-style action lines radiating outward to highlight the character''s exaggerated qualities. Include subtle humorous details like a steel nerve-shaped guitar string or iron muscles with bolts, and a large rock labeled ''brain'' sitting loosely inside the head cavity. The overall tone is light and funny, without any threatening or inappropriate elements.'),
 (236, 'Mental Health Humor, Philosophy, Word Play', 'NEUROTIC: Sane but unhappy about it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a character with a slightly frazzled appearance—disheveled hair and wide, nervous eyes—sitting at a desk with a cup of coffee spilled beside a notebook. The character is slouched, looking both tired and frustrated. Above their head is a thought bubble with the word "Sane" crossed out and replaced with "Unhappy." The background is a simple office or home workspace with a clock showing late hours, emphasizing the mental state. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated features to highlight the neurotic nature without any negativity or distress, incorporating a subtle smile to imply the irony of being ''sane but unhappy.'''),
 (237, 'Humor, Insults', 'Never argue with an idiot. They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters standing on a simple flat ground. On the left, a clean-cut, slightly annoyed person wearing a shirt and jeans, holding their hands up as if trying to explain or argue. On the right, a goofy-looking character with a silly grin, messy hair, mismatched clothes, and barefoot, clearly representing the ''idiot.'' The goofy character is happily holding a wooden stick labeled ''Experience'' and is playfully tapping the other person''s head with it. Both characters should be drawn with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humor — the annoyed person looks frustrated and surprised, while the silly character looks gleefully mischievous. The background is minimal, perhaps a simple park or street setting with a tree and bench to keep the focus on the interaction. The style is colorful, lighthearted, and cartoonish, leaning into the playful insult of the joke without any aggression or negativity in tone.'),
 (238, 'Humor, Poker Humor', 'Never do card tricks for the group you play poker with.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at a poker table with four players sitting around it. The main focus is on one player in the middle of performing a flashy card trick, holding cards fanned out dramatically. The other three players have unimpressed, annoyed, or suspicious expressions. The poker table is cluttered with poker chips, cards, and drinks. One player is crossing their arms, another is sighing heavily, and the last is giving a side-eye glance. The setting should be bright and lively but with a comic sense of tension. Include a thought bubble or small speech bubble from one player saying something like ''Focus on the game!'' to emphasize the joke, but keep it light and playful. The style should be colorful and exaggerated, with cartoonish facial expressions to highlight the humor without any violence or negativity.'),
 (239, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'Never eat more than you can lift.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person at a picnic or buffet table overloaded with food items piled high on a large tray or plate. The person struggles to lift the enormous, towering stack of food, with exaggerated effort shown by sweat drops, strained facial expression, and shaky arms. The food pile includes a mix of comical oversized sandwiches, cakes, fruits, and drinks. Around them, a few people watch, some laughing or giving knowing looks. The background is simple, bright, and cheerful to emphasize the lighthearted tone.'),
 (240, 'Cars Humor, Humor, Workplace', 'Never get in the way of a car that needs extensive body work.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a battered, old car with exaggerated dents, scratches, and missing parts like doors and a bumper. The car looks almost like a cartoon character with tired eyes formed by the headlights and a frowning front grille. There is a confused pedestrian or character standing in front of the car with a worried expression, hesitating to cross or get near it. Surrounding the car are obvious signs of heavy damage, like tools, paint cans, and a mechanic''s clipboard nearby. The background is a simple garage or street setting with a cartoonish style. The overall tone is light-hearted and funny without any violence or negative elements.'),
 (241, 'Books, Humor, Movies', 'Never judge a book by a motion picture with the same title.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large open book sitting on a table with a small movie projector next to it. The book has a surprised or disappointed facial expression with eyes and a mouth, looking towards the projector. The projector is displaying a brightly colored, exaggeratedly bad or silly movie scene on a screen behind them. Around the scene, scattered popcorn and a few film reels add to the movie theme. The background suggests a cozy living room or library setting with shelves of books and framed movie posters on the wall, one showing the same title as the book. The art style is playful and cartoonish, emphasizing the idea that judging a book based on its film adaptation leads to mismatched expectations and humorous disappointment.'),
 (242, 'Computers, Humor, Workplace', 'Never let a computer know you''re in a hurry.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a frustrated person sitting at a desk quickly trying to finish work on a slow, old-fashioned desktop computer. The computer screen displays a loading bar moving painfully slowly with a little snail icon next to it. The person''s face shows impatience and mild exasperation, tapping their fingers on the desk. Around the desk are scattered papers, a coffee cup, and a clock on the wall swirling around to emphasize the slow passage of time. The setting is a simple office or home workspace with a cheeky, lighthearted vibe emphasizing the irony of technology slowing down just when you''re in a hurry.'),
 (243, 'Humor, Motivational', 'Never let your fears stand in the way of your dreams.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon shows a character standing at a fork in a path labeled ''Fears'' on one side and ''Dreams'' on the other. The ''Fears'' path is cluttered with comically exaggerated obstacles such as tiny monsters, jagged rocks, and silly pitfalls. The ''Dreams'' path is bright and inviting, with fluffy clouds, stars, and a shining sun. The character, looking determined but slightly nervous, wears casual clothes and is stepping confidently toward the ''Dreams'' path, while behind them a shadowy, oversized fear figure perhaps shaped like a cartoon monster tries to block the way but looks harmless and goofy rather than scary. The overall tone is uplifting and funny, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions emphasizing overcoming silly fears to reach big dreams.'),
 (244, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'Never make anything simple and efficient when it can be complex and wonderful.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a cluttered desk with papers, gears, wires, and colorful contraptions surrounding them. The person looks both proud and amused, holding a ridiculously complicated gadget full of unnecessary buttons, levers, and flashing lights. Nearby, a simple and plain object, like a basic light switch or simple tool, lies untouched and ignored. The background should be a cozy room filled with quirky inventions and sketches pinned on the wall. The overall tone is lighthearted and whimsical, highlighting the joy and absurdity of complexity over simplicity.'),
 (245, 'Good Question!, Humor, Life', 'Never miss a good chance to shut up.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a cheerful, slightly mischievous-looking character standing with a finger raised as if sharing advice. The character is surrounded by speech bubbles, one bubble contains the phrase: ''Never miss a good chance to shut up.'' In the background, a group of people listens. One person looks surprised, covering their mouth with one hand, trying not to speak, while another looks amused. The setting is a casual environment like a park or a living room, with simple details like a bench or a sofa. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor of choosing silence wisely.'),
 (246, 'Humor, Life', 'Never mistake endurance for hospitality.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a cozy living room. A tired but polite guest, wearing casual clothes and holding a small suitcase, is sitting on a shabby-looking couch that’s clearly past its prime. Their facial expression shows exhaustion mixed with awkward politeness. Across from them, a weary but welcoming host stands near the door, smiling awkwardly while holding a tray with a barely half-full teacup and a lone cookie. The host’s home looks a bit crowded, with mismatched furniture and visible signs that the guest has been there a long time (maybe a pair of slippers on the floor, a sleep mask on the coffee table). A small clock on the wall shows late evening time. The overall vibe implies the guest is enduring a lengthy stay rather than feeling genuinely welcome, capturing the joke’s essence about confusing endurance with true hospitality. The art style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, focusing on exaggerated expressions and cozy but slightly tired atmosphere without any negativity or harshness.'),
 (247, 'Good Question!, Humor, Life', 'Never say anything more predictive than ''Watch this!''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing confidently with a big grin, pointing at an object or situation about to go wrong. The person is mid-sentence saying, ''Watch this!'' Around them, a chaotic sequence is about to unfold—such as a cake teetering on the edge of a table, a dog eyeing the cake, or something obviously about to result in a funny mishap. The background is a casual living room or kitchen, with exaggerated expressions on onlookers'' faces showing a mix of anticipation and concern. The overall style is light-hearted and cartoonish, emphasizing the irony of the phrase ''Watch this!'' being overly predictive of impending trouble, without showing the actual accident, just the build-up moment.'),
 (248, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'Never say never unless you''re lying.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing confidently while saying the phrase ''Never say never.'' The person has a playful smirk, and a small mischievous cartoon speech bubble pops out with the word ''Lying!'' inside it to highlight the joke. Surround the character with lighthearted thought bubbles or doodles, such as crossed-out words and big question marks, to visually represent the irony of the phrase. Keep the background simple and colorful, like a casual everyday setting (a park bench or sidewalk), so the focus stays on the character and the speech bubbles. Use exaggerated cartoon features and expressions to emphasize humor without any elements of violence, politics, or negativity.'),
 (249, 'Food Humor', 'Never staple a peanut butter and banana sandwich together.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a classic peanut butter and banana sandwich on a plate. The sandwich is exaggeratedly large and looks messy, with peanut butter oozing out and banana slices visible. A hand, wearing a funny glove or with comedic style, is holding a small stapler pressing it down on the sandwich''s corner as if trying to staple it together. The stapler should have a surprised or confused face, adding to the comedy. The background is a simple kitchen counter with a few typical kitchen items like a jar of peanut butter and a bunch of bananas. The overall style is colorful, lighthearted, and playful, emphasizing the absurdity of stapling a sandwich rather than eating it.'),
 (250, 'Word Play, Workplace', 'Never tell your boss that you work better under pressure.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a typical office environment. The main character is an employee nervously talking to their boss, who is standing with crossed arms and a stern expression. The employee''s speech bubble says, ''I work better under pressure.'' To illustrate the phrase literally, the background shows a large, exaggerated pressure gauge labeled ''Work Pressure'' with the needle dangerously close to the red zone. Nearby, a stack of papers is visibly being squished by an oversized hand labeled ''Pressure.'' The office has typical items like a desk with a computer, a coffee mug, and a calendar on the wall. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated to bring out the humor of the double meaning of ''pressure.'' No one looks hurt or upset beyond office stress.'),
 (251, 'Humor, Life', 'Never test the depth of the water with both feet.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing at the edge of a small pond or river, looking hesitant and worried. The person has one foot confidently stepping into the water while holding a shoe in their hand, and the other foot is kicking backward, already submerged and splashing water dramatically. Their facial expression should be wide-eyed and panicked, as if they''ve just realized the water is unexpectedly deep. Around them, include reeds, a few fish peeking out, and maybe a surprised frog on a rock. The background is a bright outdoor setting with a sunny sky and trees. Emphasize the splash and water depth to highlight the joke''s message about the dangers of testing water depth with both feet. Use a colorful, playful cartoon style with exaggerated expressions and motion lines for comedic effect.'),
 (252, 'Humor, Marriage Humor', 'Never trust a man who says he''s the boss at home. He probably lies about other things too.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy home living room. Center the image on a man sitting comfortably in an armchair with a confident, slightly smug expression, wearing casual clothes and holding a remote control. Nearby, a woman stands with her arms crossed, sporting a knowing smile or amused smirk, clearly skeptical of the man''s claim. A speech bubble from the man reads, "I''m the boss at home!" while a smaller thought bubble above the woman says, "He probably lies about other things too." The background should include everyday home items like a couch, a coffee table with magazines, a lamp, and family photos on the wall. The overall tone is light-hearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions typical of cartoon humor.'),
 (253, 'Humor, Pessimistic, Social Commentary', 'Never underestimate the power of stupid people in large groups.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a large, diverse crowd of people standing together in a public place like a park or town square. The people are portrayed in exaggerated, silly poses with confused or goofy expressions—some scratching their heads, some looking bewildered. The crowd is so large that it spills beyond the edges of the picture. In the foreground, a single character (looking thoughtful or wise) stands apart from the group, holding a sign or placard that reads "Never underestimate the power of stupid people in large groups." The background can include simple cityscape elements or trees to imply a communal gathering. The style should be lighthearted and colorful, emphasizing the playful absurdity of the idea without being mean-spirited or offensive. No aggressive or negative actions, just an amusing look at crowd mentality.'),
 (254, 'Humor, Language', 'Never use a long word when a diminutive one will do.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a classroom where a teacher stands at the blackboard, pointing to a complicated, long word written in big letters. Next to the teacher is a small cartoon character—a cute, tiny creature labeled ''Diminutive''—holding a much smaller, simpler word on a sign. The teacher looks serious but puzzled, while the tiny character looks confident and cheeky. The classroom has typical school elements: desks, a globe, a chalkboard with some scribbles, and a window showing a sunny day. The style is lighthearted and colorful with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor of using long versus short words.'),
 (255, 'Humor, Traffic Jokes', 'Never use directional signals when changing lanes. They only warn other drivers to speed up and not let you in.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a congested multi-lane highway with several cars. In the foreground, one car is trying to change lanes. The driver inside looks mischievous, cheekily grinning while deliberately not using the turn signal. Other nearby cars have exaggerated expressions of annoyance and frustration, speeding up with motion lines behind them to indicate acceleration. Above the lane changer, a comic-style thought bubble reads, ''Why warn them?'' The setting is daytime, with clear skies and simple roadside elements like streetlights and signs. Overall, the style is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humor of the joke about not using signals causing other drivers to speed up and block the lane change.'),
 (256, 'Animals, Humor, Life', 'Never wrestle with a pig: You both get all dirty, and the pig likes it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a muddy farmyard scene with a person and a pig both covered in mud. The person is sprawled on the ground looking frustrated and dirty, wearing casual clothes now splattered with mud. The pig, in contrast, looks quite happy and content, smiling with mud dripping from its snout and body. Around them, tufts of grass and a wooden fence frame the background. The person and pig are mid-wrestle stance, with the pig clearly enjoying the mess while the person is annoyed. The style is lighthearted and colorful, emphasizing the contrast between the pig''s enjoyment and the person''s displeasure.'),
 (257, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'Never, under any circumstances, take a sleeping pill and a laxative on the same night.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy bedroom at night. A tired-looking adult character, in pajamas, is standing between two nightstand drawers labeled ''Sleeping Pills'' and ''Laxatives.'' The character looks worried and confused, holding a sleeping pill in one hand and a laxative bottle in the other. In the background, a bed with a fluffy pillow and blanket is visible, and a digital alarm clock shows late-night time (around 11 PM). To add humor, next to the bed is a bathroom door slightly ajar with animated comic-style motion lines going in opposite directions, symbolizing conflicting bodily reactions. The character’s expression is exaggerated, wide-eyed, with sweat drops to emphasize anxiousness. The style is vibrant, lighthearted, and cartoonish with bright colors and simple shapes to invoke humor without any threat or discomfort. No explicit or graphic elements—just expressive facial features and the implication of the joke’s meaning through objects and reaction lines.'),
 (258, 'Humor, Programming, Word Play', 'Newton''s Law of Programming: For every neat enhancement there is an equally neat bug.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cluttered programmer''s workspace. At the center, a cheerful programmer is sitting at a desk filled with two computer monitors, keyboard, coffee mug, and scattered code papers. One monitor displays a neat, colorful ''enhancement'' window with a big green checkmark, while the other screen shows a bug report or an error message with a red warning symbol. Above the programmer, a playful cartoon thought bubble shows Newton''s Law of Programming written like a scientific law, perhaps with little arrows pointing between a neat enhancement and an equally neat bug, illustrated as a tiny cartoon bug holding a ruler. The background can feature sticky notes with code snippets and a poster humorously combining Isaac Newton''s apple with software icons. The overall tone is light and witty, emphasizing the programmer’s resigned but amused acceptance of bugs appearing after improvements. The style is friendly and cartoonish, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to highlight the humor in the contradiction.'),
 (259, 'Humor, Life', 'No good deed goes unpunished.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy neighborhood park. In the center, a well-meaning character wearing a friendly smile is handing a small gift—like a flower or a sandwich—to another character, who looks slightly surprised but grateful. However, just as the giver turns away, a series of comic mishaps occur: the gift unexpectedly springs to life or causes a minor chaos, like a bee buzzing out from the flower or sandwich crumbs attracting a swarm of ants, leading the giver to accidentally trip or get tangled. The background shows other cartoonish onlookers with exaggerated expressions of shock or amusement. The overall vibe is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the ironic twist of "no good deed goes unpunished." Include speech bubbles or small visual cues (like cartoon stars around a head or tiny flies) to enhance the humor without any aggressive or negative imagery.'),
 (260, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'No individual raindrop ever considers itself responsible for the flood.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a large, overflowing river or flooded street with lots of water. In the foreground, several cute, small raindrops with simple round shapes and expressive faces look oblivious and innocent, shrugging their ''arms'' or looking confused as if saying ''Not me!''. Some raindrops are mid-fall from a cloudy sky, others are already splashing into the flood below. The floodwater has little waves and maybe a floating rubber duck or a small boat to emphasize the size of the flood. The background could include houses or trees partially submerged to show the severity of the flood, but the raindrops themselves appear unaware or detached from the big problem. The overall tone is lighthearted and funny, like a playful indictment of personal responsibility in a collective problem.'),
 (261, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'No matter how much you push the envelope it will still be stationary.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, traditional paper envelope sitting on a wooden table. A cartoon character, looking slightly frustrated and determined, is shown with both hands pushing against the envelope, which is clearly not moving despite their effort. The character''s cheeks can be puffed or showing strain to emphasize pushing. Add small motion lines around the character''s hands to show effort and some comic-style ''no movement'' sign around the envelope, like sweat droplets or a small comic ''stuck'' sign above it. The setting is simple, with a bright, cheerful background and maybe a wall clock or a small plant to fill space but not detract from the humor. The overall feel is light and funny, highlighting the pun about "pushing the envelope" literally, instead of its figurative meaning.'),
 (262, 'Humor, Life', 'No matter what goes wrong, there is always somebody who knew it would.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a chaotic office or family living room where things are clearly going wrong: a spilled cup of coffee on a laptop, papers flying in the air, a broken lamp, and a frazzled person looking surprised and upset. Meanwhile, in the background or off to the side, another character is smirking knowingly with crossed arms or a finger to their temple, as if they predicted the disaster all along. The setting should be colorful and exaggerated in style, emphasizing the contrast between the chaos and the calm person who ''knew it would happen.'' Include small humorous details like a calendar with the word ''Disaster Day'' marked or a wall clock running backward, reinforcing the inevitability theme. The overall tone should be light, funny, and relatable, capturing the idea that there''s always someone who anticipated the problem.'),
 (263, 'Humor, Life, Social Commentary', 'No matter what happens, somebody will find a way to take it too seriously.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a casual, lighthearted setting like a small gathering or a party where one person makes a playful joke or silly gesture. In the background, a second person is shown reacting with exaggerated seriousness—arms crossed, frowning deeply, perhaps wearing a suit and tie to exaggerate their overly serious demeanor. Other people around them are laughing or smiling relaxedly, highlighting the contrast. Add a speech bubble coming from the serious person with something like ''This is not a laughing matter,'' while the jokester has a cheerful expression. Include subtle details like a party banner, snacks on a table, and casual clothing on the majority of the people to enhance the lighthearted atmosphere. The overall tone is playful and friendly, without any aggression or negativity, emphasizing that someone always finds a reason to get overly serious about something that should be fun or minor.'),
 (264, 'Humor, Word Play', 'No matter what you hear, the words are usually different.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon of two characters standing next to each other, both wearing rabbit ear headbands and holding large cartoonish ears to symbolize listening. There are colorful speech bubbles above the characters showing the same phrase but with each bubble containing jumbled, slightly different words to visually represent misunderstanding. The setting is a simple park bench or living room couch to imply casual conversation. Include subtle visual cues like a smashed tin can phone or slightly crossed telephone wires between them to enhance the theme that messages are altered when transmitted. The style should be playful, with exaggerated expressions of confusion and amusement on their faces, to capture the irony of the joke.'),
 (265, 'Animals, Humor, Life', 'No one can feel as helpless as the owner of a sick goldfish.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a worried person sitting at a small table next to a goldfish bowl. The person looks distressed, with exaggerated worried eyebrows and hands gripping their cheeks. The goldfish inside the bowl appears slightly droopy or sad, with tiny cartoonish sweat drops and a thermometer stuck in the water. Around the scene, include typical home details like a couch, a small plant, and a clock on the wall to create a cozy living room vibe. The overall style is bright and friendly with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the helplessness and seriousness the person feels over something seemingly minor like a small sick goldfish.'),
 (266, 'Humor, Parenting, Philosophy', 'No one ever really finds out what he believes until he begins to instruct his children.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a parent trying to explain a lesson to two curious children sitting cross-legged in front of them. The parent looks slightly confused or thoughtful, scratching their head while holding a book or a chalkboard with some simple words or pictures. The children look eager but puzzled, mirroring the parent''s uncertainty. The background is a cozy living room or a classroom with playful colors and simple decorations like a clock, family photos, or educational posters. The overall style is light-hearted, with exaggerated expressions emphasizing the parent''s moment of self-discovery and the children''s questioning faces.'),
 (267, 'Bathroom Humor, Humor', 'No one is listening until you fart.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a quiet office meeting room where a group of diverse coworkers are sitting around a conference table, looking bored, checking their phones, and doodling. At the far end, a person suddenly looks surprised and a bit embarrassed, holding their nose and slightly blushing, indicating they just farted. Immediately, all the other coworkers abruptly stop their activities and turn their attention toward that person, wide-eyed with shocked or amused expressions. Include typical office items like laptops, coffee mugs, papers, and a whiteboard in the background. The mood is light-hearted and comical, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the sudden change in attention triggered by the fart. Cartoon style with bright colors and simple lines, no harsh or mean-spirited elements.'),
 (268, 'Humor, Life, Workplace', 'No one is listening until you make a mistake.', NULL, 'A cartoon office or classroom setting where a person is trying to explain something to a group of people or colleagues. The group looks bored, uninterested, or distracted—some are looking at phones, others have sleepy expressions. Suddenly, the speaker makes a small, obvious mistake in their speech or writing (like a visible spelling error or stumbling over words). In the next panel or nearby scene, the entire group’s heads snap up, eyes wide with surprise and focus, mouths open as if all are paying intense attention for the first time. The setting should be light and humorous with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize disinterest turning into sudden alertness. Include details like a whiteboard, desk, or presentation materials to situate the scene in a learning or work environment. The style should be colorful, simple, and cartoonish with clear visuals emphasizing the change in attention triggered by the mistake.'),
 (269, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'No person was ever honored for what he received.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a simple awards ceremony stage with a podium and a big banner that says ''Honors Ceremony.'' Standing at the podium is a quirky, smiling announcer holding a microphone. In front of the stage, a person looks confused, holding an oversized gift box wrapped with big shiny ribbon, clearly expecting applause for receiving it. Nearby, a trophy display case is empty except for plaques labeled ''Honored for Giving, Achievements, Excellence.'' The audience consists of cartoon people clapping and cheering, but no one is applauding the gift-holder. The overall style is light-hearted and exaggerated, using bright colors and expressive faces to highlight the irony that people are honored for what they give or accomplish, not for what they receive. The setting is indoors with a few balloons and streamers for festive atmosphere, emphasizing the comedic contradiction in the joke’s message.'),
 (270, 'Clothing Humor, Good Question!, Laundry Humor', 'No use looking at the tag after the clothes have been shrunk.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person looking frustrated while holding a tiny shrunken sweater in one hand. The person is standing in front of a washing machine with soap suds spilling over. Nearby, the original oversized sweater with a clearly visible clothing tag is lying crumpled on a laundry basket. The tag zoom-in bubble shows a witty detail such as ''Machine wash cold'' or ''Do not shrink.'' The background includes a laundry room with a detergent bottle and drying rack, emphasizing the laundry context. The person''s exaggerated facial expression and body language highlight the humor of realizing the tag’s advice only after the clothes are ruined.'),
 (271, 'Humor, Language, Word Play', 'No word in the English language rhymes with month, orange, silver, and purple.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring a confused dictionary character with arms and eyes, holding a large magnifying glass over a page titled ''Words That Rhyme''. Around it are four colorful word bubbles shaped like comic clouds, each containing one of the words: ''month'', ''orange'', ''silver'', and ''purple''. In each bubble, illustrate the word looking sad or frustrated, maybe with small frowns or slumped posture. The setting is a cozy study room with bookshelves full of word books and a desk lamp shining light. The dictionary character is scratching its head, looking puzzled. The overall style should be lighthearted and funny, with simple, vibrant colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the rhyming struggle.'),
 (272, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Nobody is in control of their own elevator.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a small elevator with three diverse people looking slightly confused or surprised. The elevator buttons are prominently displayed with some buttons glowing, but there is also a quirky, oversized “Control Panel” that is humorously complex and comically labeled with random knobs, levers, and a big red ''Do Not Touch'' button. None of the people are pressing the buttons; instead, a small, playful robotic hand or a tiny, cheeky cartoon character (like a mischievous elevator sprite) is pressing a button from the corner, illustrating that nobody inside actually controls the elevator. The elevator''s background shows typical elevator features like floor numbers, a floor indicator with moving arrows, and a small mirror reflecting the puzzled expressions. The style is light-hearted, with exaggerated facial expressions and bright colors to emphasize the joke’s playful nature without any negativity.'),
 (273, 'Life, Workplace', 'Nobody notices what I do until I don''t do it.', NULL, 'A cartoon office scene showing a single worker sitting at a cluttered desk with a tired but content expression. Around the worker, various tasks are depicted humorously: a coffee machine brewing coffee, a printer spitting out paper, a filing cabinet with papers neatly stacked, and a plant being watered by a small automatic sprinkler. The worker is surrounded by colleague characters each looking worried or confused, glancing around and checking their watches, implying something is off. In the background, a calendar shows the current day marked with a big red X. The style is lighthearted and colorful, emphasizing the humor of quiet contributions going unnoticed until they stop happening. The scene should feel relatable and amusing, without any harsh or negative expressions.'),
 (274, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'Nostalgia isn''t what it used to be.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing an elderly person sitting in a cozy armchair, holding a photo album open on their lap. The person looks slightly puzzled or disappointed, scratching their head, with a thought bubble above them containing a simple retro symbol like an old cassette tape or vintage TV. Around the room, nostalgic items are scattered: a rotary phone on a side table, a vinyl record player, and a poster of a classic movie on the wall. The caption ''Nostalgia isn''t what it used to be'' is prominently displayed either above or below the scene, emphasizing the joke. The overall style is warm and lighthearted with exaggerated, friendly facial features to highlight the playful irony of the phrase.'),
 (275, 'Animals, Word Play', 'Not enough bucks stop here.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a bus stop sign that reads ''Not enough bucks stop here.'' Next to the sign is a confused male deer (a buck) wearing a backpack, looking puzzled as he waits for a bus. The bus is a bright, simple cartoon style vehicle approaching in the background, and a couple of other animals (like a squirrel and a rabbit) are waiting alongside the buck on the sidewalk. The setting is a suburban street with a sidewalk, a small green patch with a tree, and a clear sky. The sign is the central focus, with bold lettering to highlight the pun. The style is lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor in the play on words involving ''bucks'' as deer and ''bucks'' as money, implying not enough money to stop the bus here.'),
 (276, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'Not one shred of evidence supports the notion that life is serious.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene depicting a happy-go-lucky character walking through life on a sunny day. The character is smiling broadly, wearing casual, colorful clothes and sunglasses, with arms spread wide as if embracing the world. Around them, everyday life items—like a briefcase, a clock, a stack of papers, and a smartphone—are floating gently as if weightless or cartoonishly light, emphasizing the lightheartedness. Nearby, a serious-looking statue of Lady Justice holds scales, but the scales are humorously unbalanced with feathers and confetti instead of weights. In the background, a path winds through various simple signs that read ''Work,'' ''Bills,'' ''Deadlines,'' but these signs are playful and tilted, some with smiley faces drawn on. The overall tone is bright and cheerful, with exaggerated cartoon features and soft colors, highlighting the joke’s message that life should not be taken seriously at all.'),
 (277, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'Nothing in life is to be feared. It is only to be understood.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a curious little child with wide eyes and a thoughtful expression, holding a magnifying glass up to a cute, slightly confused-looking cartoon monster. The monster is harmless-looking with big, friendly eyes and goofy features, standing in a bright, colorful room with bookshelves full of science and nature books. A light bulb floats above the child''s head to symbolize understanding. In the background, a clock shows no urgency, suggesting calm exploration. The overall vibe is playful and encouraging, emphasizing curiosity overcoming fear with humor and warmth.'),
 (278, 'Money Humor, Word Play', 'Nothing in the known universe travels faster than a bad check.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a bad check personified as a tiny character zipping across the universe at incredible speed. Imagine the bad check as a paper check with eyes, arms, and legs, wearing running shoes and a determined expression. The background should be outer space with stars, planets, and comets to emphasize the vastness of the universe. Other cosmic objects, like a spaceship or aliens, can be looking surprised or amazed as the bad check speeds past them in a blur. Include speed lines and motion effects to show the extreme velocity of the bad check, making it clear it''s faster than anything else in space.'),
 (279, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'Nothing is ever accomplished by a reasonable man.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing two characters standing side by side. On the left is a ''reasonable man'' depicted as very calm and proper, wearing a suit and glasses, holding a clipboard with checkmarks and a list titled ''Accomplishments.'' He looks mild and organized but somewhat bored. On the right is an ''unreasonable man,'' wild-eyed, with messy clothes and hair, holding a hammer and a paintbrush, energetically working on building or painting a crazy, odd-looking invention or project that is clearly unconventional and chaotic. Around them are tools, blueprints, and half-finished crazy inventions scattered about. The background shows a workshop or creative studio with a sense of lively chaos versus dull order. The style is bright, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the contrast between the dull, ''reasonable'' guy who gets nothing done and the messy, spirited ''unreasonable'' guy who creates wildly. Neither character is aggressive or violent—just a humorous contrast of personalities and productivity.'),
 (280, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Life', 'Nothing is foolproof, to a sufficiently talented fool.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple home office. In the center, a cheerful but clueless-looking person (the ''fool'') is sitting confidently at a desk cluttered with papers, blueprints, and gadgets clearly labeled ''Foolproof Machine.'' The machine is humorously malfunctioning: smoke or sparks pop out, a warning light flashing, and parts falling off. The fool is oblivious to the chaos, smiling proudly while holding a tool upside down. Behind them, a bulletin board contains a big title saying ''Foolproof Plan'' with various diagrams, all humorously complicated and clearly flawed. The overall style is light and playful, with exaggerated expressions and bright colors to emphasize the joke''s irony about how no plan is truly foolproof for a ''talented fool.'' No violence or negative imagery.'),
 (281, 'Life, Philosophy, Workplace', 'Nothing is really work unless you''d rather be doing something else.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a relaxed person lounging comfortably in a cozy living room on a big armchair, smiling peacefully with a book in one hand and a cup of coffee on a side table. In the background, a clock on the wall shows typical working hours, and an open laptop with documents and graphs sits neglected on a desk, looking boring and tedious. Above the person, a thought bubble shows them happily envisioning doing their favorite hobby (like gardening or playing a guitar). The overall vibe is light and cheerful, emphasizing the contrast between enjoyable leisure and dreaded work, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to capture the humorous mental message of the joke.'),
 (282, 'Humor, Life', 'Nothing is so smiple that it can''t get screwed up.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person confidently holding a simple, basic object—like a plain wooden chair—looking proud and ready to complete a straightforward task. Nearby, another character, looking confused and overwhelmed, is trying to assemble the chair but has screws scattered everywhere, some falling to the floor and others stuck in wrong places. The chair is partially assembled but clearly messed up, with legs crooked or backrest tilted. The background is a typical living room or workshop setting with a toolbox open on a table, and a small sign or thought bubble above the confused character saying, ''How did this get so complicated?'' The overall tone should be lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the irony that even the simplest things can be complicated to mess up.'),
 (283, 'Humor, Life, Workplace', 'Nothing makes a person more productive than the last minute.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a messy desk cluttered with papers, a laptop, coffee cups, and a clock on the wall showing just one minute to a deadline time. The person''s eyes are wide open with a panicked but determined expression, frantically typing on the laptop and scribbling notes. Around the desk, speech bubbles or action lines emphasize rapid movement and urgency. The background is a typical office or home workspace, with a calendar or sticky notes hinting at a looming deadline. The overall tone is light and funny, capturing the idea that extreme productivity kicks in only at the last possible moment.'),
 (284, 'Life, Money Humor, Workplace', 'Nothing puts a man deeper in debt than a small raise in his salary.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a man standing on one side of a giant balance scale. On the scale''s left side, labeled ''Salary Raise,'' there is a small, shiny coin stack. On the scale''s right side, labeled ''Debt,'' there is a towering, comically large pile of bills, credit cards, and IOUs towering up several times higher than the man. The man looks puzzled and slightly worried, scratching his head while staring at the imbalance. Around him, various everyday items like a car, house, and shopping bags with price tags emphasize expenses. The background is simple and bright, with an office clock on the wall to hint that he just got a raise at work. The overall style is lighthearted and exaggerated to highlight how a small salary raise ironically leads to a much bigger debt.'),
 (285, 'Food Humor, Puns', 'Nothing tops a plain pizza.', NULL, 'Draw a cartoon scene centered on a plain cheese pizza sitting proudly on a simple wooden pizza board. The pizza should have no toppings except melted cheese, with a golden-brown crust. Above the pizza, emphasize its ''plainness'' by drawing a little crown or spotlight to humorously suggest it is ''topping'' everything. Around the pizza, include several other typical pizza toppings like pepperoni, mushrooms, olives, and peppers, placed aside or looking jealous and defeated. The background should be a cozy pizzeria with a checkered tablecloth and a few plates with various elaborate pizzas to contrast the plain one. Use bright, cheerful colors and exaggerated, funny expressions on the toppings to create a lighthearted, cartoonish vibe. The overall feel should be playful and pun-filled without any people or violence.'),
 (286, 'Humor, Life', 'Nothing will dispel enthusiasm like a small admission fee.', NULL, 'A cheerful person stands at the entrance of a small event or festival with a big, excited smile, eagerly holding a ticket in hand. Just in front of them is a friendly but slightly awkward attendant at a tiny booth, holding up a hand to indicate a small admission fee, with a price sign reading ''$1 Admission'' clearly visible. Behind the attendee, the excited crowd’s smiles quickly fade to confused or disappointed expressions as they realize they have to pay. The scene should be drawn in bright, colorful, cartoon style with exaggerated facial expressions showing enthusiasm turning into mild dismay. Include balloons or festive decorations in the background to emphasize the initial excitement of the event. The overall vibe is humorous and lighthearted without any negativity.'),
 (287, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'Nothing worth learning is learned quickly except parachuting.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene of a person mid-air, parachuting with a wide-eyed, surprised expression. The person should be wearing a simple parachute harness and helmet. Below, show a small cartoonish speedometer labeled "Learning Speed" stuck near zero, while a large arrow points to the parachuting person labeled "Fast Learning." In the background, include a few cloud puffs against a blue sky. Make the overall style light and whimsical, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke that parachuting is the only thing you learn quickly, while other learning takes more time.'),
 (288, 'Humor, Life', 'Nothing''s impossible for those who don''t have to do it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters standing side by side. One character looks confident and relaxed, leaning against a wall with a satisfied smile, arms crossed. This character has a thought bubble that depicts an impossible task, like juggling flaming swords, or walking on water, illustrated clearly but in an exaggerated, silly way. The other character is scrubbing a giant, dirty pile of dishes or struggling to carry a heavy box, looking exhausted and stressed. Both characters are in a simple domestic setting such as a kitchen or backyard, with everyday objects like a sink, dishes, boxes, and household furniture visible. The overall tone is lighthearted and comedic, with exaggerated expressions to highlight the contrast between ''not doing'' a task versus the difficulty of ''doing'' it.'),
 (289, 'Humor, Politics, Social Commentary', 'Now and then an innocent man is sent to the Legislature.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a slightly confused, nervous man wearing simple everyday clothes standing at the entrance of a large, grand government building labeled ''Legislature.'' The man looks out of place among several slick, scheming-looking politicians inside, who are depicted with exaggerated sly grins and shifty eyes. The setting should look like a classic legislative chamber with rows of desks, microphones, and flags, all drawn in a lighthearted, exaggerated manner to emphasize the surreal idea of an "innocent man" entering this environment. The innocent man’s expression contrasts sharply with the sly, cunning politicians, highlighting his naivety. Use bright, cheerful colors to keep the tone funny and non-threatening, and include speech bubbles with question marks or sweat drops to reflect the man''s confusion or nervousness. The style should clearly be cartoonish and playful, without any hints of violence or negativity.'),
 (290, 'Facts, Food Humor', 'Nutmeg is extremely poisonous if injected intravenously.', NULL, 'Draw a colorful, humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, friendly-looking nutmeg spice jar with a smiling face. The jar has cartoon hands, one holding a giant oversized syringe filled with nutmeg powder instead of liquid. The syringe is aimed away from people, emphasizing no harm. Surrounding the jar are exaggerated warning signs like a cartoon skull-and-crossbones symbol with a big red ''X'' over it, and a speech bubble from the jar saying, ''Don’t inject me!'' The background is a simple kitchen counter with other spice jars looking surprised or shocked. The overall style is playful, bright, and exaggerated, with no real people or medical equipment other than the comical syringe made from spice elements. The tone is lighthearted and silly, focusing on the unusual fact rather than any scary or harmful imagery.'),
 (291, 'Humor, Philosophy', 'OBITUARY: A final summation of our lives that, for most of us, occupies about three inches of space in what will shortly become cage liner for your neighbor''s parakeet.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small birdcage with a lively, colorful parakeet inside perched on a stand. Beneath the cage, the floor is lined with bird cage liner paper. On top of the cage liner, a tiny, crumpled obituary notice is visible, just about three inches long, with obvious but exaggerated text and a small black border like a real obituary. Nearby, a cartoonish, confused or indifferent neighbor stands holding the birdcage door open, glancing at the small obituary with mild surprise. The setting is a casual, cozy living room with simple furniture and a potted plant, making it clear this is a neighbor’s home. The style should be lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions and bright colors to enhance the humor in the idea that a meaningful life summary is reduced to tiny scraps repurposed as bird cage lining.'),
 (292, 'Love Humor, Philosophy', 'Of all forms of caution, caution in love is the most fatal.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a nervous-looking person tiptoeing very cautiously toward a large, heart-shaped object labeled ''Love.'' The heart is surrounded by warning signs like ''Beware,'' ''Handle with care,'' and ''Caution.'' The person is wearing comically oversized caution gear: a helmet, knee pads, and holding an exaggeratedly big magnifying glass to examine the heart. Around them are scattered items that represent typical warnings or obstacles in love, like a broken arrow, a spilled love potion, and a caution tape wrapped loosely around the heart. The background is light and playful with pastel colors, emphasizing a whimsical rather than serious tone. The facial expression of the character should be a mix of anxiety and exaggerated care, highlighting the joke that being overly cautious in love can be dangerous or ''fatal.'''),
 (293, 'Humor, Mental Health Humor', 'Of all the things I''ve lost, I miss my mind the most.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a middle-aged person standing in a messy living room looking slightly puzzled and scratching their head. Around them, various everyday items like keys, glasses, a wallet, and a phone are scattered or misplaced. Above their head is a thought bubble showing a little animated brain wearing a tiny suitcase and walking away as if it’s leaving them. The setting should be light-hearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the comedic loss of the brain rather than anything serious. The style should be simple and playful, like a classic comic strip character.'),
 (294, 'Bad Puns, Computers, Word Play', 'Off the modem, through the phone line, nothing but Net.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a whimsical, old-fashioned telephone line running across the image. On one end, there''s a vintage modem with blinking lights, depicted with a small face looking confused or tired. The telephone line stretches out like a path or tunnel leading to a net (like a fishnet) hanging in the air or caught between two poles. The net should look empty and a bit lonely. Surrounding the net and modem, there could be subtle digital or internet-related icons (like small Wi-Fi symbols or pixel fragments) to emphasize the pun on ''Net.'' The overall style is light, colorful, and humorous, with exaggerated expressions on the modem to convey its frustration or resignation about being ''off the modem'' and ending up with ''nothing but Net.'' There should be no people, just the tech items anthropomorphized for comedic effect.'),
 (295, 'Bad Puns, Jobs, Word Play', '''Officer, are you crying while you are writing me a ticket?'' ''Well, it is moving violation.''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set beside a roadside where a police officer is writing a ticket. The officer is depicted as slightly teary-eyed with subtle tears streaming down the cheeks but still holding a ticket book and pen. The officer wears a typical police uniform with a badge and a peaked cap. In front stands a surprised and slightly confused driver leaning out of the car window, looking at the officer and asking the question. The background shows a simple street scene with a stopped car, maybe a traffic sign indicating a speed limit or stop sign. The overall tone is light-hearted and comical, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the pun about the "moving violation." Thought bubbles or speech lines can be used to show the dialogue, highlighting the joke in the caption. The style should be colorful, cartoony, and non-threatening, suitable for all ages.'),
 (296, 'Humor, Life', 'Oh, no! Not another learning experience!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a frustrated, overwhelmed character sitting at a desk cluttered with books, papers, and a computer, indicating they''re in the middle of studying or working. The character has a stressed expression and is holding their head with one hand while looking at an open book or a laptop screen with a speech bubble above them saying: ''Oh, no! Not another learning experience!'' In the background, there are motivational posters and a coffee mug with steam rising. The overall style is lighthearted, with exaggerated facial expressions and bright colors to emphasize the comic frustration of facing continuous challenges or lessons.'),
 (297, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'Okay, who stopped the payment on my reality check?', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a confused person standing in front of a giant oversized check labeled ''Reality Check'' with a large ''Cancelled'' stamp across it. The person looks bewildered, scratching their head with a question mark bubble above them. Around them, there are floating symbols representing reality: a calendar, a clock, and a small globe. The setting is simple, like an office or a casual indoor space. The comic style is bright and exaggerated with clear, humorous expressions to emphasize the pun on ''reality check'' as both a literal financial check and a metaphor for facing reality.'),
 (298, 'Aging, Cars Humor', 'Old cars don''t die - but they do scatter their body parts everywhere.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing an old, beat-up car on a quiet country road or in a junkyard. The car has a friendly, anthropomorphic face with big eyes on the windshield and a smiling grille. Parts of the car, such as a detached door, a rusty muffler, a tire, and a bumper, are scattered around on the ground nearby. A crow or small bird is perched on one of the removed parts looking curious or amused. The background is simple and bright, with a few trees or a fence, emphasizing a lighthearted mood. The car looks like it’s trying to ''stay alive'' despite its missing parts, adding to the humor without any violence or negativity. Cartoon-style, bright colors, and exaggerated expressions to keep it playful and fun.'),
 (299, 'Aging, Bad Puns, Science', 'Old chemists never die, they just stop reacting.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two elderly male chemists in a colorful chemistry lab filled with beakers, test tubes, and bubbling flasks. One chemist has gray hair and glasses, wearing a white lab coat, looking spry and lively as he holds a flask with bubbling liquid, showing a cheerful smile. The other chemist, also elderly with a gentle smile, is sitting back in a chair with a tired or sleepy expression, but still wearing a lab coat. Above them is a large chemistry reaction equation on a chalkboard that appears to be balanced but fading or disappearing near the older chemist to humorously represent ''stopping reacting.'' The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the wordplay on ''reacting'' in chemistry and aging, with bright colors and simple cartoon-style drawing. The background includes periodic table posters and typical lab equipment to set the chemistry theme clearly.'),
 (300, 'Aging, Humor, Sports Humor', 'Old hockey fans don''t die, they just move to Toronto.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at a hockey rink with a group of elderly hockey fans gathered together. They wear vintage hockey jerseys and hats with classic team logos. Instead of being sad or serious, the fans are smiling and enthusiastically cheering. One of the older fans is shown packing a suitcase labeled ''Toronto Trip'' while another waves a Canadian flag excitedly. In the background, a scoreboard reads ''Old Fans Forever'' and the stands are decorated with banners that say ''Toronto - The Final Move.'' The overall tone is lighthearted, with exaggerated cheerful expressions and a sunny day outside the rink, emphasizing the joke that old hockey fans don''t die, they just move to Toronto, a city known for its passionate hockey culture. The style should be bright, colorful, and cartoonish, with playful, exaggerated features on the characters to emphasize the humor and warmth of the scene.'),
 (301, 'Aging, Humor', 'Old is always fifteen years older than I am.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring an adult person standing next to an elderly person. The elderly person looks cheerful and holds a large birthday cake with the number ''75'' on it. The adult, looking slightly confused or mildly frustrated, is holding a calendar or a birthday card that shows their age as ''60''. Above them is a comical thought bubble where the adult imagines the elderly person grinning and saying, ''Old is always fifteen years older than I am!'' The background is simple, perhaps a party setting with balloons and a ''Happy Birthday'' banner. Both characters should have exaggerated, friendly cartoonish features with bright colors to keep the tone light and funny.'),
 (302, 'Agriculture, Humor, Word Play', 'Old MacDonald had an agricultural real estate tax abatement.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Old MacDonald, a cheerful farmer wearing a classic straw hat, overalls, and boots, standing proudly in front of his large, colorful farm. The farm features a barn, a tractor, and various crops growing in neat rows. Above him is a large official-looking paper or sign labeled ''Agricultural Real Estate Tax Abatement'' with a big red stamp saying ''Approved.'' Old MacDonald is smiling widely, holding the document in one hand and tipping his hat with the other. Around him, animals like cows and chickens look confused or mildly amused. The background includes a sunny sky and a few trees, setting a peaceful farm atmosphere. The style is light-hearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions to enhance the joke''s play on the classic nursery rhyme and the modern tax concept.'),
 (303, 'Bad Puns, Music Humor', 'Old musicians never die, they just decompose.', NULL, 'A playful cartoon scene showing a group of old musicians styled as classic band members (e.g., one with a saxophone, one with a guitar, one with a drumsticks) standing on a grassy patch outside. Instead of looking alive, they are humorously turning into compost or soil right beneath their feet, with bits of leaves, mushrooms, and worms popping out around them. The musicians have slightly exaggerated worried but comedic expressions, with musical notes floating above their heads fading into little brown leaves. The background is bright and cheerful with a sunny sky and some flowers growing from the decomposing ground, reinforcing the pun on decomposition. The overall style is colorful, cartoonish, and lighthearted, emphasizing humor without any scary or sad elements.'),
 (304, 'Philosophy, Word Play', 'Old philosophers don''t die - they just don''t think therefore they aren''t.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in an ancient Greek-style agora with stone columns and scrolls scattered around. In the foreground, an elderly philosopher with a long white beard, toga, and round spectacles is sitting thoughtfully on a stone bench. He has a puzzled, slightly sleepy expression and a small thought bubble above his head with fading question marks. Nearby, a younger philosopher holds a scroll and points at the elder with a gentle smile, as if explaining the punchline. In the background, busts of famous philosophers with bemused faces are mounted on pedestals. The setting is bright and whimsical, with a subtle cloud in the shape of a faded brain floating above the elderly philosopher''s head to visually emphasize ''not thinking.'' The overall style is cartoonish and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions and rounded features to keep the mood light and humorous.'),
 (305, 'Programming, Word Play', 'Old programmers never die; they just branch to a new address.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring an elderly programmer character with white hair, glasses, and a cardigan, sitting at a vintage computer desk. On the screen, branching diagrams or code with arrows lead to a sign that reads ''New Address''. Around the desk, computer-related items like floppy disks, a coffee mug labeled ''Code'', and scattered papers with code snippets are present. In the background, a playful ghostly version of the same programmer floats gently upward, carrying a briefcase labeled ''Programmer''s Branch''. The overall tone is lighthearted, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the pun on branching and memory addresses in programming.'),
 (306, 'Aging, Humor, Jobs', 'Old taxi drivers don''t die, they just get lost. As usual.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring an elderly taxi driver sitting behind the wheel of a classic yellow taxi cab. The driver is an older man with gray hair, glasses slipping down his nose, and a slightly confused but good-natured expression. The taxi is parked at a crossroads with multiple street signs pointing in all directions, each sign humorously labeled with various confusing or contradictory place names (e.g., ''This Way'', ''That Way'', ''Are We There Yet?''). Around the cab, small cartoonish swirls or question marks float to emphasize his confusion. The background shows a cityscape with a few pedestrians looking on with mild amusement. The tone is lighthearted with bright colors, exaggerated features, and clear, simple lines to emphasize the joke about the taxi driver ''not dying but just getting lost again,'' playing on the stereotype of taxi drivers and their sometimes erratic navigation. No violence or inappropriate elements are present, and the overall mood is silly and charming.'),
 (307, 'Aging, Sports Humor, Word Play', 'Old tennis pros don''t die, but they don''t bounce back, either.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a tennis court with a humorous twist. In the center, an elderly tennis player with gray hair in a quintessential tennis outfit (headband, wristbands, polo shirt, shorts, and tennis shoes) leans on a tennis racket for support, looking tired but amused. Instead of the usual bright, bouncy tennis ball near them, there is a deflated, flabby-looking tennis ball lying on the court, partially squished. The tennis net is slightly sagging, echoing the ''no bounce back'' theme. In the background, a scoreboard reads something like ''Old Pros Match.'' The atmosphere is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated features to emphasize the joke about aging athletes and losing their bounce. No other players are in the scene to keep the focus on the old pro and the deflated ball.'),
 (308, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Ole and Sven are on opposite sides of a river. Ole: How do I get to the other side of the river? Sven: You ARE on the other side of the river!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters, Ole and Sven, standing on opposite banks of a calm river. Ole, looking puzzled and scratching his head, is on the left side of the river, holding a walking stick and glancing toward Sven. Sven, on the right side of the river, is smiling and pointing at Ole''s side. Both men are dressed in simple Scandinavian-style clothing with sweaters and caps. The river runs horizontally across the middle of the image, clearly separating the two characters. The background includes a few trees and bushes on each riverbank, with a bright blue sky overhead. A small wooden sign next to Ole reads ''You ARE on the other side!'' in playful lettering to emphasize the joke. The overall tone is lighthearted and friendly, drawn in a colorful, exaggerated cartoon style with expressive faces to highlight the confusion and humor of the situation.'),
 (309, 'Animals, Food Humor, Humor', 'Ole''s bull was not getting the job done with the female cows so he asked the vet for some medicine. A few weeks later: Sven: ''how''s that bull doing?'' Ole: ''he''s back to his old frisky self, getting the job done!'' Sven: ''What fantastic medicine did the vet prescribe him?'' Ole: ''I don''t know, but it tastes like licorice!''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene on a sunny day at a farm. In the foreground, Ole, a friendly-looking farmer wearing denim overalls and a straw hat, is chatting with Sven, another farmer dressed similarly but with a simple flat cap. Between them, a large, muscular bull stands proudly, looking energetic and lively with a happy, confident expression. Nearby, several content female cows graze lazily in a green pasture dotted with flowers. Ole holds a small medicine bottle labeled with a bright red cross, and a few black licorice candies scattered on a small wooden fence post next to the bottle hint at the medicine''s peculiar flavor. In the background, a sturdy red barn and a vet''s truck parked nearby give context to the scene. Both Ole and Sven are smiling and engaged in conversation, emphasizing the comedic punchline without any aggressive or suggestive behavior. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, using exaggerated cartoon expressions to enhance the humor.'),
 (315, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'One big difference between men and women is that if a woman says ''Smell this'', it usually smells nice.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters: a man and a woman standing side by side in a bright, cheerful room. The woman is holding a small, fancy perfume bottle near her wrist, smiling confidently as she gestures toward it with the phrase ''Smell this!'' above her. The man, looking curious but a bit hesitant, leans in with a slightly puzzled or skeptical expression, holding his nose with one hand as if preparing for a surprise. Around them, subtle details hint at gender stereotypes in a playful way, such as the woman’s neatly styled hair and fashionable outfit and the man’s casual, slightly disheveled look, like a t-shirt and jeans. The background is simple with a dresser or table holding a few more perfume bottles and maybe a small flower vase. The cartoon style is light-hearted with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to amplify the humor without being offensive or political.'),
 (310, 'Humor, Word Play', 'On a beautiful day like this, it is hard to believe that anyone can be  unhappy - but we''re working on it.', NULL, 'A cheerful outdoor park scene on a bright, sunny day with clear blue skies and fluffy white clouds. In the foreground, a smiling person in casual, colorful clothing holds a large sign that reads, ''Hard to believe anyone can be unhappy today!'' Nearby, a small group of cartoon-style workers wearing construction hats and overalls are humorously trying to ''work on'' making people unhappy. They might be carrying comically oversized tools like giant paintbrushes painting frowns on flowers or holding a blueprint labeled ''Unhappiness Plan''. Around them, happy people are enjoying the sunny weather: kids playing, birds singing, and flowers blooming. The overall feel is lighthearted and ironic, capturing the joke''s clever twist with exaggerated, playful expressions and a cartoon vibe, avoiding any negativity or harm.'),
 (311, 'Humor, Life, Psychology Humor', 'On average, people fear spiders more than they do death.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a person sitting comfortably on a couch with a terrified expression, staring wide-eyed at a large, friendly-looking cartoon spider perched innocently on the armrest. The spider should have big, exaggerated eyes and a slight smile, appearing harmless and even a bit cute. In the background, a shadowy, cartoon-style grim reaper figure stands quietly behind the person, looking calm and non-threatening, holding a scythe lowered to the ground. The person’s gaze is firmly fixed on the spider rather than the grim reaper. The setting is a simple living room with a picture frame on the wall showing a little calendar page with the phrase ''On average...'' written on it, referencing the joke. Use bright colors and clean lines to emphasize the playful and lighthearted mood of the scene.'),
 (312, 'Good Question!, Humor, Life', 'On the keyboard of life, always keep one finger on the escape key.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a large computer keyboard labeled ''Keyboard of Life.'' The keyboard is oversized and colorful, resembling a computer keyboard but with whimsical keys, including a prominent ''Escape'' key glowing or highlighted. A cartoon character, appearing thoughtful but relaxed, is sitting or standing beside the giant keyboard with one finger gently resting on the glowing Escape key. Surrounding the keyboard are simple symbols representing life''s ups and downs, like small clouds, sunshine, a clock, and a heart, to suggest different life situations. The setting is lighthearted and vibrant, with soft pastel colors and exaggerated proportions to enhance the humor and visual appeal. The character should look casual and approachable, emphasizing the metaphor of having an ''escape option'' in life without any stress or negativity.'),
 (313, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Once, I thought I made a mistake. But I was wrong.', NULL, 'Draw a simple, colorful cartoon scene showing a person standing in front of a large whiteboard or chalkboard. The person looks confused but then suddenly realizes something, with a light bulb glowing above their head. On the board is written the phrase ''I made a mistake'' with a big red X over it, and underneath it the corrected phrase ''But I was wrong.'' The person''s expression changes from worried to amused, shrugging with a smile. The background should be minimal, indoors, with perhaps a desk and a small plant nearby. The overall tone is light and humorous, emphasizing the play on words and the unexpected twist.'),
 (314, 'Math Humor, Word Play', 'One Bazillion = A one with a Bunch of zeroes following.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon featuring a large, exaggerated number ''1'' standing upright in the center of the scene. Behind it stretches a comically long string of zeroes that extends off the page, looping and curling whimsically to emphasize its enormous length. The number ''1'' has animated, expressive eyes and a big smile, giving it a cheerful personality. The background is simple and bright, with a subtle gradient to keep focus on the numbers. Optionally, a small character (like a curious child or a confused mathematician) stands at the start of the zeroes, scratching their head or looking amazed, adding to the joke''s playful tone. No other complex objects are needed, keeping the scene light, clear, and fun. The overall style is cartoonish with bold outlines and vibrant colors, suitable for a family-friendly visual pun about large numbers.'),
 (316, 'Humor, Programming, Workplace', 'One day I''m going to write a user-friendly program that will still respect me in the morning.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a cluttered desk with a computer, looking tired but determined. The computer screen displays code with friendly icons and messages like ''Good Morning!'' and ''Respecting User Preferences''. The person has a hopeful smile, coffee mug nearby with steam rising. Behind them, a calendar on the wall shows early morning hours, hinting they stayed up late. The setting should feel light and playful, with bright colors, simple lines, and exaggerated expressions that emphasize the mix of exhaustion and ambition. Include little details like crumpled paper balls, a clock showing morning time, and motivational posters about programming on the wall to add humor and context.'),
 (317, 'Humor, Word Play', 'One good turn gets all the blankets.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two people in bed at night. One person is happily wrapped up snugly in multiple blankets while the other looks chilly and annoyed, with only a thin sheet barely covering them. The person with all the blankets is smiling slyly, having clearly pulled the blankets over for themselves with a cheeky grin. The bed is drawn simply with a headboard and pillows. In the background, a window shows a starry night sky to emphasize bedtime. Use exaggerated expressions and warm colors for the person hogging blankets, and cool colors or shivers to emphasize the other person''s discomfort. The overall tone is light and silly, capturing the classic blanket-stealing scenario in a friendly, cartoonish style.'),
 (318, 'Good Question!, Humor, Workplace', 'One person''s error is another person''s data.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring two office coworkers at their desks, each looking at a computer screen. One person, appearing slightly frustrated, points at their screen showing a glaring mistake labeled ''ERROR!'' in big red letters. The second coworker, wearing glasses and looking amused, is holding a magnifying glass over what the first person calls an error, but on their screen it’s highlighted and labeled ''DATA!'' as if it''s a valuable find. The setting should be a light-hearted office with cubicles, desks cluttered with papers, coffee mugs, and office plants. The background can have a whiteboard with quirky graphs and charts to set the work vibe. The overall tone is playful and non-threatening, emphasizing the contrast in how the same information can be viewed differently as a mistake or useful data.'),
 (319, 'Computers, Word Play', 'One picture is worth 128K words.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing an old-fashioned computer monitor from the 1980s displaying a pixelated black-and-white photograph. Above the monitor, a speech bubble or a caption says: ''One picture is worth 128K words,'' playing on the phrase ''a picture is worth a thousand words'' but replacing it with computer memory units. The computer should have a bulky CPU tower next to it, with floppy disks stacked nearby. In the background, a confused character (cartoon person) wearing retro glasses scratches their head as they try to process the joke. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions and simple, colorful lines to enhance the humor of mixing old tech with the classic phrase.'),
 (320, 'Humor, Word Play', 'One picture is worth a thousand words. See diagram below.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a simple framed picture hung on a wall labeled ''Diagram.'' The framed picture is minimalist, like a child’s drawing or a stick figure scene, with a few squiggly lines and simple shapes suggesting a basic message. Below the picture, a small caption reads: ''One picture is worth a thousand words.'' In the foreground, a confused cartoon character with exaggerated raised eyebrows and a puzzled look stands holding a speech bubble filled with tiny words and letters overflowing around them, emphasizing the idea of many words. The overall style is light-hearted and whimsical with bright colors, clean lines, and playful expressions, suitable for a family-friendly comic panel.'),
 (321, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'One-seventh of your life is spent on Monday.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene of a cheerful weekly calendar character personified as a smiling paper sheet with arms and legs. Each day of the week is a square section on the calendar''s body. The Monday section is brightly highlighted and exaggerated to take up exactly one-seventh of the calendar’s surface, perhaps glowing or shining. The calendar character is pointing to the Monday section with a proud or exaggerated expression, conveying the joke that Monday consumes one-seventh of your life. In the background, a clock or hourglass can emphasize the passing of time. The overall tone should be lighthearted and fun, with bold outlines and simple colors suitable for a humorous cartoon style. There should be no violent or inappropriate elements, just a friendly, relatable depiction of time and the dread or prominence of Monday in a week’s cycle.'),
 (322, 'Aging, Facts, Humor', 'Only one person in two billion will live to be 116 or older.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a very long line of people waiting outside a giant, whimsical birthday cake-shaped building with a big sign that reads ''116th Birthday Club.'' The line stretches far into the distance, almost disappearing on the horizon. Near the front, a small elderly person with a party hat and a big smile stands proudly holding a gold medal labeled ''116+'' while others behind look surprised or doubtful. Above the scene, a large speech bubble shows the text ''Only one person in two billion will live to be 116 or older.'' The setting is bright and cheerful with balloons and confetti scattered around, emphasizing the rarity and celebration of reaching that age. The style is colorful and exaggerated like a funny cartoon or comic strip, with expressive faces and lighthearted details like a party banner and a clock showing the time as ’116 years.'' No violence, adult themes, or political elements.'),
 (323, 'Good Question!, History Humor', 'Only two people signed the Declaration of Independence on July 4th, John Hancock and Charles Thomson. Most of the rest signed in August 2, but the last signature wasn''t added until 5 years later.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a colonial-era room with a large wooden table covered with an oversized, old parchment labeled ''Declaration of Independence.'' Two characters, John Hancock and Charles Thomson, are seated at the table confidently signing the document with large quill pens, both smiling and looking proud. Surrounding them are empty chairs with name tags labeled with other founders'' names, loosely scattered papers, and a large wall calendar showing July 4th. In the background, a comical timeline poster hangs on the wall showing dates July 4th, August 2nd, and a humorous ''5 years later'' marker with an old man sneakily adding a final signature with a huge quill, wearing a powdered wig and glasses, looking surprised or sheepish. The atmosphere is light and playful, emphasizing the delay in signing with exaggerated expressions and props, drawn in a colorful, cartoonish style with exaggerated features and bright colors.'),
 (324, 'Good Question!, Humor, Philosophy', 'Originality is the art of concealing your sources.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in an artist''s studio or writer''s workspace. In the center, a person (the artist or writer) sits at a cluttered desk, looking slyly at a canvas or a piece of paper. Surrounding them are several paintings, sketches, or notes pinned on the wall, each styled in very different artistic ways but clearly borrowing elements from famous works or common ideas—a Mona Lisa smile, a famous cartoon character, and a classic storybook image. The person holds up a brush or pen with a cheeky grin, as if proud of their ''original'' work. Nearby, a cartoonish detective character with a magnifying glass peers suspiciously at the artwork, trying to identify the sources. The overall tone is lighthearted, with playful facial expressions and exaggerated cartoon features. Include speech bubbles or a sign that says: "Originality is the art of concealing your sources." The background is a bright, creative workspace with paint tubes, sketchpads, and quotes about creativity pinned to the walls. No violence or inappropriate content.'),
 (325, 'Humor, Science', 'Our eyes are always the same size from birth, but our nose and ears never stop growing.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a baby, a young child, and an elderly person standing side by side. Each character has exaggerated features to emphasize the joke: all three have almost identical-sized eyes (large and round for clarity), but progressively larger noses and ears as they age. The baby has small nose and ears, the child has medium-sized nose and ears, and the elderly person has very large, long ears and a big nose. They all look cheerful and slightly surprised, with the elderly person possibly holding a mirror or magnifying glass to emphasize the growth. The background is simple and bright, like a light pastel color, with minimal props, focusing on the characters'' facial features. The style is playful and cartoonish, with bold outlines and expressive faces to highlight the joke humorously and clearly.'),
 (326, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Office Humor', 'Paper clips are the larvae of coat hangers.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a small group of shiny silver paper clips on one side, looking like tiny creatures with cheerful faces. On the other side, depict larger coat hangers with friendly faces, wings or antennae, giving the impression they just hatched or evolved from the paper clips. The background can be a simple closet or office desk setting with a few scattered papers and a clothing rack. Add playful motion lines or sparkles around the paper clips transitioning into coat hangers to emphasize the joke that paper clips are ''larvae'' of coat hangers. Keep the style light, colorful, and exaggerated to enhance the whimsy and humor of the scene.'),
 (327, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'Paul''s Law: You can''t fall off the floor.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a character named Paul standing confidently on the floor with a big smile. Paul is inside a simple room with a couch, a small table, and a few framed pictures on the wall to set a cozy home environment. Above Paul’s head is a whimsical thought bubble containing the phrase “Paul’s Law: You can’t fall off the floor.” Around him, a few playful elements emphasize the joke: a pair of shoes lying neatly by the door, a small rug, and perhaps a pet cat lounging calmly on the floor. The style is light-hearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions, especially on Paul’s face, to capture the dry humor of stating something obvious as a ''law.'' No other characters are needed, but the overall tone should feel like a funny, simple everyday observation turned into a mock scientific rule.'),
 (328, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Pedestrian: A person who walks when you are walking.', NULL, 'A colorful humorous cartoon scene showing two characters walking side by side on a sidewalk in a city setting. One character looks slightly annoyed and is walking with an exaggerated slouch and arms swinging, dressed in casual clothes. The other character is walking right beside them, cheerfully matching their pace, smiling and unaware of the annoyance. The sidewalk is clearly visible with a few street signs, a tree, and a bench in the background. A small caption above them reads: ''Pedestrian: A person who walks when you are walking.'' The style is lighthearted and playful, with simple bright colors and rounded shapes to emphasize the humor without any harsh lines or details.'),
 (329, 'Humor, Jobs', 'People are usually shocked when they find out I''m not a very good electrician', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a man standing next to a lamp post that is bent and sparking, with several live wires loosely hanging around him. The man looks sheepish and embarrassed, scratching his head, wearing a tool belt filled with electrical tools like pliers and screwdrivers. In the background, a small crowd of neighbors or bystanders are looking surprised or shocked, with exaggerated wide eyes and open mouths. The setting is a suburban street with houses, trees, and a clear sky to keep it light and friendly. The overall tone should be playful and non-threatening, emphasizing the man''s ineptitude in a funny way.'),
 (330, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy', 'People can be divided into three groups: those who make things happen, those who watch things happen and those who wonder what happened.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene divided into three distinct panels arranged horizontally. The first panel shows an active, energetic character confidently assembling a large, whimsical machine with tools in hand, surrounded by gears and bolts flying. The second panel illustrates a relaxed character casually sitting on a bench or chair, watching the first character work with a curious but passive expression, perhaps holding popcorn or a drink. The third panel features a confused character scratching their head with a thought bubble showing a swirling question mark, looking bewildered while the machine in the first panel is suddenly erupting in chaotic steam and sparks. The style is light, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the personalities and contrasting attitudes, with clear labels above each panel: ''Make Things Happen,'' ''Watch Things Happen,'' and ''Wonder What Happened.'' No background distractions, just simple props like tools, a bench, popcorn, and the eccentric machine to keep focus on the characters and their actions.'),
 (331, 'Science, Word Play', 'People get sucked into black hole schemes all the time, I bet.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cosmic setting with a large, exaggerated black hole in the center. Around the black hole, various confused and comically worried people are being gently pulled toward it as if caught in an invisible vacuum. The people are cartoonish and diverse, wearing everyday clothes and looking surprised or puzzled. Some hold wallets, phones, or shopping bags labeled with words like ''Investments'' or ''Schemes.'' The black hole itself has a swirling, spiraling pattern with a sly face, smirking mischievously to emphasize the ''scheme'' aspect. A small sign nearby reads ''Black Hole Schemes - Enter at Your Own Risk!'' The background shows stars and distant planets to set the space environment. The overall tone is light-hearted and funny, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to enhance the comedic effect.'),
 (332, 'Humor, Word Play', 'People say I''m condescending. (That means I talk down to people)', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing on a small step ladder or a box, looking down at a group of people below with a smug or confident expression. The person is speaking, with a speech bubble that says, ''People say I''m condescending. (That means I talk down to people)''. The group below looks up with mixed expressions of confusion and mild annoyance. The setting is simple, like a minimalistic indoor room or a park. The style should be light-hearted and exaggerated with vibrant colors and expressive faces to highlight the joke’s sarcastic tone.'),
 (333, 'Humor, Marriage Humor, Social Commentary', 'People seldom think alike, until it comes to buying wedding presents.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene at a wedding gift table filled with many identical, identical-looking presents wrapped in the same paper, such as dozens of toasters, blenders, or identical coffee makers all stacked neatly. A diverse group of guests, each with a quirky expression showing surprise or amusement, is gathered around the table, some holding matching gifts in their hands as they look at each other bewildered. The background shows a festive wedding reception with balloons and streamers. The scene should emphasize uniformity in the gifts contrasting with the individuality of the guests, using bright and cheerful colors to keep it lighthearted and funny.'),
 (334, 'Humor, Pessimistic', 'People think I go out of my way to piss them off. Trust me, it''s not out of my way at all.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon of a grumpy person walking along a sidewalk with a mischievous smirk on their face. The person should be casually strolling but clearly taking a deliberate detour around an annoyed group of people standing nearby with crossed arms and angry expressions. The background is a simple urban scene with houses or shops in soft pastel colors to keep it lighthearted. Include visual cues that the person effortlessly and happily avoids going straight on their path, taking an exaggeratedly longer route to pass right in front of the irritated people. The style is playful and exaggerated with bold lines and expressive faces to emphasize the humor in intentionally annoying others without extra effort.'),
 (335, 'Humor, Insults, Word Play', 'People who think they know it all really annoy those of us who do.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters in a casual setting, perhaps a coffee shop or a park bench. One character appears smug, with a slight smirk, arms crossed confidently, dressed in neat, slightly pretentious clothing, suggesting they believe they know everything. The other character, standing nearby or sitting opposite, looks even more confident and slightly amused, with a knowing smile and one eyebrow raised, as if silently mocking the first. Include a speech bubble above the second character that reads, "People who think they know it all really annoy those of us who do." The background should be simple and cheerful, with light colors and unobtrusive details like a potted plant or a bookshelf to keep the focus on the two characters. The style should be a clean, light-hearted cartoon, emphasizing facial expressions and body language to convey the joke’s ironic tone without any aggressive or negative imagery.'),
 (336, 'Humor, Shopping Jokes', 'People will buy anything that''s one to a customer.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a quirky market stall labeled ''One-to-a-Customer Shop.'' The shopkeeper is standing behind a counter with a friendly grin, holding up a silly assortment of odd items each clearly marked with a small sign saying ''One Per Customer.'' Items on display include a single banana, a lone sock, a single shoe, a solitary carrot, and a single rubber duck. In front of the counter, a diverse line of eager, quirky customers is waiting, some holding baskets or shopping bags. Each customer is selecting exactly one item, looking amused or excited. The background should be colorful and playful, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke about how people buy anything if limited to one each. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with bold outlines and bright colors, emphasizing the whimsical nature of the joke without any threatening or sensitive content.'),
 (337, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'People with narrow minds usually have broad tongues.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person with an exaggeratedly narrow head and a very wide, large tongue sticking out. The person''s head should be drawn slim and elongated vertically to emphasize the ''narrow mind,'' while their tongue extends wide and thick horizontally, almost comically oversized compared to the rest of the face. The character should have a surprised or slightly confused expression, with raised eyebrows and big eyes. Surround the character with a simple, light-hearted background like a plain color or a soft gradient to keep focus on the face. No other people or objects are necessary, but the overall tone should be playful and silly to match the joke''s pun on narrow minds and broad tongues.'),
 (338, 'Food Humor, Humor, Word Play', 'PEPPIER (pehp ee ay'') n. The waiter at a fancy restaurant whose sole purpose seems to be walking around asking diners if they want ground pepper.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a fancy, upscale restaurant with elegant tables covered in white tablecloths, crystal glasses, and fancy plates. At the center of the scene, a waiter with an exaggeratedly enthusiastic smile is standing next to a table. He is dressed in a classic waiter uniform with a bow tie and apron, holding a pepper grinder high up in one hand, as if about to offer pepper to several diners. The diners look slightly overwhelmed or amused by his persistent attention. Surrounding the table are other diners who glance over, some holding forks midair, others silently giving puzzled looks. The background features classy chandeliers and framed paintings, emphasizing the fancy atmosphere. The overall style is colorful, cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions and lighthearted vibes, capturing the joke about the “peppier” waiter who seems to exist only to ask diners if they want pepper, making the waiter both the subject and the punchline of the image.'),
 (339, 'Humor, Word Play', 'PETROPHOBIC (pet ro fob'' ik) adj. One who is embarrassed to undress in front of a household pet.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a shy person standing partially undressed in a cozy living room. The person is blushing and nervously clutching a robe or towel tightly around themselves as they look down modestly. Nearby, a household pet—a curious dog or cat—is staring directly at the person with an innocent but attentive expression. The room includes typical home elements like a couch, a small table with a lamp, and a framed picture on the wall. The pet’s eyes are wide and focused, adding to the humor of the situation. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, emphasizing exaggerated facial expressions for both the person (embarrassed) and the pet (curious). The setting conveys the awkward yet funny moment someone feels embarrassed undressing around their pet, captured with playful colors and simple, clear lines.'),
 (340, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'PHONESIA (fo nee'' zhuh) n. The affliction of dialing a phone number and forgetting whom you were calling just as they answer.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in a bright, cozy living room holding a smartphone up to their ear. Their face expresses a mix of surprise and confusion, with wide eyes and a small open mouth. Above their head is a classic ''thought bubble'' with a question mark and tiny swirly lines indicating forgetfulness. In the background, a phone screen shows the call is connected (green bar or ringing icon). Nearby is a table with a forgotten notepad and pen, symbolizing their lapse in memory. The overall style is lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated features to emphasize the humorous moment of dialing without remembering the recipient.'),
 (341, 'Bad Puns, Photography Humor', 'Photographic Department Door Sign: DARK ROOM: IF YOU OPEN THE DOOR ALL THE DARK WILL LEAK OUT', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a photography studio hallway. On the wall, there is a large door with a big, bold sign above it reading: ''DARK ROOM: IF YOU OPEN THE DOOR ALL THE DARK WILL LEAK OUT.'' The door is slightly ajar, and from the opening, cartoon-style black darkness (like a smoky, shadowy cloud) is whimsically floating out and spreading into the bright hallway. Nearby, a surprised photographer wearing a lab coat and holding a developing photo is backing away with wide eyes and raised hands as if trying to stop the darkness from escaping. The hallway itself is well lit and cheerful, with framed photos hanging on the walls showcasing classic black and white pictures. The style should be colorful, lighthearted, and playful, capturing the pun of the phrase visually in a fun and innocent way, perfect for all ages.'),
 (342, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'Picture this: one-way elevators.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon depicting a tall, narrow elevator shaft with two separate glass elevators stacked vertically but facing opposite directions. One elevator is going only up, with a happy person inside pressing the ''Up'' button, and the other elevator below is going only down, with another cheerful person inside pressing the ''Down'' button. The building is shown from the side to emphasize the movement directions. A humorous sign next to the elevator buttons reads ''One-Way Elevators: Choose Your Fate!'' The style is playful and lighthearted, with exaggerated expressions of mild confusion and amusement on the passengers'' faces. The background is simple, perhaps inside an office building lobby with a floor number display next to each elevator shaft. Overall, the cartoon highlights the absurdity of having elevators that work only in a single direction in a whimsical manner.'),
 (343, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Plan to be spontaneous tomorrow.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a person standing with a puzzled but excited expression, holding a handwritten calendar marked ''Tomorrow'' in big letters. Behind them is a thought bubble with a zigzag arrow and a checklist titled ''Spontaneity Plan'' with checkmarks next to ''Wake up on time'', ''Decide what to do'', and ''Be spontaneous!'' The setting is a simple living room with a clock and a window showing daylight. The style is light-hearted and whimsical, emphasizing the irony of planning spontaneity with exaggerated expressions and fun details like scattered notes labeled ''Ideas?''.'),
 (344, 'Humor, Workplace', 'Please solve your problems in advance so I can help you quicker.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in an office or help desk setting. A friendly-looking person, drawn in a lighthearted, exaggerated cartoon style, sits behind a desk with a computer and a phone. They wear a name tag and have a slightly amused expression. In front of them stands a frustrated or confused person holding a long scroll or list labeled ''Problems.'' The key visual joke: the person behind the desk is holding a calendar or planner opened to a page marked ''Solve problems in advance,'' with a big smile, as if implying the caller should have already solved their issues before asking for help. Around them are humorous details like a clock showing busy hours, sticky notes with reminders, and colorful problem-themed icons (light bulbs, question marks) floating above. The overall tone is light, whimsical, and clearly shows impatience mixed with good humor, emphasizing the absurdity of expecting problems to be solved before they even arise, in a clever cartoon style.'),
 (345, 'Animals, Humor, Theme Park Jokes', 'Please wait until your Dumbo has come to a complete stop before disembarking.  Overheard at Disneyland', NULL, 'Draw a colorful, whimsical cartoon scene set in Disneyland. In the foreground, show a family waiting to disembark from a Dumbo ride vehicle, which is an elephant-shaped ride car. The Dumbo should be mid-air but clearly stationary, with its ears spread wide and a big friendly smile. The family members are smiling and holding onto the ride bar, looking ready but patiently waiting. In the background, include other Dumbo ride vehicles hovering gently in the sky above the circus-themed ride, bright and cheerful with vibrant reds, blues, and yellows. The setting has classic Disney amusement park elements like decorative banners, spotted tents, and happy guests walking around. Include a whimsical sign near the ride that reads, "Please wait until your Dumbo has come to a complete stop before disembarking," styled like an official ride instruction but with a slightly funny tone. The overall art style should be playful and cartoonish, emphasizing the lightheartedness of the scene without any overcrowding or complicated details, suitable for a family-friendly amusement park atmosphere.'),
 (346, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Poise: The act of raising the eyebrows instead of the roof.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a stylish person standing confidently with perfectly arched eyebrows raised high. Instead of raising the roof of a house behind them, the roof appears perfectly flat and unchanged, contrasting with their exaggerated eyebrow lift. The person''s facial expression is elegant and composed, highlighting the concept of ''poise.'' Around them, subtle comic elements like a confused neighbor looking up at the unchanged roof add humor. The background should be simple, with a cartoon-style house and clear sky, emphasizing the contrast between the raised eyebrows and the unlifted roof.'),
 (347, 'Police Humor, Word Play', 'Police are looking for criminals who stole the wheels of their cop car. They are working tirelessly to catch them.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene outside a police station at night. A police car is parked with no wheels, resting awkwardly on stacks of colorful donuts or cinder blocks to emphasize the missing tires. Two cartoon police officers stand beside the car: one is scratching his head looking puzzled, while the other is energetically writing notes on a clipboard. Nearby, a sign labeled ''Police Station'' is visible. In the background, a full moon shines, and a small silhouette of fleeing thieves can be seen rolling away on stolen wheels, laughing mischievously. The style should be light-hearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions on the officers to highlight the joke about them ''working tirelessly.'' Keep the colors bright and the lines clean to give it a fun, cartoonish vibe without any violent or suggestive elements.'),
 (348, 'Humor, Social Commentary, Word Play', 'Polite conversation is rarely either.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at a fancy tea party with several well-dressed characters sitting around a table, all speaking to each other with overly formal and polite expressions but with obvious signs of awkwardness or tension. Some characters have raised eyebrows, forced smiles, or slightly uncomfortable body language. Speech bubbles show polite but awkward phrases like ''Oh, such a delightful weather, isn’t it?'' and ''Your hat is... quite unique!'' The background is an elegant parlor with fancy wallpaper, a chandelier, and delicate china cups on the table. The overall mood is comically stiff, suggesting that while everyone is being polite, the conversation is clearly not lively or genuinely friendly. The style is light and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the irony.'),
 (349, 'Humor, Motivational, Philosophy', 'POSITIVE THINKING: Self-improvement through self-deception.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person looking at themselves in a bedroom mirror. The person is smiling confidently and wearing casual clothes. Behind the person is a wall with motivational posters, one prominently reads ''Positive Thinking!'' with bright, cheerful colors. On a nearby table are self-help books stacked messily with titles like ''Self-Improvement'' and ''Mindset Magic.'' Nearby, a little floating cartoon cloud above the person’s head shows a thought bubble with the words ''Self-deception'' crossed out and replaced by ''Self-improvement'' in bold letters. The overall mood is light and playful, emphasizing the irony of the phrase, with exaggerated cheerful colors and a playful font for all text elements. No other people or animals are included in the scene.'),
 (350, 'Bad Puns, Jobs, Word Play', 'Postmen never die, they just lose their zip.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful postman standing in the middle, looking a bit confused or surprised. His uniform looks slightly disheveled, with his postal jacket partially unzipped and the zipper visibly missing or broken. Around him are flying envelopes and letters, some mid-air as if they''ve just slipped out of his bag. The background is an urban street with mailboxes and houses. Above or beside him, a whimsical wavy line or ghostly outline suggests he is fading or ''losing his zip,'' playing on the idea of losing energy or life. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions and bright colors to emphasize the pun without any harsh or negative elements.'),
 (351, 'Cars Humor, Food Humor, Word Play', 'Pound for pound, hamburgers cost more than new cars.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small, juicy hamburger with a price tag hanging from it that reads a very high dollar amount, placed on a scale. On the opposite side of the scale is a shiny, compact new car with a much smaller price tag. The scale is tilted dramatically toward the hamburger side to exaggerate the idea that the hamburger ''weighs'' more monetarily. The background is simple, with a grocery store aisle visible behind the hamburger and a car dealership lot behind the car. The style is colorful and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions: the hamburger might have a smug or proud face, while the car looks surprised or confused. No people are necessary, and the focus is on the scale, the price tags, and the two objects—highlighting the joke about cost comparison in a playful way.'),
 (352, 'Humor, Workplace', 'Preudhomme''s Law of Window Cleaning: It''s on the other side.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person cleaning a large window from the inside of a house. The person is holding a squeegee and has a puzzled, slightly frustrated expression. Outside the window, another person is standing on the opposite side of the glass, also holding a squeegee, equally puzzled. The window spans the center of the image, showing clear reflections, emphasizing that both are trying to clean the same window but each from their respective side. The background inside the house shows a simple cozy room with a potted plant and a small table, while outside there is a bright sunny day with a tree and some clouds. The style is light-hearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the confusion and humor of the situation where the dirt or streaks are always ''on the other side.'' Avoid any violent or political imagery, keeping it friendly and family-appropriate.'),
 (353, 'Humor, Pop Culture', 'Princess Leia is technically a Disney princess now', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Princess Leia standing in the center dressed in her iconic white robes and signature cinnamon bun hairstyle. She''s holding a small Disney castle model in one hand, with a playful, slightly surprised expression on her face. Around her are subtle references to both Star Wars and Disney: a faint magical sparkle effect around the castle, a background blend of a galaxy with stars and a Disney theme park castle silhouette. A few other classic Disney princesses like Cinderella or Snow White peek from behind the castle, looking amused or surprised to see Leia with them. The overall style is colorful, lighthearted, and whimsical, emphasizing the playful merger of the two worlds without any tension or conflict. No violent or political imagery, focusing purely on imagination and fun crossover vibes.'),
 (354, 'Food Humor, Humor, Life', 'Probably nothing in the world arouses more false hopes than the first four hours of a diet.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a kitchen table looking hopeful and determined, with a calendar on the wall showing ''Day 1'' and a clock indicating four hours have passed. The table is mostly empty except for a small, sad salad bowl and a glass of water. Around the person’s head are thought bubbles depicting delicious and indulgent foods like pizza, cake, and burgers, symbolizing temptation. The person has a hopeful expression turning into slight disappointment or struggle as time passes. The kitchen should look bright and inviting, contrasting with the person''s wavering optimism about the diet. Style is colorful, light-hearted, and exaggerated to emphasize the mood shift from enthusiasm to doubt, with no violent or inappropriate elements.'),
 (355, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Procrastinate NOW', NULL, 'A single-panel humorous cartoon featuring a laid-back character sitting comfortably in an armchair with a calendar and clock prominently displayed nearby. The calendar page shows a big, bold date circled with the words "Deadline" or "Due Date" visible, but the character is clearly relaxed, with feet up on a coffee table and a casual smile. The clock’s hands point to a time suggesting the deadline is near, but the character holds a coffee mug with the phrase "Procrastinate NOW" on it. Around the room, subtle humorous details, like a cluttered desk with papers stacked haphazardly and a sticky note saying "Start tomorrow," emphasize the irony of urging to procrastinate immediately. The style is bright and colorful, with exaggerated expressions to enhance the comic effect, ensuring it feels lighthearted and fun without any negative or violent elements.'),
 (356, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'PROCRASTINATION: The art of kee... (I think I''ll finish this thought tomorrow...)', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting at a cluttered desk littered with papers, a coffee cup, and a clock showing late afternoon. The person looks distracted and relaxed, leaning back in their chair with a half-smile, gazing off into the distance. Above their head is a speech bubble that starts with the phrase ''PROCRASTINATION: The art of kee...'' but trails off with a smaller bubble saying ''(I think I''ll finish this thought tomorrow...)''. The room has casual elements like a calendar on the wall showing an overdue date, and a small growing plant on the windowsill symbolizing time passing. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish, emphasizing a whimsical and relatable atmosphere about putting off tasks.'),
 (357, 'Humor, Programming, Word Play', 'Profanity is the one language all programmers know best.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a stressed programmer sitting at a cluttered desk covered with multiple computer monitors, keyboards, and empty coffee cups. The programmer looks frustrated, with a furrowed brow and hands raised in exasperation. Around the programmer''s head are little comic-style speech bubbles filled with typical symbols representing swear words (like @#!%&*). The computer screens display lines of messy, error-filled code. Behind the programmer, a whiteboard features diagrams and notes mixed with colorful profanity symbols. The setting is a typical office or home workspace with tech gadgets and sticky notes scattered about. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the universal frustration and humorous language all programmers share when debugging or coding.'),
 (358, 'Cartoon, Humor, Word Play', 'PROFANITYPE: n. The special symbols used by cartoonists to replace swear words (points, asterisks, stars, and so on). It is yet to be determined which specific character represents which specific expletive.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a comic artist at a drawing table cluttered with pencils, sketch pads, and cartoon strips. The artist is mid-draw, looking thoughtfully at the panel where a character''s speech bubble is filled with a jumble of special symbols such as @, #, %, and *. The comic strip on the table clearly shows these symbols used to censor swear words, with small doodles or notes pointing to each symbol like a legend, humorously trying to guess which symbol stands for which curse. In the background, there is a whiteboard or poster titled ''PROFANITYPE'' with a playful definition written underneath. The setting is lighthearted and creative, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions on the artist to emphasize the fun confusion about the use of these symbols. No violence or offense is depicted; it’s purely about cartoon censorship symbols.'),
 (359, 'Humor, Pranks, Science', 'Professor Eppendorf''s Laboratory Novelties and Practical Jokes: REMOTE-CONTROLLED GEIGER COUNTER: Looks and acts like a real geiger counter but you can make the needle jump at the press of a button. Hide the remote control in your pocket and make the needle move when people check themselves for radiation. They''ll go into hysterics thinking thay have received a lethal dose! Yuks galore!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a quirky science laboratory labeled ''Professor Eppendorf''s Laboratory''. On a cluttered wooden table, there is a classic-looking Geiger counter with a needle gauge prominently displayed. The Geiger counter looks old-fashioned but functional. Nearby, a mischievous scientist with wild hair, glasses, and a lab coat holds a small remote control with a big grin on his face. The remote is clearly pointed toward the Geiger counter. In front of the table, a worried-looking person is holding the Geiger counter to their chest, eyes wide with panic as the needle jumps wildly. Around them, scientific glassware, beakers, test tubes filled with colorful liquids, and scattered papers add to the lab atmosphere. Emphasize exaggerated cartoonish expressions: the scientist is gleefully sneaky, and the person testing themselves is comically alarmed, amplifying the joke’s playful prank vibe. The overall color scheme should be bright and lively to enhance the whimsical mood, and a little sign in the background reads ''Novelties and Practical Jokes''.'),
 (360, 'Engineering, Programming, Science', 'Programming is part engineering, part science, part art, a little luck and usually not that difficult.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a programmer sitting at a cluttered desk with a computer surrounded by various symbols representing different fields. On one side, there is a blueprint and a wrench depicting engineering; on another side, a microscope and a chemistry flask to represent science; nearby, a painter''s palette and brush symbolize art. Above the programmer’s head is a small glowing four-leaf clover representing ''a little luck.'' The programmer looks calm and confident with a slight smile, typing away while a half-empty coffee cup sits nearby. The background includes a lightbulb overhead, suggesting ideas, and a few code snippets floating around. The style should be light-hearted and colorful with exaggerated cartoon features for each element, emphasizing the blend of disciplines, but also the casual ease implied by the ''usually not that difficult'' line.'),
 (361, 'Humor, Language, Word Play', 'Pronoun: a noun that turned professional.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring a talking dictionary or grammar book character with eyes and a big smile. Next to it, show a confident-looking pronoun character dressed in a business suit, standing tall with a briefcase or a name badge that says ''Professional''. Include small speech bubbles with simple examples like ''he'', ''she'', ''they'' floating around to emphasize that it is a pronoun. The background could be a simple office environment with desks, computers, and paperwork to reinforce the ''professional'' theme. The style should be playful and light-hearted, with exaggerated friendly facial expressions and bright colors to make the scene amusing and approachable.'),
 (362, 'Good Question!, Humor, Workplace', 'Proof: you''re always losing paper clips, and there are always more coat hangers than expected in the closet.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a cluttered office closet. On the left side, a tired office worker is searching frantically through a pile of scattered paper clips on the floor and inside a small open box labeled ''Paper Clips'', looking puzzled and slightly frustrated. To the right, the closet rack is overloaded with many clothes hangers, some tangled and spilling over, far more than what would be expected for the number of coats present. The worker wears office attire, and above them, a small caption or thought bubble reads: ''Proof: Always losing paper clips and too many coat hangers.'' The overall vibe is lighthearted and exaggerated to emphasize the chaotic abundance of coat hangers and the mysterious disappearance of paper clips, with bright colors and simple cartoon lines to enhance the humor.'),
 (363, 'Humor, Motivational, Workplace', 'Pros are people who do jobs well even when they don''t feel like it', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters in a simple office setting. One character, looking tired and unenthusiastic with messy hair and slouched posture, is sitting at a desk cluttered with papers and a computer. A second character, bright-eyed and energetic, stands beside them with a thumbs-up and a friendly smile. A caption bubble above the standing character reads, ''Pros are people who do jobs well even when they don''t feel like it.'' The background includes an office clock showing late hours and a coffee cup with steam rising, emphasizing fatigue. The style is light-hearted with exaggerated expressions to convey both exhaustion and determination in a playful manner.'),
 (364, 'Humor, Mental Health Humor', 'Psychiatrists say that 1 of 4 people are mentally ill.  Check 3 friends.  If they''re OK, you''re it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene with four friends sitting together on a park bench. Three of the friends look visibly calm and relaxed, smiling and chatting. The fourth friend looks wide-eyed, confused, and slightly worried, realizing they might be the ''mentally ill'' one. Above them, a thought bubble from the worried friend says, ''If these three are okay... then I’m it!'' In the background, a small sign reads ''Psychiatrist says 1 in 4 people are mentally ill.'' The style is lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the joke. No violent or sensitive content.'),
 (365, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Science', 'Psychoceramics: the study of crackpots.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a quirky, eccentric-looking professor standing next to a large, ancient pottery vase with a big visible crack down the middle. The professor wears round glasses, a tweed jacket with elbow patches, a bow tie, and holds a magnifying glass examining the crack closely. Around him are shelves filled with various pots and vases, some intact and some obviously cracked, labeled with funny names like ''Crazy Vase'' and ''Wobbly Jug''. A small chalkboard nearby reads ''Psychoceramics: The Study of Crackpots'' in playful handwriting. The room looks like a lighthearted mix of a pottery studio and a wacky science lab. The overall style is colorful and exaggerated, typical of a cartoon, emphasizing the pun by visually combining ''psychology/psychoceramics'' and cracked pottery (''crackpots''). No people other than the professor, no violence or political elements included.'),
 (366, 'Humor, Language', 'PSYCHOPHOBIA: n. The compulsion, when using a host''s bathroom, to peer behind the shower curtain and make sure no one is waiting for you.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a small, slightly cramped bathroom of a guesthouse. The central character is a wide-eyed, nervous-looking person standing in front of a closed bathroom door, slightly ajar, holding a roll of toilet paper. They are peeking cautiously behind a colorful shower curtain with exaggerated eyes looking around, as if expecting someone to jump out. The shower curtain should have playful patterns like ducks or bubbles. The bathroom has typical elements: a sink with a mirror, a towel rack, a toilet, and a small window showing a hint of bright sunlight outside to indicate daytime. The character’s body language shows wariness mixed with awkwardness, one hand clutching toilet paper, the other pulling the curtain back slightly with fingers. A small speech bubble or thought bubble might contain the word "Psychophobia?" or a question mark to highlight the joke. The overall style is light-hearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor and anxiety of the moment, avoiding any scary or aggressive elements.'),
 (367, 'Animals, Humor', 'PUPKUS (pup kus'') n. The moist residue left on a window after a dog presses it''s nose to it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a cheerful dog pressing its nose firmly against a glass window from the outside. The window shows a clear, exaggerated wet nose print shaped like a heart or paw on the glass. Inside, a person looks amused or puzzled, pointing at the funny nose mark. The setting is a bright, sunny day with simple background details like a house exterior and a few flowers near the window. The style is colorful and playful, capturing the silly and endearing moment of a dog leaving a moist smudge on the glass.'),
 (368, 'History Humor, Humor, Philosophy', 'Puritanism: The haunting fear that someone, somewhere may be happy.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a gloomy, stern-looking Puritan man in traditional 17th-century attire, including a tall black hat with a buckle, a white collar, and dark clothing. He is peeking anxiously and suspiciously from behind a large wooden door or corner of a building. Through a window or slightly open door nearby, show a small cheerful scene with bright colors, such as a few happy people dancing, laughing, or enjoying a sunny picnic with balloons or musical instruments. The contrast between the Puritan''s dark, fearful expression and the joyful scene visible through the window highlights his ''haunting fear'' that someone may be happy. Add exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize humor, with the Puritan appearing almost haunted or shocked. Background should be simple, with a hint of a colonial village, wooden houses, or a church to set the historical mood without overcrowding the image.'),
 (369, 'Humor, Life, Workplace', 'Quality: If you don''t have time to do it right, when will you have time to do it over?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a stressed-out character sitting at a cluttered desk surrounded by stacks of papers, tools, and a ticking clock prominently displayed on the wall. The character looks frazzled, with wild hair and sweat drops, holding a checklist with a big red question mark. A thought bubble above the character''s head shows two images: one of the character carefully and slowly completing a task with a happy, content expression, and another of the character rushed, making mistakes, then having to redo the work in frustration. The room should have a humorous, exaggerated style with bright colors to emphasize the contrast between doing it right the first time and having to redo it. Include a calendar on the wall showing tight deadlines and a coffee cup to add to the busy work atmosphere. Make sure the tone is light, playful, and clearly expresses the dilemma of rushed work versus quality work and redoing tasks.'),
 (370, 'Humor, Science, Word Play', 'Quantum Particles: the dreams that stuff is made of.', NULL, 'A colorful, whimsical cartoon scene featuring a cozy bedroom with a child tucked into bed, their head resting on a pillow shaped like an atom. Above the bed floats a translucent thought bubble filled with tiny, smiling quantum particles depicted as cute, glowing orbs with eyes and tiny limbs, performing various dream-like activities such as bouncing around, forming patterns, and creating sparkles. The room contains scientific elements like a poster of an atom on the wall, a telescope by the window, and a bookshelf labeled ''Physics for Kids.'' Soft pastel colors dominate the scene, giving it a dreamy, imaginative atmosphere. The style is playful and lighthearted, emphasizing the joke''s pun that quantum particles are the ''dreams'' that make up matter, blending science with fantasy humor.'),
 (371, 'Humor, Language, Philosophy Humor', 'Qvid me anxivs svm? -- Alfredo E. Neumanus.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon-style scene featuring a Roman senator or scholar dressed in a traditional toga, standing in a grand ancient Roman forum with classical columns and a large stone scroll in his hand. The character looks puzzled and slightly anxious, scratching his head as he studies the scroll that bears the phrase ''Qvid me anxivs svm?'' in stylized Latin letters. In the background, a small group of toga-clad citizens whisper and point at him with amused expressions. The overall tone is light and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions emphasizing confusion and mild worry. The setting includes Roman architecture, stone benches, and some scrolls scattered around to reinforce the ancient theme. Bright colors and clear lines give it a comical, cartoon feel without any harsh or serious elements, capturing the humor of an ancient-style philosopher humorously expressing existential anxiety in Latin.'),
 (372, 'Music Humor, Word Play', 'Rap music is my second favorite type of music. Every other form of music is tied for #1.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful person with headphones enjoying music. They stand in front of a large colorful scoreboard divided into two sections: one reads ''Second Favorite: Rap Music'' with a single star, and the other shows a crowded tie with many music genres all jumbled together under ''First Favorite: All Other Music.'' Around the person are musical notes floating in the air, with little icons representing different genres like rock guitars, classical violins, jazz saxophones, and pop microphones, all grouped equally on the ''First Favorite'' side. The character has a playful smirk and is shrugging as if proud of their quirky ranking system. The background should be bright and vibrant to keep the mood light and funny, emphasizing the joke''s wordplay about music preferences.'),
 (373, 'Aging, Humor, Life', '60 might be the new 40, but 9:00 pm is the new midnight.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing an older person, around 60 years old, looking tired but content on a cozy couch at home. The background includes a clock on the wall clearly showing 9:00 pm. Nearby, a calendar page or a sign reads ''60 = 40?'' to humorously suggest age comparison. The person is yawning or half-asleep with a warm blanket and a cup of tea or hot cocoa on a side table. The room is softly lit, emphasizing a peaceful early evening vibe. The scene captures the joke that while 60 might feel like 40 in spirit, the usual going-to-bed time has gotten much earlier, with 9:00 pm now feeling as late as midnight once did. The style is light, colorful, and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions for a funny yet relatable mood.'),
 (374, 'Aging, Humor', 'I remember being able to get up without making sound effects.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a middle-aged or elderly person slowly rising from a chair in a cozy living room. The person looks slightly exaggerated with a theatrical grimace of effort on their face. Around them, several colorful sound effect words like ''Creak!'', ''Squeak!'', and ''Groan!'' are whimsically drawn in comic-style bubbles, emphasizing the noise they make while standing up. The room includes a comfortable armchair, a small side table with a cup of tea, and a pair of slippers left neatly on the floor. The overall mood is lighthearted and playful, with warm colors and exaggerated cartoon expressions to create humor out of the everyday struggle of aging bodies making sounds when getting up.'),
 (375, 'Aging, Bad Puns, Humor', 'I run like the winded.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person trying to run but clearly out of breath and struggling. The character should be shown mid-run with exaggerated tired expressions: sweat pouring down their face, tongue hanging out, and puffed cheeks. Their legs could be comically wobbly or dragging slightly to emphasize exhaustion. The background could include a running track or a park path with a few cartoon-style dust clouds or motion lines to indicate movement. Nearby, a small gust of wind character with a cheeky smile and little arms blowing air towards the runner would add to the pun. The overall style should be light, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the joke’s humor without any violence or negativity.'),
 (376, 'Aging, Humor, Life', 'The older I get, the earlier it gets late.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing an older person sitting in a cozy living room with a puzzled and slightly amused expression, glancing at a traditional wall clock. The clock’s hands show an unusually early time, like 6 PM, but a calendar or a window outside suggests it''s already ''late'' in the day (dusk or early evening light). Nearby, there''s a comfy armchair, a small side table with a cup of tea or coffee, and a calendar or a newspaper with the date prominently displayed. The older person''s casual clothes and gray hair hint at their age. The setting is warm and inviting, emphasizing the idea that ''late'' arrives earlier as one ages. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions and simple but clear lines, reinforcing the joke without any negativity or complexity.'),
 (377, 'Animals, Bad Puns', 'A bicycle can''t stand on its own because it''s two-tired.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a bicycle with exaggerated tired-looking eyes and droopy posture, leaning over with its two wheels flattened as if it''s exhausted. The bike is on a simple flat road or pavement with a subtle, wavy line suggesting fatigue. Nearby, a small speech bubble from the bike says, "I''m two-tired!" The background is light and cheerful with a sunny sky and a few fluffy clouds. Optional: a small cartoon character or animal nearby looking amused or puzzled by the bike''s condition. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and soft lines to emphasize the pun without any people or complex backgrounds.'),
 (378, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'A boiled egg is hard to beat.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a kitchen countertop where a personified boiled egg stands like a boxer in a boxing ring. The egg has muscular arms with boxing gloves, a determined facial expression, and a shiny hard shell. Around the egg, other breakfast items like a frying pan, a raw egg with a worried face, and a whisk cheer or look surprised. The background includes kitchen elements like an egg carton, stove, and cooking utensils to set the scene. The atmosphere is lighthearted and comical, emphasizing the pun that a ''boiled egg is hard to beat.'''),
 (379, 'Animals, Bad Puns', 'A chicken crossing the road is poultry in motion.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful chicken mid-stride crossing a two-lane road. The chicken is slightly exaggerated with big eyes and a confident smile, emphasizing its purposeful walk. The road should be simple, with clear lane markings, and a simple countryside or suburban background including a few trees and perhaps a friendly sun in the sky. Above or near the chicken, a small motion blur or speed lines indicate movement to emphasize ''in motion.'' Include a playful signpost on the roadside that says ''Crosswalk'' or ''Chicken Crossing.'' The overall art style is bright, colorful, and cartoonish with clear outlines, making it suitable for light-hearted humor without any violence or negativity.'),
 (380, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'A friend of mine tried to annoy me with bird puns, but I soon realized that toucan play at that game.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring two birds interacting in a playful way. One bird is a toucan with its large, colorful beak, looking cheeky and confident. The other bird looks slightly annoyed or frustrated, perhaps a small songbird or parrot, holding a tiny speech bubble with a pun or joke symbol (like a word bubble with a bird silhouette or a pun-related symbol). The background should be a simple, bright outdoor setting with a tree branch where they perch. Include playful visual cues like small musical notes or speech bubbles to indicate conversation and puns. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions on the birds'' faces to highlight the humor about wordplay related to the toucan pun.'),
 (381, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'A pun entered the room and kills 10 people. Pun in, ten dead.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene set in a simple room with a door labeled ''Room.'' In the center, a large walking pun character is personified: a playful word bubble with a smiling face and arms and legs. The pun is cheerfully stepping into the room. Scattered nearby are cartoonish characters looking surprised or fainted, with subtle ''Zzz'' or dizzy stars above their heads to indicate they are unconscious rather than harmed. The phrase ''Pun in, ten dead'' is whimsically illustrated above in bubbly, playful lettering. The overall atmosphere is lighthearted and fun, with exaggerated expressions on all characters, emphasizing wordplay rather than violence. The style is clean and bold, typical of a funny comic strip.'),
 (382, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'Broken pencils are pointless.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a broken pencil lying flat on a wooden desk or table. The pencil is visibly snapped in two near the tip, with the sharpened end showing bluntness and no lead sticking out. The pencil has expressive cartoon eyes and a small frowning mouth to convey a sad or frustrated emotion. Around the pencil, a few small paper scraps or a crumpled note add to the environment of uselessness. The background is simple and light-colored to keep focus on the pencil. Optionally, the scene could include an unbroken pencil standing upright nearby, looking smug or confident, emphasizing the contrast between the broken pencil''s ''pointlessness'' and the intact pencil''s usefulness. The overall style is whimsical and friendly, with bold outlines and bright colors suitable for a lighthearted cartoon joke.'),
 (383, 'Bad Puns, Good Question!, Humor', 'Did you know they won''t be making yard sticks any longer?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful, slightly confused-looking man standing in a backyard holding an old-fashioned wooden yardstick. The yardstick should look classic with clear measurement markings. Behind him is a neatly trimmed lawn with a small garden fence, and a sign stuck in the ground that says, ''No More Yardsticks!'' Nearby, a factory with a ''Yardstick Factory'' sign has a ''Closed'' banner hanging on its gate. The man is scratching his head, looking at the yardstick with exaggerated puzzlement. The sky is bright and sunny to keep the mood light and funny. The overall style is simple, colorful, and cartoony with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the joke''s absurdity and the punchline about yardsticks no longer being made.'),
 (384, 'Bad Puns, Science, Word Play', 'Entropy: it ain''t what it used to be.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a relaxed scientist or professor standing next to a large chalkboard filled with doodles and equations about entropy and disorder. The scientist has a whimsical, slightly tired expression and is holding a piece of chalk in one hand while shrugging with the other. On the chalkboard, write the phrase "Entropy: it ain''t what it used to be" in bold letters. Around the scientist, depict everyday objects getting messier or more disorganized: a spilled box of papers, an unraveling ball of yarn, and a melting ice cube on a plate. The background should be a simple laboratory or classroom setting with a humorous and light atmosphere, using bright, cheerful colors. The style should be cartoonish with exaggerated features to emphasize the joke''s playful tone, avoiding any negative or controversial imagery.'),
 (385, 'Bad Puns, Music Humor', 'He often broke into song because he couldn''t find the right key.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a man standing confused in front of a giant piano door with multiple exaggerated oversized keys scattered around on the ground. The man is holding a tiny, comically oversized keychain with a single key on it, looking puzzled as if trying to open the piano door with it. Musical notes float around his head, and he is mid-song, mouth open as if singing. The setting is simple, indoors, with a spotlight highlighting the man and the piano door. Add a small speech bubble with a musical note and a question mark to emphasize confusion about the ''right key''. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish with bright colors and exaggerated expressions.'),
 (386, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Humor', 'How do bears catch fish? With their bear hands!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, friendly-looking bear standing by a lively riverbank surrounded by trees. The bear is playfully trying to catch fish with its bare paws, splashing water everywhere. The fish are mid-jump, looking surprised or amused. Nearby, a few fish jump out of the water attempting to avoid the bear''s ''bear hands.'' Include some whimsical, exaggerated expressions on the bear and fish to enhance the humor. The background should be bright and cheerful with a clear blue sky, and some rocks and plants along the riverbank. The overall style is colorful and lighthearted, capturing a fun, pun-inspired moment without any violence or danger.'),
 (387, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor, Humor', 'How do you turn deviled eggs into regular eggs? An eggsorcism', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a plate of deviled eggs on a kitchen table. The deviled eggs have little devil horns and tiny pitchforks, looking mischievous. Beside the plate, a cartoon priest or exorcist character, dressed in a robe with a small cross necklace, is performing an ''eggsorcism'' by waving a miniature holy water sprinkler or holding a tiny Bible over the eggs. The eggs look surprised or scared, with little sweat drops on their faces. The kitchen background is simple and bright, with a window showing sunshine outside. The style should be lighthearted and funny, with exaggerated expressions on both the eggs and the exorcist character to emphasize the pun.'),
 (388, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'I broke my finger last week. On the other hand, I''m okay.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing with a cheerful expression. The person is holding up one hand showing a bandaged finger clearly broken, with a little plaster or splint visible. The other hand is raised in a thumbs-up gesture, clean and perfect. The background is simple, perhaps a plain wall or a kitchen setting, to keep the focus on the hands. The caption or speech bubble from the person says: ''I broke my finger last week. On the other hand, I''m okay.'' The overall tone is lighthearted, with exaggerated cartoonish features like big eyes and a wide smile to emphasize the pun.'),
 (389, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'I didn''t like my new beard, but then it grew on me.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a man looking at himself in a bathroom mirror with a skeptical or unhappy expression. On his chin, a patchy or small beard is starting to visibly grow. Nearby, an animated beard character with eyes and a smiling face is happily climbing up his cheek or jawline, as if literally ''growing on'' him. The background shows typical bathroom elements like a sink, toothbrush, and mirror with a few humorous details such as beard grooming tools or a calendar marking days passing. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the pun in the joke with clear facial expressions and the animated beard as a whimsical character.'),
 (390, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'I heard about a lab in California growing medical marijuana - a flock of terns landed in their field and ate all their weed. They say no tern was left unstoned.', NULL, 'A colorful and whimsical cartoon scene set in a sunny California field filled with tall cannabis plants. Several cheerful terns (small seabirds with white and gray feathers and black caps) are perched on and flying around the marijuana plants. Some terns are shown playfully nibbling on the leaves, with silly expressions suggesting they are ''high'' or goofy, like blurry eyes or goofy smiles. The field should look lush and green, with a simple sign that reads ''Medical Marijuana Lab'' near the edge. In the background, a surprised scientist or farmer wearing a lab coat and sunglasses stands scratching their head, watching the birds. Add a subtle smoke wreath drifting around the terns to hint humorously at the ''stoned'' pun. The whole style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, emphasizing the pun and playful mood without anything inappropriate or violent.'),
 (391, 'Bad Puns, Cartoon, Word Play', 'I heard Swedish war ships have bar codes on the sides. That way, when they return to port, they can Scandinavian', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, classic Swedish warship docked at a bustling harbor. The ship''s hull is humorously covered with big black and white barcode stripes running vertically, resembling a supermarket barcode. Nearby, a couple of dock workers wearing typical uniforms look amused or puzzled, holding clipboard and scanners as if they are scanning the ship. One of them holds a handheld scanner beeping as it points at the barcode on the ship. In the background, a signpost reads ''Swedish Naval Base'' in a simple font. The water is calm, and seagulls fly overhead. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions on the dock workers and the ship''s barcode clearly visible and central to the image. No violence or complexity, just a playful scene blending naval imagery with a grocery-store barcode concept.'),
 (392, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor, Word Play', 'I just swallowed some food coloring. I feel like I''ve dyed a little inside.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful person standing in a kitchen with a slightly surprised expression. The person has a few colorful stains in their mouth and on their tongue, glowing or dripping with various bright food coloring shades like red, blue, and green. Nearby on the counter are several small bottles or tubes labeled as food coloring with vivid colors spilling or sprinkled around. The background is simple, maybe with a kitchen sink and counter, to keep focus on the character and bottles. The person''s thought bubble reads, "I feel like I''ve dyed a little inside," with a subtle smile, emphasizing the wordplay. The overall tone is playful and funny, using bright colors and exaggerated expressions in a cartoon style without any harsh or dark elements.'),
 (393, 'Bad Puns, Humor', 'I know a guy who''s addicted to brake fluid. Says he can stop anytime.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a man standing beside a car, holding a large bottle labeled ''Brake Fluid'' with a mischievous grin. The man should appear slightly exaggerated with wide eyes and a cheeky smile. The car''s brake pads and wheels are visible to emphasize the theme. Nearby, include a small comic-style speech bubble above the man that reads, ''I can stop anytime.'' The background should be simple, possibly a garage or a road setting, with bright, friendly colors to keep the mood light and funny. The style should be playful and exaggerated, suitable for a family-friendly cartoon joke.'),
 (394, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'I once entered 10 puns in a best pun contest and thought I would win, but no pun in ten did', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a cheerful man standing on a stage at a pun contest. The stage has a banner reading ''Best Pun Contest'' in big colorful letters. The man is holding a pile of papers labeled ''10 Puns'' with a confident smile, but nearby a judge is shaking their head or shaking a finger disapprovingly. Around them are audience members in the background, some giggling, some looking unimpressed. The setting should be bright and lighthearted with simple stage props like a microphone stand and a spotlight focused on the man. Emphasize playful expressions to capture the pun and wordplay humor without any negative or aggressive vibes.'),
 (395, 'Bad Puns, Jobs, Mining Humor', 'I pulled a muscle digging for gold. It was a miner injury.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful miner wearing a yellow hard hat with a headlamp, overalls, and sturdy boots. He is struggling a bit, holding his arm or shoulder with a pained but comedic expression. Around him are mining tools like a pickaxe stuck in a small pile of dirt and scattered gold nuggets sparkling nearby. The background shows a simple mine entrance with wooden supports and a cart full of gold pieces. The miner’s speech bubble reads, ''It was a miner injury.'' The art style is lighthearted, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the pun on ''miner'' and ''minor'' injury without any harsh or serious tone.'),
 (396, 'Bad Puns, Word Play', 'I tried to catch some fog, but I mist', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a person standing in a foggy landscape early in the morning. The person should look slightly frustrated or puzzled, with arms outstretched as if trying to grab something intangible. Around them, the fog is thick and swirly, visually emphasizing that it’s impossible to catch. Include subtle visual pun elements, like a thought bubble showing a net or a lasso aimed toward the fog but with the word ''MIST'' humorously floating away just out of reach. The setting is outdoors with a few faint outlines of trees or hills in the background to highlight the foggy atmosphere. The style is lighthearted and whimsical, using soft colors and exaggerated expressions to enhance the joke without any violence or complex backgrounds.'),
 (397, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'I wanted to watch the world origami championships, but it was only on paper view.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person sitting in front of a TV or computer screen labeled ''World Origami Championships.'' The screen displays simple paper shapes like cranes and boats instead of live video. Next to the person, there''s a large paper folded into an origami shape with a tiny ticket stub or sign that says ''Paper View Only.'' The person scratches their head or looks puzzled. The background is a cozy living room with a lamp and a stack of origami papers on a table. The overall mood is light-hearted, with exaggerated expressions and bright colors to emphasize the pun on ''paper view'' instead of ''pay-per-view.'''),
 (398, 'Bad Puns, Travel Humor', 'I was going to buy a money belt for our latest trip, but it seemed like such a waist of money', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in a store aisle filled with travel accessories. The main character is holding a money belt around their waist with a puzzled and slightly amused expression. The money belt is exaggeratedly bulky and clearly labeled ''Money Belt.'' Nearby, a price tag floats showing an expensive price. Around the character, there are travel items like suitcases, passports, and maps on shelves. The background has playful travel posters on the walls. The setting is lighthearted and colorful, emphasizing the pun by visually focusing on the money belt around the waist as a ''waste'' of money, with a slight visual emphasis on the waist area (perhaps with small motion lines or sparkles). No people are upset or serious, and the overall style is goofy and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions and bright colors to enhance the humor without any negativity.'),
 (399, 'Bad Puns, History Humor, Word Play', 'I, for one, like Roman Numerals.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person happily standing next to a large, ancient Roman numeral chart on a scroll or stone tablet. The character is smiling proudly with thumbs up, wearing casual modern clothes and perhaps a laurel wreath loosely on their head as a playful nod to Roman culture. Around them are various Roman numerals (I, V, X, L, C, D, M) displayed prominently, with some characters reading the numbers in an exaggerated or playful way. The background is simple and bright to emphasize the cheerful mood, with a lighthearted tone suggesting someone genuinely enthusiastic about Roman numerals. No dark or violent imagery, just an upbeat, pun-friendly environment that conveys a mild joke about liking Roman numerals, which can be read both as ''like them'' and a possible subtle nod to the complexity or iconic style of these numbers.'),
 (400, 'Bad Puns, Cartoon, Food Humor', 'In the army of corny jokes, I''m the kernel', NULL, 'Draw a cartoon scene featuring a small army of anthropomorphic popcorn kernels dressed in military uniforms. The central figure is a proud, smiling popcorn kernel standing confidently at attention, wearing a general''s hat and holding a tiny flag with a corny joke symbol (like a smiling ear of corn). Surrounding this ''kernel'' are other popcorn kernels in soldier gear, some with goofy expressions, some mid-popping into fluffy popcorn. The background should look like a whimsical battlefield made of popcorn boxes and popcorn bags scattered around. Use bright, cheerful colors and a lighthearted, humorous cartoon style to emphasize the pun on ''army'' and ''kernel.'' Avoid any weapons or violence; the focus is on cute popcorn characters in a playful military setting.'),
 (401, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'It''s hard to explain puns to kleptomaniacs because they always take things literally.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters: one is a person looking slightly confused or frustrated, trying to explain something, while the other is a kleptomaniac depicted humorously, sneaking away holding a big oversized pun displayed as a word or phrase on a large sticky note or speech bubble. The kleptomaniac should have a playful, exaggerated sneaky expression and be tiptoeing away, literally ''taking'' the pun. The setting can be a simple room or park bench to keep focus on the interaction. Include a thought bubble above the confused person showing different puns or wordplays to reinforce the joke about puns. Keep the colors bright and the expressions exaggerated for comedic effect in a clear cartoon style without any threatening or negative elements.'),
 (402, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Fishing Humor', 'I''ve always admired fishermen - they are reel men.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a fisherman standing proudly on a small wooden dock by a lake. He is wearing classic fishing gear: a fishing hat with hooks and lures attached, a vest with many pockets, and rubber boots. In one hand, he is holding a fishing rod with a big fish caught on the line, and in the other hand, he is giving a thumbs-up. Nearby, a smiling fish is leaping out of the water, with cartoonish motion lines showing the jump. Above the fisherman, a speech bubble reads, ''I’m a reel man!'' emphasizing the pun. The background includes a bright sunny sky, trees lining the lake, and a wooden sign by the dock that reads ''Welcome to Reel Lake.'' The style is colorful, cheerful, and exaggerated for comedic effect, capturing the pun on ''reel'' and ''real'' in a lighthearted way.'),
 (403, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'Soup that tastes great is souper', NULL, 'A cheerful cartoon scene featuring a steaming bowl of soup sitting on a small table. The bowl has a happy, smiling face with big eyes and is surrounded by little cartoon stars or sparkles to emphasize that it tastes great. Above or near the bowl, include playful lettering with the word "Souper!" in a fun, bold font. The background is simple and bright to keep focus on the bowl. Optional props include a spoon held by an unseen hand or resting next to the bowl, and maybe a small chef''s hat on top of the bowl to add humor and personality. The overall style is lighthearted and whimsical, suitable for a humorous pun visual.'),
 (404, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'Steak Puns: now there''s a medium where anything well done is rare.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a steakhouse restaurant setting where three steaks are anthropomorphized with cute eyes and expressive faces. One steak in the center is smiling confidently and labeled ''Medium'' with a chef''s hat on top. On one side, a steak looking tired and a bit rare is labeled ''Well Done'' and on the other side, a steak looking surprised and rare is labeled ''Rare''. Above them, a speech bubble coming from the ''Medium'' steak says, "Now there''s a medium where anything well done is rare." The background shows a wooden table with a plate, a knife, and fork, and a rustic steakhouse ambiance with warm lighting. The overall artistic style is light, colorful, and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions on the steaks to emphasize humor and the pun.'),
 (405, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Cartoon', 'The Energizer Bunny was arrested - charged with battery.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing the Energizer Bunny, the iconic pink rabbit wearing sunglasses and holding drumsticks, standing at a police station being ''arrested.'' The bunny should look slightly mischievous but not scared. A police officer, with a friendly smile, is holding a clipboard labeled ''Charge: Battery.'' Next to the bunny, include a large battery symbol or an oversized AA battery on the floor to emphasize the pun. The background should have typical police station elements like a badge on the wall, a wanted poster with a picture of the bunny, and a holding cell door partly open. The style is colorful and lighthearted with exaggerated cartoon features to keep it funny and playful.'),
 (406, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor, Word Play', 'The fastest way to quit being vegan is cold turkey.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person looking shocked or surprised while holding a peeled, whole cold turkey (the raw, uncooked kind) in their hands. The person is standing in a kitchen with a refrigerator in the background and a calendar on the wall showing a crossed-out ''vegan'' label on a certain date, suggesting they''ve just quit being vegan. On a nearby counter, there are some fresh vegetables left untouched with a ''Vegan'' sign next to them. The cold turkey is dramatically emphasized, perhaps with speed lines or motion marks to illustrate the ''fastest way''. The overall tone is light and funny, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expression that captures the pun on ''cold turkey'' meaning both quitting abruptly and the food itself.'),
 (407, 'Bad Puns, Technology Humor, Word Play', 'The inventor of auto-correct just died -- may he roast in piss.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simplistic graveyard with a single headstone. The gravestone has the words ''Auto-Correct Inventor'' engraved on it. Standing next to the gravestone is a confused-looking cartoon character holding a phone, looking frustrated because the phrase ''roast in peace'' on his phone autocorrected to ''roast in piss''. The phone screen humorously shows the autocorrect suggestion with a red underline or popup bubble highlighting the mistake. In the background, there is a scroll-like signpost with the original phrase ''rest in peace'' crossed out and replaced with ''roast in piss''. The style should be lighthearted and comical, with exaggerated facial expressions and bright colors, emphasizing the irony and annoyance of autocorrect mistakes without any harsh tone.'),
 (408, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'The short fortune teller who escaped from prison was a small medium at large.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a short, quirky fortune teller who has just escaped from prison. The fortune teller is small in stature, wearing colorful, stereotypical fortune teller clothes including a headscarf, large hoop earrings, and holding a crystal ball that glows mysteriously. He stands confidently just outside orange prison bars or a broken cell door labeled ''Prison.'' Around him are comic-style motion lines showing movement away from the prison. Above or beside him, a sign reads ''Small Medium at Large'' in playful, bold letters. The background should be simple, focusing on the fortune teller, the jail cell, and the pun expressed visually, making it clear this is a lighthearted cartoon pun. The style is bright, cheerful, and exaggerated with a slight caricature look, emphasizing the joke on the fortune teller being a ''medium'' and at ''large'' (escaped). No violence or harsh imagery.'),
 (409, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Puns, Word Play', 'Time flies like an arrow. Fruit flies like a banana.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene split into two parts side-by-side. On the left, a classic arrow is soaring swiftly through the air with a bright blue sky and a stopwatch or clock nearby to emphasize the phrase "Time flies like an arrow." On the right, a bunch of cheerful, cartoonish fruit flies with tiny wings are buzzing happily around and landing on a large, ripe banana. The fruit flies should have exaggerated, cute features like big eyes and smiling faces to add humor. The background is light and simple, with maybe a kitchen table or fruit bowl hinted at behind the banana. The overall style is playful and colorful with clear visual contrasts between the two parts representing the wordplay in the joke.'),
 (410, 'Bad Puns, Computers, Office Humor, Puns', 'To whoever took my Microsoft Office: I will find you. You have my Word.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in an office environment. In the foreground, a frustrated office worker stands with crossed arms, wearing business casual clothes, staring at an empty desk where a computer monitor and keyboard should be. A sticky note is prominently stuck on the desk or monitor stand that says ''To whoever took my Microsoft Office: I will find you. You have my Word.'' In the background, subtle visual hints show missing icons labeled ''Word,'' ''Excel,'' and ''PowerPoint'' floating away like little cartoon characters or ghostly app icons flying out an open window. The atmosphere is light and amusing, with exaggerated facial expressions and playful details like a spilled coffee cup or scattered papers to add to the chaos, but no violence or negativity. The style is colorful, simple, and whimsical to emphasize the pun on Microsoft Office and Word.'),
 (411, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Camping', 'Two Eskimos sitting in a kayak were chilly, so they lit a fire in the craft. Unsurprisingly it sank, proving once again that you can''t have your kayak and heat it too.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two Eskimos sitting inside a small wooden kayak floating on calm water. Both Eskimos wear traditional fur-lined parkas and look shivery and cold, with visible cartoonish shivers and chattering teeth. One Eskimo is holding a small wooden matchbox and the other is carefully lighting a small campfire inside the middle of the kayak. The kayak is visibly starting to take on water around the fire, with small splashes and bubbles showing the effects of the fire''s heat on the water. Both Eskimos have surprised, worried expressions as the kayak begins to sink, tilting slightly forward. The background should be a chilly arctic scene with icebergs and snow-covered land visible in the distance under a pale blue sky. The cartoon style should emphasize exaggerated expressions and a playful, light-hearted mood without any danger or discomfort to the characters.'),
 (412, 'Bad Puns, Office Humor', 'Whiteboards are remarkable.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a whiteboard in a bright, cheerful classroom or office setting. The whiteboard has a big smiley face drawn on it with expressive eyes and a wide grin. Around the whiteboard, a few colorful markers are scattered, some with little limbs and happy faces, looking proud or excited. The whiteboard stands on an easel or mounted on a wall, slightly angled as if ''posing''. The background includes a teacher or office worker gesturing toward the whiteboard with an impressed or amazed expression. The style is light-hearted and fun, using simple, bold lines and bright colors, evoking a playful and friendly atmosphere that highlights the pun on "remarkable" (as the whiteboard can be written on with markers).'),
 (413, 'Bad Puns, Farming Humor, Humor, Puns', 'You know how farmers make crop circles? They use a protractor', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a farmer standing in a large wheat field under a bright blue sky. The farmer wears overalls, a straw hat, and holds an oversized protractor the size of a large sheet of paper. Behind him are several perfectly straight crop lines forming parts of a crop circle pattern, emphasizing angles and curves like a geometric drawing. A tractor is parked nearby with its wheels leaving neat lines in the soil. The farmer looks proudly at his work, with a friendly smile. Include a few crows or birds on the side watching curiously. The overall tone is light and playful, with clear lines and bright colors suitable for a family-friendly comic strip.'),
 (414, 'Camping, Puns, Travel Humor', 'An RV is the best investment you can make in wheel estate!', NULL, 'Draw a colorful cartoon scene featuring a large, cheerful RV parked prominently in a sunny campground. The RV should look inviting and well-kept, with wheels clearly visible. Surround the RV with a playful sign that reads ''Best Investment in Wheel Estate!'' in bright, fun letters. Include some happy campers around the RV, maybe a family or friends smiling and admiring the vehicle. The background can show trees, a picnic table, and maybe some rolling hills to set a relaxing vacation vibe. The overall tone is lighthearted and humorous, emphasizing the pun on ''real estate'' by focusing on a ''wheel estate'' pun with the RV as the centerpiece.'),
 (415, 'Camping, Humor, Life, Word Play', 'God gave us shin bones so we could find trailer hitches in the dark.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing barefoot in a dark backyard at night. The person looks surprised and slightly in pain, holding their leg where their shin has just bumped into a trailer hitch attached to a parked trailer or truck. The trailer hitch is clearly visible and glowing faintly to indicate that it is the ''hidden'' object causing the pain. Nearby, a cheeky, friendly-looking cartoon depiction of God is subtly shining a small spotlight or holding a flashlight aimed just at the trailer hitch, smiling knowingly. The background should be simple with a fence, some grass, and a moon in the sky to emphasize the night setting. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish, focusing on the relatable scenario of accidentally hitting your shin on a trailer hitch in the dark.'),
 (416, 'Camping, Humor, Word Play', 'How many RVers does it take to change a light bulb? Only one - the others are dealing with their grey water issues.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large RV or camper parked at a campsite. In front of the RV, one cheerful camper stands on a small ladder changing a light bulb in the RV’s exterior light fixture. Nearby, two other campers are busy with exaggerated and messy grey water tanks or hoses, struggling comically with leaking or overflowing grey water. One camper might be holding a bunch of tangled hoses with water splashing out, while the other looks frustrated and is holding a wrench or bucket. The background shows a simple campsite with trees and a picnic table, adding to the outdoor setting. The style is lighthearted, detailed enough to clearly show the RV, the actions of the characters, and the humorous struggle with grey water tasks.'),
 (418, 'Bad Puns, Camping, Word Play', 'You can''t run through a campsite. You can only ran. Because it''s past tents.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at a campsite with a cheeky play on words. In the foreground, a person mid-run looks confused and slightly frustrated as they try to run through a campsite entrance. The campsite entrance is marked by a sign that says ''Campsite'' and a large wooden gate with several colorful tents pitched beyond it. Nearby, a small campsite map is shown with a dotted path leading through the ''tents'' area. To emphasize the pun, an anthropomorphic tent with eyes and a smirking face stands blocking the runner’s path, holding out a hand to signal ''stop.'' The runner is cut off mid-stride, and a speech bubble coming from the tent says, "You can''t run here, it''s past tents!" The sky is bright and sunny, with some trees and campfires in the background to set the outdoorsy vibe. The overall art style is light-hearted, colorful, and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions to highlight the joke.'),
 (419, 'Camping, Humor', 'You might be a RVer if roughing it is only water and electric.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a cozy RV parked in a scenic campground with trees and a campfire nearby. Inside the RV, a relaxed person is sitting comfortably on a plush chair with a cup of coffee, watching TV. Outside, the usual camping survival elements like a rugged tent and a small campfire with marshmallows on sticks are lightly faded or overshadowed by the RV''s creature comforts. A water hose and an electric cable are connected from the RV to nearby hookup posts labeled ''Water'' and ''Electric.'' The caption or a small signboard near the RV says ''Roughing It.'' The overall atmosphere is cheerful and lighthearted, contrasting the rustic outdoors with the convenience of a fully hooked-up RV experience.'),
 (420, 'Camping, Humor, Life', 'You might be a RVer if you find yourself spending an inordinate amount of time discussing the merits of different toilet papers.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two middle-aged RV travelers standing next to a colorful camper van parked at a sunny campsite. They are both intensely examining several different rolls of toilet paper laid out on a folding table between them. One person holds up a roll labeled ''Ultra Soft,'' while the other holds a roll labeled ''Eco-Friendly.'' Around them, typical camping elements like a campfire, folding chairs, and trees can be seen. Both travelers have amused yet serious expressions, as if engaged in a deep debate about which toilet paper to choose. Include small details like a picnic basket, a map, and a sign that says ''Welcome to Happy Trails RV Park.'' The overall style should be light-hearted and cartoonish, emphasizing the quirky obsession with toilet paper among RV enthusiasts without any negative or political undertones.'),
 (421, 'Camping, Humor, Word Play', 'You might be a RVer if you hang a ladder on your ladder.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing the side of a recreational vehicle (RV) parked at a campsite. On the RV, there is a large, extendable ladder attached for climbing onto the roof. Hanging from that ladder is a smaller, traditional household ladder dangling loosely as if ready to be used. Include a cheerful person dressed in casual camping clothes, glancing at the setup with a playful smirk or amused expression. Surround the RV with typical campsite elements such as a picnic table, a campfire, some trees, and a few camping chairs, creating a relaxed outdoor atmosphere. The style should be bright, colorful, and exaggerated for comedic effect, emphasizing the silliness of putting a ladder on another ladder as an essential RV hack or quirk.'),
 (422, 'Camping, Humor, Life', 'You might be a RVer if you think 300 square feet of living space is really living!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing the interior of a very cozy RV. The RV is drawn in cross-section so the entire interior is visible. Inside, a cheerful person is happily lounging on a tiny sofa that looks almost as big as the available space. Around them, there are compact furniture pieces like a foldable table, a small kitchenette, and a bed folded up to maximize space. A window shows a sunny outdoors with a campfire and a forest scene, indicating they''re in nature. The person has a big smile and relaxed posture, portraying contentment with their small living area. A small caption or sign inside the RV reads "300 sq ft = Really Living!" to emphasize the joke. The style is colorful, lighthearted, and cartoonish, with exaggerated proportions to highlight the smallness of the space yet the person''s happiness. Nothing crowded or claustrophobic, just cozy and cheerful.'),
 (423, 'Camping, Humor', 'You might be a RVer if you think it is completely normal to drive a F-450(or any dually) to the store to pick up a few groceries.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing beside a huge, exaggeratedly large Ford F-450 dually truck parked right outside a small grocery store. The truck looks oversized and comically big compared to the modest-sized store and a few shopping carts nearby. The person is casually holding a small grocery bag, appearing completely unfazed by the massive vehicle they drove just to get a few groceries. There should be a sign on the store reading ''Grocery Store'' and a few other shoppers with normal-sized cars giving amused or confused looks at the large truck. The colors should be bright and cartoonish, emphasizing the absurdity of using such a big vehicle for a small errand.'),
 (424, 'Camping, Puns, Travel Humor', 'You might be a RVer if you think the capital of the United States is Elkhart, Indiana', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing an RV parked in a scenic spot with a family or an individual happily standing outside the RV. In the background, a large, colorful road sign reads ''Welcome to Elkhart, Indiana'' and looks oversized and prominent, as if mistaken for the nation''s capital. The character(s) should be pointing or looking proudly at the sign, with exaggerated happy or confident expressions. The RV should look detailed but friendly and inviting, with outdoor camping gear like folding chairs and a small grill nearby. The setting includes a sunny sky, trees, and a hint of a highway or rest stop to emphasize travel. The overall tone is lighthearted, poking fun at RV enthusiasts'' close connection to travel locations like Elkhart, known for RV manufacturing.'),
 (425, 'Animals, Chickens, Puns', 'Did''ya hear about the chicken who could only lay eggs in the winter? She was no spring chicken.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a chicken standing proudly on a snowy winter landscape, surrounded by a few freshly laid eggs on the ground. The chicken wears a tiny scarf and earmuffs to emphasize the cold season. In the background, leafless trees and snowflakes falling from the sky reinforce the winter setting. A small sign next to the chicken reads ''No Spring Chicken'' as a playful pun. The style is bright and colorful, with exaggerated, cute features on the chicken to enhance the humor and friendliness of the scene.'),
 (426, 'Chickens, Food Humor, Puns', 'Egg salad is technically still chicken salad.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a sandwich sitting on a plate with a thought bubble. Inside the thought bubble is a confused, cartoon-style chicken wearing glasses and holding a recipe book titled ''Salads.'' The sandwich is labeled ''Egg Salad'' with a few chopped eggs visible, while next to it on the table is a separate, traditional chicken salad sandwich with chunks of chicken. The chicken is scratching its head, looking puzzled as if trying to understand why egg salad might count as chicken salad. The background is a simple kitchen setting with a window and a salt shaker for added detail, all drawn with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to enhance the humor.'),
 (427, 'Animals, Chickens, Humor, Social Commentary', 'I have a dream that one day chickens will be able to cross the road without being judged on their motives.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confident, anthropomorphic chicken standing at a crosswalk, ready to cross a road. The chicken has an expressive face showing a mix of determination and slight frustration. On the sidewalk, several other animals and humans are standing, whispering and side-glancing at the chicken with exaggerated judging expressions (raised eyebrows, crossed arms, side-eye). Above the scene, a large billboard or sign resembles a famous inspirational quote style, with the words: "I have a dream that one day chickens will cross the road without being judged." The background includes a simple country road with a few trees, a bright sky, and a peaceful neighborhood setting. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the chicken''s desire for equality and fairness in crossing the road without suspicion or judgment. The art style is colorful and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions and simple, clear lines to enhance humor.'),
 (428, 'Animals, Chickens, Puns', 'What do you call a chicken crossing the road? Poultry in motion.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene depicting a cheerful chicken walking briskly across a typical two-lane road. The chicken wears a determined expression and mid-step its wings are slightly out to balance itself. The road should be shown from a side view with a dashed center line. On the side of the road, include a small signpost with a playful hint of motion—like cartoon motion lines around the chicken''s legs or dust clouds behind to emphasize movement. The background features green grass and a bright blue sky with a few fluffy clouds. The overall style is lighthearted and fun, with exaggerated, rounded shapes to enhance the humor and cuteness of the scene. No people or vehicles are needed to keep the focus on the ''poultry in motion'' pun.'),
 (429, 'Animals, Chickens, Puns', 'What do you get when a chicken lays an egg on top of a barn? An eggroll.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a classic red barn with a slanted roof under a bright blue sky with a few fluffy white clouds. On top of the barn''s roof sits a plump, cartoon-style chicken looking a bit proud or surprised. Directly beneath the chicken, a large egg is gently rolling down the curved roof, depicted with motion lines to show it''s moving. Nearby on the ground, a smiling egg character with arms and legs looks up at the rolling egg, as if excited or cheering. The setting is a cheerful farmyard with some green grass, a wooden fence, and a couple of cartoon-style chickens pecking around in the background. The overall style is lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated, rounded shapes and big expressive eyes on the animals and the egg for extra humor.'),
 (430, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Chickens, Food Humor', 'Which day of the week do chickens hate most? Fry-day!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a group of cartoon chickens standing outside on a farm. The setting shows a bright sunny day with a classic red barn in the background and a wooden fence. In the foreground, three chickens are gathered, looking alarmed and gossiping as they point towards a calendar hanging on a fence post. The calendar clearly highlights the day labeled ''Friday,'' but with the word replaced humorously as ''Fry-day'' in bold, sizzling letters with little cartoon flames around it. Nearby, a chef''s frying pan floats in the air with steam rising, hinting at cooking but portrayed in a light-hearted, non-threatening way. The chickens have exaggerated, expressive faces showing nervousness and fear. The overall style is colorful, exaggerated, and playful, emphasizing the wordplay on ''Friday'' and ''fry.'' The scene invites laughter without any violence or negativity, capturing the pun visually.'),
 (431, 'Animals, Chickens, Puns, Sports Humor', 'Why did the chicken cross the basketball court? He heard the referee calling fowls', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene on a basketball court with a chicken walking confidently across the court. The chicken is in mid-stride, looking slightly puzzled but determined. The basketball court has clear markings, hoops on both ends, and a referee standing in the background blowing a whistle while making a hand signal as if calling a foul. Above the referee, a speech bubble says ''Fowls!''. The setting is bright and colorful, with a few scattered basketballs and a scoreboard visible. The overall style is playful and exaggerated, emphasizing the pun between ''fouls'' in basketball and the chicken ''fowls''.'),
 (432, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Chickens, Humor', 'Why did the chicken cross the playground? To get to the other slide.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene set in a playground on a sunny day. The main focus is a cheerful cartoon chicken mid-step, crossing from one side to the other. On one side of the playground is a classic slide with a ladder, and on the other side is another identical slide to emphasize ''the other slide.'' Around the playground, include swings, a sandbox, and a few playful trees to add context. The chicken should have a cute, slightly exaggerated expression of determination or curiosity. The style is lighthearted and whimsical with bright colors and simple shapes to evoke humor and playfulness. No people are needed, only the chicken and playground equipment to keep the focus on the joke''s punchline about the chicken crossing to the other slide, a pun on ''other side.'''),
 (433, 'Christmas, Puns', 'What kind of cars do Santa''s elves drive? Toy-otas', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Santa''s elves standing proudly next to several small, brightly colored cars that look like toys. The cars are styled like compact, playful versions of Toyota vehicles, featuring exaggerated features such as oversized wheels and candy cane-striped paint jobs, with little elf hats on the antennas. The elves are dressed in classic green and red outfits with pointy hats and curled shoes, smiling and waving. In the background, North Pole scenery is visible with snowy ground, candy canes, and Santa''s workshop. A sign next to the cars reads "Toy-otas" in a playful font. The overall atmosphere is cheerful and festive, emphasizing the pun between ''toy'' and ''Toyota'' in a lighthearted, cartoon style without any violence or negative elements.'),
 (434, 'Bad Puns, Christmas', 'Did you know Santa has a 10th reindeer named Olive? It''s in that Rudolph song - you know - ''Olive the other reindeer''', NULL, 'Draw a cheerful cartoon scene featuring Santa Claus in his traditional red suit and hat, standing next to his sleigh filled with presents. In front of the sleigh, show nine classic reindeer pulling it, but in the center, instead of a reindeer, draw a cute, whimsical olive with tiny reindeer antlers and a red nose, playfully blending in with the other reindeer. Make the olive slightly anthropomorphic, with big expressive eyes and a smile. Above them, include a musical note or a speech bubble referencing the famous Rudolph song lyric "Olive, the other reindeer." The background should be a snowy night sky with stars to set a festive Christmas mood. The overall style should be colorful, lighthearted, and humorous, emphasizing the pun visually.'),
 (435, 'Christmas, Puns, Word Play', 'Did you know Santa has a 10th reindeer Olive? It''s in the Rudolph song - ''Olive the other reindeer''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Santa Claus standing next to his traditional team of eight reindeer plus Rudolph with his glowing red nose. In front of them is a cute reindeer wearing a small green olive as a necklace or hat, looking proud and slightly confused. Above them, a musical note banner floats with the lyrics ''Olive, the other reindeer'' in playful, whimsical font. The scene is set on a snowy rooftop under a starry night sky with the silhouette of a chimney and a sleigh filled with gift bags. Santa is smiling and pointing at the olive-wearing reindeer while the others look on with surprised expressions. Everything is drawn in bright colors with exaggerated cartoon features to amplify the joke''s playful tone.'),
 (436, 'Christmas, Pop Culture, Puns', 'How did the young Jedi always know what they were getting for Christmas? They could sense their presents.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a young Jedi child standing in front of a Christmas tree decorated with lights and ornaments. The Jedi wears a simple tunic and a small lightsaber hanging from a belt. The child has a peaceful, knowing smile on their face, eyes slightly closed as if concentrating or sensing something. Around them, faint, glowing, force-like waves or sparkles are illustrated emanating from the child toward several wrapped Christmas presents under the tree. The setting should be cozy and festive with holiday decorations like stockings on a nearby mantle and a glowing fireplace in the background. The tone is lighthearted and magical, emphasizing the child''s connection to the Force and holiday cheer.'),
 (437, 'Christmas, Puns, Word Play', 'How does Christmas Day end? With the letter ''Y''!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on Christmas Day evening. Central to the image is a large, smiling letter ''Y'' wearing a Santa hat and standing like a character. Around it, a cozy living room is decorated festively with a Christmas tree decked with ornaments and lights, stockings hanging on a fireplace mantel, and wrapped presents scattered on the floor. A family (two adults and a child) are sitting on a couch, looking amused as they point toward the letter ''Y''. The clock on the wall shows late evening (around 11:59 PM). The mood is cheerful and lighthearted, with warm colors and exaggerated cartoon features conveying a friendly holiday atmosphere. The letter ''Y'' is the punchline character, embodying the joke that Christmas Day ends literally with the letter ''Y''.'),
 (438, 'Christmas, Holiday Humor, Puns', 'How much does Santa pay to park his sleigh? Nothing - it''s in the house!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing the interior of a cozy, festive house decorated for Christmas. Santa Claus is parked inside near a large fireplace, with his sleigh and a team of reindeer comfortably settled in like they are guests in a living room. The sleigh is full of colorful wrapped gifts. The reindeer are lounging on armchairs or a rug, looking relaxed and happy. A large ''No Parking'' sign is visible outside through a window, while inside a small sign humorously reads ''Parking: Free for Santa.'' The house has festive decorations such as stockings hung on the mantle, a brightly lit Christmas tree, and snow visible outside the window. The overall tone is warm, cheerful, and playful.'),
 (439, 'Christmas, Holiday Humor, Puns', 'I couldn''t decide over Christmas break if I liked eggnog or not. I think I''m eggnostic', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set during Christmas break inside a cozy living room decorated with holiday decorations like a Christmas tree, stockings, and twinkling lights. In the center, depict a cheerful person holding a cup of eggnog in one hand, looking thoughtfully confused with a raised eyebrow and a slight smile, scratching their head with the other hand. Nearby on a table, show a carton or bottle labeled ''Eggnog'' with a few spilled drops to add humor. Include a small thought bubble above the person''s head containing a light bulb crossed out or a question mark next to an egg-shaped icon to hint at the pun ''eggnostic.'' The overall mood is light-hearted and playful, with bright, warm Christmas colors and a clean, simple cartoon style emphasizing the pun without needing words in the scene itself.'),
 (440, 'Christmas, Humor', 'KK/WT: Ho-Ho ? (Ho-Ho-Who?) Your Santa impression needs some work...', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a living room decorated for Christmas with a Christmas tree, presents, and holiday lights. In the center, a child is standing with a playful smirk, holding a finger to their lips as if teasing. Opposite the child, an adult dressed as Santa Claus is trying to say ''Ho-Ho-Ho'' but instead looks confused and is saying ''Ho-Ho-Who?'' The adult''s Santa hat is slightly askew, and there’s a speech bubble coming from the child that says, "Your Santa impression needs some work..." The overall vibe is lighthearted and playful, with warm colors and exaggerated, friendly expressions to emphasize the joke''s fun and gentle teasing tone. No one looks upset, just amused by the mix-up in the Santa impression.'),
 (441, 'Christmas, Food Humor, Puns', 'The sweater I got for Christmas was picking up lots of static electricity. I took it back and exchanged it and they gave me a different one free of charge.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy clothing store decorated for Christmas, with garlands and a small Christmas tree nearby. In the foreground, a smiling customer is holding a large, fluffy sweater that has visible ''static electricity'' sparks illustrated as small zigzag yellow lines crackling around it, making their hair stand on end humorously. Across the counter, a friendly store clerk is handing over another sweater that has a smooth, harmless look with no sparks. Both characters wear casual winter clothes, and the setting includes shelves filled with folded sweaters and holiday gift signs. The mood is lighthearted and festive, emphasizing the funny situation of exchanging a ''static-charged'' sweater for one ''free of charge.'''),
 (442, 'Animals, Christmas, Puns, Winter Humor', 'What did one snowman say to the other? ''Is it just me, or do you smell carrots?''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting two snowmen standing outdoors in a snowy winter landscape. One snowman is leaning slightly toward the other, with a curious expression. Both snowmen have classic coal eyes, a carrot nose, stick arms, and a scarf. The snowman on the left is sniffing the air with a puzzled look, while the other snowman looks amused or surprised. Around them, snow-covered trees and a gentle snowfall set the scene. There could be a subtle hint of melted carrot pieces or small orange smells visually represented as wavy lines near their noses to emphasize the joke. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated cartoon features such as big eyes and wide smiles to enhance the comedic effect.'),
 (443, 'Christmas, Puns, Word Play', 'What did the wise men say after they offered up their gifts of gold and frankincense? Wait, there''s myrrh.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing the three wise men from the Nativity story standing together. Two of them are holding out traditional gifts: one with a small treasure chest labeled ''Gold'' and the other holding a fancy bottle labeled ''Frankincense''. The third wise man is pointing forward with a lightbulb or a surprised expression as if he’s just realized something, with a speech bubble that says, ''Wait, there’s myrrh.'' They are all dressed in bright, colorful robes and turbans, standing in a desert-like setting with a simple starry night sky in the background. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the pun and moment of revelation.'),
 (444, 'Christmas, Humor, Word Play', 'What do you call a kid who doesn’t believe in Santa? A rebel without a Claus', NULL, 'Create a humorous cartoon scene featuring a confident, cheeky kid standing with arms crossed and a slight smirk on their face. The kid should be dressed in casual, modern clothing and appear slightly rebellious but playful. To the side, depict a classic jolly Santa Claus character looking surprised or confused, with his trademark red suit, white beard, and hat. Around them, add festive holiday decorations like Christmas trees, presents, and twinkling lights to set a Christmas atmosphere. The background could be indoors in a cozy living room with a fireplace and stockings hanging, highlighting the Santa theme. The overall style should be bright, colorful, and exaggerated for comedic effect, with expressive faces and light-hearted cartoon proportions.'),
 (445, 'Christmas, Puns', 'What do you call people who are afraid of Santa? Claustrophobic', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a group of nervous or scared people backed up against walls or each other inside a small room labeled ''Santa''s Workshop.'' The people look wide-eyed and anxious, some peeking over their shoulders. In the center, a friendly, classic Santa Claus stands with a big smile, holding a sack of presents, completely unaware of their fear. The room is decorated with Christmas lights, candy canes, and presents stacked around. The overall tone is light and funny, with exaggerated expressions of claustrophobia—such as a person pressed against a wall with their hands holding onto the sides, and another clutching a wrapped gift tightly in panic.'),
 (446, 'Christmas, Language, Puns', 'What do you call Santa''s helpers? Subordinate Clauses', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Santa Claus in his cozy North Pole workshop. Santa is at a wooden desk with a big book labeled ''Christmas List'' open. Around him are several small elves dressed in festive outfits, wearing pointy hats and shoes, busily working. These elves are depicted as ''subordinate clauses'' by having small captions with grammatical terms above their heads (e.g., ''because he said so,'' ''while making toys,'' ''if the reindeer rest''). Santa looks amused and is pointing at one elf holding a pencil. The background shows holiday decorations like a Christmas tree with twinkling lights, candy canes, and wrapped presents. The style is light, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the pun by blending Christmas helpers with grammar elements in a playful, non-threatening manner.'),
 (447, 'Christmas, Puns', 'What goes ''oh-oh-oh''? Santa walking backward.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Santa Claus walking backwards. Santa is in his classic red suit with white trim, black boots, and a big sack of gifts slung over his shoulder. His face has a surprised or confused expression as he looks over his shoulder while stepping backward. Above his head, three speech bubbles show the sounds ''oh-oh-oh'' to mimic the usual ''ho-ho-ho'' but reversed. The background is a snowy winter night with twinkling stars and a few decorated pine trees. The overall tone is playful and lighthearted, emphasizing the wordplay in the joke.'),
 (448, 'Animals, Christmas, Pop Culture, Puns', 'What is the Grinch''s least favorite band? The Who', NULL, 'Create a humorous cartoon scene showing the Grinch standing with a grumpy expression, crossing his arms, next to a simple cartoon stage. On the stage, depict a silhouette or iconic logo of the rock band The Who, such as a large target symbol or a figure with a guitar. The background should hint at a Whoville setting with whimsical houses and holiday decorations, but keep the focus on the Grinch’s annoyed face and the band''s symbol. The atmosphere should be lighthearted and colorful with exaggerated features for comedic effect. Include small musical notes floating around the band symbol to show it represents music. The Grinch should clearly look displeased or irritated by the presence of ''The Who.'' No other characters are needed.'),
 (449, 'Christmas, Puns', 'What kind of cars do Santa''s elves drive? Toy-otas', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing Santa''s workshop outside the North Pole. In the foreground, two small elves are happily driving tiny cars styled like classic Toyota models but clearly designed as toys — bright red and green with oversized wheels and playful details like candy cane stripes and bells. One elf waves cheerfully out the window. Nearby, a large ''Santa''s Workshop'' sign is visible with snow gently falling. In the background, a sleigh pulled by reindeer is parked beside a pile of wrapped presents. The overall tone is festive, cheerful, and whimsical, capturing the pun about ''Toy-otas'' with visual emphasis on the toy-like quality of the cars and the playful elves driving them.'),
 (450, 'Christmas, Holiday Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'What nationality is Santa Claus? North Polish', NULL, 'A cheerful, cartoon-style Santa Claus dressed in his traditional red suit with white trim stands at the North Pole. Instead of his usual rosy cheeks, Santa has a friendly, exaggerated Polish folk hat on his head (like a colorful traditional Polish cap). Behind him is a snowy signpost that reads ''North Pole'' with a small Polish flag attached. Around Santa, elves look on with amused expressions, and reindeer peek out from behind snowy trees. The scene is bright, colorful, and playful, capturing a lighthearted cultural pun without any harshness or negativity.'),
 (451, 'Christmas, Puns', 'What''s every elf''s favorite type of music? Wrap, of course.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful elf in a festive workshop setting. The elf is wearing a classic green outfit with a pointy hat and curly-toed shoes. Around the elf are colorful Christmas presents wrapped in shiny paper with big bows. The elf is joyfully DJing on a turntable made from gift-wrapping supplies—like rolls of wrapping paper, scissors, and tape dispensers. Musical notes float around him, and the word ''Wrap'' appears in playful bubble letters above. In the background, Christmas decorations like a small decorated tree, hanging ornaments, and twinkling lights create a festive atmosphere. The elf’s face shows excitement and enjoyment as if he’s really into his favorite music genre: ''wrap'' music. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the pun.'),
 (452, 'Christmas, Puns', 'What''s the difference between the Christmas alphabet and the regular alphabet? The Christmas alphabet has no-el.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene split into two panels. On the left panel, show a regular alphabet block set (like children''s toy blocks arranged A to Z) on a plain background, with bright, simple colors. On the right panel, show a Christmas-themed alphabet set where the letters are decorated with festive elements: some blocks wrapped in red and green stripes, others with holly or candy cane patterns. Highlight the letters ''N'', ''O'', and emphasize ''EL'' glowing or sparkling to indicate the pun on ''No-el'' (like ''No L''). Include a cheerful, smiling Christmas tree in the background and maybe a Santa hat resting on one of the blocks to reinforce the holiday mood. Keep the style light, playful, and suitable for a broad, family-friendly audience. The text or caption can appear above or below the panels, reading "What''s the difference between the Christmas alphabet and the regular alphabet? The Christmas alphabet has no-el."'),
 (453, 'Christmas, Holiday Humor, Puns', 'What''s the very best Christmas present you can gives someone? A broken drum - nobody can beat that!', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene featuring a Christmas living room decorated festively with a Christmas tree adorned with ornaments and a star on top. In the center, a cheerful person is handing over a wrapped gift shaped like a drum to another surprised recipient. The drum should look obviously broken — cracked shell, maybe a dent or a missing drumstick taped to the side. The recipient’s expression is a mix of confusion and amusement. Around them, subtle holiday decorations like stockings, gifts, and twinkling lights make the setting clear and warm. The style should be lighthearted, with exaggerated facial expressions and bright colors to emphasize humor without anything violent or inappropriate.'),
 (454, 'Christmas, Music Humor, Puns', 'Who is Santa''s favorite singer? Elfis.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon depicting Santa Claus standing in a cozy, festive North Pole workshop filled with Christmas decorations such as a Christmas tree, colorful lights, and wrapped presents. Santa is cheerfully listening to an elf dressed in a sparkly rockstar outfit reminiscent of Elvis Presley, complete with a pompadour hairstyle and flashy sunglasses. The elf is holding a vintage microphone and striking a classic Elvis pose with one hand in the air and one leg bent. Nearby, other elves are clapping and smiling, enjoying the performance. The setting is bright, colorful, and playful, emphasizing the holiday spirit with a fun musical twist.'),
 (455, 'Animals, Christmas, Puns', 'Why did Rudolph never go to school? He was elf-taught.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene featuring Rudolph the red-nosed reindeer standing proudly outside a small rustic schoolhouse with a big ''School'' sign above the door. Rudolph is wearing a mischievous, confident smile and has a little book open in front of him as if he’s been studying by himself. Next to him, a group of elves dressed in classic green outfits with pointy hats are looking puzzled or shrugging their shoulders. The background shows snowy ground and a few pine trees. The style is lighthearted and humorous, with exaggerated expressions and bright colors to enhance the playful pun. The focus is on Rudolph being independent and self-learning, highlighting the ''elf-taught'' wordplay with elves nearby for context.'),
 (456, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Movies, Pop Culture', 'Chuck Norris admitted to using a stunt double in one of his movies, but only for the crying part.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing proudly on a movie set. He should have a confident, tough-guy stance, wearing typical cowboy/action hero attire (boots, jeans, bandana or leather jacket). Next to him is a stunt double—a smaller, exaggeratedly sensitive-looking version of Chuck crying dramatically with tears streaming down his cheeks. The stunt double holds a tissue box and looks overly emotional. The movie set around them includes cameras, lights, and a director’s chair with a clapperboard showing the film title. Add a speech bubble above Chuck Norris that says, ''I only used a stunt double for the crying part.'' The overall art style should be lighthearted, cartoonish, and comical, emphasizing the contrast between tough Chuck and his overly emotional stunt double without any harshness or negativity.'),
 (457, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Video Games', 'Chuck Norris appeared in the ''Street Fighter II'' video game, but was removed by Beta Testers because every button caused him to do a roundhouse kick. When asked bout this ''glitch'', Chuck Norris replied, ''That''s no glitch.''', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene set inside an arcade with a classic ''Street Fighter II'' arcade game machine front and center. On the screen, a pixelated character resembling Chuck Norris is shown mid-air executing a dynamic roundhouse kick with exaggerated motion lines to emphasize the action. Nearby, a group of frustrated beta testers, cartoonishly drawn with laptops and notepads, look surprised and bewildered as every button they frantically press causes the character to kick. The arcade background includes other classic arcade machines and posters on the walls. Above everything, a speech bubble from the Chuck Norris character saying, ''That''s no glitch.'' The overall tone is playful and exaggerated, with bright colors and expressive faces to highlight the absurdity of the non-stop roundhouse kicking action.'),
 (458, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris beat the sun in a staring contest.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris and the sun engaged in a staring contest. Chuck Norris is portrayed as a confident, strong man with a slight smirk, sitting calmly in a simple armchair outdoors. The sun, anthropomorphized with a big face, eyebrows furrowed and glaring intensely, is positioned directly opposite Chuck, shining brightly with expressive eyes locked onto his. The background shows a simple blue sky with a few clouds, emphasizing the outdoor daytime setting. Both characters have exaggerated, focused eyes to highlight the intensity of the contest. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, with bright colors and playful expressions, creating a fun and absurd scene without any violence or complexity.'),
 (459, 'Chuck Norris, Puns, Tech Humor', 'Chuck Norris burst the dot com bubble.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris in his classic pose—arms crossed, stern expression, wearing a cowboy-style outfit or martial arts attire. He stands triumphantly on top of a bursting bubble labeled ''.com'' which is dramatically popping beneath him, with exaggerated comic-style burst lines and small tech-related icons (like a computer mouse, a smartphone, and website symbols) flying out from the burst bubble. The background is simplified with a city skyline or office buildings representing the tech industry. Include a few small characters or tech workers looking shocked or surprised at the bubble bursting. The overall tone is light and playful, emphasizing Chuck Norris'' legendary tough-guy image causing the tech bubble to burst through sheer force.'),
 (462, 'Chuck Norris, Good Question!, Math Humor', 'Chuck Norris can divide by zero.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon of Chuck Norris standing confidently at a large, old-fashioned chalkboard filled with complicated math equations. Chuck Norris is shown punching the air triumphantly with one fist. On the chalkboard, prominently displayed, is the equation ''1 ÷ 0 ='' with a big question mark and a spiral-like explosion of colorful mathematical symbols swirling around it, illustrating the impossible nature of dividing by zero. Chuck Norris has his iconic beard and cowboy attire, with a glint in his eye suggesting superhuman strength and calm mastery over the impossible math challenge. The setting is a classroom or a funny math competition stage with a few bewildered cartoon mathematicians or students looking on with surprised expressions. The overall style is light, exaggerated, and playful to capture the larger-than-life fictional abilities of Chuck Norris in a comical way.'),
 (460, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris can clap with one hand.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in a simple outdoor setting, such as a sunny park or plain background. Chuck Norris is drawn as a strong, iconic martial artist with his signature beard and serious expression. He is shown attempting to clap with just one hand: his palm is facing upward, fingers slightly curled, and the other hand is nowhere to be seen, emphasizing the impossible feat. To add humor, a small cloud of dust or ''clap sound'' lines are emanating from the single hand. Around him, a few amazed cartoon characters—perhaps children or onlookers—watch with wide eyes and dropped jaws to accentuate the absurdity of the joke. The style should be light-hearted, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the comedic, impossible nature of the scenario without any violence or danger.'),
 (461, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Puns', 'Chuck Norris can cook minute rice in 30 seconds.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris in a kitchen. He stands confidently next to a stove with a pot labeled ''Minute Rice'' on the burner, which has a tiny timer showing 30 seconds instead of one minute. Chuck is drawn with exaggerated tough-guy features—muscular, wearing a martial arts outfit or casual tough clothes. Around him, steam rises dramatically from the pot, creating an almost superhero-like aura. In the background, a clock on the wall grabs the viewer’s attention by clearly showing only 30 seconds passed. Add a few surprised or amazed characters watching Chuck from the side, their eyes wide and jaws dropped. The overall tone is light-hearted and comedic, with bright colors and a cartoonish style emphasizing the ridiculousness of the joke.'),
 (463, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Puns', 'Chuck Norris can do a wheelie on a unicycle.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring Chuck Norris performing an impossible stunt: doing a wheelie on a unicycle. Show Chuck in his iconic rugged look, wearing a martial arts outfit or casual tough-guy attire, with a confident expression. The unicycle should be exaggeratedly small and simple, with one large wheel. Chuck is lifting the front part of the unicycle up high, balancing effortlessly on the rear wheel only, displaying a sense of motion and balance. The background can be a simple outdoor park or street scene to keep focus on the stunt, with maybe a few surprised or amazed onlookers in the distance reacting with wide eyes and open mouths in comic amazement. Use bright, bold colors and clean lines to emphasize the cartoon style, and possibly add a small dust cloud or speed lines near the wheel to suggest movement and energy, enhancing the absurdity of the trick.'),
 (464, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Puns', 'Chuck Norris can dribble a bowling ball.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently on a bowling alley lane. He is mid-dribble, bouncing a giant, shiny bowling ball like a basketball. Chuck Norris is drawn with exaggerated muscles, wearing casual martial arts attire with a black belt, and his iconic beard and stern expression. The background shows bowling pins waiting at the end of the lane, with a few spectators in the stands looking amazed or bewildered. The bowling ball is oversized compared to a regular basketball, adding to the absurdity. The scene should capture a playful and exaggerated atmosphere with bright colors and dynamic motion lines emphasizing the dribbling action.'),
 (465, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris can get in a bucket and lift it up with himself in it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing Chuck Norris, depicted as a strong, confident man with his iconic beard and intense stare, inside a large metal bucket. The bucket is being lifted off the ground, held firmly by Chuck Norris himself, who is gripping the rim with both hands from inside. The setting is simple, with a plain light-colored background to keep focus on the scene. Chuck Norris is smiling slightly, showing his effortless strength. The bucket should look like an ordinary large bucket, big enough to fit a person, and the drawing style should be bold and colorful, emphasizing exaggerated cartoon features to add humor and charm.'),
 (466, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Word Play', 'Chuck Norris can have both feet on the ground and kick butt at the same time.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently with both feet firmly planted on solid ground, but with a dynamic action pose that shows him simultaneously delivering a powerful kick with one leg. Show a comic-style ''kick butt'' effect, such as an exaggerated burst or impact cloud near his foot, emphasizing the contradictory feat of standing still and kicking fiercely at the same time. The background should be simple, perhaps a plain outdoor scene with a few rocks or grass to emphasize his grounded stance. Illustrate Chuck Norris with his iconic beard and serious facial expression. The overall style should be bright, colorful, and exaggerated for comedic effect, reminiscent of a fun comic strip or superhero cartoon.'),
 (467, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Chuck Norris', 'Chuck Norris can kill two stones with one bird.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in a rugged outdoor setting. He is in mid-action, throwing a small colorful bird with exaggerated motion lines flying from his hand. Nearby, two smooth, round stones are placed close together on the ground, and one stone shows a tiny shocked face while the other looks surprised, as if about to be affected by the bird. Chuck Norris has a determined, calm expression, wearing his signature martial artist outfit or casual tough-guy clothes. The background should be simple with a hint of nature: a few trees, some grass, and a clear sky. The style should be bright, cheerful, and exaggerated for comedic effect, like a classic cartoon. Include a small comic-style text bubble near Chuck saying something like “Watch this!” to emphasize the joke''s punchline. The scene must avoid any violence, showing a playful, absurd interpretation of the phrase.'),
 (468, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris can make a slinky go upstairs.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing at the bottom of a staircase in a casual but confident pose, with his iconic beard and cowboy boots. In front of him, a colorful metal slinky is stretched out and animatedly climbing the stairs on its own, defying gravity. The staircase is indoors, simple with carpeted steps, and there is a surprised cartoon character (maybe a bystander with a shocked expression and raised eyebrows) watching the slinky''s impossible upward movement. The atmosphere is light and funny, emphasizing the absurdity of the slinky going upstairs because of Chuck Norris’s legendary tough persona. Bright colors and exaggerated expressions enhance the comedic effect.'),
 (469, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris can slam a revolving door.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing Chuck Norris, a muscular man with a confident expression and iconic beard, standing next to a revolving door. The revolving door is depicted as a typical glass and metal entrance to a building, but humorously it appears to be stopped mid-spin with exaggerated motion lines showing it trying to turn. Chuck Norris is posed in mid-action, one hand open and pressing firmly against the revolving door panel like he''s about to slam it shut, with comic-style impact effects like “BAM!” or “SLAM!” around the door. Around him, bystanders look surprised or amazed. The scene should have bright, cheerful colors and exaggerated features to emphasize the impossibility and humor of slamming a revolving door. No violence, just playful exaggeration of Chuck Norris’s legendary strength and abilities.'),
 (470, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris can sneeze with his eyes open.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a muscular, serious-looking Chuck Norris standing confidently in the center of the frame. His head is tilted slightly back as he is mid-sneeze, with his mouth open and eyes wide open, clearly not blinking or closing his eyes despite the sneeze. Around him, various cartoon-style motion lines emphasize the force of the sneeze. Nearby, some small objects like cups or papers shake or flutter as if affected by the sneeze''s power. The background is simple and colorful, keeping the focus on Chuck Norris and the exaggerated sneeze action. The style is lighthearted and fun, capturing the joke''s absurdity in a playful way without any violence or political references.'),
 (471, 'Bad Puns, Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris can start a fire with an ice cube.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in the center. He is holding a small, clear, shiny ice cube in one hand, with a playful smirk on his face. In front of him, a small campfire ignites instantly, with bright, warm orange and yellow flames licking upward from the ice cube itself, despite the obvious contradiction. Around him are symbolic outdoor elements like a simple log bench, a few rocks forming a campfire circle, and a backdrop of trees or a wilderness area to suggest a camping setting. Chuck is drawn with exaggerated strong features and a rugged look—mustache, bandana, and a cowboy-style shirt—to accentuate the classic Chuck Norris meme vibe. The style should be colorful, cheerful, and in a lighthearted cartoon style, emphasizing the impossible nature of starting a fire with ice, making the scene amusing and exaggerated without any danger or negativity.'),
 (472, 'Chuck Norris, Good Question!, Humor', 'Chuck Norris can tie his shoes with his feet.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon-style drawing showing Chuck Norris sitting on the ground with a confident smirk. His legs are crossed in front of him, and both of his feet are up near his hands, each foot tying the laces of a sneaker on the opposite foot. The shoes are classic sneakers with visible untied laces, mid-tying. Around him, subtle action lines emphasize his skill and balance. The background is simple and clean to keep focus on the character. Chuck Norris is depicted with his iconic beard and hairstyle, wearing casual clothes like a plain T-shirt and jeans. The overall tone is lighthearted, showcasing the absurd idea of someone being able to tie shoes with their feet in a funny and exaggerated manner.'),
 (473, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Puns', 'Chuck Norris can unscramble an egg.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in a kitchen, wearing a black martial arts gi with his signature beard and hair. In front of him on the table is a large, transparent egg shell that looks cracked and scrambled inside with its yolk and whites visibly flying around. Chuck is calmly holding a pair of chopsticks or a small knife, skillfully putting the flying scrambled egg contents back together into a whole, perfectly intact egg. The kitchen background is simple and bright, with a few cooking utensils and a frying pan on the stove. Several small cartoon-style sparks or magical swirls emanate around Chuck''s hands to emphasize his superhuman, almost magical ability. The overall style is light-hearted and exaggerated for comedic effect, highlighting the impossible ''unscrambling'' feat as a unique Chuck Norris power without any violence or negative imagery.'),
 (474, 'Chuck Norris, Good Question!, Humor', 'Chuck Norris counted to infinity... twice.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris standing confidently with arms crossed and a smirk on his face. Behind him is a giant, swirling infinite loop symbol (∞) glowing brightly, representing infinity. To emphasize the joke, have two identical infinite loop symbols side by side floating above his head, indicating he counted infinity twice. The background is simple and playful with stars or sparkles to add a legendary vibe. Chuck Norris should be drawn in a classic action-hero style, with a martial arts outfit or casual tough-guy clothes, and exaggerated facial hair to make him instantly recognizable. The overall tone is light-hearted and exaggerated, capturing an impossible feat done with effortless coolness.'),
 (475, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris does not get frostbite. Chuck Norris bites frost.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in a snowy, icy landscape. He is wearing a casual outfit with rolled-up sleeves and a determined expression. In front of him is a large, cartoonish frost monster or icicle creature, which looks surprised and a bit scared as Chuck reaches out and bites it with exaggerated teeth. Snowflakes fall gently around, and the chilly environment is emphasized by frosty breath and icy details on the ground. The overall style is playful and exaggerated, with bright colors and bold outlines to emphasize the absurdity of Chuck Norris biting frost instead of getting frostbite himself.'),
 (476, 'Bad Puns, Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris does not hunt because the word hunting implies the possibility of failure. Chuck Norris goes killing.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in a rugged outdoor setting. He is muscular and wearing a cowboy hat, with a serious but slightly exaggerated determined expression. Around him are scattered hunting gear like a bow, rifle, and a camouflage backpack lying unused on the ground. In the background, instead of animals hiding or running, cartoon animals (like a deer, rabbit, and boar) are cartoonishly scared and fleeing in all directions. The caption or a thought bubble above Chuck Norris reads, ''I don''t hunt... I go killing.'' The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing Chuck Norris''s legendary tough persona without any violence shown explicitly. Draw in a colorful, clean cartoon style with exaggerated expressions and dynamic motion lines to show the fleeing animals'' panic.'),
 (477, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris does not sleep. He waits.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon featuring Chuck Norris as a tough, rugged man sitting calmly in a simple armchair. The room is dimly lit like a typical living room with a clock on the wall showing a late hour. Chuck Norris is wide awake, eyes open and alert, with a slight smirk. Instead of lying in bed, he is patiently waiting with crossed arms and legs, radiating calm confidence. Around him, objects like a sleeping bag or a bed stand unused and lonely, emphasizing that he does not sleep. The style is bold, colorful, and exaggerated to capture the humorous essence of Chuck Norris''s legendary toughness and stoicism.'),
 (478, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris doesn’t turn on the shower. He stares at it until it starts to cry.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in a simple bathroom. He is a muscular man with a stern expression, arms crossed, and a slightly intimidating aura. In front of him is a shower with water droplets transforming into animated cartoon tears running down its glass door and a sad face on the showerhead or glass, as if it’s crying. The bathroom is minimalistic but clearly a shower stall with a shower curtain or glass panel. The lighting highlights Chuck Norris’s serious stare directed at the shower. The overall style is light-hearted and exaggerated, emphasizing the joke that the shower starts to cry rather than turning on.'),
 (479, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris doesn''t do pushups, he pushes the Earth down.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris in mid-pushup position outdoors, with a confident, almost nonchalant expression. Instead of the usual floor beneath him, the Earth is depicted as a small globe being pushed down slightly by his hands. The globe looks like a classic Earth with blue oceans and green continents. Around him are exaggerated motion lines showing the Earth being pushed down with great force. The background is simple, perhaps a bright sky with a few clouds. Chuck Norris is drawn in an exaggerated heroic style, wearing a simple t-shirt and jeans, with a subtle smirk. The scene is lighthearted and funny, emphasizing the absurdity of the punchline without any violence or tension.'),
 (480, 'Chuck Norris, Programming, Puns', 'Chuck Norris doesn''t need garbage collection because he doesn''t call.Dispose() - he calls.DropKick().', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple, colorful computer programming office. In the center, a bold and confident cartoon character styled as Chuck Norris stands with crossed arms and a tough expression. Around him are floating computer code snippets and a large trash bin labeled ''Garbage Collection''. On one side, a confused-looking programmer wearing glasses is holding a laptop showing code with ''.Dispose()'' method. Chuck Norris points his finger dramatically toward the trash bin as if demonstrating, while the trash bin humorously shows action lines as if it’s about to be ''kick-dropped'' out of the scene. The style should be light-hearted and exaggerated, with comic-style motion lines and expressive faces, emphasizing the joke about Chuck Norris replacing a technical programming method with a kick. The background should be a bright office with desks, computers, and some programming posters on the wall to reinforce the tech atmosphere.'),
 (481, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris doesn''t need to shave - his beard is scared to grow.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently with a slight smirk on his face. His beard is patchy and sparse, with tiny expressive eyes and a scared expression, looking nervously sideways or shrinking back as if intimidated. Show a close-up of Chuck''s face where the beard appears almost alive, cowering or slinking away. The background is simple and light-hearted, like a plain color or a subtle dojo setting to hint at Chuck’s martial arts persona. Make the overall style playful and exaggerated, emphasizing the beard''s ''fear'' humorously, without any violence or aggression.'),
 (482, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris doesn''t turn on the shower. He stares at it until it starts to cry.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing in a bathroom. Chuck is depicted with his iconic beard and stern, intense gaze directed at a classic showerhead mounted on the wall. The showerhead has animated, teardrop-shaped water droplets falling from it, looking like it''s crying. The bathroom setting is simple with tiles on the walls, a shower curtain slightly pulled back, and a soap dish. Chuck stands confidently with his arms crossed or hands on hips, giving the impression that his powerful stare alone is causing the shower to ''cry'' water. The overall style is lighthearted and exaggerated to emphasize the joke''s humor without any violence or aggression.'),
 (483, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris doesn''t wear a watch. He decides what time it is.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in the center. He is depicted with a tough, determined expression, wearing casual clothes but notably without any watch on his wrists. Around him, multiple clocks on a wall show different times, but Chuck is pointing with his thumb over his shoulder at no particular clock, as if commanding the time itself. The background is simple and brightly colored to highlight Chuck as the focus. Include a few exaggerated visual elements like sparkles or glowing lines around Chuck''s finger to emphasize his power to decide the time. The overall style is lighthearted and comedic, with bold outlines and exaggerated features typical of funny cartoons.'),
 (484, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Pop Culture', 'Chuck Norris'' email address is gmail@chucknorris.com', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in the center. He is drawn in a classic tough-guy pose with a slight smirk, wearing his iconic black outfit and clenched fists. Floating prominently in front of him is a large, stylized email envelope icon with the email address text: ''gmail@chucknorris.com'' in bold letters. The background is simple and clean, with a computer or a laptop on a nearby desk displaying an open email client. The atmosphere is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the joke about Chuck Norris having the most straightforward, no-nonsense email address. The style is colorful and exaggerated, typical of fun cartoon humor without any violence or political elements.'),
 (485, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris has a mug of nails instead of coffee in the morning.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris sitting at a kitchen table in the morning. Instead of a normal coffee mug, he is holding a large mug filled with shiny metal nails sticking out of the top. Chuck Norris has a serious, unfazed expression, with a slight smirk. Around him, typical breakfast items are on the table like a plate with toast and a newspaper, but the focus is on the mug. The background shows a cozy kitchen with a window letting in sunlight, adding warmth to the scene. The style is bright and colorful, exaggerated slightly for comic effect, with bold lines and simple shading to emphasize the joke that Chuck Norris’s morning ''coffee'' is as tough as him.'),
 (486, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris has never blinked in his entire life. Never.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently center frame. He has his trademark beard and intense gaze, with eyes wide open and unblinking. Around him, exaggerated flying dust particles or small objects aim toward his face as if testing whether he blinks, but he remains completely still and unfazed. The background is simple with a light gradient and some comic-style lines emphasizing his unblinking stare. The overall style is bold, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the joke''s hyperbolic nature, with a caption bubble or banner above Chuck reading: "Chuck Norris has NEVER blinked." The tone is light-hearted and playful, with no violence or intensity, just comic exaggeration.'),
 (487, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris is the only man to ever defeat a brick wall in a game of tennis.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris on one side of a tennis court, holding a tennis racket and looking confident and heroic. On the other side, instead of a human opponent, there is a large brick wall standing upright, with a quirky expression—eyebrows furrowed, eyes narrowed, and maybe even a sweat drop to show struggle. Tennis balls are flying back and forth between Chuck and the wall. The background should be a simple outdoor tennis court with a net in the middle. The style is exaggerated and playful, with bold outlines and bright colors, capturing the ridiculousness of a man competing against a brick wall.'),
 (488, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris is the only man who can fight himself and win.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris in a split image style: on one side, Chuck Norris stands in a classic martial arts fighting stance, looking fierce and confident. On the opposite side, an identical Chuck Norris mirror image is in a fighting stance matching the first, as if they are about to battle each other. The background is simple with a dojo or training mat floor. Between them, cartoon action lines and comic-style impact effects indicate an intense face-off. Chuck Norris’s expressions show determination and slight smirks, emphasizing that he’s fully in control and winning. The scene is lighthearted and exaggerated, with no violence shown, just the concept of him fighting himself.'),
 (489, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris is the only person that can punch a cyclops between the eye.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently and smiling, his fist extended forward as if mid-punch. In front of him is a large, comical cyclops with one giant central eye staring straight ahead. The cyclops is wearing a surprised expression, wincing slightly as if just got punched right in the middle of its eye. The background is simple and lighthearted, maybe an open field or a dojo setting to keep focus on the characters. The cyclops is exaggerated with a big round head, one large eyeball in the center, and oversized hands. Chuck Norris should look cool and calm, sporting his iconic beard and martial arts attire or plain clothes that hint at toughness. The style is bright, colorful, and playful, typical of a cartoon, with bold outlines and expressive faces to emphasize humor and absurdity of the scene.'),
 (490, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Pop Culture', 'Chuck Norris is the reason why Waldo is hiding.', NULL, 'A vibrant, humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently with his signature beard and martial arts outfit. He is looking directly at the viewer with a slight smirk. Nearby, a character resembling Waldo from ''Where''s Waldo?'' is peeking nervously from behind a large tree, partially hidden, clearly trying to avoid Chuck Norris. The background is a colorful park or forest setting full of bushes and trees to emphasize hiding spots. Waldo’s classic red-and-white striped shirt and glasses make him easily recognizable. The tone is light and playful, with exaggerated expressions on both characters: Chuck Norris looks intimidating but comedic, while Waldo looks comically fearful. Add a few small details like a magnifying glass or a ‘Where’s Waldo’ book resting on the ground to hint at the classic search game. The overall style should be a funny, clean cartoon with bold lines and bright colors, suitable for all ages.'),
 (491, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Pop Culture', 'Chuck Norris knows Victoria''s secret.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently with his arms crossed and a slight smirk. He is positioned in front of a door labeled ''Victoria''s Secret'' with an exaggerated sparkling glow coming from behind the door to emphasize the ''secret.'' Nearby, amused onlookers like a few cartoon men and women are peeking at him with wide eyes and surprised expressions. The background should be simple, perhaps with a subtle hint of a lingerie boutique sign or display nearby, to set the context. The style is light and playful, with bold outlines and vibrant colors, emphasizing the humor and legendary toughness associated with Chuck Norris without implying anything inappropriate or serious.'),
 (492, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris made a Happy Meal cry.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small, classic Happy Meal box from a popular fast food chain with a scared, teary-eyed face on the front. The box is personified with big cartoon eyes and a mouth trembling in fear, with tears streaming down the sides. Standing next to the Happy Meal is a larger-than-life, exaggerated caricature of Chuck Norris in a tough martial arts pose, wearing his iconic beard and karate gi, with an intense and confident expression. The background is simple, perhaps a fast food restaurant or playground setting, but the focus is on the contrast between the intimidating Chuck Norris figure and the crying Happy Meal. The overall tone is playful and lighthearted, using exaggerated facial expressions and poses to emphasize the joke without anything violent or aggressive depicted directly.'),
 (493, 'Animals, Chuck Norris, Puns', 'Chuck Norris makes onions cry.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in the center, with a big, tough grin on his face. Around him are several onions, anthropomorphized with cartoon eyes and teardrops streaming down their cheeks, clearly crying. The onions should look cute and exaggerated, with small faces expressing sadness or fear. Chuck Norris can be shown with his signature beard and martial arts attire, maybe with his arms crossed or performing a classic roundhouse kick. The background is simple—a kitchen counter or garden setting to hint where onions grow or are prepared. Bright, bold colors and clean lines keep the image lighthearted and fun with no violence, just the idea that Chuck Norris’s presence alone causes onions to cry, flipping the usual concept of onions making humans cry on its head.'),
 (494, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris never retreats; he just attacks in the opposite direction.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing Chuck Norris in a confident martial arts stance on a battlefield. There are two arrows pointing forward to indicate an attack direction but Chuck Norris is shown with a smirk, turning and kicking energetically in the exact opposite direction of the arrows. The background should be playful and exaggerated with dust clouds or motion lines emphasizing speed and power. Nearby, a confused group of generic soldiers or opponents watch in bewilderment. Make sure the characters have exaggerated, expressive cartoon faces to highlight the humor and absurdity of attacking by going backwards.'),
 (495, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris once bowled a perfect game with a marble.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently on a bowling lane. Instead of a regular bowling ball, he is holding a small shiny marble about the size of a marble game piece. The pins at the end of the lane are toppling dramatically, falling down in perfect alignment as if hit by an invisible force. Chuck Norris has a calm, slightly smug expression with his arms crossed or one hand holding the marble. The bowling alley is brightly lit with a scoreboard above displaying a perfect score of 300. Around him, a few surprised spectators with exaggerated shocked and amazed expressions are watching. The overall tone is light and humorous, with exaggerated cartoonish features and vibrant colors.'),
 (496, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris once had a heart attack. His heart lost.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris as a muscular, confident action hero standing victoriously in the center. Nearby, his heart is depicted as a small, cartoonish pink heart character lying on the ground with a defeated, dazed expression — possibly with little cartoon stars circling its head to indicate it lost the fight. Chuck Norris strikes a triumphant pose with fists on hips and a slight smirk. The background is simple and focused on emphasizing the funny battle between Chuck Norris and his heart. Use bright colors and bold lines for a playful, lighthearted comic style. Include a small caption or speech bubble near Chuck saying something like ''Winner!'' for visual humor.'),
 (497, 'Animals, Chuck Norris, Exaggeration', 'Chuck Norris once kicked a horse in the chin. Its descendants are now known as giraffes.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently in a cowboy outfit with one leg raised as if he just delivered a powerful side kick. Nearby, a bewildered horse is humorously stretched upward with an extremely long neck, resembling a giraffe. The background includes a simple ranch setting with a wooden fence and some green grass. The horse-turned-giraffe looks surprised and slightly confused, emphasizing the absurdity of the joke. The style should be playful and exaggerated, with bright colors and clear, bold outlines to enhance the humor.'),
 (498, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris once roundhouse kicked someone so hard that his foot broke the speed of light', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing in a classic martial arts pose with one leg extended mid-roundhouse kick. His expression is fierce but exaggeratedly confident. The background shows a blurred streak representing the broken sound barrier and a glowing trail illustrating the foot surpassing the speed of light, depicted as a colorful light beam shooting forward. Nearby, a surprised cartoon character is flying backward with exaggerated motion lines, eyes wide and mouth open in shock. The setting is simple with no violence, just dynamic action lines and comic effects emphasizing immense speed and power. The overall tone is lighthearted and exaggerated, capturing a superhuman feat humorously.'),
 (499, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris once shot an enemy plane down with his finger, by yelling, ''Bang!''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon depicting Chuck Norris standing confidently on the ground with a stern, focused expression. He is pointing his index finger straight ahead like a gun, and from his mouth comes a bold comic-style speech bubble that says, ''Bang!''. In front of him, high in the sky, a cartoonish enemy plane appears to be dramatically falling out of control, with smoke trailing and its nose pointed downward. The background shows a clear blue sky with a few fluffy clouds. The style is exaggerated and playful, emphasizing Chuck Norris’ legendary toughness and the absurdity of shooting down a plane just by yelling.'),
 (500, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Chuck Norris once told a woman to calm down and she did', NULL, 'A cartoon scene with a large, tough-looking Chuck Norris character standing confidently with his arms crossed and a slight smirk. Facing him is a woman who looks visibly upset but is taking a deep breath, calming down noticeably. The setting is simple and humorous, maybe a park bench or a neutral background to keep the focus on the characters. Chuck Norris has exaggerated muscles and a cowboy-style outfit. The woman should appear surprised by her own calmness, with a small, relieved smile forming. The style is light-hearted, exaggerated, and cartoonish, making the intensity of Chuck Norris comically powerful but friendly.'),
 (501, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris once went skydiving, but promised never to do it again. One Grand Canyon is enough.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris mid-air during a skydive. Show him with a confident, stoic expression wearing a jumpsuit and goggles, free-falling against a dramatic backdrop of the Grand Canyon below. Emphasize the canyon''s vast depth and recognizable red rock formations for clarity. Include a speech bubble above Chuck Norris that reads: ''One Grand Canyon is enough.'' Optionally, depict a tiny parachute just beginning to deploy or humorously absent to reinforce the joke. The style should be lighthearted and exaggerated, with bright colors and bold outlines, capturing a playful tone without any violence or danger.'),
 (502, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris once won a game of Connect Four in three moves.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris sitting confidently at a small game table, with a bright aura of exaggerated toughness around him. On the table is a Connect Four vertical grid, where only three colorful game pieces have been placed by Chuck, already forming a winning line. Around him, three stunned and exaggeratedly shocked opponents, one dropping their game piece in disbelief, another holding their head, and the third with wide eyes and mouth agape. The background is simple, emphasizing the game and the characters, using vibrant colors and exaggerated facial expressions to amplify the humor. A small scoreboard nearby shows ''Moves: 3'' in bold letters. The scene should capture an epic, almost superhero-like vibe about an absurdly fast victory in what is normally a slow-paced game, making clear the joke about Chuck Norris'' legendary abilities, all depicted in a playful, non-violent manner.'),
 (503, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris once won an arm wrestling tournament with both arms tied behind his back.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris sitting at a small arm wrestling table, grinning confidently. Both his arms are securely tied behind his back with thick ropes, clearly visible to the viewer. Across the table sits a surprised opponent, straining hard to win but clearly overwhelmed. The setting is a simple tournament room with a few spectators in the background, some with jaws dropped or hands on cheeks in disbelief. The overall style is exaggerated and playful, emphasizing the impossible feat with exaggerated facial expressions and a light-hearted atmosphere.'),
 (504, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris'' tears cure cancer. Too bad he has never cried.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon depicting Chuck Norris standing confidently in the center with a big, stern expression and arms crossed. Around him, glowing, sparkling teardrops hang in midair, shimmering as if magical, labeled ''Cure for Cancer'' in small text. The background shows a cheerful, sunny environment with flowers and a few mysterious broken bottles labeled ''Medicine'' on the ground to add humor. To emphasize the joke, a small speech bubble from Chuck Norris says, ''I never cry.'' The overall vibe should be lighthearted, with exaggerated cartoonish features and bright colors to highlight the joke''s fantastical nature.'),
 (505, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Pop Culture', 'Chuck Norris tells Simon what to do.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris and Simon Cowell on a simple stage or spotlighted area. Chuck Norris stands confidently with a stern but calm expression, dressed in his iconic martial arts outfit or casual tough-guy clothes, pointing a finger authoritatively at Simon Cowell. Simon Cowell looks surprised, slightly confused, and a little intimidated, holding one hand up as if unsure how to respond. The background is minimal, perhaps with a few stylized stars or comic action lines around Chuck to emphasize his commanding presence. The style is light-hearted and exaggerated, with friendly cartoonish proportions and bright colors, focusing on the humorous role reversal of Chuck Norris, known for his domineering pop-culture persona, telling the usually authoritative Simon what to do.'),
 (506, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Chuck Norris used to beat up his shadow because it was following to close. It now stands 15 feet behind him.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris walking outside on a sunny day with a confident, tough guy expression. He is in casual clothes, maybe a denim jacket and jeans, fists clenched in a playful fighting stance. Behind him, his shadow is exaggeratedly far back — about 15 feet behind him instead of right at his feet as shadows normally are. The shadow looks scared or intimidated, with cartoonish wide eyes and a small sweat drop, peeking around nervously as if trying to stay as far away as possible. The setting is a simple outdoor sidewalk with some trees and grass. The overall style is bright and colorful with exaggerated expressions highlighting humor and the absurdity of a shadow standing so far behind its owner.'),
 (507, 'Chuck Norris, Coronavirus, Humor', 'Chuck Norris was exposed to COVID, and the virus was in quarantine for a month.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris standing confidently with his arms crossed and a serious look on his face. Around him, a group of tiny, cartoonish virus characters wearing face masks and looking frightened or sad are trapped inside a transparent quarantine box or cage labeled ''Quarantine''. The box is placed near Chuck Norris, emphasizing that the virus is held captive and isolated because of him. The background is simple, with maybe a few stars or comic-style action lines radiating from Chuck to highlight his toughness. The overall style is light, colorful, and exaggerated, suitable for a fun, family-friendly cartoon.'),
 (508, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Programming', 'Chuck Norris writes code that optimizes itself.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris sitting confidently at a computer desk. The room is a simple programmer''s workspace with a monitor displaying lines of glowing green code that seem to be moving and rewriting themselves autonomously without any keyboard input. Chuck Norris is relaxed, leaning back in his chair with a calm, almost bored expression, one hand casually resting on the desk and the other holding a coffee mug. The background includes typical programming decor: a coffee cup, sticky notes with coding jokes, and a few tech-related posters. The overall tone is light and funny, emphasizing the impossible power of Chuck Norris making code optimize itself magically, without any effort on his part.'),
 (509, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Puns', 'Chuck Norris''s belly button is actually a power outlet.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon of Chuck Norris standing confidently with his shirt slightly lifted to reveal his belly button. Instead of a normal belly button, show a classic power outlet embedded on his belly with two vertical slots and a round grounding hole. Sparks or light rays can humorously emit from the outlet to emphasize energy or power. Chuck Norris should have a serious, tough expression, iconic beard and hair, and a martial arts outfit or casual clothes to make him easily recognizable. The background should be simple, maybe a plain color or a subtle burst effect to highlight the power outlet belly button as the focal point. No violence or weapons; the tone is playful and exaggerated superhero-style humor.'),
 (510, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Death once had a near-Chuck-Norris experience.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring Death personified as the Grim Reaper, complete with a black hooded cloak and a scythe. He should look surprised and a bit intimidated, with wide eyes and raised eyebrows, stepping back slightly. Opposite him stands a chiseled, larger-than-life Chuck Norris character in a confident martial arts stance, perhaps with a slight smirk, wearing his iconic beard, cowboy boots, and a karate gi or casual clothes emphasizing toughness. The background should be simple, like a neutral color or with subtle action lines to emphasize the confrontation. Add a small speech bubble above Death saying, ''Wait, what?!'' to enhance the humor. The overall style should be playful and exaggerated to emphasize the joke’s funny reversal of roles.'),
 (511, 'Chuck Norris, Horror Humor, Humor, Pop Culture', 'Freddy Krueger has nightmares about Chuck Norris.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a dark, spooky bedroom with Freddy Krueger lying in bed, eyes wide open and clearly terrified. Freddy, recognizable by his iconic striped red-and-green sweater, brown fedora, and bladed glove, is clutching his blanket tightly. Above him, thought bubbles show an intimidating and exaggeratedly tough Chuck Norris, posed in a classic martial arts stance with a stern expression. The room is decorated with typical scary elements like cobwebs, a creaky wooden floor, and moonlight casting eerie shadows. Freddy''s bed is styled like a horror-themed bed but with a comedic twist, such as a ‘Nightmare on Elm Street’ poster on the wall with Freddy looking worried. Chuck Norris appears larger-than-life in the thought bubble, almost superhero-like, to emphasize the joke that Freddy, the master of nightmares, is the one who actually fears Chuck Norris. The overall style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions to evoke humor rather than fear.'),
 (512, 'Camping, Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Ghosts tell Chuck Norris stories around the campfire.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at night in a forest clearing around a glowing campfire. Several friendly, translucent ghosts with exaggerated, playful expressions sit in a circle, each with wavy, ethereal bodies and floating slightly above the ground. In the center, one ghost animatedly gestures as if telling an exciting story. Nearby, the iconic figure of Chuck Norris stands confidently, wearing his classic martial arts outfit, with a subtle, amused smile. The background includes tall trees and a moonlit sky with a few stars. The campfire has small logs arranged in a circle, and there''s a light smoke trail rising. The overall mood is lighthearted and funny, capturing the idea that even ghosts tell tales about Chuck Norris around the campfire.'),
 (513, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor, Pop Culture', 'If paper beats rock, rock beats scissors, and scissors beats paper, what beats all 3 at the same time? Chuck Norris.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in a simple, colorful style. Show three oversized objects on a table or platform: a crumpled sheet of paper, a jagged rock, and a pair of shiny scissors arranged in a circle to represent the classic rock-paper-scissors game. In the center, draw a larger-than-life, cartoonish Chuck Norris character standing confidently with a bold stance, wearing a martial arts gi and a black belt. His expression should be calm but imposing, with a slight smirk. Around him, add comedic motion lines or glow to emphasize power and invincibility. The background should be minimal and bright, keeping the focus on the game objects and Chuck Norris. Ensure the scene is lighthearted, fun, and clearly references the iconic martial artist as the unbeatable force who can beat all three items at once.'),
 (514, 'Animals, Chuck Norris, Exaggeration', 'If you want a list of Chuck Norris'' enemies, just check the extinct species list.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris standing confidently in the center with his arms crossed and a serious expression. Around him are several extinct animals like a dodo bird, a woolly mammoth, a saber-toothed tiger, and a dinosaur, looking defeated or scared. In the background, a large open book titled ''Extinct Species List'' is propped up on a stand, with a page clearly showing pictures or sketches of these creatures. The setting is bright and colorful, with exaggerated cartoon features, comical expressions on the animals, and a light-hearted tone to emphasize the joke that Chuck Norris is responsible for extinction of species.'),
 (515, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'In Pamplona, Spain, the people may be running from the bulls, but the bulls are running from Chuck Norris.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a sunny street in Pamplona, Spain, during the famous Running of the Bulls festival. Show a crowd of panicked people frantically running forward, faces wide-eyed and expressions of fear. Behind them, instead of bulls chasing the runners, depict several large bulls sprinting away in a comical, exaggerated frightened manner with sweating brows and scared eyes. The focus is on a confident, muscular Chuck Norris character leading the bulls, walking calmly and coolly with sunglasses on and a slight smirk. The bulls are clearly running away from him, looking back nervously. Include traditional Pamplona architecture in the background, like old stone buildings and banners. The overall style should be bright, cartoonish, and humorous, emphasizing the role reversal between bulls and people for a lighthearted and playful vibe.'),
 (516, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'It takes Chuck Norris 20 minutes to watch 60 Minutes.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring Chuck Norris sitting comfortably in a living room armchair with a large TV remote in one hand. The TV screen prominently shows the logo of the news magazine show ''60 Minutes'' (a simple clock face with the words ''60 Minutes''). Around Chuck Norris, include a visible clock on the wall showing 20 minutes passing. Exaggerate Chuck Norris’s confident, calm expression as if he’s unaffected by normal time constraints. Emphasize the contrast between the title ''60 Minutes'' on the TV and the much shorter 20-minute time span indicated by the clock. The style should be colorful and playful, with bold outlines and expressive exaggeration, like a classic cartoon about superhuman abilities. No violent or aggressive elements, just a lighthearted, slightly ironic tone highlighting the joke about Chuck Norris’s legendary toughness and speed.'),
 (517, 'Chuck Norris, Good Question!, Humor, Pop Culture', 'On the day the man who invented the telephone got home He had five missed calls from Chuck Norris', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a vintage setting with a man dressed in old-fashioned 19th-century clothes, standing at the doorstep of his quaint home holding an early model of a telephone. The man looks surprised and slightly overwhelmed as he looks at the device, which is ringing relentlessly with flashing icons representing five missed calls. Above or beside him, a tough, cartoonish Chuck Norris character stands confidently with crossed arms, wearing cowboy attire with a determined expression, as if daring or jokingly intimidating. The background shows a simple, cozy house facade with a wooden door and a mailbox. The overall mood is playful and lighthearted, emphasizing the contrast between the historical inventor and the modern, legendary figure of Chuck Norris.'),
 (518, 'Animals, Chuck Norris, Exaggeration', 'Once time a cobra bit Chuck Norris. After five days of excruciating pain, the cobra died.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Chuck Norris standing calmly and confidently, arms crossed, with a slight smirk on his face. Nearby, a cobra lies on its back with X''s over its eyes, clearly defeated and cartoonishly exaggerated to show it has ''died.'' The cobra shows signs of weakness like limp coils and a small sweat drop. Chuck Norris is depicted as a tough, muscular man wearing casual clothes with a martial arts vibe (e.g., a black belt or simple shirt and jeans). The background is simple and bright, maybe a desert or jungle edge to imply the cobra''s habitat. There could be a small clock or calendar page showing ''5 days later'' to emphasize the time element of the joke. Overall, the style is lighthearted, colorful, and playful, capturing the absurdity and exaggeration of the joke without any violence or threat.'),
 (519, 'Chuck Norris, Good Question!, Humor, Pop Culture', 'Superman owns a pair of Chuck Norris undies.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing Superman standing proudly with his iconic red cape and blue suit. The focus is on his underwear area, where a flashy, oversized pair of white briefs is visible over his pants. These briefs have a bold, exaggerated ''Chuck Norris'' label on the waistband, making it clear they belong to Chuck Norris. Superman has a confident, slightly amused expression. Next to him stands a cartoonish Chuck Norris character, arms crossed with a stoic look, wearing his signature beard and casual clothes. The setting is simple—a bright, colorful cityscape background with a few skyscrapers and a clear blue sky, emphasizing the superhero context humorously. The style is playful and vibrant, with exaggerated expressions and clear text on the underwear waistband for comedic effect.'),
 (520, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'The dark is afraid of Chuck Norris.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a scene at night with a pitch-black shadowy darkness personified as a large, spooky, but comically scared figure with wide eyes and trembling. Facing it is Chuck Norris in his classic stoic martial arts pose, looking confident and unbothered. The darkness figure is shrinking back nervously, perhaps sweating or with cartoonish trembling lines around it. The background has a starry night sky and a simple landscape like a field or empty street to emphasize the night setting. The overall style is light-hearted and exaggerated to capture the funny contrast between Chuck Norris’s legendary toughness and the usually scary darkness being scared.'),
 (521, 'Animals, Chuck Norris, Exaggeration', 'The dinosaurs looked at Chuck Norris the wrong way once. You know what happened to them.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene showing a group of dinosaurs, including a T-Rex, Triceratops, and Stegosaurus, looking confused and a bit worried. They are standing in a prehistoric landscape with volcanoes and palm trees in the background. In front of them stands a muscular, confident Chuck Norris character wearing his signature outfit (casual, with a beard and a stern expression). Chuck Norris is casually cracking his knuckles or flexing his muscles, looking calm but intimidating. The dinosaurs, wide-eyed and slightly backing away, give the impression that they just realized they made a big mistake. The style is humorous and light-hearted, with exaggerated expressions on the dinosaurs and Chuck Norris to emphasize the joke''s punchline. Include a subtle caption or speech bubble near the dinosaurs with something like ''Uh-oh...'' for added effect.'),
 (522, 'Chuck Norris, Health Humor, Puns', 'The flu gets a Chuck Norris shot every year.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing the flu virus as a tiny, green, angry-looking germ trying to enter a human body. Next to it stands Chuck Norris depicted as a strong, tough cowboy character wearing a hat and cowboy boots, with a confident, no-nonsense expression. Chuck Norris is holding a giant oversized syringe labeled ''Chuck Norris Shot'' aimed toward the flu virus. The background is a simple doctor''s office or clinic setting with a medical poster showing immune system cells cheering. The flu virus looks startled and scared, backing away comically from the syringe. Bright, bold colors and exaggerated facial expressions emphasize the humor.'),
 (523, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, History Humor', 'The Great Wall of China was originally created to keep Chuck Norris out. It didn''t work.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing the Great Wall of China stretching across a hilly landscape with traditional Chinese watchtowers. At one point, the wall has a large crack or gap where Chuck Norris is effortlessly kicking through the wall. Chuck Norris is depicted as a confident, strong action hero (in a simple cartoon style), wearing a martial arts outfit with a black belt. Around him, broken bricks fly into the air, emphasizing his unstoppable power. In the background, a frustrated, bewildered looking ancient Chinese soldier or guard stands holding a spear, scratching his head or looking defeated. The overall mood is light, playful, and exaggerated to show Chuck Norris''s legendary toughness against an iconic monument.'),
 (524, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'The only time Chuck Norris was ever wrong was when he thought he had made a mistake.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon featuring Chuck Norris standing confidently with his arms crossed and a slight smirk. Behind him is a chalkboard or digital screen with a large checkmark labeled ''Correct'' and a tiny, almost hidden, erased ''Mistake'' written faintly. Around him, a few smaller characters, looking puzzled or amazed, point at the board. The background is simple with a spotlight effect on Chuck Norris to emphasize his legendary infallibility. The style should be light-hearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions and bold outlines to enhance the comedic effect.'),
 (525, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Pop Culture', 'The show Survivor had the original premise of putting people on an island with Chuck Norris, but there were no survivors.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a tropical island with sand, palm trees, and a small campfire. In the center stands a tough, exaggeratedly muscular Chuck Norris character wearing his iconic martial arts outfit, flexing his muscles with a serious expression. Surrounding him are several confused and defeated reality show contestants in typical Survivor gear (bandanas, casual outdoor clothing, backpacks) sitting or lying around looking exhausted, with no energy left. One contestant looks at the viewer with a speech bubble saying ''No survivors… literally.'' The background shows a bright sunny sky and a simple wooden sign that says ''Welcome to Survivor.'' The overall style is playful and exaggerated to clearly convey the joke without any violence: the ''no survivors'' punchline is expressed through the weary contestants overshadowed by the formidable Chuck Norris figure.'),
 (526, 'Cartoon, Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Weather Humor', 'There has never been a hurricane named Chuck because it would have destroyed everything.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a giant, menacing tropical hurricane with a swirling storm cloud in the shape of a strong, tough man named ''Chuck.'' This character is flexing his bulging muscles and has a confident, cocky grin. Around him, trees are bent over, houses are tilted or slightly damaged, fallen street signs and debris swirl in the wind, and a few frightened animals like birds and squirrels scatter away. In the background, a weather station building looks on in shock, with a meteorologist holding a clipboard and waving hands in disbelief. A large wooden sign next to the character reads ''Hurricane Chuck.'' The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions and action lines to emphasize the power of ''Chuck'' the hurricane. The color palette uses stormy blues, grays, and a hint of vibrant colors for the sign and house details to keep it fun and visually engaging.'),
 (527, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'Time waits for no man. Unless that man is Chuck Norris.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a rugged, muscular Chuck Norris standing confidently in the middle of a city street. Around him, large, classic clock faces with arms and legs try to move forward but freeze in place, looking startled or intimidated by Chuck Norris. One clock might be sweating nervously or holding up its hands in surrender. Chuck is giving a stern, playful glare or a smirk, with his arms crossed. The background is simple but includes street elements like a sidewalk and a lamppost to set the urban scene. The style is bright, colorful, and exaggerated in a lighthearted cartoon style, emphasizing Chuck Norris''s legendary tough persona and the idea that even time is stopped by him.'),
 (528, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Math Humor', 'When Chuck Norris does division, there are no remainders.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing Chuck Norris standing confidently at a classroom chalkboard filled with math division problems. The division problems have no remainders and are perfectly solved, with large zeros prominently displayed. Chuck Norris is drawn with a slight smirk, wearing his iconic beard and casual martial arts attire. Around him, shocked students and a surprised math teacher hold their hats or scratch their heads in amazement. The chalkboard has bold, clean division signs and numbers, emphasizing the absence of any remainders. The setting is a bright, simple classroom with desks and posters of multiplication tables on the walls. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions to amplify the joke''s essence.'),
 (529, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'When Chuck Norris enters a room, he doesn''t turn the lights on, he turns the dark off.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Chuck Norris confidently stepping into a dimly lit room. Chuck is depicted with a strong, heroic stance in casual yet iconic attire (e.g., denim jacket, beard). Instead of a light switch, he is dramatically pressing an invisible button mid-air with a smirk, and around him, the darkness visibly ''retreats'' or ''recedes'' as if being pushed away by his presence. The room behind him has shadows and dark corners, but as he steps in, the shadows comically pull back like curtains or smoke vanishing, revealing a well-lit space. Make the lighting effect exaggerated and playful, with cartoonish beams of light pushing back dark swirling shadows. Include simple background elements like a couch, a lamp (off), and a small table to suggest an ordinary room. The style is colorful, fun, and clearly lighthearted without any violence or negativity.'),
 (530, 'Chuck Norris, Exaggeration, Humor', 'When Chuck Norris plays dodgeball, the balls dodge him.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene of a gymnasium during a dodgeball game. In the center is a muscular, confident Chuck Norris character with a stern but calm expression, standing with his arms slightly raised and ready to catch or dodge. Around him, several dodgeballs in mid-air are visibly moving away rapidly, with motion lines and small surprised cartoon eyes on the balls to emphasize they are trying to escape him. Several players on the sidelines watch in amazement, some shielding their eyes or dropping their own dodgeballs in disbelief. The gym has typical features like a basketball hoop, wooden floor, and a scoreboard showing ''Chuck Norris: 1, Everyone Else: 0''. Use bright, simple colors with exaggerated cartoon features for a light and funny atmosphere without any violence or aggression.'),
 (531, 'Chuck Norris, Humor', 'When Chuck Norris was born, the only person who cried was the doctor. Never slap Chuck Norris.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a newborn baby Chuck Norris lying in a hospital bassinet, looking completely calm and unbothered. Nearby, a doctor wearing scrubs and a stethoscope is wiping tears from his eyes, looking shocked and emotional. The doctor should have exaggerated teary eyes and a trembling lower lip. The hospital room is simple, with a window showing a sunny day outside. Next to the bassinet is a bold sign or caption that says, ''Never slap Chuck Norris.'' The overall style should be lighthearted with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humor and the superhuman toughness implied by the joke.'),
 (532, 'Chuck Norris, Humor, Pop Culture', 'When the Boogeyman goes to sleep every night he checks his closet for Chuck Norris.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a bedroom at night. The Boogeyman, a shadowy and slightly scary but comical monster with glowing eyes, is standing beside his bed wearing pajamas and holding a flashlight. He is nervously looking toward an open, well-lit closet door. Inside the closet stands Chuck Norris, confidently posing with crossed arms, a stern yet calm expression, wearing a martial arts gi. The room is simple with a bed, bedside table with an alarm clock, and a window with moonlight shining through. The overall mood is playful and funny, emphasizing the role reversal where the Boogeyman is scared and cautious about Chuck Norris hiding in his closet. The style should be bright and colorful with exaggerated and cartoonish expressions to add humor.'),
 (533, 'Corona, Humor', 'I tried to make a Corona Virus joke in April. Nobody laughed then, but eventually everyone got it.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene set in April with a nervous-looking person standing on a small stage labeled ''Comedy Open Mic April.'' The person holds a microphone and has a speech bubble that says, ''Why did the virus go on vacation? Because it wanted some social distancing!'' The audience is shown looking confused or not laughing. In the background, a calendar page clearly showing ''April'' is pinned on a wall. Next to this scene, a second panel shows the same person months later on the same stage, but now the audience is laughing heartily, holding masks and sanitizer. The caption above the two panels reads: ''Nobody laughed then... but eventually everyone got it.'' The style should be light-hearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the awkwardness and eventual humor. Avoid any depiction of illness symptoms, people looking sick, or anything scary.'),
 (534, 'Corona, Humor, Puns, Shopping Jokes', 'The LEGO store reopened after the lockdown, and folks were lined up for blocks.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene outside a LEGO store with a big LEGO logo above the entrance. The store has large glass windows showing shelves filled with LEGO sets inside. In front, a diverse line of happy, eager people extends outward, curving around the sidewalk. The line is cleverly made to look like it’s composed of LEGO blocks stacked one after another to represent ''lined up for blocks.'' Some people in line are holding LEGO bricks or small assembled LEGO figures, excited and chatting. The background shows a sunny day with a few fluffy clouds, and a small sign near the door reads ''Open after lockdown.'' The overall style is lighthearted, bright, and playful, emphasizing the pun with the visual of people forming a block-like queue.'),
 (535, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Corona, Humor', 'What''s the difference between a hot dog and an anti-vaxxer? The hot dog might have SOME brains in it', NULL, 'A colorful and humorous cartoon scene featuring two main characters side by side. On the left, a classic hot dog with ketchup and mustard in a bun, smiling and showing a tiny cartoon brain popping out of its top bun in a playful way. On the right, a person depicted as an anti-vaxxer with a confused expression, exaggeratedly scratching their head as if puzzled or lacking understanding. The background is simple and bright, suggesting a lighthearted mood. Include a speech bubble above the hot dog saying, "I''ve got some brains!" and another from the anti-vaxxer with a question mark to emphasize confusion. No violence or negativity should be present. The style is cartoonish with bold outlines and vibrant colors, focusing on the humorous contrast between the two characters'' expressions and the small brain detail on the hot dog.'),
 (536, 'Corona, Health Humor, Humor, Word Play', 'You think Corona virus is bad? Peekaboo virus is even worse. You go straight to ICU.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a hospital ICU room with a surprised, wide-eyed patient lying in a bed. The patient is playfully covering their face with their hands like in a game of peekaboo, with a ghostly or mischievous virus character hovering nearby, playfully popping out from behind a curtain or medical equipment. The ICU setting should include typical hospital details such as a heart monitor, IV stand, and medical posters on the walls, adding to the humor by contrasting the serious setting with the silly peekaboo virus. The virus character should look silly and non-threatening, with a big smile and cartoonish eyes, emphasizing the joke''s playful nature rather than medical reality. Use bright, cheerful colors and exaggerated expressions to keep the cartoon lighthearted and funny.'),
 (537, 'Dad, Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'Breaking news: A red ship and a blue ship have collided in the Caribbean... apparently, the survivors are marooned.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene set on a bright, sunny Caribbean beach. In the background, two ships lean toward each other, one painted bright red and the other bright blue, with obvious cartoonish damage where they have collided. On the sandy shore in the foreground, a group of people look surprised and slightly worried as they stand among scattered crates and beach items. Some survivors are wearing typical stranded expressions. To emphasize the pun, around their feet and scattered on the sand are several large maroon-colored backpacks or sacks labeled ''MAROONED,'' as if the survivors have literally been ''marooned'' with maroon items. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated, with bold lines and vibrant colors to imply humor rather than drama or danger.'),
 (538, 'Dad, Food Humor, Puns', 'Cannibal says: a sandwich is a sandwich, but a manwich is a meal!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a friendly-looking cannibal sitting at a rustic wooden table in a jungle or tribal setting. The cannibal should be mid-sentence with a big grin, holding a large sandwich in one hand labeled simply ''Sandwich'' with typical sandwich fillings (lettuce, tomato, cheese). On the table in front of him is a giant sandwich labeled ''Manwich'' that humorously looks like a sandwich with a small cartoon man peeking out or sitting inside it, smiling as if he’s part of the meal. Surrounding the cannibal are lighthearted jungle elements, like palm leaves and vines. The atmosphere should be playful, colorful, and cartoonish without anything scary or violent, emphasizing the wordplay and pun on ''manwich'' as a meal rather than just a sandwich.'),
 (539, 'Dad, Puns', 'I entered a dad joke competition and won $1000. It was a grand dad joke.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful man proudly holding a large trophy labeled ''Dad Joke Champion'' and a big check for $1000. Next to him, an old, dignified-looking man wearing a crown and a sash that says ''Grand Dad'' stands with a smile, as if sharing the prize or being part of the joke. The setting is a simple stage with a banner overhead reading ''Dad Joke Competition.'' There is a small audience in the background laughing and clapping. The style is colorful and light-hearted with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the pun on ''grand dad joke.'' No violence or anything inappropriate should be included.'),
 (540, 'Bad Puns, Dad, Humor, Word Play', 'I really feel like I have a bad posture. I have a hunch.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring a character, standing slightly hunched over with exaggerated bad posture to highlight their discomfort. The character could be an ordinary adult wearing casual clothes, with a visible ''hunch'' on their back that looks like a small bump or lump shaped like a question mark, to visually represent the pun. The character has a puzzled or slightly concerned expression on their face, maybe holding their lower back with one hand. The background is simple, like a plain room or park setting, with no additional characters or objects distracting from the scene. Use a lighthearted, cartoonish style with bright colors and clear outlines to keep the mood funny and light, rather than serious.'),
 (541, 'Animals, Dad, Humor, Puns', 'If a clown farts, does it smell funny?', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene featuring a cheerful clown in a classic circus outfit: oversized shoes, bright red nose, big curly hair, and striped pants. The clown is standing on a simple circus ring with a red carpet circle beneath. The clown has a surprised yet amused expression, holding its nose while small comic-style odor lines (wavy lines) rise from its rear. Nearby, a small bunch of circus animals including a laughing seal, a giggling elephant, and a smiling monkey are reacting to the smell in a humorous, exaggerated way. The background is cheerful with balloons and circus tents lightly sketched. The overall style is lighthearted, playful, and exaggerated for comedic effect, resembling a colorful, kid-friendly cartoon.'),
 (542, 'Dad, Math Humor, Puns', 'I''m going to a Fibonacci conference this year. They promise it will be as big as the last two put together!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a conference hall with a big banner that reads ''Fibonacci Conference''. In the foreground, a cheerful character wearing a name tag is excitedly telling another person, ''They promise it will be as big as the last two put together!'' Behind them, three conference rooms are visible, labeled with numbers: ''Room 1'', ''Room 2'', and to the right, a much larger room labeled ''Room 3'', which is roughly the combined size of the first two rooms. The rooms could be illustrated as blocks whose sizes visually match the Fibonacci sequence (small, medium, then large). Add playful details like posters with spiral and number patterns and an audience or attendees milling about, some looking intrigued or puzzled by the concept. Make sure the style is lighthearted, colorful, and cartoonish to emphasize the joke''s clever play on Fibonacci growth without any intense or complex elements.'),
 (543, 'Dad, Humor, Word Play, Workplace', 'I''m pretty sure that hotel receptionist was checking me out', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a modern hotel lobby. The main focus is a young man standing at the front desk, looking slightly flustered and blushing, with a shy smile on his face. Across the desk, a hotel receptionist, a friendly-looking woman, is glancing sideways at him with a knowing smirk and raised eyebrow, as if giving him a playful once-over. The desk should have a computer monitor and a bell, and behind the receptionist, a sign that reads ''Hotel Reception'' or a stylized hotel logo. The background shows some simple lobby details like a potted plant and a wall clock. The art style is light, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the humor and playful mood without any suggestiveness or discomfort. The overall vibe is cheerful and silly, capturing the pun on ''checking out'' as both hotel procedure and flirtation.'),
 (544, 'Dad, Puns', 'It''s inappropriate to make a dad joke if you''re not a dad. That''s a faux pa.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful middle-aged man wearing a stereotypical "dad" outfit: a plaid shirt tucked into khaki pants, loafers, and glasses. He is standing in a living room with a big grin, holding a big book labeled "Dad Jokes" in one hand. Across from him stands a younger person looking confused and embarrassed, nervously trying to hold back a groan. Floating above the younger person''s head is a comic-style speech bubble with the phrase, "That''s a faux pa!" Behind them, a decorative wall clock shaped like a faux pas (pun on a foot in a shoe) adds a subtle visual cue for humor. The overall style is light-hearted and cartoonish with bright colors, exaggerated facial expressions, and playful details to emphasize the wordplay and social awkwardness of telling dad jokes when you’re not a dad.'),
 (545, 'Dad, History Humor, Political Humor, Puns', 'Joseph Stalin should have known communism wouldn''t work... I mean seriously, there were red flags everywhere.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring Joseph Stalin standing in a field filled with numerous large red flags planted in the ground all around him. Stalin, drawn with his iconic mustache and military uniform, has a puzzled or concerned expression on his face, scratching his chin as he looks around at the red flags. The background is a simple clear sky and some grass to keep the focus on the ''red flags.'' The style should be lighthearted and exaggerated for comedic effect, with bright colors emphasizing the red flags. No violence or political tension; just an amusing visual pun on "red flags" and communism.'),
 (546, 'Dad, Family, Puns', 'My son just became a father for the first time today... to pass the paternal torch, he asked me where I kept all my dad jokes, so I told him - they are stored in my dadabase.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two men—a proud father and his adult son—standing together in a cozy living room. The father is handing over a large, overflowing bookshelf labeled ''DAD JOKES'' to his son, who looks excited and slightly amused. The bookshelf is cartoonishly big, filled with books, scrolls, and sticky notes, all labeled with silly pun titles. Near the bookshelf is a computer terminal or server tower humorously labeled ''DADABASE'' with blinking lights and a digital screen displaying the word ''Loading Dad Jokes...''. Both men are smiling warmly, embodying a lighthearted passing of tradition. The room has family photos on the walls, including a framed picture of the father holding a baby. The style is colorful and friendly, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke’s pun on "database" and "dadabase." The overall vibe is cheerful and comical without any violence, politics, or inappropriate content.'),
 (547, 'Bad Puns, Dad, Food Humor, Workplace', 'The CEO of Pepsi was fired this morning. He tested positive for coke.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a business office with a surprised CEO sitting at a large desk labeled ''Pepsi.'' The CEO is a middle-aged man in a business suit, looking shocked with wide eyes and raised eyebrows. On the desk is a big soda bottle clearly labeled ''Pepsi.'' Standing next to the CEO is a friendly-looking doctor or lab technician holding a clipboard that reads ''Test Results'' with a positive ''+'' sign next to a smaller bottle labeled ''Coke.'' In the background, a bulletin board or whiteboard shows the word ''Fired!'' in big red letters. The office has a few playful soda-related decorations like a Pepsi logo poster and a cup with a straw. The overall style is bright, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the pun on the word ''coke'' as both a drug test and the rival soda brand, with no aggressive or negative elements in the scene.'),
 (548, 'Dad, Humor, Puns', 'What happens to a dad joke once it is delivered? It''s fully groan', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful dad standing with a big grin, holding a microphone as if delivering a joke. In front of him, several audience members with exaggerated expressions of groaning—some have their hands on their faces, others rolling their eyes or leaning back dramatically. In the background, a large speech bubble coming from the dad contains the pun text: ''It''s fully groan.'' The setting is a simple living room or comedy stage with a spotlight on the dad, emphasizing the joke delivery. Include playful visual elements like musical notes or small cartoon groan sound effects around the audience''s heads to emphasize the pun on ''groan'' sounding like ''grown.'' The overall tone should be lighthearted and fun, in a colorful and exaggerated cartoon style, without any negativity or mean-spiritedness.'),
 (549, 'Dad, Humor, Word Play', 'What starts with ''w'' and ends with ''hat''. (No, that wasn''t a question, just a statement of fact...)', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a quirky character—a smiling person with a surprised or amused expression—standing next to a large oversized word puzzle board. The board prominently displays the letters ''w'' at the start and ''hat'' at the end, with a big blank space in the middle to highlight the joke’s wordplay. The character is holding one finger up, as if making a point, while a speech bubble above them says: ''No, that wasn’t a question, just a statement of fact…''. The setting is bright and playful with simple background colors to keep focus on the character and the word puzzle. The font of the letters on the board should be bold and cartoonish. The scene is lighthearted and emphasizes the word joke without any violent or controversial elements.'),
 (550, 'Bad Puns, Dad, Puns', 'When does a bad pun become a dad joke? When it becomes apparent', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a large pun-themed courtroom or science lab labeled ''Pun Lab'' with a giant shining light bulb above it to signify ''apparent.'' In the center, a bad pun character personified as a goofy, sad-looking pun with googly eyes and a frown is crossing an imaginary line titled ''Dad Joke Threshold.'' Nearby, a cheerful dad figure with a thumbs-up and a classic ''Dad'' hat is pointing at the pun, smiling and perhaps rolling his eyes. Surrounding them are floating, oversized word bubbles containing silly puns and dad joke elements, with the word ''Apparent'' brightly highlighted. The background is colorful and playful, with exaggerated cartoon expressions and simple props like a big magnifying glass or pun-related symbols such as a banana peel or cheese wedge to emphasize humor without any violence or politics.'),
 (551, 'Dad, Humor', 'When is a dad joke apparent? When it is delivered', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a friendly middle-aged dad standing next to a speech bubble. The dad is smiling widely and wearing casual clothes, such as a plaid shirt and jeans. The speech bubble coming from him contains a very simple and obvious pun or joke, symbolizing a ''dad joke'' being told out loud. Around him, a few family members or friends have mixed reactions: one person rolling their eyes playfully, another person chuckling, and a child with an exaggerated groan or facepalm. The setting is a cozy living room with a couch, a lamp, maybe a wall clock showing ''pun time.'' The overall atmosphere is lighthearted and silly, emphasizing the idea that a dad joke becomes obvious simply by being spoken aloud. The cartoon style should be colorful, friendly, and exaggerated to highlight the humor without being aggressive or sarcastic.'),
 (552, 'Animals, Dad, Humor, Puns', 'Why don''t cannibals eat clowns? Because they taste funny.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a puzzled but friendly-looking cannibal sitting at a rustic wooden table in a jungle setting. On the table is a cartoon clown character, complete with colorful oversized shoes, a red nose, rainbow-colored wig, and bright makeup, looking surprised but unharmed. The cannibal holds a fork and knife hesitantly, sniffing or tasting a small bite from the clown''s shoe or hand with a confused expression. Nearby, a speech bubble above the cannibal reads, "They taste funny!" The background includes jungle foliage with vines and trees, and a bright sunny sky to keep the mood light and funny. The overall style is exaggerated and playful, with bold outlines and vibrant colors, capturing the pun visually without any scary or violent elements.'),
 (553, 'Did''ya Hear, Dyslexics, Philosophy Humor, Puns', 'Did you hear about the dyslexic agnostic insomniac who stays up all night wondering if there really is a Dog?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a character looking tired and confused late at night. The character should have disheveled hair, dark circles under their eyes, and be sitting on a bed or armchair surrounded by nighttime elements like a clock showing a late hour and a moon visible through a window. Above the character, depict a thought bubble illustrating the mix-up: instead of the usual question ''Is there a God?'', show a dog with a questioning expression wearing a little halo or glowing softly, emphasizing the pun on ''Dog'' instead of ''God''. The setting should feel whimsical and playful, using bright, exaggerated cartoon expressions to highlight the character’s insomnia, doubt (agnosticism), and dyslexia through visual cues like jumbled letters or symbols floating around their head. Keep the style lighthearted with exaggerated, comical features and a cozy nighttime indoor background with a lamp casting a soft glow.'),
 (554, 'Did''ya Hear, Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'Did you hear about the underwear company that only allowed brief phone calls?', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon storefront scene depicting an underwear company shop named ''Brief Calls Inc.'' The shop has a large, eye-catching sign featuring an underwear icon and a vintage phone receiver with a clock dial integrated into the design to emphasize ''brief calls.'' Outside the shop, a cheerful shopkeeper wearing funny boxers and a nametag stands behind a counter, holding a classic telephone receiver to his ear with a big smile. Around him, customers line up, some holding phones, appearing amused or impatient. Above, playful speech bubbles show very short phone conversations with ellipses and quick ''Hello? Bye!'' text to reflect brief calls. The background should be simple and bright, with a sidewalk and a few humorous details like a clock showing very short time intervals and underwear hanging or displayed in the window. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, capturing the pun on ''brief'' as both underwear and short phone calls.'),
 (555, 'Did''ya Hear, Food Humor, Humor, Puns', 'Did''ya hear about the cheese factory explosion in Wisconsin? De brie was everywhere', NULL, 'Draw a colorful, humorous cartoon scene of a cheese factory explosion. The factory building should be in the background with some smokey puffs and cartoon-style explosion lines emanating from it, but no flames. In the foreground and midground, portray chunks and drips of various types of cheese flying through the air—most prominently pieces of Brie with its distinctive white rind and soft interior. Include other cheese shapes like Swiss and cheddar for variety. Show some cheese pieces comically landing on nearby grass, animals (like cows looking surprised), and workers wearing casual factory uniforms with comical shocked expressions but no injury. The setting is a cheerful countryside farm with green rolling hills and a clear blue sky. The style is exaggerated and playful, emphasizing the pun by making the cheese explosion look silly and messy but not harmful or scary.'),
 (556, 'Bad Puns, Did''ya Hear', 'Did''ya hear about the guy who broke both his left arm and left leg? He''s all right now.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a man with crutches and a sling supporting his left arm and a cast on his left leg. He is smiling confidently and giving a thumbs-up with his right hand. The setting is a simple doctor’s office or waiting room with a small chair, a medical poster on the wall showing a human skeleton with left limbs highlighted, and a calendar. The man’s left arm and leg appear obviously injured, yet he looks cheerful and relaxed, emphasizing the pun. A speech bubble above him says, "I''m all right now!". The overall style is lighthearted, colorful, and exaggerated to highlight the joke without any grim or serious tone.'),
 (557, 'Bad Puns, Did''ya Hear, Humor', 'Did''ya hear about the guy who got hit in the head with a can of soda? He was lucky it was a soft drink.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a slightly dazed man standing with a surprised and confused expression on his face. Above his head, a smiling, anthropomorphic can of soda is gently bouncing off him, depicted with soft motion lines to indicate it''s not hard or painful. The soda can has big friendly eyes and a playful grin, emphasizing it as a ''soft drink.'' Around them is a simple urban or park background with a few bushes and a bench to keep the scene light and relatable. The man''s hair is slightly ruffled from the gentle impact. The style is bright and colorful with exaggerated facial expressions to enhance the joke''s pun. No harsh or violent imagery, just playful and cartoonish interaction between the man and the ''soft'' soda can.'),
 (3217, 'Random', 'I wondered why the football was getting bigger and bigger - and then it hit me.', NULL, NULL),
 (558, 'Did''ya Hear, Puns', 'Did''ya hear about the kidnapping at school? Everything''s fine now. He woke up.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a bright, cheerful elementary school classroom. In the center, a confused but sleepy kid is just waking up on the floor near a small desk, rubbing his eyes. Nearby, a couple of kids and a teacher look relieved and slightly amused. There is a school backpack lying casually beside the sleeping kid, and a fun classroom background with colorful posters, a chalkboard, and desks. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the pun of ''kidnapping'' meaning a child literally ''napping'' (sleeping). The style is simple and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions of surprise, relief, and drowsiness to capture the joke''s clever wordplay.'),
 (559, 'Bad Puns, Did''ya Hear, Movies, Word Play', 'Did''ya hear about the movie ''Constipation''? No? That''s because it hasn''t come out yet', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy living room with a classic movie poster stand prominently displaying a poster titled ''Constipation''. The poster shows a lock with chains over an old-fashioned film reel, symbolizing the movie being ''locked'' or ''not released''. Nearby, a confused person with exaggerated puzzled expression is scratching their head or looking around, clearly unaware of the movie. Include subtle visual puns like a calendar on the wall with the current date circled and a toilet paper roll on a side table to hint at the theme without being explicit. Use bright colors, rounded lines, and lighthearted character design for a family-friendly, approachable, and funny feel.'),
 (560, 'Did''ya Hear, Puns, Word Play', 'Did''ya hear about the new broom that came out? It''s sweeping the nation', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene featuring a large, cheerful broom with eyes, a wide smile, and arms holding a tiny flag. The broom is sweeping across a simplified map of a country (like the United States), with tiny cartoon houses and trees being gently swept along behind it like a wave. Around the broom, little cartoon people cheer and wave small banners that say ''Go Broom!'' The sky is bright and sunny, and the style is lighthearted and whimsical, emphasizing the pun ''sweeping the nation'' by showing the broom literally sweeping the map in a playful, non-threatening way.'),
 (561, 'Did''ya Hear, Food Humor, Puns, Science', 'Did''ya hear about the new restaurant on the moon? The food is ok but there''s no atmosphere', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing the inside of a futuristic restaurant located on the moon. The setting is a round dining area with large windows revealing the lunar surface and Earth in the background. Two cartoon characters—an astronaut and a casual diner in a space suit—are sitting at a simple table with plates of food that look ordinary and unimpressive. The astronaut is shrugging and looking disappointed. Above them, a speech bubble reads, ''The food is ok but there''s no atmosphere.'' The restaurant interior looks very bare and empty, emphasizing the pun on ''no atmosphere.'' Little details like floating crumbs or zero gravity food crumbs add whimsy. The overall style should be colorful, lighthearted, and clearly a cartoon to match the joke’s playful tone.'),
 (562, 'Animals, Did''ya Hear, Puns, Space Humor', 'Did''ya hear that SpaceX launched several cows into orbit? It was the herd shot around the world.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in outer space showing several cows floating in zero gravity wearing tiny astronaut helmets. The cows look surprised and cheerful as they orbit around a small, stylized Earth visible in the background. One cow is holding a small flag that says ''SpaceX'' while another is happily mooing with stars twinkling around. The cows are arranged in a loose circular orbit path labeled ''The herd shot around the world.'' The backdrop features a few planets and a rocket ship with the SpaceX logo blasting off from Earth in the distance. The whole scene has a lighthearted, colorful, and playful cartoon style with exaggerated expressions on the cows to emphasize the joke.'),
 (563, 'Animals, Did''ya Hear, Puns', 'Did''ya hear the one about the skeleton that couldn''t go to the party? He had no body to go with', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful skeleton standing outside a lively party. The skeleton is portrayed as a classic white bone figure with a friendly smile but looking slightly sad or disappointed as it stands alone. In the background, there''s a colorful party inside a warmly lit house with a welcome banner reading ''Party Time!'' Visible through partly open doors and windows are silhouettes of dancing figures and decorations like balloons and streamers. The skeleton holds a small party invitation card in one hand and scratches its skull with the other, emphasizing its loneliness. Around the skeleton’s feet lies a shadow that forms the shape of a human body silhouette, hinting at the joke''s pun. The scene should be bright, cartoonish, playful, and non-threatening, capturing a light-hearted and silly mood without any horror elements.'),
 (564, 'Animals, Did''ya Hear, Puns', 'Did''ya know alligators can grow up to 15 feet? Most only have 4 though.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a grassy swamp with a large, proud alligator smiling as it stands next to a giant 15-foot tall measuring stick. The alligator is clearly oversized and impressive. Nearby, four tiny alligators, each about the height of a small child, stand lined up next to the same measuring stick looking tiny and somewhat bewildered. The large alligator gestures towards the measuring stick while the little ones look up at it. The setting should be colorful and lighthearted, with some reeds, lily pads, and water in the background to express a swamp environment. The overall tone is playful and comical, emphasizing the joke''s pun on ''feet'' as both length and actual ''feet'' (toes) on alligators. The alligators’ feet could be exaggeratedly large or small to reinforce the humor without feeling threatening or scary.'),
 (565, 'Did''ya Hear, Good Question!', 'Did''ya know the latest version of the Oxford English Dictionary does not contain the word ''gullible''?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon-style drawing showing a large, thick Oxford English Dictionary open on a wooden desk. The focus is on a page with words and definitions, but the word ''gullible'' is missing, illustrated by a big empty space or a question mark. Nearby, a person with a puzzled and slightly embarrassed expression is scratching their head, clearly looking at the book, unsure if they believe the claim. Behind them, a mischievous-looking character or a small cartoon bird labeled ''Gullible'' is smirking or chuckling, adding to the joke. The setting is a cozy library or study room with bookshelves filled with colorful books in the background, giving a scholarly vibe. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, using exaggerated facial expressions and fun elements like question marks and thought bubbles to emphasize confusion and humor.'),
 (566, 'Don''t Say It!, Humor, Word Play', 'I can make apocalypse jokes like there is no tomorrow', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a cheerful character confidently standing on a stage with a microphone, delivering a joke. The background shows a dramatic, exaggerated apocalypse setting with a burning sun and cracked earth, but drawn in a lighthearted, cartoonish style without fear or violence. The character is smiling broadly, shrugging as if to say "there''s no tomorrow," while behind them, a calendar on a wall displays the date ''Today'' with the next day humorously torn off or missing. Include simple, bright colors and exaggerated expressions to keep the tone witty and playful.'),
 (567, 'Don''t Say It!, Humor, Puns', 'I can''t tell you the one about the roof, because it''s over your head', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a confused person standing outside their house looking up at the roof. Above them, a simple house with a peaked roof is clearly visible. On the roof, a cheerful cartoon character (personified roof) is leaning down, winking and holding a finger to its lips as if saying ''shh''. Above this character, a speech bubble reads, ''It''s over your head!'' The style should be colorful, light-hearted, and humorous, with exaggerated facial expressions on both the confused person and the animated roof to emphasize the pun. The background can be a sunny day with a few clouds to keep it bright and friendly.'),
 (568, 'Bathroom Humor, Don''t Say It!, Puns', 'I don''t have any jokes about toilet paper - they''re all tearable', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a roll of toilet paper sitting on a small stage with a microphone, as if performing stand-up comedy. The toilet paper roll has a cheerful, animated face with big eyes and a wide smile. Around the stage are a few rolls of toilet paper sitting in an audience, each showing expressions of groaning or laughing at the joke. In the background, a banner reads ''Toilet Paper Comedy Night.'' The setting should be lighthearted and colorful, with the roll under a spotlight and a simple comedy club vibe. Include some scattered torn pieces of toilet paper on the floor to hint at the pun ''tearable.'''),
 (569, 'Don''t Say It!, Food Humor, Puns', 'I don''t like jokes about pizza. They''re too cheesy.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a large, anthropomorphic pizza slice standing upright with a slightly annoyed or tired facial expression. The pizza slice has exaggerated gooey cheese dripping off its edges, with pepperoni eyes and a mouth. Nearby, a small character (could be a person or a simple cartoon figure) is holding a microphone or telling a joke, looking amused. The background is simple, maybe a kitchen or pizzeria setting with a pizza oven and flour bags. The scene should emphasize the ''cheesy'' aspect by making the cheese notably thick and stringy, almost like melted goo, to visually reinforce the pun. The overall tone is light and playful, with bright colors like red, yellow, and green. No violence or anything inappropriate.'),
 (570, 'Don''t Say It!, Humor, Social Commentary, Word Play', 'I don''t make fat people jokes, because they wouldn''t be appreciated by the wider audience', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a comedy stage with a microphone and a spotlight shining on a cheerful stand-up comedian. The comedian is holding a microphone and smiling broadly while facing an audience filled with diverse people of various shapes, sizes, and expressions, including a few overweight individuals who are smiling or laughing warmly. The background has a simple brick wall common to comedy clubs. Above the scene or on a small sign near the stage, include a visible gag in text: ''I don''t make fat people jokes, because they wouldn''t be appreciated by the wider audience.'' The overall tone is lighthearted and friendly, with bright colors and exaggerated cartoonish features to emphasize humor and inclusivity without offending anyone.'),
 (571, 'Don''t Say It!, Food Humor, Puns', 'I don''t make jokes about German sausage - they''re the wurst!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful German sausage character with a smiling face, wearing a traditional Bavarian hat (like a Tyrolean hat with a feather). The sausage is standing on a wooden platter with mustard and sauerkraut next to it. Above the sausage, a speech bubble says, "I''m the wurst!" In the background, there is a simple German beer hall atmosphere with a wooden bench and a sign featuring the German flag colors. The tone is light and playful, focusing on the pun without any violence or offense.'),
 (572, 'Don''t Say It!, Humor, Workplace', 'I don''t make jokes about retired people, because they don''t work', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters: one active, middle-aged person holding a microphone and grinning as if telling a joke, and an elderly person relaxing in a rocking chair with a content smile, wearing casual retired clothing like a cardigan and slippers. The setting is a cozy living room with a small side table holding a coffee cup and a newspaper with the headline ''Retirement Life.'' The active person looks playful and animated while the retired person appears relaxed and amused. Include light-hearted speech bubbles: the active person says, ''I don''t make jokes about retired people…'' and the retired person happily finishes with, ''…because they don''t work!'' The overall tone is friendly and gentle humor, with bright colors and exaggerated, expressive cartoon faces to emphasize the joke’s playful vibe.'),
 (573, 'Bad Puns, Don''t Say It!, Humor, Word Play', 'I don''t make jokes about unemployed people, because they never work', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a stand-up comedian on a small stage with a microphone in hand, smiling and delivering the joke. In the audience, there are a few characters representing unemployed people, sitting in chairs looking surprised but not offended. The backdrop shows a simple comedy club setting with a ''Comedy Night'' sign and a spotlight on the comedian. The comedian''s speech bubble reads, "I don''t make jokes about unemployed people, because they never work." The overall tone is light and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the pun.'),
 (574, 'Don''t Say It!, Humor, Political Humor, Word Play', 'I don''t tell jokes about communism because aren''t funny unless you share them with everyone.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a casual living room. In the center, a cheerful person is standing with a big grin, holding a microphone or a paper with a joke written on it. Around them, several friends or family members are gathered, all smiling or chuckling, emphasizing a shared moment of laughter. Above the scene, a speech bubble from the person says, ''I don''t tell jokes about communism because aren''t funny unless you share them with everyone.'' Background elements include a cozy couch, a coffee table with snacks, and a few playful posters or decorations hinting at equality or sharing, such as a pie chart split evenly or people passing a pie around. The overall tone is light-hearted and cartoonish, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the communal humor concept.'),
 (575, 'Don''t Say It!, Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'I don''t tell PMS jokes because they aren''t funny. Period.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a friendly-looking stand-up comedian on stage holding a microphone, looking amused but polite. Behind the comedian is a large speech bubble with the text: "I don''t tell PMS jokes because they aren''t funny. Period." The audience is a small group of diverse cartoon characters reacting with mixed expressions — some smiling, some indifferent. The stage has a simple curtain backdrop and a spotlight focused on the comedian. A small clock on the wall shows the time, emphasizing the stand-up setting. The overall art style should be lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the joke’s tone without offending anyone.'),
 (576, 'Construction Humor, Don''t Say It!, Word Play', 'I had a joke about construction, but I''m still working on it', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a friendly construction worker standing next to a half-built wooden sign that reads ''Joke Under Construction.'' The worker is wearing a yellow hard hat, a bright orange safety vest, and blue jeans. He has a cheerful smile and is holding a hammer in one hand and a blueprint rolled up in the other. The background features a simple construction site with orange cones, a small pile of bricks, a wooden sawhorse, and a partially built fence. Above the scene, a thought bubble shows a comedic unfinished joke being built with bricks and nails. The overall style is colorful, lighthearted, and cartoonish, emphasizing the idea that the joke is a work in progress without any pressure or stress.'),
 (577, 'Aging, Don''t Say It!, Humor, Social Commentary', 'I had a joke about Social Security, but most Baby Boomers won''t get it', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two groups of people, clearly differentiated by age. On the left, a younger person, perhaps in their 20s or 30s, is holding a microphone or telling a joke with a speech bubble showing the text: ''I had a joke about Social Security, but most Baby Boomers won''t get it.'' On the right, a group of Baby Boomer-aged characters look confused or bewildered, scratching their heads or raising eyebrows. The background can have subtle hints like a calendar showing a recent year and maybe a Social Security card or symbol floating faintly behind to emphasize the topic. The style should be light-hearted and exaggerated to keep a humorous and friendly tone. The characters should have expressive faces to highlight the generational gap in understanding the joke, with the younger group smiling and the Baby Boomers appearing puzzled.'),
 (578, 'Bad Puns, Don''t Say It!, Food Humor', 'I was going to share a vegetable joke, but it''s corny', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful ear of corn standing upright with a big, friendly grin. The corn should have cartoonish eyes and arms, holding a microphone as if about to tell a joke on a small stage. Around it are audience members that are various vegetables like a smiling carrot, a broccoli with glasses, and a tomato laughing. The background shows a simple comedy club setting with a small spotlight over the corn and a brick wall behind. Include a small sign on the wall reading ''Vegetable Comedy Night.'' The overall mood is light and funny, emphasizing the pun ''corny'' through the main character being literally corn ready to deliver a joke but hesitating.'),
 (579, 'Bad Puns, Don''t Say It!, Sports Humor', 'I''m not a big fan of archery - it has too many drawbacks', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon of a cheerful cartoon character standing next to an archery target. The target is full of arrows stuck in it, but some arrows are humorously bent, broken, or stuck in awkward places like the floor or the character''s quiver. The character is holding a bow limply with a slightly disappointed or unimpressed expression, shrugging their shoulders. A speech bubble above the character reads, ''I''m not a big fan of archery - it has too many drawbacks.'' In the background, include a few comical ''drawbacks'' such as arrows bouncing off tough objects like trees or arrows tangled in a nearby bush. The scene should be bright and colorful, emphasizing the lighthearted and silly nature of the pun without any aggressive or negative imagery.'),
 (580, 'Don''t Say It!, Puns, Sports Humor', 'Jokes about bowling aren''t really funny, so I''ll spare you the pain', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene of a bowling alley with colorful bowling lanes and pins. In the foreground, a character with a friendly, slightly embarrassed expression is holding a bowling ball loosely at their side, shrugging. Above or beside them, a speech bubble says, "Jokes about bowling aren''t really funny, so I''ll spare you the pain." The scene should include pins set up at the end of the lane, a ball return machine, and perhaps a small scoreboard showing a low score. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions, bright colors, and clean lines to emphasize the playful mood without any aggressive or negative imagery.'),
 (581, 'Bad Puns, Don''t Say It!, Health Humor, Humor', 'People think my diabetic jokes are harsh, but hey - it''s not like I can sugarcoat them', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person standing at a comedy club stage with a microphone. The backdrop has a sign saying ''Comedy Night''. The person should have a playful smirk and be gesturing with one hand while holding the microphone in the other. Nearby, a big sugar cube shaped like a microphone stand is melting, with droplets running down to the floor. Around the stage, a few audience members are shown either groaning, laughing nervously, or shaking their heads. Include a small diabetic test kit and an insulin pen casually resting on a stool next to the comedian. The overall vibe should be lighthearted and whimsical, with bright colors and exaggerated cartoon expressions to emphasize the pun about not being able to ''sugarcoat'' the jokes. Avoid any dark or serious tones.'),
 (582, 'Career Humor, Don''t Say It!, Humor, Irony', 'People used to laugh when I said I wanted to be a comedian - well - nobody''s laughing now.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small comedy club stage with a single spotlight on a sad-looking stand-up comedian holding a microphone. The comedian is a middle-aged person with a slightly disheveled appearance and a hopeful smile fading into disappointment. Around the club, the audience seats are completely empty, emphasizing that no one is laughing or watching. A small sign behind the comedian reads ''Comedy Night.'' On the floor near the comedian, a single crumpled-up joke sheet lies, with a faint laughing face doodle crossed out. The overall mood is light-hearted but depicts the irony that the comedian once dreamed of making people laugh, but now no one is laughing at all. The style should be colorful and exaggerated facial expressions, typical of the cartoon humor genre, keeping it cheerful yet fitting the joke''s tone.'),
 (583, 'Bad Puns, Bathroom Humor, Don''t Say It!', 'Poop jokes aren''t my favorite, but they''re a solid #2', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing a friendly, smiling number 2 character standing upright with arms and legs. The number 2 is made to look lively and cheerful, maybe with cartoon eyes and a big grin. Next to it, place a simple cartoon poop emoji with a similarly friendly face, looking slightly embarrassed or shy. They are standing side by side on a plain background, perhaps with a subtle joke setting like a bathroom door labeled ''Restroom'' in the background or a hint of bathroom tiles. The overall vibe should be lighthearted and silly, emphasizing the pun on ''solid #2'' with exaggerated expressions to enhance the humor.'),
 (584, 'Animals, Don''t Say It!, Humor, Puns', 'Some people say giving animals helium is just wrong, but I say - Hey - whatever floats your goat', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small confused goat floating gently in the air, tied to a big helium balloon. The goat looks surprised but calm, with a simple light blue sky background and a few fluffy clouds. Below, a person with a playful grin holds the string of the balloon. The person is shrugging as if saying ''Hey - whatever floats your goat.'' The scene should be colorful, friendly, and light-hearted, emphasizing the pun visually without any negativity or harm to the goat. Balloons and the goat should be drawn with exaggerated cartoonish features to enhance the humor.'),
 (585, 'Don''t Say It!, Humor, Pop Culture', 'What did Kermit the frog say at Jim Henson''s funeral? Nothing', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at a simple funeral outdoors with a modest wooden coffin surrounded by a few mourners looking somber but calm. At the center is Kermit the Frog, standing quietly beside the coffin. Kermit should be drawn in his classic green puppet style, with his mouth closed to emphasize silence. The setting includes some wilting flowers and a banner or sign nearby that says ''Jim Henson'' to indicate whose funeral it is. The overall style is lighthearted and respectful with soft colors and gentle details to keep the tone humorous but appropriate.'),
 (586, 'Dyslexics, Poetry, Word Play', 'A dyslexic poet writes inverse', NULL, 'A whimsical cartoon scene showing a poet sitting at a wooden desk cluttered with papers and an ink bottle with a quill. The poet looks quirky and slightly puzzled, wearing round glasses and a beret. The papers around the desk have visibly scrambled or backwards text and poetry lines written in an upside-down or inverse style, with letters and words appearing flipped or reversed. Behind the poet is a wall with a framed picture of a mirror or an inverted poem. The setting is cozy, with a softly lit room, a small stack of poetry books, and a cup of tea nearby. The overall tone is lighthearted and clever, emphasizing a playful mix-up of writing and language without any negativity. The style is a colorful, simple cartoon with exaggerated expression and visual wordplay to illustrate the ''inverse'' nature of the dyslexic poet''s work.'),
 (587, 'Dyslexics, Humor, Word Play', 'A dyslexic walks into a bra', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person standing with one foot halfway into a large, oversized bra hanging in a clothing store or lingerie shop. The person looks puzzled or slightly embarrassed, glancing down at their foot inside the bra cup as if they mistakenly walked into it instead of a door. The background should include clothing racks or shelves with bras and underwear to establish the setting. The style is lighthearted and comical, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the misunderstanding without any negativity or awkwardness.'),
 (588, 'Agnosticism, Dyslexics, Word Play', 'Did''ya hear about the agnostic dyslexic that believes there is no dog?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person standing between two large signs. One sign says ''God'' with a question mark above it, and the other sign says ''Dog'' but the letters are jumbled to represent dyslexia (e.g., ''Dgo''). The person scratches their head, with a puzzled expression, trying to decide which sign to believe. In the background, a cute cartoon dog looks bewildered, possibly tilting its head. The setting is simple, with soft colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize confusion and irony. The style is light and playful, reminiscent of classic comic strips, ensuring the tone is cheerful and non-serious.'),
 (589, 'Bad Puns, Dyslexics, Humor', 'Did''ya know there''s a special razor for dyslexics? It''s the best thing since sliced beard', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful man standing in front of a bathroom mirror holding a razor. Above him is a sign or label on the razor box that reads ''Special Razor for Dyslexics.'' The man has a neatly trimmed beard, but his beard is humorously sliced like a loaf of bread, with each slice separated and slightly floating apart to emphasize the pun. The bathroom setting includes a sink with shaving foam, a towel hanging nearby, and a small loaf of sliced bread on the counter for visual comparison. The man’s expression is proud and amused, as if excited about his new razor. The overall atmosphere is light and comical with vibrant colors and exaggerated cartoon features to emphasize the pun ''sliced beard'' playing off ''sliced bread.'' No other characters or complex backgrounds are needed to keep the focus on the joke.'),
 (590, 'Dyslexics, Humor, Language, Word Play', 'I went to the doctor and got a prescription for dailysex, but my wife insists it''s for dyslexia', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene in a doctor''s office. Show a slightly confused man sitting on an examination table holding a prescription paper with the word ''dailysex'' clearly printed on it. Nearby, his wife stands with a raised eyebrow, arms crossed, holding a dictionary or book labeled ''dyslexia.'' The doctor, a friendly-looking character wearing a white coat and stethoscope, is smiling awkwardly behind a desk, as if unsure about the mix-up. Include typical doctor office elements like a medical chart on the wall, a window with a sunny sky outside, and a few medical instruments on a nearby table. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, emphasizing the humorous misunderstanding caused by the similar-looking words ''dailysex'' and ''dyslexia.'' No background clutter or anything violent or inappropriate.'),
 (591, 'Bad Puns, Dyslexics, Word Play', 'If life gives you melons you may be dyslexic', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person standing outdoors under a bright sun, holding a large watermelon in one hand. The character has a puzzled or slightly confused expression while looking at the watermelon. Nearby, a speech bubble shows the phrase: "If life gives you melons you may be dyslexic." Around the person, a few other assorted fruits (like lemons and apples) lie on the grass to emphasize the play on words. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with bold, simple lines and bright colors to create a fun comic vibe.'),
 (592, 'Dyslexics, Puns, Word Play', 'They said I''d never be any good at poetry - but so far I''ve made 3 jugs and a vase!', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a cheerful, slightly quirky person proudly standing in a cozy pottery studio cluttered with shelves. On the shelves are three handmade jugs and a uniquely shaped vase, all colorful and clearly hand-crafted with some whimsical imperfections. The person holds a lump of clay in one hand and a potter’s tool in the other, smiling confidently. Behind them is a chalkboard with the phrase “Poetry Workshop” crossed out and replaced by “Pottery Workshop” to emphasize the wordplay. The overall style is lighthearted and humorous, with exaggerated expressions and bright, inviting colors to capture the pun on ''poetry'' sounding like ''pottery.'','),
 (593, 'Animals, Dyslexics, Word Play', 'What do dyslexic zombies eat? Brians', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two zombies in a graveyard under a full moon. One zombie looks confused, scratching its head, while the other eagerly holds out a large, realistically drawn human brain as if about to eat it. A sign nearby reads ''Brain Buffet'' with letters slightly jumbled or wobbly to hint at dyslexia. The zombies have typical cartoonish zombie features: greenish skin, tattered clothes, and exaggerated expressions. The background includes tombstones and a spooky tree, but with a lighthearted and playful atmosphere rather than scary. The brain should look a bit comical and oversized to emphasize the joke, and the zombies should appear more silly than frightening. The style is colorful and cartoonish, with clear visual cues to dyslexia and zombies combined humorously without any violence.'),
 (594, 'Dyslexics, Humor, Word Play', 'What do the letters D.N.A. stand for? National Dyslexics Association.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a group of three people standing outside a building labeled ''National Dyslexics Association'' with a big sign that has the letters ''D.N.A.'' prominently displayed. One person looks confused scratching their head, holding a biology book with a DNA double helix on the cover, while another smiles holding a welcome pamphlet labeled ''National Dyslexics Association.'' The building''s facade is playful and colorful, with a banner that reads ''Welcome Dyslexics!'' In the background, a small poster illustrates the double helix structure of DNA but humorously crossed out or replaced with scrambled letters to highlight the dyslexia joke. The style should be light-hearted, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize confusion and humor, using bright, cheerful colors and simple cartoon lines.'),
 (595, 'Dyslexics, Humor, Pirates', 'What does a Dyslexic Pirate Say? RRAAAAAAAAAAA!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a pirate with typical pirate attire: a tricorn hat, eye patch, striped shirt, and a wooden leg. The pirate is standing on a wooden ship deck with the ocean and a bright blue sky in the background. He is shouting ''RRAAAAAAAAAAA!'' very loudly, with exaggerated sound waves coming out of his mouth. Around him are amusing little details: a parrot on his shoulder looking surprised, a treasure chest in the corner, and a pirate flag fluttering above. The pirate''s expression is comically fierce but friendly, showing his enthusiasm in saying his version of a pirate yell. The style should be colorful and playful, with bold outlines and exaggerated expressions to maximize comedic effect. No violence or scary elements, just a funny interpretation of a pirate’s typical shout distorted in a dyslexic way.'),
 (596, 'Engineering, Engineers, Humor, Workplace', 'Normal: if it ain''t broke, don''t fix it. Engineer: if it ain''t broke, it doesn''t have enough features yet.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in an office or workshop. On the left side, a casually dressed person labeled ''Normal'' is holding a slightly broken gadget or machine, with a speech bubble saying, ''If it ain''t broke, don''t fix it.'' They look relaxed and confident. On the right side, an engineer wearing a shirt with a gear or circuit icon stands proudly next to a very overcomplicated, cluttered machine with many unnecessary gadgets, blinking lights, buttons, gauges, and wires everywhere. The engineer''s speech bubble says, ''If it ain''t broke, it doesn''t have enough features yet.'' The background shows tools and blueprints pinned to the wall to emphasize a technical workspace. Both characters have exaggerated, friendly cartoon expressions to enhance the humor without being aggressive or mean. The overall style is colorful, lighthearted, and playful, emphasizing the contrast between simplicity and over-engineering.'),
 (597, 'Engineering, Engineers, Humor, Pessimistic', 'Optimist: the glass is half-full. Pessimist: the glass is half-empty. Engineer: that glass is twice as big as it needs to be.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring three characters standing side-by-side, each holding a glass filled halfway with water. The first character, labeled ''Optimist,'' looks cheerful and points at their half-full glass with a big smile. The second character, labeled ''Pessimist,'' looks unhappy or worried, staring at their half-empty glass with a frown. The third character, labeled ''Engineer,'' looks analytical and amused, holding a tape measure or ruler, measuring the glass and saying something with a smirk. The glass in the Engineer''s hand is noticeably much larger than needed for the amount of water it contains, emphasizing the joke. Background is simple, clean, and bright, with a lighthearted, cartoonish style that emphasizes character expressions and the oversized glass. No other objects or complex backgrounds needed to keep focus on the three characters and their glasses.'),
 (598, 'Engineers, Humor, Jobs, Puns', 'The graduate with a science degree asks, ''Why does it work?'' The graduate with an engineering degree asks, ''How does it work?'' The graduate with an accounting k asks, ''How much will it cost?'' The graduate with an arts degree asks, ''Do you want fries with that?''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a graduation ceremony or a social gathering with four graduates standing side by side, each dressed in different but clearly identifiable graduation gowns with labels or icons representing their fields: science (wearing a lab coat with a beaker emblem), engineering (wearing a hard hat and holding a wrench), accounting (wearing glasses and holding a calculator), and arts (wearing a beret and holding a fast-food tray with fries and a drink). Each graduate has a speech bubble with their respective question: science graduate''s bubble says, ''Why does it work?''; engineering graduate''s bubble says, ''How does it work?''; accounting graduate''s bubble says, ''How much will it cost?''; arts graduate''s bubble says, ''Do you want fries with that?'' The background should be simple, perhaps on a stage or at a diploma ceremony with a banner saying ''Graduation Day,'' and the overall style is colorful and cartoonish, emphasizing each character''s personality with exaggerated expressions showing curiosity, practicality, focus on money, and casual friendliness respectively.'),
 (599, 'Engineering, Engineers, Humor', 'Two engineering students were walking across a university campus when one said, ''Where did you get such a great bike?'' The second engineer replied, ''Well, I was walking along yesterday, minding my own business, when a beautiful woman rode up on this bike, threw it to the ground, took off all her clothes and said, ''Take what you want.'' The first engineer nodded approvingly and said, ''Good choice; the clothes probably wouldn''t have fit you anyway.''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a sunny university campus with green grass and a few scattered trees. Two young male engineering students are walking side by side on a paved path. One student looks curious and is pointing at a shiny, somewhat nerdy-looking bike parked nearby. The other student appears calm and slightly smug as he tells the story. In the background, a ghostly or faint visual thought bubble shows a comical flashback: a confident, attractive woman riding the bike, suddenly throwing it down, and stepping away with a playful expression, arms wide open as if offering the bike and clothes. To keep it light and funny, the woman is drawn wearing a towel or exaggeratedly oversized sunglasses and a hat, suggesting she’s undressing but still tasteful and non-explicit. The first student’s face shows a knowing smile after his comment about the clothes not fitting. The overall style is bright, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the humor and exaggeration of the story without any inappropriate detail.'),
 (600, 'Facts, Humor, Math Humor, School', '10.0 times 0.1 is hardly ever 1.0.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon style scene featuring a classroom setting with a large blackboard in the background. On the blackboard is the math expression ''10.0 × 0.1'' written in big, bold chalk letters and below it, the answer ''1.0'' is faintly written and crossed out. In front of the board stands a quirky, slightly confused math teacher scratching their head, holding a piece of chalk. In the foreground, a student sits at a desk looking puzzled, with a thought bubble showing numbers and question marks swirling around. Around the room, small humorous math-related decorations like a calculator with googly eyes, a ruler looking surprised, and a poster saying ''Math is Fun!'' add to the lighthearted mood. The overall atmosphere is playful and educational, highlighting the joke about the uncommon but precise decimal math fact in a funny way without any tension or negativity.'),
 (601, 'Facts, Good Question!, Math Humor', '111,111,111 x 111,111,111 = 12,345,678,987,654,321', NULL, 'Draw a whimsical cartoon scene showing a giant chalkboard or whiteboard in a classroom or study room. On the board, prominently display the math equation: ''111,111,111 x 111,111,111 = 12,345,678,987,654,321'' in bold, clear handwriting. In front of it, depict a friendly, slightly nerdy-looking teacher or professor with glasses and a pointer stick, smiling proudly as if revealing a magical mathematical secret. Nearby, show a few cartoon-style students or animals looking amazed, surprised, or baffled by the long, perfectly sequential number result, with wide eyes and exaggerated expressions. Add some playful mathematical symbols floating around, like plus signs, multiplication symbols, and question marks, to emphasize the cleverness of the number pattern. The overall style should be colorful, lighthearted, and humorous, capturing the mind-blowing nature of the math trick as if it’s a fun discovery rather than a serious lesson.'),
 (602, 'Facts, Humor, Puns, Science', '186,000/mps: it''s not just a good idea, it''s the law.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a smiling, confident speedy character representing light zooming along a road at an extremely high speed. The road has a large, official-looking speed limit sign that reads "186,000 mps" (meters per second). The light character could be a bright, shining bolt or a glowing streak with eyes and a cheeky grin. Nearby, a friendly police officer is holding up a ''speed limit enforced by the laws of physics'' ticket book, pointing at the speed limit sign with a no-nonsense but comedic expression. The scene should be colorful, lively, and exaggerated to emphasize the absurdity and playfulness of enforcing physical constants like speed limits. Background can be simple, perhaps a starry sky or space theme to hint it’s the speed of light. The style should be a cartoon with clear, bold lines and expressive characters to enhance humor without any violence or negativity.'),
 (603, 'Facts, Math Humor, Puns, Science', '2 + 2 = 5 for extremely large values of 2.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in a classroom or office setting. In the center, a quirky-looking mathematician or scientist, wearing thick glasses and a lab coat, stands proudly next to a large blackboard or whiteboard. Written on the board in big, bold numbers is the equation ''2 + 2 = 5.'' Above or below the equation, in smaller handwriting, is the caption: ''for extremely large values of 2.'' The character strikes a confident pose, pointing at the equation with a pointer stick or marker. Around the character, a few puzzled onlookers with exaggerated confused expressions are scratching their heads or exchanging questioning looks. The background is simple, with a few math-related posters or charts, such as numbers, symbols, or graphs. The overall style is colorful, light-hearted, and exaggerated, emphasizing the absurdity and humor of the playful mathematical error.'),
 (604, 'Exaggeration, Facts, Humor, Science', '3026 years from now it will need to be really good or really bad. It''s 5050.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a futuristic calendar or digital clock displaying the year ''5050'' in big, bold numbers. Next to it, a quirky character (perhaps a time traveler or a futuristic historian) looks puzzled, scratching their head while holding a thick book labeled ''History of Years.'' Behind them, a simple timeline stretches from ''2023'' to ''5050,'' with a big question mark hovering over the year 5050. The background should be a light, playful futuristic cityscape with flying cars and robots casually going about their day, adding a subtle sci-fi vibe. The overall style is bright and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions on the character''s face to emphasize the joke about how, 3026 years from now, the year 5050 needs to be either really good or really bad to be notable. No violence, politics, or anything mature—just fun and lighthearted.'),
 (605, 'Animals, Facts, Good Question!, Humor', 'A camel has 3 eyelids.', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful camel standing in a sunny desert landscape with dunes and a bright blue sky. The camel, drawn with exaggerated large eyes, is winking to emphasize its unique feature. The camel''s three eyelids should be clearly visible and distinct — the top, middle, and bottom eyelids layered humorously with playful expressions on each eyelid, as if the middle eyelid is waving hello or making a funny face. Nearby, a curious desert explorer or a scientist wearing a safari hat holds a magnifying glass up to the camel’s eye, looking surprised or amazed. The style is colorful and lighthearted, with simple but expressive character designs. Include a small desert cactus and a few scattered rocks to add to the desert environment. The overall mood is playful and educational, highlighting the interesting fact about camels in a fun way.'),
 (606, 'Animals, Facts, Humor, Word Play', 'A chicken is a means for one egg to produce another.', 'George Bernard Shaw (1856-1950)', 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful chicken standing proudly in the center of a farmyard. The chicken has an exaggerated, smug expression, maybe wearing glasses or a tiny graduation cap to suggest intelligence. Around the chicken, two large eggs are depicted with friendly faces, one on each side. Between the eggs, a simple, playful arrow or dotted line connects one egg to the chicken and then another arrow leads from the chicken to the second egg, illustrating the joke that the chicken acts as a means for one egg to produce another. The background is a bright and colorful barnyard setting with a wooden fence, a few tufts of grass, and maybe a sunrise to set a joyful tone. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with bold outlines and expressive characters to clearly convey humor without text or speech bubbles.'),
 (607, 'Animals, Facts, Good Question!', 'A crocodile cannot stick out its tongue.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a friendly-looking crocodile with its mouth wide open. The crocodile is sitting on a riverbank with bright green scales and a big, goofy smile. Emphasize that its tongue is completely inside its mouth and clearly not sticking out. Nearby, a puzzled frog or bird looks up at the crocodile in amazement or confusion. Include a sunny sky, some water reeds, and a small sign next to the crocodile that reads: ''Try sticking out your tongue!'' The style should be colorful, lighthearted, and exaggerated for comedic effect, with the crocodile’s tongue noticeably hidden and the other animal reacting playfully to the fact that the crocodile cannot stick its tongue out.'),
 (608, 'Bad Puns, Facts, Objects Humor', 'A flashlight is a case for holding dead batteries.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a flashlight lying on a table. The flashlight''s body is slightly open or transparent, revealing several unhappy-looking, tiny batteries inside it. The batteries have cartoon faces with dull expressions, indicating they are ''dead'' or exhausted. Around the flashlight, scattered cartoon sparks or faint light rays struggling to shine add to the comedic effect that the flashlight isn’t working. The background can be a simple night-time indoor setting, like a dimly lit room with a small side table, to emphasize the flashlight context. The tone should be light and playful, using bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions on the batteries to highlight the joke visually.'),
 (609, 'Animals, Facts, Humor, Science', 'A snail breathes through it''s foot.', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, colorful snail with a comically exaggerated foot, like a big, fleshy shoe or sock with visible nostrils on the sole, inhaling deeply through it. The snail''s face is cheerful with big, expressive eyes and a wide smile, clearly enjoying the air intake through its foot. The background is a simple garden setting with green grass, a few flowers, and maybe a small mushroom for context. Nearby, a curious insect or small animal, like a ladybug or worm, looks up at the snail with a puzzled or surprised expression. The overall style is playful and cartoonish, using bright colors and bold outlines to emphasize the humor and absurdity of a snail breathing through its foot.'),
 (610, 'Animals, Facts, Humor', 'A snail can sleep for three years.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, sleepy snail resting comfortably on a green leafy bed. The snail should look exaggeratedly relaxed, with half-closed eyes and a tiny nightcap on its head to emphasize sleepiness. Around the snail, place whimsical elements suggesting a long nap: a calendar showing three years with pages flying off, a clock with its hands spinning, and a dust-covered book titled ''Snail Sleeping Guide.'' The background should be a peaceful garden setting with soft colors and a gentle sunny sky indicating the passage of time. The all-around vibe is light and funny, emphasizing the snail''s extended sleep rather than anything threatening or serious.'),
 (611, 'Facts, Humor, Science', 'A sneeze travels at over 100 miles per hour.', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a giant sneeze depicted as a gust of wind zooming across a suburban street at high speed. The gust should have a playful, exaggerated face with puffed cheeks and blowing lips, to personify the sneeze. The street can have everyday elements like houses, trees, a mailbox, and maybe a cat or dog being blown backwards comically by the sneeze''s force. Add motion lines to emphasize the speed of the sneeze, and a nearby person caught mid-sneeze, with wide eyes and an open mouth just letting out the powerful burst. The overall tone is light and funny with bright colors and exaggerated expressions in a cartoon style to highlight the absurdity of a sneeze traveling more than 100 miles per hour.'),
 (612, 'Facts, Humor, Pop Culture', 'Actor Tommy Lee Jones and vice-president Al Gore were freshman roommates at Harvard', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a college dorm room with two young men resembling a young Tommy Lee Jones and a young Al Gore, styled in vintage 1970s college attire. They are roommates looking awkwardly at each other while sitting on their respective beds in a small, cluttered dorm room decorated with Harvard pennants and books. One side has a poster of a serious movie on the wall behind Tommy Lee Jones, who looks disinterested or deadpan, while the other side has a poster about environmental or scientific topics above Al Gore’s side. The beds have simple bedding, and there’s a small desk cluttered with typical student items like notebooks, a lamp, and coffee cups. The scene should have a lighthearted, slightly exaggerated cartoon style, emphasizing the contrast in their personalities and future paths, with playful facial expressions and body language suggesting the humor of imagining these two famous individuals as young college roommates without any direct references to politics or jobs.'),
 (613, 'Facts, Pop Culture, Puns', 'All of the clocks in the movie ''Pulp Fiction'' are stuck on 4:20.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene inspired by a movie theater lobby with a big movie poster for ''Pulp Fiction'' prominently displayed. Around the poster, include several old-fashioned clocks hanging on the wall, all showing the exact same time: 4:20. The clocks should be exaggerated and comical, with big numbers and quirky clock hands. Include some popcorn buckets and movie tickets on a counter nearby to emphasize the cinema setting. Possibly add a few casually dressed moviegoers looking at the clocks with confused or amused expressions to add humor. Keep the overall style bright, colorful, and cartoonish with exaggerated features for comedic effect.'),
 (614, 'Animals, Facts, Good Question!', 'All polar bears are left handed.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a group of polar bears on an icy landscape. Each polar bear is playfully using its left paw for various activities, such as waving, holding a fish, or giving a thumbs-up with its left paw. One polar bear is looking confusedly at its right paw, as if trying to figure out what to do with it. The background includes icebergs and a light blue sky with a few clouds. The style is lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions on the bears to emphasize the joke. The scene is friendly and funny, avoiding anything violent or inappropriate.'),
 (615, 'Dark Humor, Facts, Marine Humor, Word Play', 'Any ship can be a minesweeper ... once.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small, simple ship labeled ''Minesweeper'' sailing on the ocean with a surprised and worried captain looking out over the bow. The ocean surface has comic-style floating sea mines with little angry faces and spikes, clearly menacing the ship. In the background, a second ship sails safely at a distance, labeled ''Regular Ship,'' looking calm and unaware. The sky is sunny with a couple of fluffy clouds. The style should be light-hearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions on the captain and the sea mines to emphasize the joke’s dark humor in a non-threatening way. Avoid any violence; focus on the imminent but comically over-the-top danger the ship is about to face.'),
 (616, 'Facts, Humor, Irony', 'Anybody can win, unless there happens to be a second entry.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two competitors standing side by side in a silly, exaggerated contest environment like a small game show stage or a backyard game setup. One competitor looks excited and confident, holding a trophy labeled ''Winner'' with a big smile. The other competitor appears frustrated or annoyed, arms crossed, facing away slightly. Between them on a small table or podium is a sign reading ''Competition''. Around them, a simple audience of cheerful or confused cartoon characters watches, some whispering to each other. The background is colorful with festive bunting or balloons to set a lighthearted, playful mood. The style is bright, friendly, and exaggerated for comic effect with no violence or negativity, emphasizing the irony of "anybody can win unless there''s a second entry."'),
 (617, 'Facts, Humor, Irony, Life', 'Anything free is worth what you paid for it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful character holding a large, brightly wrapped gift box with a big ribbon, looking proud and excited. Nearby stands another character with a skeptical or amused facial expression, pointing at the gift. The setting is a casual living room with a couch, a small coffee table, and a few scattered gift boxes labeled ''FREE.'' Above them, a speech bubble reads: "Anything free is worth what you paid for it." The style is simple and colorful, with exaggerated expressions for comedic effect, emphasizing the irony of receiving something free but questioning its value.'),
 (618, 'Facts, Good Question!, Humor, Pop Culture', 'At some point in your life, you will do an Elvis impersonation.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person mid-Elvis impersonation in a playful, exaggerated style. The character is wearing a classic Elvis-style outfit: a white jumpsuit with a high collar, flashy rhinestones, and a wide belt. They have slicked-back hair with sideburns and are striking a famous Elvis pose, one arm bent with fingers snapping, and legs apart in a dance stance. The background shows a casual room setting, like a living room with a couch, a small stage area or rug, and perhaps a mirror where the person is watching themselves perform. Include a small cat or dog looking confused or unimpressed nearby for extra humor. The colors are bright and vibrant, making the scene lively and funny without any violence or offense. The overall mood is lighthearted and celebratory, capturing the idea that everyone at some point tries to do an Elvis impersonation for fun.'),
 (619, 'Animals, Exaggeration, Facts, Sports Humor', 'Average life span of a major league baseball: 7 pitches.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a baseball stadium. Center the image around a sad, anthropomorphic baseball character with big, expressive eyes and a small frown. The baseball should have arms and legs, and be dramatically worn out with scuff marks, stitches coming loose, and sweat drops to show exhaustion. The baseball is standing near the pitcher''s mound, holding a small white flag as if surrendering. Around it, a scoreboard or sign displays the text ''Average life span: 7 pitches!'' In the background, a cheerful pitcher is winding up to throw another pitch, while teammates and fans look on with surprised or amused expressions. The style should be colorful, lighthearted, and clearly cartoonish, exaggerating the baseball''s worn-out expression and the comical short life span it depicts. Avoid any aggressive or violent poses, focusing instead on the baseball’s tired, comedic personality.'),
 (620, 'Facts, Humor, Parenting', 'Babies are born without knee caps. They don''t appear until the child reaches 2 to 6 years of age.', NULL, 'A cute, humorous cartoon scene showing a toddler crawling on the floor with their knees bent, but instead of normal knees, their knees are soft and transparent as if they have no visible knee caps. Nearby, an adult pointing with a playful smile is showing a big, colorful chart on the wall titled ''Knee Cap Development Timeline,'' with cartoon knee caps gradually appearing on kids from ages 2 to 6, illustrated by progressively bigger and shinier knee caps on cartoon children in the chart. The background is a cozy living room setting with toys scattered around to emphasize the child''s age. The style should be bright, cheerful, and exaggerated in a gentle, fun way to illustrate the interesting anatomical fact humorously.'),
 (621, 'Facts, Good Question!, Objects Humor', 'Ballpoint pens never run out of ink; they get lost.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing a frustrated person sitting at a desk cluttered with papers and several ballpoint pens scattered everywhere. The person looks confused and is searching under the desk and behind objects, clearly looking for a pen. Some pens have little cartoon footprints leading away as if they walked off. A speech bubble from the person says, ''Ballpoint pens never run out of ink; they get lost.'' The background includes a calendar and a coffee mug, giving the feel of a casual office or home workspace. The style is bright, cheerful, and exaggerated to enhance the humor without any violence or negativity.'),
 (622, 'Facts, Humor, Shopping Jokes, Word Play', 'Bargain: Something you can''t use at a price you can''t resist.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing in front of a store shelf labeled ''Bargains'' filled with unusual, impractical items like a single left sock, a broken clock, a tangled ball of Christmas lights, and an empty picture frame. The person looks puzzled but tempted, holding a price tag showing a ridiculously low price ($0.99). A cartoon thought bubble above their head reads: ''Something you can''t use at a price you can''t resist.'' The setting is a brightly lit, colorful discount store with exaggerated price tags and comically odd products. The character is dressed casually and exhibits a mix of confusion and desire, emphasizing the absurdity of buying useless items simply because they''re cheap.'),
 (623, 'Animals, Facts, Good Question!, Humor', 'Cows kill more people than sharks every year. As a matter of fact - cows don''t kill ANY sharks!', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing two animals: a large friendly-looking cow standing on dry land, maybe a farm setting with a few tufts of grass and a simple wooden fence in the background; and nearby, a confused or surprised-looking shark half-submerged in a small pond or water trough beside the cow. The cow should appear calm and innocent, while the shark looks bewildered or shocked, as if it cannot believe it''s being compared to the cow. Add a lighthearted tone with exaggerated facial expressions (big eyes, raised eyebrows) to emphasize the joke. Include a simple caption or speech bubble from the cow saying something like ''I don''t kill any sharks!'' or from the shark, ''Wait, what?'' This cartoon should be colorful, playful, and not serious or scary, delivering the irony in a fun visual way.'),
 (624, 'Animals, Facts, Humor, Pop Culture', 'Debra Winger was the voice of E.T.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused animation studio recording booth. Inside the booth is a microphone stand with a big microphone and headphones hanging nearby. A large poster of E.T., the famous alien from the movie, is on the wall behind the microphone. A female voice actress with short brown hair is nervously looking at a script titled ''E.T. Lines''. Outside the booth, two cartoon animators or sound engineers are whispering to each other, one holding a clipboard with a speech bubble showing the text ''Debra Winger was the voice of E.T.?'' The expressions on their faces are puzzled and surprised. The studio is filled with typical soundproofing panels, a mixing board with knobs and sliders, and a few sci-fi props like a small glowing alien figurine on the desk. The overall style is lighthearted and silly, emphasizing the mismatch of the famous Hollywood actress Debra Winger with the iconic voice of a beloved alien character.'),
 (625, 'Facts, History Humor', 'Did you know that eye drops today use the same ingredients as were used in China 5,000 years ago?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a modern-day person holding a small bottle of eye drops and looking surprised. They are standing next to a large, ancient scroll unrolled on a table that has Chinese characters and illustrations of plants and herbs. Behind the scroll is a friendly, wise-looking ancient Chinese herbalist wearing traditional robes and a hat, pointing proudly at the scroll. Both characters appear in a lighthearted, exaggerated cartoon style with big expressive eyes. The background should be simple, perhaps showing a mix of an ancient apothecary and a modern pharmacy shelf with various eye drop bottles. This contrast highlights the joke about the timeless ingredients used in eye drops. The mood is cheerful and whimsical, with soft colors and a few floating question marks or lightbulb icons over the modern person''s head to emphasize surprise and discovery.'),
 (626, 'Facts, Humor, Language, Word Play', 'Fact: ''fasten'' and ''loosen'' have opposite meanings. Yet, attach the prefix ''un-'' to both and the words mean the same.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon-style scene showing two large word bubbles. One bubble depicts the word ''fasten'' with a smiling cartoon character trying to tie a big, knotted rope. Next to it, another bubble shows the word ''loosen'' with the same character struggling to untie the same rope. Between them, a playful character labeled ''Un-'' with a mischievous grin stands holding a big prefix banner ''un-''. Under these word bubbles, two smaller bubbles display ''unfasten'' and ''unloosen'' with the character happily waving both hands as if the words have become friends or twins. The background is simple, light color with a few comedic motion lines to emphasize the struggle and humor. The overall vibe is lighthearted and educational with a pun-filled personality.'),
 (627, 'Facts, Humor', 'Fact: the ten most frequently used words in the English language (making up about one-fourth of all our reading) are: the, of, and, a, to, in, is, I, that, it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a large, colorful, oversized book open on a table. The pages of the book are filled with giant, bold words: ''the'', ''of'', ''and'', ''a'', ''to'', ''in'', ''is'', ''I'', ''that'', ''it'', arranged in a playful, eye-catching way. The words appear to be animated characters with smiling faces and little arms, hopping around or waving cheerfully. In the background, a person wearing glasses and holding a magnifying glass is looking at the words with a curious, slightly amused expression. The setting is bright and friendly, with a simple library atmosphere including a couple of shelves with books and a cozy reading lamp. The art style is fun and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions and vibrant colors, emphasizing the funny fact about these common words dominating English text.'),
 (628, 'Facts, Humor', 'Fact: the vocabulary of the average person consists of five to  six thousand words.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting at a desk with a huge open book labeled ''Vocabulary Dictionary'' that looks thick and intimidating. The person is scratching their head, looking puzzled and overwhelmed. Around the desk are scattered flashcards with simple words like ''cat'', ''dog'', ''run'', ''jump''. In the background, a thought bubble shows a string of random letters and words jumbling up, indicating confusion. The setting is a cozy study room with a cup of coffee and a small plant on the desk. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated to emphasize the irony of having a large vocabulary but still feeling confused.'),
 (629, 'Animals, Facts, Good Question!', 'Fish cough.', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a small fish underwater inside a brightly colored coral reef environment. The fish is mid-swim with wide, surprised eyes and is depicted with exaggerated cartoon-style bubbles coming out of its mouth that resemble a cough. Around the fish, other sea creatures like a crab, starfish, and a snail look on with curious or shocked expressions. Include light beams filtering from the water surface above to add depth. The style should be playful and whimsical, with vivid underwater colors like blues, greens, and coral reds. The overall tone is lighthearted and funny, emphasizing the absurdity of a fish coughing underwater.'),
 (630, 'Facts, Food Humor, History Humor, Puns', 'Hormel Foods mad the first batch of Spam in 1937. I heard they''re going to start making the second batch sometime next month.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a retro-style kitchen or factory floor with a large, old-fashioned machine labeled ''Spam Maker 1937''. The machine has a giant lever, gears, and steam coming out, all in a comical, exaggerated style. Nearby, there''s a calendar on the wall flipping to next month, emphasizing the long pause between batches. A confused worker in 1930s attire stands next to the machine scratching his head, holding a can of Spam from 1937, while a modern worker wearing a baseball cap and holding a clipboard looks puzzled at the machine, as if he just discovered it again. The background includes vintage posters advertising Spam and a clock showing that a very long time has passed. The overall tone is light and silly, using exaggerated expressions and an old-meets-new contrast to highlight the joke about the absurd delay in making the second batch of Spam.'),
 (631, 'Animals, Facts, Good Question!, Humor', 'Humans with two legs have an above average number of legs, compared to the entire population.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing various creatures standing together on a grassy field. In the center, a confident human character with two legs stands tall and proud, smiling broadly. Around the human, there are different animals and imaginary creatures with a variety of leg counts: a snake slithering with no legs, an insect with six legs, a crab with eight legs, a bird with two legs but wings visible, and a cartoon alien with multiple legs. Above the group, a simple caption or thought bubble reads: ''Humans with two legs have an above average number of legs!'' The style is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions emphasizing surprise and curiosity on the faces of the animals as they look toward the human. The background is simple with a clear sky and a few clouds to keep focus on the characters. The overall tone is bright, colorful, and friendly.'),
 (632, 'Cartoon, Facts, Good Question!, Humor', 'If Barbie were life-size, her measurements would be 39-23-33.  She would stand 7 foot tall and have a neck twice the length of a normal human''s neck.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon of a tall, exaggerated life-size Barbie doll standing next to a normal-sized adult woman for scale. Life-size Barbie should be about 7 feet tall with a ridiculously long neck twice as long as an average human''s neck, curving slightly. She has the classic Barbie blonde hair, bright pink dress, and iconic high-heeled shoes. The woman''s expression is a mix of surprise and disbelief as she looks up at Barbie''s towering height and impossibly long neck. Include a height chart on the wall behind them, clearly showing the 7-foot mark beside Barbie. Place a measuring tape stretched vertically from Barbie''s head to her feet. The setting is a brightly lit room with pastel colors and a simple background to keep focus on the giant doll and comparison. The cartoon style should be lighthearted, with exaggerated proportions to emphasize the humor without being mean-spirited.'),
 (633, 'Animals, Facts, Humor', 'If cats COULD text you back, they would not.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting on a couch holding a smartphone with a missive screen showing a blank message screen or a question typed out but no response yet. Nearby, a cat is perched lazily on the back of the couch, looking completely indifferent with half-closed eyes and a smug expression. The cat is ignoring the phone entirely, maybe playfully batting or sitting on a tangled phone charger or phone remote. The setting is a cozy living room with soft colors and playful details to highlight the cat''s aloof personality. The person looks expectant but puzzled or frustrated, while the cat embodies complete disinterest as if texting back is a ridiculous idea. The overall vibe should be lighthearted with exaggerated expressions on both characters to emphasize the humor of cats being notoriously unresponsive to humans'' attempts at communication.'),
 (634, 'Facts, Good Question!, Puns', 'If the No. 2 pencil is the most popular pencil, why is it still No. 2?', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a yellow No. 2 pencil with a big, cheerful smile and expressive eyes standing proudly on a desk. The pencil wears a little crown or medal labeled ''#1'' to emphasize it being the ''most popular.'' Next to it, a confused or skeptical looking No. 1 pencil stands with raised eyebrows, holding a question mark sign. The background should resemble a simple classroom or office desk cluttered with scattered papers, an eraser, and a sharpener. Include a speech bubble coming from the No. 2 pencil that says, ''If I''m the most popular, why am I still No. 2?'' The overall tone is light-hearted and playful, with exaggerated cartoon-style expressions and bright colors to keep it fun and friendly.'),
 (635, 'Facts, Puns, Social Commentary, Technology Humor', 'If the software is free, YOU are the product', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a modern office environment. In the center, a cheerful software vendor (cartoon character) is enthusiastically handing out boxes labeled "Free Software" to a diverse group of people (users) who look excited and eager. Behind the vendor, a large conveyor belt humorously shows the users themselves being processed and wrapped up like products, complete with price tags and barcodes. The conveyor belt leads to a big shipping box labeled "Your Data" ready to be shipped out. The background includes computer screens with lines of code and social media icons to hint at digital services. The overall style is bright and friendly, with exaggerated expressions to enhance the comic effect, emphasizing the ironic twist that the free software users are actually the products being sold, not the software itself.'),
 (636, 'Facts, Pop Culture, Star Wars', 'James Doohan, who plays Lt. Commander Montgomery Scott on Star Trek, is missing the entire middle finger of his right hand.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a friendly and slightly surprised caricature of James Doohan as Lt. Commander Montgomery Scott from Star Trek. He is wearing his recognizable Starfleet uniform with a Star Trek insignia. The focus is on his right hand, which is clearly visible but missing the entire middle finger. Around him could be a speech bubble or a small sign with a funny or lighthearted comment alluding to the missing finger without being offensive. The background is simple, maybe a subtle spaceship interior or the Star Trek bridge, depicted in cartoon style with clean lines and bright colors. The overall mood is lighthearted and respectful, emphasizing the unique fact about the actor with playful exaggeration of his hand for comedic effect.'),
 (637, 'Animals, Facts, Humor', 'Lizards communicate by doing pushups.', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two lizards in a sunny desert setting with cacti and rocks. One lizard is lying on its belly, comically doing exaggerated pushups with small puffed cheeks of effort. The other lizard watches nearby with a cartoonish speech bubble showing simple symbols like ''Hi!'' and ''Hello!'' to suggest they''re trying to ''talk.'' The background is minimal but colorful, emphasizing the humor in lizards communicating through exercise movements rather than sound. Make the lizards cute and slightly anthropomorphic, with big expressive eyes to add charm and humor.'),
 (638, 'Celebrity Humor, Facts, Good Question!, Humor', 'Marilyn Monroe had six toes.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon-style portrait of Marilyn Monroe styled like an old Hollywood movie poster. The scene focuses on Marilyn sitting elegantly on a classic dressing room stool, looking surprised as she lifts up one foot toward the viewer. The foot humorously shows six toes, each toe exaggerated and cartoonishly rounded to highlight the extra one. The dressing room mirror behind her reflects her face with a playful shocked expression. The background includes classic Hollywood elements like bright round vanity lights around the mirror, a makeup table with brushes and lipstick, and a star-shaped nameplate that reads ''Marilyn Monroe.'' The mood is light-hearted and whimsical, with soft pastel colors and smooth, rounded lines to keep the tone funny and non-threatening. No other characters are needed in the scene.'),
 (639, 'Calendar Humor, Facts, Good Question!', 'Months that begin on a Sunday will always have a ''Friday the 13th.''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon calendar page is shown prominently in the center, with the month labeled at the top. The month starts with a big, bold Sunday highlighted in bright yellow or a cheerful color. The dates line up clearly, making the 13th day fall on a Friday, which is marked with both a smiling cartoon sun wearing sunglasses and a little mischievous black cat sitting next to the number 13. Nearby, a character (a friendly looking person or an imaginative calendar mascot) points happily at the Friday the 13th date, as if revealing a fun fact. The background is light and cheerful with subtle calendar motifs, such as a clock or leaf icons, to keep the focus on the calendar month and the connection between Sunday beginnings and Friday the 13th. The style should be clean, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the amusing relationship between the days of the week and dates without any scary or negative elements.'),
 (640, 'Animals, Facts, Food Humor, Science', 'Mosquitoes are attrracted to people who have recently eaten bananas.', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a group of playful mosquitoes eagerly flying toward a person who just finished eating a bunch of bananas. The person is standing in the center, happily holding a peeled banana with a big smile. Around the person, multiple tiny mosquitoes with exaggerated eager expressions and cartoonish big eyes are attracted, buzzing and hovering close, some wearing little noses sniffing the air. In the background, a confused person who hasn''t eaten bananas stands nearby, swatting mosquitoes away unsuccessfully. The setting is a simple outdoor park with green grass and a clear blue sky. To add to the humor, a small sign on the ground reads ''Banana Buffet: Beware!'' The overall style should be lighthearted, colorful, and funny without any dark or scary elements.'),
 (641, 'Did''ya Hear, Facts, Humor', 'On average, 100 people choke to death on ballpoint pens every year.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a group of about four funny-looking human characters standing around an oversized ballpoint pen that is lying on the ground like a big fallen log. The characters look exaggeratedly shocked and are making silly expressions of surprise or mild panic. One character is nervously pointing at the pen while another is holding their throat as if they almost choked. The setting is a simple, colorful office or school room with a desk in the background scattered with papers and a pencil holder. The oversized pen is very detailed, with a shiny tip and a bright blue or black ink tip, emphasizing its ballpoint pen nature. There are no violent elements; the tone is light and silly, capturing the funny, absurd idea that pens could be choking hazards. A small sign or chart in the background humorously reads: "100 people choke on ballpoint pens every year," reinforcing the joke in a visual way. The overall style is clean, bright, and cartoonish, focusing on exaggerated facial expressions and playful body language.'),
 (642, 'Facts, Food Humor, Good Question!, Science', 'Pearls melt in vinegar.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a shiny pearl necklace resting in a small glass bowl filled with vinegar. The pearl necklace appears sad and slightly melting, with one or two pearls drooping or slipping off the string like they are dissolving. Nearby, a curious anthropomorphic pearl (with eyes and a worried face) looks on nervously at the vinegar. Add a kitchen counter setting with a vinegar bottle labeled clearly, and maybe a confused character holding a pearl, scratching their head while reading a small chemistry book titled ''Science Facts.'' The overall style should be lighthearted and playful with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke''s punchline about pearls melting in vinegar, capturing the unexpected chemical reaction humorously without any violence or complex elements.'),
 (643, 'Facts, Puns, Word Play', 'Racecar backwards is still Racecar. Racecar upside down is very expensive.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon showing a sleek red racecar on a racetrack. The left side of the image shows the racecar from the side in a normal upright position, with a big smiling face on its windshield, looking proud. Above it, the word "Racecar" is written clearly. To the right, the same racecar is flipped upside down, showing its wheels in the air, looking surprised or shocked with wide eyes and a small speech bubble with a money symbol ($$$) to indicate expense. Floating near the upside-down car is a bright price tag dangling, labeled "$100,000" or similar. The background is a racetrack with cheering simple cartoon spectators in the stands. The style is light, fun, and exaggerated, with bold outlines and bright colors to emphasize the joke visually without any violence, politics, or inappropriate content.'),
 (644, 'Facts, Humor, Puns, Science', 'Scientists say the universe is made up of protons, neutrons and electrons. They forgot to mention morons.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a quirky scientist''s laboratory. Center the scene on a whiteboard or large chalkboard filled with a colorful, simplified diagram of an atom: a nucleus with protons and neutrons (small labeled spheres) and electrons orbiting around it. Introduce a third group of cartoon characters labeled ''morons'' — goofy-looking, silly creatures or humans with clueless expressions and exaggerated features (crossed eyes, drooling, or scratching heads) awkwardly standing or floating around the atom but clearly out of place. The scientist, wearing a lab coat, glasses, and holding a pointer, looks slightly baffled or amused standing beside the board. Add humorous props like beakers, test tubes, and atom models on tables and shelves to create a lively lab environment. Use bright, playful colors and exaggerated, rounded shapes to enhance the cartoonish, lighthearted tone without implying anything negative about actual people.'),
 (645, 'Animals, Facts, Fun Facts, Good Question!', 'Slugs have 4 noses', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful slug character in a simple garden setting (grass, a few flowers, maybe a small rock). The slug is facing the viewer with a friendly smile. On its head, prominently show four distinct, cute, and exaggerated noses arranged in a row, each with different shapes or sizes to stand out. Surround the slug with a few small insects or garden elements looking surprised or intrigued by the slug''s multiple noses. Use bright, playful colors and a lighthearted comic style, emphasizing the unusual and funny fact about the slug’s noses without any scary or unpleasant elements.'),
 (646, 'Animals, Facts, Good Question!', 'Squids can have eyes the size of a volleyball.', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a giant squid underwater with one enormous eye exaggeratedly the size of a volleyball. The squid should look friendly and a bit surprised or proud to show off its huge eye. Nearby, a scuba diver wearing classic diving gear looks amazed, with their mouth open and hands raised. Include some underwater elements like fish, seaweed, and bubbles to set the scene. The volleyball should be clearly sized compared to the squid’s eye for comic effect, perhaps with the squid holding it like a trophy or comparing the eye to a nearby actual volleyball floating underwater. The style should be playful, colorful, and light-hearted, focusing on the absurdity and fun of the squid''s huge eye size without any scary or dark elements.'),
 (647, 'Facts, Humor, Life, Word Play', 'The adult version of head, shoulders, knees and toes is wallet, glasses, keys and phone.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring an adult version of the classic children''s song ''Head, Shoulders, Knees and Toes.'' Show a cheerful adult standing upright with four labeled items on their body: a wallet positioned where the head would be, a pair of glasses resting on where the shoulders are, a set of keys hanging by the knees, and a smartphone held near the toes. The background is simple, such as a plain room or park, to keep the focus on the adult and their everyday essentials replacing body parts. Use bright, playful colors and exaggerated, funny expressions to emphasize the clever twist on the children''s rhyme. Include subtle musical notes around the adult to hint at the song, but keep the overall tone light and silly, capturing the humor of grown-up priorities.'),
 (648, 'Animals, Facts, Good Question!', 'The catfish has over 27,000 taste buds.', NULL, 'A funny cartoon scene showing an exaggerated catfish underwater, drawn with a big silly grin. The catfish should have oversized lips and whiskers, and its entire body is covered with little labeled taste buds. Around the catfish, small bubbles contain tiny flavor icons like a lemon slice, a chili pepper, a drop of honey, and a salt shaker to highlight its taste senses. The underwater background is simple with a few playful fish and water plants. Use bright, cheerful colors with a lighthearted cartoon style and include a quirky sign underwater that reads ''27,000 Taste Buds!'''),
 (649, 'Facts, History Humor, Military Humor, Word Play', 'The name Jeep came from the abbreviation used in the army for the ''General Purpose'' vehicle, G.P.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a classic military jeep in the center, painted in army green with a star on the door. Above it, a large speech bubble coming from the jeep says ''GP'' in military-style stencil font, followed by an arrow pointing to the full phrase ''General Purpose Vehicle'' written in a playful, hand-lettered style. In the background, a simple army base setting with a few tents, a soldier in green uniform scratching his head in confusion, and a signpost labeled ''Jeep History Museum.'' The overall vibe is lighthearted and educational, with exaggerated cartoon features like oversized wheels on the jeep and the soldier having a cartoonishly puzzled expression. The style should be colorful and clean with minimal detail to emphasize the joke about the abbreviation turning into the name ''Jeep.'' No violence or aggressive elements.'),
 (650, 'Books, Cartoon, Facts, Good Question!', 'The name Wendy was made up for the book ''Peter Pan''.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy old library or study room filled with shelves of books. At the center, show a cheerful author sitting at a wooden desk, writing in a large open book labeled ''Peter Pan''. Above the author’s head, depict a thought bubble with the name ''Wendy'' floating inside it, as if the author just invented it. Nearby, have a playful cartoon version of Wendy Darling with a surprised or curious expression, sitting on a pile of storybooks. The background should include classic elements from Peter Pan, like a small flying fairy with sparkles, a pirate hat on a shelf, and a globe or map pinned on the wall. The overall vibe should be light-hearted and whimsical, highlighting the origin of the character''s name in a fun, imaginative way. Use bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humor in the idea that the author simply made up the name ''Wendy'' for the story.'),
 (651, 'Facts, Humor, Language, Word Play', 'The only 15 letter word that can be spelled without repeating a letter is uncopyrightable.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful dictionary character with eyes and a big smile, holding open a page showing the word ''uncopyrightable'' highlighted in bright colors. Surround the dictionary with letters of the alphabet, each letter appearing only once, arranged neatly around the word. Next to the dictionary, draw a playful banner or label that reads ''No Repeats!'' in bold, fun lettering. The background should be simple and colorful, resembling a school or library setting, with a few scattered letters floating or bouncing lightly to emphasize the uniqueness of the word. The overall style should be lighthearted and whimsical, suitable for all ages.'),
 (652, 'Facts, History Humor, Social Commentary', 'The Pentagon in Arlington, Virginia, has twice as many bathrooms as necessary. When it was built in the 1940''s, the state of Virginia still had segregation laws requiring separate toilet facilities for blacks and whites.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon drawing of the Pentagon building, shown as a large five-sided structure labeled ''The Pentagon'' with a small sign underneath reading ''Arlington, Virginia.'' Surrounding the building are multiple exaggerated, comically oversized bathroom signs indicating separate facilities labeled ''White Restrooms'' and ''Black Restrooms'' with arrows pointing in opposite directions. The cartoon should show two distinct restroom entrances clearly marked to highlight segregation from the 1940s era. The setting includes a 1940s-style background with vintage cars and people wearing period clothing to subtly indicate the time period. The tone is light-hearted and satirical, focusing on the absurdity of the historical context related to the number of bathrooms rather than any sensitive content.'),
 (653, 'Animals, Facts, Good Question!', 'The world''s termites outweigh the world''s humans 10 to 1.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing an enormous mound of termites on one side of a scale, clearly outweighing a group of small, cartoonish humans on the other side. The termites should be exaggerated in size for comedic effect, with little smiling or busy termite characters crawling over the mound. The humans look surprised or confused as they balance precariously on their scale side. The setting is simple, with the scale standing on a neutral background, emphasizing the size difference. Lighthearted, bright colors with clear, simple lines to evoke a playful cartoon style.'),
 (654, 'Facts, Math Humor', 'There are 293 ways to make change for a dollar.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a perplexed person standing at a large shop counter labeled ''Change for a Dollar.'' The person is holding a dollar bill and looking confused at a huge, overflowing jar or box behind the counter filled with many different coins—pennies, nickels, dimes, and quarters—all jumbled together. Nearby, a shopkeeper wearing a striped apron and a quirky smile gestures at a large chalkboard or sign beside them that says ''293 Ways to Make Change for a Dollar!'' The background is a simple friendly store interior with shelves and a cash register. The style is bright, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the absurdity and complexity of so many ways to give change, creating a lighthearted and funny atmosphere without any violence or offense.'),
 (655, 'Bad Puns, Facts, Humor', 'There are 3 kinds of people: those who can count and those who can''t.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two groups of people. On the left, a small group of three people confidently counting on their fingers with happy expressions. On the right, another group looking confused and frustrated, scratching their heads or holding a calculator upside down. Above them floats a large, playful text that reads: ''There are 3 kinds of people: those who can count and those who can''t.'' The background is simple and colorful, with a classroom or casual setting (like a park bench) to keep it light and friendly. Include subtle visual cues like numbers or math symbols around to emphasize counting.'),
 (656, 'Facts, Food Humor, Good Question!', 'There are an average of 178 sesame seeds on a McDonald''s Big Mac bun.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene featuring a giant McDonald''s Big Mac bun as the central object. The bun is oversized and clearly labeled ''Big Mac Bun'' with sesame seeds visibly scattered all over the top. A cheerful cartoon character, resembling a scientist or statistician, stands next to the bun holding a clipboard and magnifying glass, counting or examining the sesame seeds with exaggerated focus. Around the bun, small speech bubbles or thought clouds float showing numbers like ''178'' with sesame seed icons. The background is a simple fast food restaurant setting with a whimsical vibe: a McDonald''s sign in the distance, a tray with fries and a soda next to the bun, and a few sesame seeds humorously floating or falling off the bun. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish with bright colors, rounded shapes, and big smiles on the character. No text except the numbers and labels on objects should be included in the image.'),
 (657, 'Facts, Math Humor, Programming, Puns', 'There are only 10 types of people in the world: Those who understand binary, and those who don''t.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring two groups of people standing on either side of a large binary numeral ''10'' prominently displayed in the center. On the left side, depict a small group of tech-savvy characters with glasses, laptops, and lightbulbs above their heads, clearly understanding the ''10'' as the number two in binary. On the right side, show a confused group scratching their heads or looking puzzled, holding question marks above their heads as they try to interpret the ''10''. The background can be a simple classroom or office setting with a whiteboard or chalkboard displaying ''There are only 10 types of people in the world'' written at the top. Keep the style light and colorful with exaggerated expressions to emphasize humor and the difference in understanding. Avoid any violence or negative stereotypes, focusing on a friendly and funny vibe emphasizing the joke about binary number knowledge.'),
 (658, 'Facts, Humor, Money Humor, Social Commentary', 'There are three classes of people: the haves, the have-nots, and the still paying for it''s.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring three distinct characters standing side by side. The first character, labeled ''The Haves,'' looks wealthy and relaxed, wearing fancy clothes with a smug smile, maybe holding a bag of money or a credit card. The second character, labeled ''The Have-Nots,'' appears frustrated or worried, in simple or worn-out clothes, empty pockets turned inside out. The third character, labeled ''Still Paying For It,'' looks tired but hopeful, holding a large receipt or bill labeled ''Loan'' or ''Installments,'' wearing casual clothes and maybe carrying shopping bags with tags that say ''Payment Plan.'' The background should be simple, like a plain city street or park, to focus on the characters. The style should be colorful and exaggerated with big facial expressions to emphasize the humor and contrast between the groups. The overall tone is lighthearted and funny, with a clear visual distinction among the three classes and a playful text bubble above each character showing the label as a part of the joke.'),
 (659, 'Facts, Good Question!, History Humor, Music Humor', 'Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star was composed by Mozazrt when he was 5 years old.', 'Snapple bottle cap', 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a very young Mozart, a five-year-old child dressed in old-fashioned 18th-century clothing (a frilly collar and a small powdered wig), sitting at a small wooden piano with a big, satisfied grin. Above him, musical notes float playfully around. In the background, a night sky visible through a window shows a bright, twinkling star with a little smile, as if approving the music. The setting is a cozy room with classical music sheets scattered on the piano and floor. The overall tone is lighthearted and whimsical, emphasizing the surprise of a child prodigy''s achievement with a fun, childlike atmosphere.'),
 (660, 'Body Positivity Humor, Good Question!', 'Can fat people go skinny-dipping?', NULL, 'A playful cartoon scene at a small, sunny pond surrounded by trees and bushes. In the foreground, a chubby person wearing a brightly colored swimsuit stands at the edge of the water, hesitating and scratching their head with a puzzled, innocent expression. The water looks inviting and sparkly. Nearby, a slimmer friend wearing sunglasses and confidently already swimming in the water, smiling and waving. A signpost by the pond humorously reads, ''Skinny-Dipping Zone.'' The overall style is lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated, rounded character designs to emphasize the humorous contrast in body types. The scene feels cheerful and silly, without any negative or mean-spirited tone.'),
 (661, 'Animals, Good Question!, Puns, Word Play', 'Can one bird make a pun? No, but toucan', NULL, 'A colorful, cheerful cartoon scene featuring two birds perched on a tree branch. One bird is a toucan with its large, distinctive beak, looking proud and playful. The other bird is smaller and more ordinary-looking, perhaps a simple sparrow, looking confused or unimpressed. Above them is a speech bubble from the smaller bird asking, ''Can one bird make a pun?'' and the toucan answering with a big smile, ''No, but toucan!'' The background is a sunny blue sky with fluffy clouds and green leaves, drawn with bright, bold colors to emphasize the lighthearted and humorous tone. The style should be whimsical and exaggerated, like a simple cartoon or comic strip, making it clear the joke revolves around the pun on ''toucan'' and ''two can.'''),
 (662, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'Can you be a closet claustrophobic?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person trying to squeeze into a small, overcrowded closet filled with clothes, boxes, and shoes. The person looks visibly uncomfortable, sweating and slightly panicked, with wide eyes and a nervous expression. The closet door is half-closed, just barely fitting the person inside. Around the closet, a neat bedroom background is visible to emphasize the contrast between the open space outside and the cramped space inside. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, using exaggerated expressions and simple, bright colors to enhance the comedic effect.'),
 (663, 'Good Question!, Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'Can you buy an entire chess set in a pawn-shop?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene inside a quaint pawn shop with a cluttered interior. In the foreground, show a customer holding up a box labeled ''Chess Set'' looking confused and asking the shopkeeper a funny question. The shopkeeper is behind the counter, slightly amused, wearing a nametag and gesturing toward a display on a shelf. On that shelf, draw oversized chess pawns and other chess pieces scattered around, with some items resembling traditional pawnshop goods like old watches, guitars, or jewelry. To add humor, include a literal pawn piece (from chess) wearing a hat or glasses to anthropomorphize it playfully. The setting should feel lighthearted with warm colors and exaggerated cartoon expressions emphasizing the pun on ''pawn'' meaning both the chess piece and the pawn shop. Overall, keep the style whimsical and friendly without any harsh lines or dark elements.'),
 (664, 'Good Question!, Humor, Irony, Social Commentary', 'Despite the cost of living, have you noticed how it remains so popular?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a lively, crowded supermarket named ''Cost of Living Mart.'' The entrance has a large, brightly colored sign with the store name. Inside, various shoppers of different ages and backgrounds happily browse aisles overflowing with everyday items like food, toiletries, and household goods. A cash register in the foreground shows an exaggeratedly high total amount, making a shopper gasp in mock surprise while still holding their full shopping basket. Nearby, a store employee gives a thumbs-up with a big smile, implying the store''s popularity despite high prices. The background includes price tags with comically inflated numbers, but the shoppers look cheerful and engaged. The overall style is cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the ironic humor of the cost of living still being ''popular'' or in demand, despite its expense. The tone is lighthearted and playful, with no violence or negativity.'),
 (665, 'Animals, Bible Humor, Good Question!, Puns', 'Did Noah keep his bees in archives?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon featuring Noah''s Ark floating on calm water with a large wooden box labeled ''ARCHIVES'' prominently on the deck. Around the box, several cartoon bees with tiny wings and cheerful expressions are buzzing and hovering. Noah, a kindly old man with a long beard and biblical attire, is smiling and pointing at the box as if explaining it to a pair of curious animals nearby, such as a giraffe and a lion. The sky is bright with a rainbow in the background, enhancing the lighthearted and punny atmosphere. Make sure the bees look cute and friendly, and the ark is recognizable with animals peeking out from the windows or decks, but no other distractions. The scene should have a playful, whimsical cartoon style, emphasizing the pun on ''archives'' as a place where bees might be kept by Noah.'),
 (666, 'Good Question!, Humor, Time Humor', 'Did you know that the next second is really only a second away?  OOPS - you missed it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a large, playful clock with a surprised face looking at its own ticking second hand. The second hand is just moving past the number one, symbolizing the next second that has just passed. Nearby, a cheerful character with wide eyes and an open mouth, as if they just realized something, looks slightly confused or shocked, pointing at the clock. The background is simple and colorful with floating, whimsical numbers around to emphasize the concept of time passing quickly. Include little motion lines around the second hand to show it just moved. The style should be lighthearted and funny, suitable for all ages, with no complex or abstract elements.'),
 (667, 'Christmas, Good Question!, Humor', 'Didn''t you ever wonder how Santa Claus got into your house when you didn''t even have a chimney?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy living room decorated for Christmas, with a Christmas tree, presents underneath, and festive decorations like stockings and lights. In the center, show a puzzled child looking toward a surprised Santa Claus who is standing awkwardly next to a closed fireplace that clearly has no chimney above it. Santa should be wearing his classic red suit and hat, scratching his head or shrugging with a comical expression as if unsure how he got in. The room should also include a window with curtains drawn, adding to the mystery. Overall, the style should be light and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions and bright colors to emphasize the fun and whimsical nature of the question about Santa’s entry method without a chimney.'),
 (668, 'Animals, Good Question!, Puns', 'Did''ya hear about the chameleon that couldn''t change color? He had a reptile dysfunction', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene featuring a frustrated chameleon sitting on a leafy tree branch. The chameleon looks confused and sad, with wide eyes and drooping posture. Surrounding it are bright leaves and colorful flowers, but the chameleon is a dull, unchanging gray color, clearly standing out. Nearby, another chameleon character (happy and colorful) looks on sympathetically or puzzled. Include a small, humorous sign hanging from the branch that reads ''Reptile Dysfunction Clinic.'' The style should be lighthearted and whimsical, with rounded shapes and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke without any harshness. The background is a simple jungle environment with vibrant greens and a clear sky. The overall tone is playful and silly, capturing the humor of the chameleon’s unfortunate condition in a cartoon style.'),
 (669, 'Good Question!, Humor, Puns, Workplace', 'Do cemetery workers prefer the graveyard shift?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a spooky but lighthearted cemetery at nighttime. In the foreground, two cemetery workers dressed in typical work clothes (reflective vests, work boots, and hats) stand near an open grave holding shovels. One worker looks tired, yawning and holding a coffee mug labeled ''Graveyard Shift.'' The other points to a nearby clock on a tombstone, showing a late night hour (around midnight). In the background, tombstones, trees, and a softly glowing full moon create a classic graveyard atmosphere. To add humor, a friendly ghost floats nearby, wearing a nightcap and holding a sign that says ''Welcome to the graveyard shift!'' The overall style is a lighthearted, colorful cartoon with exaggerated expressions on the workers'' faces to emphasize the pun on ''graveyard shift.'' No scary or scary elements, just a funny play on words in a whimsical setting.'),
 (670, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Good Question!', 'Do hungry crows have ravenous appetites?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a crow perched on a tree branch, looking enthusiastically at a picnic table filled with various food items. The crow has a cheeky, eager expression and is wearing a little bib to emphasize its hunger. On the picnic table are plates with food such as sandwiches, fruit, and crumbs scattered around. In the background, other woodland animals like squirrels and rabbits watch the crow with amused expressions. The setting is a bright, sunny park with green grass and a few trees. The style is colorful and lighthearted, with exaggerated facial expressions to bring out the humor of the crow being ''ravenous.'' No text is included in the image, but the visual should clearly evoke the pun linking ''crows'' and ''ravenous appetites.'''),
 (671, 'Geography Humor, Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'Do people in Australia call the rest of the world ''up over''?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful Australian person, wearing a stereotypical Aussie hat with corks dangling and holding a boomerang, standing on a small globe or planet labeled ''Australia.'' The globe is tilted so Australia is shown at the bottom with a label ‘Down Under’ to emphasize position. Above, a group of diverse people representing the rest of the world look up curiously from a floating platform or cloud labeled ''Up Over.'' The Australian is pointing upward toward the group, with a puzzled but playful expression. The background is bright and cheerful with a simple blue sky, and arrows or dotted lines could show ''up'' and ''down'' directions humorously reversed. The style is light, cartoonish, and friendly with exaggerated features for comedy, avoiding any stereotypes beyond lighthearted Australian icons and globe representation. There are speech bubbles suggesting the question, but no text needed inside the drawing itself.'),
 (672, 'Good Question!, Humor, Irony, Philosophy Humor', 'Do people who think they know everything really know everything?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing confidently with their arms crossed and a smug smile, wearing glasses and a casual outfit, in the middle of a simple room. Above their head is a big thought bubble filled with a jumbled mix of question marks, exclamation points, and random symbols to represent confusion and uncertainty. Surrounding the person are smaller floating question marks and light bulbs that are turned off, emphasizing doubt. The background is minimalistic with a bookshelf and a small table holding an open book titled ''Everything There Is To Know''. The overall style should be lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the irony of someone who thinks they know everything but clearly doesn’t. The cartoon style should be vibrant and exaggerated, with expressive facial features and clean lines to highlight the comedic effect.'),
 (673, 'Aviation, Bad Puns, Good Question!, Jobs', 'Do pilots take crash-courses?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a confused pilot standing beside a small airplane on a runway. The pilot is wearing a classic pilot''s uniform with a hat and sunglasses, scratching their head in puzzlement. Next to the pilot is a large, colorful book titled "Crash Courses" with an image of a plane on the cover. Around them are speech bubbles with question marks, emphasizing confusion. The background is a simple airport runway with a control tower far in the distance, and the sky is clear and bright. The overall style is light-hearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the pun in the joke about ''crash courses.'' No violent or serious elements – just a fun take on wordplay involving pilots and learning courses.'),
 (674, 'Animals, Good Question!, Puns, Science', 'Do radioactive cats have 18 half-lives?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a quirky laboratory with a whiteboard covered in scientific formulas and a big chart titled ''Radioactive Half-Lives.'' In the center, a comically exaggerated cat with bright green glowing stripes and a slightly frazzled, surprised expression sits on a lab table. The cat is surrounded by test tubes, Geiger counters with happily clicking needles, and a scientist wearing oversized glasses, holding a calculator and scratching their head in confusion. Nearby, a large poster on the wall humorously illustrates the concept of half-life using slices of cheesecakes gradually disappearing. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors emphasizing the cartoon style and making the radioactive theme fun rather than scary. No dark or serious elements are included.'),
 (675, 'Cartoon, Good Question!, Puns, Space Humor', 'Do stars clean themselves with meteor showers?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in outer space showing a big, bright star personified with a friendly face, big eyes, and a wide smile. The star is holding a large cartoon-style broom or mop, sweeping or cleaning space dust off its glowing surface. Around the star, several small meteors are flying toward it like a shower of droplets, as if they are water droplets falling to help clean the star. Include a backdrop of sparkly stars, planets in the distance, and a dark starry sky to set the space environment. The overall tone is lighthearted, colorful, and playful, with exaggerated expressions on the star to show it enjoying or responding to the ''meteor shower cleaning.'' The style should be simple, bright, and cartoonish to emphasize the joke visually without any threatening or negative imagery.'),
 (676, 'Computers, Good Question!, Holiday Humor, Puns', 'Do you know why computer scientists confuse Christmas and Halloween? Because 31 OCT = 25 DEC.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a computer scientist sitting at a desk cluttered with tech gadgets and empty coffee cups. On one side of the desk, there is a small decorated Christmas tree with lights and ornaments. On the other side, there is a pumpkin carved with a silly face, glowing from inside. A computer monitor in front of the scientist displays the code snippet ''31 OCT = 25 DEC'' in large font. The scientist looks puzzled yet amused, scratching their head. The background includes typical office elements such as shelves with programming books, a calendar flipped to December, and a small stack of Halloween candy. The overall style is colorful and playful to convey the nerdy humor about number systems (octal and decimal) mixing holiday dates.'),
 (677, 'Good Question!, History Humor', 'Do you think that when they asked George Washington for ID that he just whipped out a quarter?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at a modern-day convenience store or security checkpoint. George Washington, depicted in classic 18th-century attire with a powdered wig and colonial coat, stands at the counter holding up a large quarter coin prominently in front of a cashier or security guard who looks confused or surprised. The quarter shows George Washington''s face clearly, and the setting includes a small sign saying ''Please show ID''. The cashier is wearing a typical uniform and name tag, with a raised eyebrow expression. The background shows shelves with snacks or typical store items to place the scene in a present-day setting, contrasting with Washington''s historical appearance. The style should be light, colorful, and exaggerated in a friendly cartoon manner emphasizing the humor of using a quarter as ID.'),
 (678, 'Good Question!, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'Does killing time damage eternity?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a giant hourglass labeled ''Time'' with some grains of sand personified as little characters inside. One tiny character is holding a pickaxe, chipping away at the sand inside the hourglass as if ''killing time.'' Outside the hourglass, a relaxed and slightly confused-looking figure representing ''Eternity'' is standing or floating with an exaggeratedly calm expression, unaffected, surrounded by an infinite starry sky or a never-ending looping symbol (like an infinity sign). The setting is surreal and playful, emphasizing the absurd idea of harming something infinite by messing with something finite, with bright colors and simple, exaggerated shapes to enhance the cartoon effect. No violence, just whimsical interaction between time and eternity.'),
 (679, 'Good Question!, Puns, Science', 'Does the name Pavlov ring a bell?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon showing a man standing next to a large bell. The man looks thoughtful and slightly confused, scratching his head. Behind him is a simple classroom or laboratory setting with a chalkboard that has a simple drawing of a dog and a bell, referencing Pavlov''s classical conditioning experiment. The bell is large, shiny, and prominently displayed to emphasize the pun. Include a small, happy cartoon dog sitting nearby, looking expectantly at the bell. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions to convey the pun''s humor visually.'),
 (680, 'Family, Good Question!, Humor, Life', 'Ever notice that when you move your couch you find many unusual items?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person in a casual home setting lifting or pushing a couch to one side, revealing a cluttered floor space underneath and behind it. The floor under the couch is scattered with an assortment of unusual, unexpected items like a lone sock, a forgotten TV remote, a sandwich, an old shoe, a family photo frame, a rubber duck, coins, and maybe a stray cat or a small plant pot. The person has a surprised and amused expression, with wide eyes and raised eyebrows, clearly discovering these odd objects. The room should feel cozy but slightly messy, with a lamp, a coffee table, and a rug visible. The style is bright and cartoonish, emphasizing exaggerated facial expressions and the random nature of the hidden items, to capture the relatable humor of everyday life discoveries.'),
 (681, 'Food Humor, Good Question!, Humor, Puns', 'Ever slip a bar of chocolate into your pocket, ''just for a second''?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene centered around a person standing with a slightly guilty and sheepish expression, holding their empty pocket turned inside out. Behind them, another person is catching them mid-act, pointing at the pocket with a playful smirk. On the ground near the first person, a small half-eaten bar of chocolate wrapper is crumpled. The setting is casual, like a living room or a candy store, with a few exaggeratedly large chocolate bars on a table nearby. The style is light-hearted and colorful, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the joke about ''just for a second'' slipping chocolate into a pocket leading to inevitable snacking. No violent or negative imagery, just fun and relatable mischief involving chocolate and pockets.'),
 (682, 'Good Question!, Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Ever stop to think, and forget to start again?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in the middle of a park with a confused and puzzled expression. The person is holding a large, exaggeratedly detailed thought bubble above their head, which contains a swirling spiral representing their thoughts getting lost. Around them are humorous visual clues: a small, forgotten to-do list floating in the air, a clock showing time passing, and a tiny cartoon bird perched on their shoulder looking equally bemused. The background is a simple, friendly park with a bench, a tree, and a winding path that loops back on itself, symbolizing the idea of forgetting to resume thinking. Use bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to enhance the lighthearted, relatable nature of the joke.'),
 (683, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'Ever walk into a room full of mind readers playing charades?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy living room where a group of people are playing charades. The room has a round coffee table strewn with game cards and snacks. Around the table, multiple characters look confused and surprised, scratching their heads or wide-eyed, as if caught off guard by the game. One person is miming dramatically, while another nearby looks like they’re reading minds, with cartoon-style glowing eyes or a lightbulb above their head. A third character is holding their forehead as if struggling, and the background shows a playful atmosphere with a game scoreboard on the wall. The overall vibe is light, fun, with exaggerated cartoon expressions emphasizing the irony of mind readers playing a guessing game where reading minds would give an unfair advantage.'),
 (684, 'Good Question!, Humor, Philosophy Humor', 'Have you ever imagined a world with no hypothetical situations?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a whimsical, colorful imaginary world. In the foreground, show a thought bubble coming from a puzzled person sitting on a bench, looking confused and scratching their head. The thought bubble contains various quirky, abstract sketches of ''hypothetical situations,'' such as a flying pig, a talking clock, and a dragon riding a bicycle, all crossed out with big red ''X'' marks. Behind the person, depict a dull, gray, and overly plain cityscape symbolizing a world without imagination or hypotheticals—empty streets, identical gray buildings, and no signs of inventive or creative ideas. The overall tone should be lighthearted and funny, with exaggerated facial expressions and fantasy elements that emphasize the contrast between a lively imaginative world and the dull reality without hypothetical situations. Use bright colors for the imaginative bubble and muted tones for the background to increase the comedic effect.'),
 (685, 'Animals, Good Question!, Puns', 'Have you ever seen a toad on a toadstool?', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing a small, cute toad sitting comfortably on top of a large, classic red-and-white spotted toadstool mushroom. The toad looks slightly surprised or puzzled, with big, wide eyes, as if caught in an unexpected situation. Around them is a whimsical forest floor with green grass, small flowers, and other smaller mushrooms. The lighting is bright and cheerful, emphasizing the playful and lighthearted mood of the joke. The style is simple and exaggerated, with bold outlines and vibrant colors. The focus is on the toad perched on the toadstool, clearly showing the pun visually.'),
 (686, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'How can there be self-help ''groups''?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a small group of people sitting in a circle for a self-help meeting. Each person looks confused or puzzled, scratching their heads or shrugging. There is a large banner behind them that reads ''Self-Help Group'' with quotation marks around ''Help'' to hint at irony. In the center, one person raises their hand as if asking the question, ''How can there be self-help "groups"?'' The room is simple, with chairs arranged in a circle, a small table with a box of tissues, and a calming plant in the corner. The characters have exaggerated cartoon expressions of bewilderment. The style is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the confusion around the oxymoron of a ''self-help group.'' No dark or serious tones.'),
 (687, 'Good Question!', 'How come in baseball when you strike out it''s bad, and in bowling it''s good?', NULL, 'Single-panel, split-scene cartoon with a vertical dividing line down the middle showing two contrasting sports moments side-by-side.Left side (baseball):- A dejected batter at home plate, shoulders slumped, helmet tipped forward over his eyes. His bat lies on the ground beside him.- The umpire behind the catcher has one hand raised and a stern expression; big red letters above read “STRIKEOUT” with a flashing X.- Background: a small, disappointed crowd with slumped faces and a concession-stand sign that says “Broken Dreams Hot Dogs.”- Color palette: classic baseball greens and muted tones to emphasize gloom.Right side (bowling):- A jubilant bowler mid-pose with fist pumped and a huge grin. The bowling ball has just hit the pocket; pins are exploding upward like confetti.- Above them, a scoreboard flashes “STRIKE!” in bright, celebratory letters with stars and confetti graphics.- Background: enthusiastic fans cheering, a banner reading “Perfect!” and a gutter decorated with party streamers.- Color palette: bright, warm colors (yellow, orange) to show celebration.Add exaggerated, cartoony expressions, motion lines (swing arc on left, pins flying on right), and a small caption at the bottom: “Same word. Different outcome.”'),
 (688, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'How do you get off a non-stop flight?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a commercial airplane cabin. The airplane is shown mid-flight with clouds and sky visible through small oval windows. At the center aisle, a frustrated passenger is standing up, wearing casual clothes and looking confused or worried, as if trying to figure out how to get off the plane despite the flight being non-stop. Other passengers sit in their seats around them, some looking amused or puzzled. The flight attendant nearby is shaking their head or shrugging with a friendly smile, indicating that getting off isn''t possible yet. The airplane''s cabin should have typical details like overhead bins, seatbacks with tray tables, and the aisle carpet. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humor of trying to exit a non-stop plane mid-flight, an obviously impossible task. No violent or inappropriate elements, just a funny visual of the literal interpretation of the joke question.'),
 (689, 'Animals, Good Question!, Humor', 'How do you lift an elephant with one hand? You can''t, because elephants don''t have any hands.', NULL, 'Create a humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing next to a very large elephant. The person is looking perplexed and holding up one hand as if trying to figure out how to lift the elephant. The elephant should be very large, with an expression of calm confusion, and clearly have only four legs and a trunk—no hands. Around them, add a few humorous details like a speech bubble above the person reading, ''How do you lift an elephant with one hand?'' and a thought bubble from the elephant saying, ''I don''t have any hands!'' The background should be simple, maybe a savannah or plain park setting, to keep the focus on the interaction. The style should be exaggerated and cartoony, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke''s silliness.'),
 (690, 'Good Question!, Humor, Puns, Steven Wright', 'How do you tell when you''re out of invisible ink?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person holding a pen labeled ''Invisible Ink'' and staring at a completely blank white sheet of paper on a desk. The person is scratching their head in puzzlement, eyebrows raised, with a small question mark above their head. The background is a light, cheerful office or study room with a bookshelf, a cup of coffee, and some colorful stationery scattered around. To emphasize the joke, a faint outline of invisible writing can be shown on the paper, slightly shimmering or glowing to hint that there was supposed to be words but none are visible. The style should be bright, simple, and playful, highlighting the irony that invisible ink leaves no visible trace, and hence it is impossible to tell when it''s empty. No people or expressions should appear frustrated or angry, just lighthearted confusion.'),
 (691, 'Good Question!, History Humor', 'How do you write zero in Roman numerals?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in an ancient Roman classroom. In the center, a Roman teacher in traditional toga stands at a large stone tablet easel, holding a piece of chalk. He looks puzzled or shrugging. Facing him, a group of cartoon Roman students dressed in tunics sit at stone desks, some scratching their heads or shrugging as well. The teacher is writing Roman numerals on the board: I, V, X, L, C, D, M. At the bottom of the board, there is a big question mark next to an empty space where ''zero'' would be. Around the classroom, classic Roman decorations like columns and laurel wreaths are visible. The mood is lighthearted and funny, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the confusion about how to represent zero in Roman numerals. No one appears upset—just playfully puzzled by the concept of zero being absent in Roman numeral system.'),
 (692, 'Good Question!, Puns, Science, Space Humor', 'How does NASA organize a party? They planet', NULL, 'Draw a colorful, humorous cartoon scene depicting an outer space party organized by NASA. In the foreground, a friendly astronaut stands next to a large, round table shaped like a planet with rings, resembling Saturn. The table is decorated with party items like cups, snacks, balloons, and a banner that says ''Party Time!'' floating in zero gravity. Around the table are small planets with faces, wearing party hats and holding tiny cups, as if attending the party. In the background, a rocket ship with NASA logos hovers and emits festive lights and confetti. Stars and other celestial bodies sparkle against a dark space backdrop. The astronaut holds a clipboard labeled ''Plan-et Party Checklist'' with a checklist showing checkmarks. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with bright, cheerful colors emphasizing the pun on ''planet'' and ''plan it.'''),
 (693, 'Good Question!, Humor, Science, Word Play', 'How is mercury a liquid at room temperature, yet a large solid when orbiting close to the sun?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon split scene with two panels side by side. On the left, show a small, shiny mercury thermometer personified as a quirky liquid character, lounging casually in a cozy living room labeled ''Room Temperature.'' The mercury liquid character should appear relaxed, maybe with sunglasses and a drink, sitting on a couch shaped like a thermometer. On the right panel, depict the planet Mercury near a blazing sun, but humorously exaggerated as a big, solid block of ice or a heavy ice cube wearing a sun hat and sweating nervously from the intense heat, standing on a small rocky terrain labeled ''Orbiting Close to the Sun.'' Add some humor by showing the sun frowning or looking puzzled at this paradox. The overall tone is light and funny, in a colorful, simple cartoon style with exaggerated facial expressions on both characters and objects to capture the joke about mercury''s different states in two contexts: the element and the planet.'),
 (694, 'Cultural Humor, Efficiency Humor, Good Question!', 'How many Germans does it take to screw in a light bulb? Just one. They are very efficient and not very funny.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene illustrating the joke about Germans and efficiency. Draw a single German person, dressed in stereotypical, light-hearted traditional German attire (like lederhosen, a hat with a feather, or a simple modern outfit with a name tag saying ''Efficient Worker''). They are standing on a small step stool, confidently screwing in a shining light bulb into a plain ceiling socket. Around them are several unscrewed light bulbs lying neatly in a row, showing the work was quick. In the background, include a wall clock with its hands moving very fast, emphasizing speed and efficiency. The character should have a serious, focused expression to contrast humorously with a thought bubble containing a blank face or a simple ''...'' to imply not very funny. Use bright, friendly colors and exaggerated cartoon style, with clean lines and simple backgrounds to keep the focus on the character and light bulb. Avoid any negative stereotypes or harsh elements, focusing instead on the idea of efficiency and the joke’s punchline about humorlessness.'),
 (695, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'How many of you believe in telekinesis? Raise my hands...', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a casual setting, such as a small auditorium or classroom. A quirky, slightly nerdy character stands at the front, facing an audience of diverse people sitting in chairs. The character has a half-serious, half-smiling expression and is holding up both their own hands. The audience members, puzzled and looking around at each other, have their hands down, clearly not raising anyone else''s hands. To exaggerate the joke, a few people''s hands are awkwardly mid-air, but not coordinated, and some are just staring at the speaker. The setting includes details like a whiteboard behind the speaker with the words “Telekinesis Survey” written at the top. The tone is light and goofy, with exaggerated facial expressions showing confusion and mild amusement. Include playful speech bubbles: from the speaker saying “Raise my hands...” and from an audience member expressing bewilderment. The style is colorful, cartoonish, and simple, emphasizing the absurdity of expecting the audience to physically raise the speaker’s hands telekinetically.'),
 (696, 'Good Question!, Hardware Humor, Programming, Workplace', 'How many programmers does it take to change a lightbulb? None. It''s a hardware problem.', NULL, 'Draw a colorful, humorous cartoon scene featuring a frustrated programmer sitting at a messy desk cluttered with computer parts, monitors, and coffee mugs. The programmer is wearing glasses and a hoodie, staring at a dark lightbulb screwed into a ceiling fixture above them. Nearby, a confused-looking person holding a screwdriver is trying to twist the lightbulb, while the programmer waves a hand dismissively or points toward a computer tower. The background should include tech gadgets, wires, and posters about coding. The mood is light and playful, emphasizing the stereotype that programmers don’t fix hardware issues, only software. The overall style should be exaggerated and cartoonish with bright colors and expressive faces to capture the humor without violence or negativity.'),
 (697, 'Good Question!, Science, Word Play', 'How many weeks are there in a light year?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a confused scientist or student standing in front of a large blackboard filled with complex math and physics formulas related to light speed and time. The character scratches their head, looking puzzled and holding a ruler or calendar. Floating nearby is a playful lightbulb with legs and a face, walking along a path marked with weeks and calendars, symbolizing the pun on a ''light year'' confused as weeks. The background should have stars and outer space elements to hint at astronomy, but the setting is clearly a classroom or study with humorous, exaggerated expressions and props to highlight the joke''s confusion between ''light year'' as a distance and ''weeks'' as a time measurement. The overall style is colorful and cartoonish, with exaggerated features and lighthearted vibe, making the pun approachable and visually funny without any negativity or aggression.'),
 (698, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'If a book about failures doesn''t sell, is it a success?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a bookstore with a large, prominently displayed book titled ''Failures'' on a stand. The book has a sad face drawn on its cover to personify failure. Around the stand, there are very few people, and the books have visible price tags with a downward arrow indicating poor sales. A cartoonish salesman or store clerk scratching their head with a puzzled expression while holding a sales report showing zero sales. Nearby, a big sign reads ''Bestseller?'' with a question mark, emphasizing the irony. The background is colorful and cheerful, contrasting with the pun in the joke. The overall tone is lighthearted and funny, with exaggerated facial expressions on the characters and the book to highlight the irony of the joke.'),
 (699, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'If a jogger runs at the speed of sound, can he still hear his walkman?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a jogger running at lightning speed, depicted by motion blur lines and speed streaks behind them. The jogger wears typical running clothes and a classic walkman with headphones. Around the jogger''s head, sound waves or musical notes are illustrated trying to catch up with him but trailing far behind. The background shows a park with trees and a winding path, emphasizing movement. The jogger has a slightly puzzled or amused expression, glancing back at the walkman. The colors are bright and playful to emphasize the humor and cartoon style. Include a speedometer hovering nearby showing an exaggerated speed labeled ''Speed of Sound.'' No violent or inappropriate elements, just lighthearted and imaginative.'),
 (700, 'Food Humor, Good Question!, Puns', 'If a parsley farmer is sued, can they garnish his wages?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a small, sunny farm. In the foreground, a quirky parsley farmer wearing overalls and a straw hat stands looking surprised and a bit worried. Next to him is a large, leafy parsley plant with bright green leaves. To the side, two cartoonish, serious-looking business characters in suits hold a legal document labeled ''Lawsuit Notice.'' One of them points at the parsley plant, while the other holds out a briefcase with dollar signs on it. Above the scene, a playful, large text bubble contains the joke: ''If a parsley farmer is sued, can they garnish his wages?'' The background includes a simple farmhouse, a wooden fence, and a few garden tools whimsically arranged. The overall style is colorful, lighthearted, and exaggerated to emphasize the pun on ''garnish'' — both the herb and the legal term, making the farmer look both confused and clever.'),
 (701, 'Animals, Good Question!, Puns', 'If a pig can''t squeal, does that mean it''s disgruntled?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene with a confused pig standing in a typical farmyard setting, looking sideways with a puzzled expression. The pig should have a small speech bubble containing a question mark or a little scribble to show confusion. Around the pig, include a classic red barn and some hay bales, with a few farm animals like a chicken or a cow looking curiously at the pig. Make sure the pig looks normal but silent—no open mouth, indicating it can''t squeal. Emphasize a light-hearted, playful style with bright colors and round shapes to keep the tone very friendly and funny. Include a small signpost near the pig that says ''Disgruntled?'' as a visual pun to reinforce the joke''s wordplay. The whole scene should look like a single panel comic strip with a clean and simple background to keep focus on the pig and the pun.'),
 (702, 'Good Question!, Humor, Military Humor', 'If a stealth bomber crashes in a forest, will it make a sound?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a dense, lively forest with tall trees, bushes, and animals like birds, deer, and squirrels peeking out curiously. In the center, a sleek, black stealth bomber plane is humorously half-crashed into the ground or tangled in the trees, but it looks almost invisible or camouflaged with shadowy or transparent effects to suggest its stealthiness. The animals nearby have exaggerated confused or surprised expressions, some with tilted heads as if wondering if they heard anything. A question bubble floats above the scene asking, ''If a stealth bomber crashes in a forest, will it make a sound?'' The style is lighthearted and colorful, with soft outlines typical of cartoons to keep the tone funny and clean.'),
 (703, 'Good Question!, Puns, Word Play, Workplace', 'If a train station is where the train stops, what is a work station?', NULL, 'A colorful, funny cartoon scene showing two contrasting ''stations'' side by side. On the left, a classic train station with a cartoon train stopped at the platform, steam puffing and a big station sign saying ''Train Station.'' On the right, a humorous take on a ''work station'' — a cluttered office desk with a computer, keyboard, coffee mug, papers, and an overwhelmed, tired-looking cartoon person sitting in an office chair, surrounded by piles of documents and sticky notes, maybe with a clock showing late hours. The office space should look busy and chaotic, contrasting with the calm train platform. Both scenes are connected by an imaginary dotted line to emphasize the wordplay between ''train station'' and ''work station.'' Style: cheerful, bright colors, exaggerated expressions, friendly and lighthearted cartoon style.'),
 (704, 'Bad Puns, Good Question!, Word Play', 'If athletes get athlete''s foot, do astronauts get mistletoe?', NULL, 'A funny cartoon scene featuring two characters side-by-side: on the left, a sweaty athlete in running clothes with exaggerated big feet covered in cute cartoonish spots or fungi labeled ''athlete''s foot''; on the right, an astronaut in a bulky space suit floating in zero gravity with a big sprig of green mistletoe hanging above or attached to their helmet. Both look puzzled and slightly amused as they glance at each other. The background is split: a sports field with a running track behind the athlete, and a starry outer space scene with planets and stars behind the astronaut. Use bright, cheerful colors and playful, exaggerated expressions to enhance the humor and whimsy of the joke without any harsh or scary details.'),
 (705, 'Good Question!, Humor, Pop Culture, Word Play', 'If Barbie''s so popular, why do you have to buy all her friends?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a kid''s bedroom filled with various Barbie dolls. In the center, a slightly confused child is holding a Barbie doll in one hand and a price tag in the other. Surrounding the child are shelves cluttered with many Barbie friends—each doll with different hairstyles, outfits, and accessories. Above the child’s head is a thought bubble showing a big crowd of glamorous Barbie dolls smiling and waving, highlighting Barbie''s ''popularity.'' On a side table, scattered money bills or coins hint at the cost of all the extra dolls. The room should be colorful, playful, and exaggerated to accentuate the child''s baffled expression about why so many friends have to be bought, creating a lighthearted, cartoonish vibe without any negative or violent content.'),
 (706, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'If blind people wear dark glasses, why don''t deaf people wear earmuffs?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters standing side by side in a bright, simple setting. On the left, a cheerful person with sunglasses on, representing a blind person, is smiling confidently. They wear classic dark sunglasses. On the right, a confused-looking person who appears deaf stands without earmuffs, scratching their head or shrugging. Around them, floating question marks emphasize the confusion or curiosity. The background is plain with a subtle suggestion of an indoor or outdoor casual environment, like a park or sidewalk. The style is light-hearted, colorful, and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the humor and the playful questioning of the joke. No text needed in the image; the visual contrast between sunglasses and absence of earmuffs should be clear and central to the humor.'),
 (707, 'Good Question!, Religion Humor, Word Play', 'If Catholics only have mass on Sundays, do they cease to exist the rest of the week?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a puzzled person standing outside a church on a sunny weekday. The church is clearly marked with a big sign reading ''Catholic Church'' and a schedule board that shows ''Mass: Sundays only.'' The person is scratching their head with a confused expression, looking down at their smartphone that displays a calendar with all days except Sunday marked as ''No Mass.'' To add humor, a ghost-like transparent figure representing the church''s ''existence'' is shown faintly fading away outside the church during the other days of the week. The style is light-hearted and cartoony, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the joke''s play on existence and weekly mass timing. The background shows common weekday elements like people walking dogs, cars driving by, and a calendar floating above the character''s head to highlight the concept of time passing during the week.'),
 (708, 'Animals, Good Question!, Humor', 'If cats and dogs didn''t have fur would we still pet them?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting on a couch looking puzzled and curious. In front of them are a cat and a dog, both completely hairless and looking slightly surprised or confused. The cat is sleek and wrinkled like a Sphynx breed with large ears, while the dog is similarly hairless, showing smooth skin with visible playful expressions. The person’s hand is hesitantly reaching out mid-air as if unsure whether to pet them or not. Around the room are small humorous details like a scratching post and a dog toy nearby. The setting is a cozy living room with warm colors to add lightheartedness. Perhaps a thought bubble above the person’s head with a question mark or the words “Would we still pet them?” to emphasize the joke’s core question.'),
 (709, 'Good Question!, Science', 'If ice floats, why is Antarctica at the bottom of the earth?', NULL, 'Create a humorous cartoon showing a simple, colorful globe of the Earth. The globe should have a visibly exaggerated bottom labeled ''Antarctica,'' colored with large blocks of ice. On top of the globe, depict floating ice cubes bobbing in water with little cartoonish faces looking confused or surprised. Add a curious cartoon character (human or animal) standing next to the globe scratching their head or holding a question mark above their head, pondering the apparent contradiction. The style should be lighthearted and fun, with clear labels on the globe and ice cubes to emphasize the joke''s question about ice floating and Antarctica''s position at the bottom of the Earth. Avoid any violent or controversial elements—focus on a playful, educational, and silly scene that captures the joke''s confusion and curiosity.'),
 (756, 'Cartoon, Engineering, Humor', 'Rube Goldberg, famed for his cartoons of crazy inventions, was a sewer engineer for the city of San Francisco.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a city engineering office labeled ''San Francisco Sewer Department.'' At the center is a quirky, slightly disheveled man resembling Rube Goldberg, wearing a hardhat and holding a blueprint covered with wildly complicated contraptions involving pipes, levers, pulleys, and buckets of water all interconnected in absurd ways. Behind him, a wall has framed cartoons showing intricate, nonsensical machines. Nearby is a large open manhole with a confused city worker peeking inside at a bizarre Rube Goldberg-style invention managing the sewer flow, complete with spinning wheels, swinging pendulums, and dripping pipes. The style is light-hearted and exaggerated, with bright colors, exaggerated expressions, and playful mechanical details, capturing the whimsical madness typical of Rube Goldberg inventions in an everyday city engineering context. No violence, politics, or anything inappropriate included.'),
 (710, 'Food Humor, Good Question!, Word Play', 'If peanut butter cookies are made from peanut butter, then what are Girl Scout cookies made out of?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person, perhaps a child or teenager, looking thoughtfully at a plate piled with several colorful Girl Scout cookies varieties (like Thin Mints, Samoas, and Tagalongs). The person has a comical puzzled expression, with a big question mark floating above their head. On the table next to the plate, there is a jar of peanut butter labeled clearly, and a small stack of peanut butter cookies on a separate plate. Behind the person is a speech bubble with the joke text: ''If peanut butter cookies are made from peanut butter, then what are Girl Scout cookies made out of?'' The background is simple and cheerful, emphasizing the contrast between peanut butter cookies and Girl Scout cookies with distinct visual styles to highlight the joke''s play on ingredients. The overall style is colorful, lighthearted, and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions and details to enhance the humor without any negative or violent elements.'),
 (711, 'Good Question!, Humor, Science', 'If people evolved from monkeys, why are monkeys still around?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused human standing next to a monkey. The human looks puzzled scratching their head, wearing casual modern clothes. The monkey, sitting on a tree branch nearby, looks at the human with a raised eyebrow as if saying, ''Why are you asking me?'' In the background, there is a lush jungle setting with several other monkeys playing around or curiously observing the conversation. Above the human and monkey, a speech bubble contains the joke question: ''If people evolved from monkeys, why are monkeys still around?'' The overall tone is lighthearted, with exaggerated cartoon features and bright colors to add humor and charm.'),
 (712, 'Good Question!, Word Play', 'If shoelaces always untie and headphone always tangle, why don''t we use headphone cables in shoes and shoelaces in headphones?', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person holding up a shoe with tangled headphone wires as shoelaces and a pair of headphones with long, untied shoelaces instead of regular cables. The shoe is oversized with bright, comically twisted headphone cables sticking out where the laces should be, and the headphones look puzzled as long, colorful shoelaces dangle messily from the ear cups. The setting is a casual room with a small table holding a tangled mess of regular shoelaces and headphone wires. The person has a playful, puzzled expression, scratching their head as they wonder about the swap. Exaggerate the twists and loops in both the headphone wires and shoelaces to emphasize their problematic nature, in a lighthearted cartoon style with bold lines and bright colors, avoiding any complexity or realistic detail to keep the humor clear and accessible.'),
 (713, 'Good Question!, Space Humor', 'If space is a vacuum, who changes the bags?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in outer space featuring an astronaut floating next to a giant space vacuum cleaner shaped like a classic household vacuum but with a clear, oversized bag labeled ''Space Vacuum Bag''. The astronaut, wearing a traditional spacesuit with a visible name tag, is scratching their helmet in confusion. The vacuum floats amongst stars, planets, and small space debris. Nearby, a confused-looking alien with multiple eyes peeks from behind a small asteroid holding a replacement vacuum bag, looking equally unsure. The background is a colorful starry cosmos with Earth visible in the distance. The mood is light and comical, emphasizing the absurdity of the question about who changes the ‘vacuum bags’ in space.'),
 (714, 'Good Question!, Humor, Police Humor, Word Play', 'If the cops arrest a mime, do they tell him he has the right to remain silent?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a city street with a police officer standing next to a mime who is in classic mime attire: white face paint, black beret, striped shirt, suspenders, and white gloves. The mime is in a typical exaggerated ''silent'' pose with hands framing his face or pretending to be inside an invisible box. The police officer is holding a notepad and speaking, with a speech bubble that says, ''You have the right to remain silent!'' The background includes a police car with flashing lights and a few amused onlookers chuckling or pointing. The style is lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions on the characters to emphasize the joke''s irony and playful misunderstanding of the mime''s silent nature. No violence or tension, just a funny interaction.'),
 (715, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'If the funeral procession is at night, do folks drive with their lights off?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene of a nighttime funeral procession driving down a quiet road. The procession consists of a classic black hearse and several black cars following behind. The hearse has visible headlights on, but the other cars behind are humorously depicted with their headlights off, making it look like glowing taillights floating in the dark. The background shows a moonlit sky with a few stars, and some trees lining the road. A confused driver in one of the cars looks nervously at their dashboard, unsure if the lights should be on or off. Include small humorous details like a speech bubble above the confused driver saying, ''Should we turn them off?''. The overall tone should be light, silly, and playful with clean cartoon lines and exaggerated expressions on the drivers'' faces to convey the joke clearly without any dark or morbid elements.'),
 (716, 'Bad Puns, Good Question!, Science, Word Play', 'If the speed of light is 186,000 miles per second, what''s the speed of heavy?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a classroom or casual science setting. In the center, a quirky teacher or scientist with wild hair and glasses stands by a blackboard. On the blackboard, the equation ''Speed of light = 186,000 miles per second'' is clearly written. The teacher looks puzzled or amused, holding a pointer or piece of chalk, glancing at a confused student scratching their head. Near the bottom of the board, the phrase ''What''s the speed of heavy?'' is written, emphasizing the pun. The classroom has a few science-related props like a globe, a small telescope, and a physics textbook on a desk. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions to capture the play on the word "heavy" vs. "light". No violence or inappropriate content is shown, just a funny moment of wordplay in a science learning environment.'),
 (717, 'Good Question!, Language, Objects Humor', 'If tin whistles are made out of tin, what do they make fog horns out of?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters standing by the water''s edge on a misty day. One character is holding a shiny tin whistle and looking curiously at it. The other character is pointing towards a giant foghorn mounted on a pier or dock, which is emitting visible, thick fog clouds shaped like waves or musical notes. The background shows a soft, foggy atmosphere with water and a few distant boats barely visible through the fog. Both characters have exaggerated puzzled or amused expressions. Include a playful detail like a musical note floating from the tin whistle and a larger, comical sound wave or cartoon-style fog puff coming out of the fog horn. The art style is colorful, light-hearted, and cartoonish with clean lines and simple shapes to emphasize the joke without any harsh or realistic details.'),
 (718, 'Food Humor, Good Question!, Puns', 'If white wine goes with fish, do white grapes go with sushi?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person sitting at a sushi bar. In front of them, instead of a usual sushi plate, there is a plate with neatly arranged bunches of white grapes. Next to the grapes, a bottle of white wine with a fish-shaped label is open with a wine glass half full. The person, with raised eyebrows and a quirky smile, is looking at the grapes and the sushi chef behind the bar who scratches his head puzzled. The setting is bright and cheerful with sushi rolls and traditional Japanese decor in the background. Include a small sign on the bar that reads, ''What pairs with sushi?''. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the funny question about pairing grapes with sushi instead of wine with fish.'),
 (719, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'If you can''t drink and drive, why do bars have parking lots?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set outside a lively bar with a bright neon sign reading ''The Tipsy Tavern.'' The bar has a large parking lot visible in the foreground, filled with various cars parked neatly. A few comical characters stand around: one looking puzzled, scratching their head, wearing casual clothes and holding a drink with a funny expression as if questioning the situation. Another character, a bartender inside, leans close to the open door and grins knowingly, holding a cocktail shaker. The scene highlights the irony: the parking lot is clearly meant for patrons, but the question about drinking and driving contrasts with it humorously. Include some whimsical details like a ''No Drinking & Driving'' sign near the parking lot entrance that seems slightly overlooked. The overall tone is light-hearted and playful with exaggerated cartoon features—big eyes, expressive faces, and vibrant colors—to emphasize the joke''s irony without any violent or inappropriate content.'),
 (720, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'If you had everything, where would you keep it?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing puzzled in a tiny, cluttered room that is crammed full of a wild assortment of objects, all labeled "everything." The room is bursting at the seams, with items overflowing from shelves, spilling from boxes, hanging from the ceiling, and stacked in towering piles nearly blocking the door. The person has a comical, exaggerated confused expression, scratching their head. Include a thought bubble above their head with the question "If you had everything, where would you keep it?" The scene should convey the visual joke about the impossibility of having and storing ''everything'' in one small space. Use bright and playful cartoon colors with exaggerated proportions to emphasize the overcrowded chaos humorously without any negativity or mess beyond comedic clutter.'),
 (721, 'Good Question!, Word Play', 'If you jog backwards, will you gain weight?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a person jogging backwards on a sidewalk or park path. The jogger looks puzzled, glancing over their shoulder as they run backwards, with exaggerated wide eyes and a question mark above their head. Behind them, a floating, oversized scale hovers midair showing weight numbers, while a few crumbs or snacks like a donut and an apple float nearby, adding to the playful confusion. The background shows a simple park setting with a tree, a bench, and a squirrel watching curiously. The style is colorful and lighthearted, emphasizing the silly idea of gaining weight by jogging backwards.'),
 (722, 'Good Question!, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'If you try to fail, and succeed, which have you done?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person standing at a crossroad with two signposts labeled ''Fail'' pointing left and ''Succeed'' pointing right. The person is scratching their head in puzzlement while holding a large oversized checklist titled ''Try to Fail.'' Behind them is a smiling thought bubble with a trophy, and behind the other side a broken pencil on the ground. The background is bright and cheerful with a few simple trees and clouds. The art style is playful and exaggerated to emphasize the person''s bewilderment at the paradox of trying to fail but succeeding.'),
 (723, 'Dyslexics, Good Question!, Word Play', 'If you''re cross-eyed and have dyslexia, can you read all right?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person with noticeably crossed eyes holding a book upside down, squinting and looking confused. The person has a playful, puzzled facial expression as they try to read. Nearby, a small playful character or mascot labeled ''Dyslexia'' is playfully spinning some of the letters floating around the person’s head. The background is a simple cozy room with a bookshelf and a reading lamp, emphasizing the reading context. The tone of the drawing is lighthearted and fun, with exaggerated facial features and cartoonish, swirling letters around the person''s head to indicate confusion caused by both crossed eyes and dyslexia.'),
 (724, 'Food Humor, Good Question!, Humor', 'Is coffee a miracle drug? I think so.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person holding a large steaming cup of coffee with a delighted expression. The background shows a bright morning kitchen setting with a sun shining through the window and a coffee maker on the counter. To highlight the joke, a label on the coffee cup reads ''Miracle Drug'' in a playful font. The character is surrounded by everyday morning items: an alarm clock showing early morning time, a sleepy-eyed pet (like a cat or dog) nearby yawning, and a newspaper folded on the table. Lighthearted and colorful style with exaggerated facial expression to emphasize the joy and energy from drinking coffee. No harsh lines or complexity—simple and inviting cartoon style.'),
 (725, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'Is it ethical to yell ''Movie!'' in a crowded firehouse?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a busy firehouse. Several firefighters wearing classic yellow firefighter uniforms and helmets are standing around inside a big garage filled with firefighting gear: hoses, axes, helmets on hooks, and a big red fire truck parked to the side. One firefighter stands in the middle with a surprised and confused expression, holding a megaphone and shouting ''Movie!'' loudly. Around him, other firefighters look startled or puzzled, some covering their ears or looking toward the shouting firefighter. The firehouse sign or wall clock is visible to set the indoor scene. The style should be bright, colorful, and exaggerated with cartoonish expressions to emphasize the humor and absurdity of yelling ''Movie!'' in a firehouse, playing on the double meaning of ''movie'' and ''move.'' No violence or danger should be depicted, keeping the joke lighthearted and silly.'),
 (726, 'Good Question!, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'Is it possible to be totally partial?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing at a crossroads labeled with two opposing signs: one saying ''Totally'' and the other saying ''Partial.'' The character looks confused and puzzled, scratching their head and with exaggerated wide eyes. Behind them, a thought bubble shows a silly imaginary scale balancing ''Total'' on one side and ''Partial'' on the other, teetering humorously. Include bright colors and simple, playful lines to emphasize the joke''s philosophical wordplay. Avoid any text beyond the signs and the thought bubble symbols. The overall tone is lighthearted and whimsical, focusing on the play on words around ''totally'' and ''partial.'''),
 (727, 'Good Question!, Humor, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'Is sloppiness in speech caused by ignorance or apathy?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters sitting at a small café table outside. One character is a neatly dressed person holding a notepad and pointing thoughtfully as if asking a serious question. The other is a very casual, sloppily dressed person with messy hair, slouched posture, and a casual, indifferent expression, lazily sipping a coffee. Above them, a comic speech bubble displays the question: "Is sloppiness in speech caused by ignorance or apathy?" The café scene has whimsical details like exaggerated coffee cups and a menu board with silly items. The background is a simple city street with a couple of pedestrians looking amused. The art style is colorful and playful with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humorous contrast between the diligent and careless characters.'),
 (728, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'Is the glass half empty, half full, or twice as large as it needs to be?', NULL, 'A cartoon scene featuring a large, exaggerated glass of water sitting on a simple table. The glass is clearly filled to the halfway point. Next to the glass, a cheerful, curious person with a questioning expression is scratching their head and looking at the glass. Above the glass, three floating cartoon thought bubbles show: one with a sad face and a half-empty glass, one with a happy face and a half-full glass, and one with a funny image of the same glass but comically oversized, dwarfing the person. The style is lighthearted and colorful with simple lines emphasizing the humor. The setting is minimalist with no distracting background, focusing on the glass, the person, and the thought bubbles to highlight the joke''s wordplay about perspective and size.'),
 (729, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'Is there an imaginary cure for hypochondria?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a quirky, slightly worried-looking character sitting in a cozy living room. The character is holding a huge, colorful book titled ''Imaginary Cures for Real Problems.'' Around them, floating in cartoonish thought bubbles, are playful, imaginary medicine bottles labeled with funny, made-up names like ''Placebo Potion'' and ''Fictional Fix.'' The character has wide eyes and an exaggerated questioning expression, scratching their head as if deeply puzzled. In the background, a wall calendar marks the date, and a small, cute pet (like a dog or cat) looks on curiously. The overall tone is lighthearted and whimsical, illustrating the mental image of pondering an imaginary cure for hypochondria without any negativity or seriousness. The art style should be simple, colorful, and cartoony, with clear, exaggerated facial expressions and props to enhance the joke’s playful mood.'),
 (730, 'Good Question!, Philosophy Humor, Steven Wright', 'OK, so what''s the speed of dark?', NULL, 'Draw a cartoon scene showing a curious person, looking puzzled while holding a speedometer. The person should be standing in a dark room where one side is fully illuminated and the other side is completely dark. The speedometer''s needle is spinning wildly as if trying to measure something invisible. Include a thought bubble above the person''s head that says, ''OK, so what''s the speed of dark?''. The style should be lighthearted and whimsical with bright colors on the lit side and deep blues or blacks on the dark side, emphasizing the humorous confusion over an impossible concept.'),
 (731, 'Engineering, Humor, Science', 'RAPID DECELERATION TRAUMA... is the trauma suffered by an object in motion, that decelerates at a rate more rapid than the object is able to absorb the stresses endured during the deceleration phase.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon style scene featuring a small car or toy car zooming forward with motion lines indicating high speed. The car suddenly hits a wall or a giant cushion labeled ''Rapid Deceleration'' with a comic impact effect (like stars or birds flying above). Above or next to the car, include a large text box in a scientific or technical font that reads: ''RAPID DECELERATION TRAUMA... is the trauma suffered by an object in motion, that decelerates at a rate more rapid than the object is able to absorb the stresses endured during the deceleration phase.'' The background should be simple and bright with exaggerated expressions of the car (like curved eyes or cartoonish ''pain'' marks) to emphasize the joke. Avoid any real human injuries or violent elements, keeping it light and funny. The overall style should be colorful and playful, similar to classic educational cartoons but with a comedic twist.'),
 (732, 'Good Question!, Humor, Money Humor', 'Real faith is sending the IRS your tax return and two Lotto tickets.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person nervously mailing their tax return envelope at a post office mailbox labeled ''IRS''. The character is a middle-aged individual with raised eyebrows and a hopeful but anxious smile. Peeking out from the envelope are two bright, colorful Lotto tickets alongside the tax return papers. Behind the person, a post office clerk watches with a knowing, slightly amused expression. The background shows a typical post office interior with a ''Tax Season'' sign and a calendar marked April 15. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the mix of anxiety and hope tied to the joke, without any dark or intense elements.'),
 (733, 'Humor, Programming, Workplace', 'Real programmers... don''t dress for success unless they are trying to convince others that they are going on job interviews.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two programmers sitting in a casual office environment. One programmer is wearing a messy t-shirt with code symbols, jeans, and slippers, working comfortably at his computer surrounded by coffee cups, snack wrappers, and multiple monitors displaying lines of code. The other programmer is standing up in the foreground, wearing a sharp business suit and tie, holding a briefcase and looking slightly awkward or out of place. A wall clock and some tech posters or sticky notes are visible in the background. The environment clearly looks like a relaxed tech workspace that contrasts with the dressed-up programmer, highlighting the joke that programmers usually dress down unless they are preparing for a job interview. The overall tone should be lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the contrast between casual and formal attire in a humorous way.'),
 (734, 'Humor, Technology Humor, Workplace', 'Real Techs are born without a biological clock. If they aren''t near a window they can''t tell if it''s night or day. Unless someone tells them dinner''s ready, they forget to eat.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a cluttered, dimly lit tech workshop filled with computer parts, monitors, cables, and gadgets scattered around. In the middle, a distracted technician with messy hair and glasses is sitting in front of multiple screens glowing brightly, unaware of the time. Behind him, a window shows a clear contrast with bright daylight outside on one side and nighttime stars on the other, emphasizing confusion about day and night. Nearby, a colleague or family member stands holding a plate with a steaming dinner, waving and calling out cheerfully. The technician looks puzzled and somewhat surprised as he glances up from his work. The overall mood is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions and details like a clock with no hands on the wall to visually reinforce the joke about lacking a biological clock. Include subtle tech-themed decorations like a “Real Techs” mug or a poster that humorously says “Biological Clock Not Found.”'),
 (735, 'Humor, Technology Humor, Workplace', 'Real Techs can''t explain their job to anyone but another Real Tech. This is because the explanation is both too complicated and too boring.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two tech people standing in an office filled with computers, wires, and tech gadgets. One tech person is enthusiastically explaining something complicated with tangled speech bubbles full of confusing symbols, code snippets, and math formulas. The other person looks completely lost and bored, eyes half-closed and slumped posture, holding a coffee cup. Nearby, a third person (non-tech) is trying to listen but is clearly overwhelmed and about to fall asleep, with a thought bubble showing a simple smiley face to indicate confusion. The background has amusing details like a whiteboard with indecipherable graphs, a stack of programming books, and a clock showing late hours to emphasize the boring and complex nature of the explanation. The overall style is light-hearted, exaggerated, and cartoonish, focusing on the comedic disconnect between tech people and non-tech listeners.'),
 (736, 'Money Humor, Tech Humor, Workplace', 'Real Techs don''t believe in budgets. A good idea is a good idea no matter what it costs.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a modern tech company office. In the center, a confident tech worker wearing glasses and casual clothes (like a T-shirt with a circuit pattern) is standing next to a whiteboard with a chaotic flowchart full of expensive-sounding tech buzzwords and dollar signs. The tech worker is holding a glowing lightbulb above their head, symbolizing a ''good idea.'' Nearby, a stressed-out finance person with a calculator and a big budget spreadsheet labeled ''Company Budget'' looks bewildered and worried. Around them, items like high-end computers, gadgets, and floating dollar signs emphasize cost concerns. The office background shows desks cluttered with coffee cups, cables, and sticky notes. The mood is playful, highlighting the contrast between the carefree tech mindset and the strict budget limitations, with exaggerated facial expressions to enhance the humor.'),
 (737, 'Food Humor, Jobs, Technology Humor', 'Real Techs don''t believe in health food. They can subsist indefinitely on Twinkies and Coca-Cola.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a simple, slightly messy tech office. In the center, a relaxed, tired-looking software technician sits at a cluttered desk with multiple computer monitors showing code. On the desk, prominently display a large stack of Twinkies boxes and several bottles or cans of Coca-Cola. The technician holds a half-eaten Twinkie in one hand and sips from a Coke can with the other, smiling contentedly. Around the workspace, include typical tech-related items such as a keyboard, mouse, coffee cup, and some cables. The background can show a whiteboard with technical doodles or flowcharts. The overall vibe is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the joke that techs survive solely on junk food, without any hint of judgment or health concerns.'),
 (738, 'Humor, Technology Humor, Workplace', 'Real Techs don''t do status reports or work to schedules. Brilliance arrives when it arrives.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon office scene featuring a laid-back tech worker at their cluttered desk. The tech is casually dressed, maybe with a t-shirt and hoodie, leaning back in their swivel chair with feet up on the desk, hands behind their head and a relaxed, confident smile. On the desk are typical tech gadgets: a laptop with code visible on the screen, empty coffee cups, scattered sticky notes labeled ''Brilliance Ideas'' and ''Maybe Tomorrow.'' Nearby, a wall clock shows an unusual random time like 3:17. The background features a whiteboard with the sarcastic note: ''No Status Reports, No Deadlines – Brilliance Arrives When It Arrives.'' Add a calendar flipped to a month but with no dates marked, emphasizing no schedule. The overall style should be bright and cartoonish with exaggerated relaxed posture and playful decor to underline the joke’s humor about informal work culture among tech professionals.'),
 (739, 'Humor, Life, Technology Humor', 'Real Techs don''t have nice looking lawns. This is for the same reason they don''t have tans. Besides, why mow grass when it''s just going to grow out again?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a tech professional relaxing in a backyard. The lawn is wildly overgrown with tall, unruly grass and some weeds poking through. The tech person is sitting comfortably in a lawn chair with a laptop on their lap, wearing casual tech-style clothes like a hoodie and glasses, showing no concern for the messy lawn. Nearby, there is an old, unused lawnmower left forgotten, covered partly by the growing grass. In the background, a bright sun shines in the sky, but the tech person has very pale skin with no tan, emphasizing their indoor lifestyle. Small elements like a coffee mug with a tech logo and a Wi-Fi router or antenna on a nearby table add to the tech vibe. The overall scene is lighthearted and emphasizes a techie’s relaxed attitude towards traditional yard work and outdoor activities, drawn in bright colors with simple shapes and exaggerated features for comedic effect.'),
 (740, 'Irony, Technology Humor, Workplace', 'Real Techs expect it to work the first time. They fix it when it doesn''t, but they don''t like it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a tech repair shop or a small office. At the center, a frustrated but determined-looking technician, wearing a shirt with a small ''Tech Support'' logo, sits at a cluttered desk filled with various gadgets like a laptop, smartphone, and tangled wires. The technician is staring at a computer screen with an error message or a broken device in front of them. Behind them, a thought bubble shows a smiling version of the same technician imagining everything working perfectly on the first try, with green check marks and a thumbs-up. The background includes posters with funny tech-related sayings like ''Expect it to work the first time!'' or ''We fix it when it breaks.'' The overall tone is light-hearted and funny, focusing on the contrast between expectations and reality in tech work, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to enhance the comic effect.'),
 (741, 'Nerd Humor, Technology Humor, Workplace', 'Real Techs have no blank paper on which to write. They were brought up writing on scraps and the backs of octal dumps. It was good enough for their teachers and it''s good enough for them.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cluttered, slightly chaotic workspace of a computer technician. The tech is a quirky-looking person wearing glasses and a T-shirt with a pixelated computer icon. Around them are scattered scraps of paper filled with handwritten notes and strange octal number dumps (strings of zeros and ones or digits 0-7) on the back sides of papers, old floppy disks, and coffee-stained notebooks. The technician holds a tiny torn piece of paper in one hand and a pencil in the other, looking both determined and slightly amused. In the background, you see a whiteboard with a complex, nerdy diagram, and a vintage computer monitor displaying hexadecimal or octal code. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, using cartoon exaggeration like animated question marks or light bulbs around the tech’s head to symbolize problem-solving and nostalgia. The environment looks busy but cozy, emphasizing a humorous embrace of old-school, resourceful tech habits rather than neat organization.'),
 (757, 'Exaggeration, Humor, Philosophy Humor', 'Ruckert''s Law: There is nothing so small that it can''t be blown out of proportion.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene featuring a tiny object—like a small pebble or an ant—in the center of the image. Surrounding it are exaggeratedly large objects or reactions: for example, a huge magnifying glass dramatically magnifying the small object to an enormous size, and a group of cartoon characters reacting with shock, surprise, or excitement as if the tiny object is a big deal. The background could be a simple living room or backyard setting to keep the focus on the tiny object and the exaggerated size difference. The style is playful and whimsical, with bright colors and expressive, humorous character faces emphasizing the joke about blowing something small way out of proportion.'),
 (742, 'Humor, Technology Humor, Workplace', 'Real Techs haven''t seen their desks for at least two years. They know something''s holding up all that paper, but they''re not sure what it looks like.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside an office workspace. The foreground shows a very messy desk completely buried under an enormous, chaotic pile of paper stacks reaching well above the height of a seated person. A tired-looking tech worker wearing casual office attire—such as a T-shirt, hoodie, and glasses—is standing beside the desk with a confused expression, scratching his head while peering at the mountain of papers. The background includes typical tech office elements: a computer monitor on the side partially visible behind the stacks, a coffee mug with steam rising, some scattered cables, and maybe a small potted plant wilting under the paper''s shadow. The overall room is dimly lit to suggest neglect and disuse. The style should be cartoonish with exaggerated features to emphasize the absurd height and clutter of the paper pile, as well as the tech''s puzzled expression. Include a small caption or thought bubble above the tech reading, ''Not sure what’s holding all this up...'''),
 (743, 'Humor, Technology Humor, Workplace', 'Real Techs know what firmware is but can''t explain it to anyone else.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a confused person (a ''customer'') standing in front of a tech technician. The technician wears a shirt or badge labeled ''Tech Support'' and is holding a small, glowing microchip labeled ''Firmware.'' The technician has a thoughtful, slightly puzzled look, as if struggling to explain, with speech bubbles showing a jumble of technical symbols and question marks. Behind them, a large computer or gadget with flashing lights sits on a desk. The customer scratches their head looking utterly baffled. Background is a simple tech support office with posters of computers and wires, drawn in bright, playful colors to keep the tone light and funny.'),
 (744, 'Humor, Pop Culture, Science', 'Reality is for people who can''t face science fiction.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters standing side by side. On the left, a person dressed in everyday casual clothes is holding a newspaper titled ''Today’s Reality'' and looking somewhat bored or unimpressed. On the right, another character is dressed in a futuristic sci-fi outfit with glowing gadgets, a hoverboard at their feet, and a small robot companion. This sci-fi character looks confident and excited, pointing towards a bright, imaginative background filled with flying cars, alien landscapes, and starships. Between them, a speech bubble from the sci-fi character says, "Reality is for people who can''t face science fiction." The style should be lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated cartoon expressions emphasizing the contrast between mundane reality and exciting sci-fi fantasy. The setting can be a neutral simple background fading from a dull urban area near the reality character to a vibrant sci-fi world near the other character.'),
 (745, 'Dark Humor, Irony', 'Remember it''s always darkest just before it goes totally black.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a dark room with a worried person holding a flashlight that just turned off. The setting is comically dim with the person squinting, looking confused and startled. Behind them, a wall clock shows late night hours to emphasize darkness. Around the person, various objects like a chair, a table, and a cat are barely visible in the gloom. Above the scene, a speech bubble reads: "Remember it''s always darkest just before it goes totally black." The overall mood is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions and simple line art to emphasize the irony of the phrase.'),
 (746, 'Humor, Laundry Humor, Puns', 'Remember, if you lose a sock in the dryer, it comes back as a Tupperware lid that doesn''t fit any of your containers.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a laundry room with a front-loading dryer door wide open. Emerging from the dryer is a confused, mismatched sock floating mid-air, looking surprised, while next to it, a bright red Tupperware lid with a puzzled face (cartoon eyes and mouth) is slightly warped and clearly too large for a nearby plastic container sitting on the floor. The laundry room has a basket full of socks with some missing pairs, and containers of various shapes and sizes scattered around, emphasizing the mystery. The background should be simple with light colors and a washing machine next to the dryer, and the floor has a few random socks and lids strewn about. The overall tone is whimsical and playful, emphasizing the joke about lost socks turning into mismatched lids from the dryer.'),
 (747, 'Bad Puns, Office Humor, Word Play', 'Remember, the paper is always strongest at the perforations.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person holding a large piece of notebook paper with visible perforations. The person has a puzzled or thoughtful look on their face as they tug gently on the paper right at the perforated edge. The paper is exaggeratedly large, almost poster-sized, to highlight the perforations. Nearby, a comically exaggerated ruler or strength-testing device (like a dumbbell) is resting, implying the person is ''testing strength.'' The background is simple, perhaps a classroom or a home office with a desk, pencil, and maybe some scattered torn pages. The overall style is bright, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the irony that the paper is strongest where it is actually weakest (the perforations). No violent or political elements; just a playful visual pun about paper strength and perforations.'),
 (748, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor', 'Remember, you''re unique, just like everybody else.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a group of diverse people standing side by side in a bright, cheerful setting such as a park or a casual outdoor gathering. Each person has distinctive traits emphasizing their uniqueness—different clothing styles, hairstyles, expressions, and accessories. Above the group, a colorful banner reads, ''Remember, you''re unique!'' Below or beside the group, a thought bubble or a quirky sign humorously adds, ''Just like everybody else.'' The characters smile knowingly, adding to the lighthearted irony of the message. The style is simple and playful, with exaggerated cartoon features and bold outlines to emphasize the humor without any threatening or controversial elements.'),
 (749, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy Humor', 'Remember: No matter where you go, there you are.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing cheerfully in the middle of a variety of different, exaggerated, and contrasting locations all cramped together in one picture. For example, the left side features a tropical beach with a palm tree, the right side shows a snowy mountain peak, behind them is a city skyline with tall buildings, and in front a desert with a cactus. The person stands centered with a confident and slightly amused expression, pointing to themselves as if reminding the viewer of their presence amid all these places. The background can be whimsically split or blended to emphasize the variety of locations. Use bright colors and exaggerated features for each setting, with clear labels or simple iconic items (like a sun with sunglasses on the beach, a penguin in the snowy part, skyscrapers in the city, and a cartoon cactus in the desert). The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, capturing the philosophical joke that no matter where you go, you are always there.'),
 (750, 'Geography Humor, Good Question!', 'Reno, Nevada is west of Los Angeles, California.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon map scene showing a very confused tourist standing at a signpost that points in multiple directions. The signpost has two big arrows: one labeled ''Los Angeles, CA'' pointing east, and another labeled ''Reno, NV'' pointing west. The tourist, wearing a hat and a fanny pack, is scratching their head with a puzzled expression. The background includes a simple cartoonish representation of the California and Nevada border with exaggerated mountains and desert scenery. A small airplane flies overhead carrying a banner that says ''Geography is tricky!'' The overall style is bright and colorful with exaggerated expressions and clear text on the signpost, emphasizing the mix-up about the relative west-east positions of Reno and Los Angeles.'),
 (751, 'Animals, Humor, Word Play', 'Researchers for the Massachusetts Turnpike recently found 200 dead crows and there was an immediate concern about Avian Flu. A pathologist examined the crows and found the cause of death to be vehicular impacts. They then determined that 98% of the vehicles were trucks, and only 2% were cars. They then hired an Ornithological Behaviorist to determine the cause of that disproportionate percentage, and he quickly determined the cause. When crows eat road kill, they always have a look-out crow in a nearby tree to warn of danger. They discovered that while all the lookout crows could shout ''Cah!'', not a single one could shout ''Truck!''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene near a busy highway depicting several cartoon crows. Most crows are gathered around a roadkill animal on the side of the road, pecking away. One crow is perched high up in a tree nearby acting as a lookout. This lookout crow has its beak open, as if shouting, with a speech bubble that says ''Cah!'' Numerous vehicles—mostly large trucks and a few small cars—are passing by on the road. The trucks look intimidating and large, while the cars are smaller and more nimble. Some crows are shown startled or reacting to the trucks but not the cars. The overall tone is light and funny, with exaggerated expressions on the crows. Include a highway sign that says ''Massachusetts Turnpike'' to set the location. The scene is colorful and playful, emphasizing the irony that the crows only recognize the sound "Cah!" (mimicking cars) and not "Truck!" as a warning, leading to the disproportionate number of crow-truck collisions.'),
 (752, 'Engineering, Puns, Science', 'Resistance is useless - if less than 1 ohm.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple electronics lab. In the center, a small resistor character with tiny arms and legs, a frustrated or defeated expression on its face, is being confronted by a large, tough-looking power source or current flow represented with animated electrical sparks or lightning bolts. The resistor wears a little headband or sweatband to emphasize struggling. Nearby, a digital multimeter shows a reading just below 1 ohm. The background includes typical electronics components like a breadboard, wires, and a circuit diagram with ohm symbols. The style should be lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke about resistance values being ''useless'' if less than 1 ohm. No realistic humans or harsh elements are needed; just cute, anthropomorphic electronic parts in a lab setting.'),
 (753, 'Irony, Philosophy Humor, Social Commentary', 'REVOLUTIONARY: An oppressed person waiting for the opportunity to become an oppressor.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a single character standing anxiously on a sidewalk, looking up at a large, towering statue labeled ''OPPRESSOR'' holding a big baton. The character has humble clothes and a hopeful yet nervous expression. Behind the character, a crowd of other everyday people wait in line, some whispering excitedly, as if waiting for their turn. Above them is a billboard reading ''Revolutionary Training Center: From Oppressed to Oppressor!''. The style is colorful and exaggerated, with caricatured figures to highlight the humor. The setting is a city square with a few protest signs folded in the background to hint at past struggles. The overall tone is light and funny, using visual irony to depict the cycle of oppression in a non-violent, witty way.'),
 (754, 'Good Question!, Humor', 'Right-handed people live, on average, nine years longer than left-handed people do.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters side-by-side on a timeline labeled ''Average Lifespan.'' On the left, a cheerful, right-handed person with a big smile is happily waving with their right hand, standing around an age marker of, say, 80 years. On the right, a slightly confused left-handed person is standing at a younger age marker, about 9 years less, with a puzzled look and scratching their left head. Above them, a large quirky sign reads, ''Right-handed people live 9 years longer!'' The background is simple with bright colors and playful font. Include details like a clock or calendar pages falling to emphasize time passing, and the characters should be cartoonish and friendly-looking, making the joke light-hearted and funny rather than serious.'),
 (755, 'Bad Puns, Objects Humor', 'Rubber bands have snappy endings!', NULL, 'Draw a cheerful, cartoon-style rubber band character with big expressive eyes and a wide smile. The rubber band is in mid-air, stretched out and about to snap back with a small comic ''SNAP!'' motion line. Around it, show a little comic-style speech bubble or caption that reads ''Snappy endings!'' The background can be simple, maybe a desk or office environment to hint at everyday use. The overall vibe should be lighthearted and playful, with bold outlines and bright colors to emphasize the humor.'),
 (758, 'Cars Humor, Humor, Life', 'Rule Of Thumb For Taxi Drivers: Stopping A Car: If you can''t read the odometer of the car in front of you at a stoplight, you''re too far back.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at a red traffic light with two cars lined up. The focus is on the back car, driven by a friendly-looking taxi driver wearing a classic taxi cap and a big smile. The taxi driver is leaning forward, squinting intensely to try to read the odometer of the car directly in front. The front car is a typical sedan with its dashboard clearly visible through the windshield, showing a large, exaggerated odometer display with big numbers. Around the taxis, there are comical motion lines suggesting the driver''s effort to focus. Both cars are drawn with exaggerated, expressive faces on their front grills to add personality and humor. The background shows a simple city street with a red traffic light overhead and a few stylized buildings to set the urban scene. The overall tone is lighthearted and cartoonish with bright colors and round, playful shapes to emphasize the joke visually without any aggression or negativity.'),
 (759, 'Food Humor, Life, Puns', 'Rule Of Thumb: Opening A Bottle Of Wine: When deciding when to open a bottle of wine, remember most wine is as good when it''s a year old as it will ever be  and will go downhill after its third birthday.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person holding a wine bottle with a big smile, standing next to a large calendar showing the passage of time with dates marked: 1 year old, 2 years old, and 3 years old. The calendar has funny, exaggerated expressions on each date: the 1-year mark has a happy face, the 2-year mark looks neutral, and the 3-year mark is depicted with a sad or wilting face, as if the wine is going downhill. Nearby, a wine glass is half full with wine, and maybe a small thought bubble above the person’s head picturing a clock or hourglass. The setting is light and friendly, with simple lines, bright colors, and cartoonish exaggeration to make the concept of wine aging playful and easy to understand. Add a sign reading "Rule of Thumb" above the person or the calendar for clarity.'),
 (760, 'Food Humor, Puns, Wine Humor', 'Rule Of Thumb: Red wines should breathe two minutes for every year between  the vintage and the present date.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person holding a glass of red wine with a confused expression. Next to them is a large, exaggerated hourglass with red wine filling the top bulb and a calendar with years marked on it next to the bottom. A speech bubble from the person says, “Two minutes for every year?”, highlighting the time needed for the wine to breathe. In the background, a wine bottle labeled with a distant vintage year (e.g., 1990) sits on a table covered with several clocks and timers, emphasizing the concept of time. The setting is a cozy, playful wine cellar or kitchen with a whimsical style, bright colors, and cartoonish exaggeration of objects to emphasize humor without any violence or inappropriate content.'),
 (761, 'Food Humor, Puns', 'Rule Of Thumb: Serving Wine: There are six glasses of wine in a bottle.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a partially opened wine bottle on a table with six empty wine glasses arranged around it. Each glass should be oversized and comically large compared to the bottle, emphasizing the joke''s exaggeration. A cheerful character, perhaps a waiter or a casual wine drinker, can be gesturing with one hand showing the number six, smiling confidently as if explaining the ''rule of thumb.'' The setting can be a cozy dining room or a casual party atmosphere with subtle wine-related decorations like corkscrews, a wine rack, or grapevines in the background. The style should be lighthearted and playful, using bright colors and exaggerated expressions to highlight the joke’s humor without any negativity or complexity.'),
 (762, 'Good Question!, Music Humor', 'Rule Of Thumb: Tuning A Musical Instrument: A stringed instrument is less apt to slip out of pitch if the strings are tuned up from flat than it is if the strings are tuned down from sharp.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon of a stringed musical instrument, such as a violin or guitar, with exaggerated facial features showing it ''worrying'' or ''relaxing.'' One side shows the strings being tuned up from flat with an enthusiastic character confidently tightening tuning pegs, and the instrument smiling or looking stable. On the other side, show strings being tuned down from sharp, with a nervous or stressed character carefully loosening tuning pegs, and the instrument looking shaky or about to ''slip.'' Include musical notes floating around to emphasize tuning, and a cartoon-style hand with a thumb prominently pointing upwards near the ''tuned up'' side to play on the ''rule of thumb.'' The background is a cozy music room or stage, with humorous small details like a metronome bobbing worriedly and a tuner device displaying tuning status. Keep the style light, colorful, and playful with simple, exaggerated expressions and clear visual cues about tuning direction and the ''rule of thumb.'''),
 (763, 'Aging, Health Humor, Puns', 'Running in your 50s-60s is a great way to meet people. A friend just met a paramedic, 3 nurses, a cardiologist, and nearly met Jesus himself!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a middle-aged person, jogging outdoors on a park trail with an exaggerated expression of surprise and slight distress. Around the runner, several characters are approaching or attending to them: a friendly paramedic with a medical bag crouching next to the runner, three nurses with stethoscopes and clipboards standing nearby offering help, and a cheerful cardiologist with a heart model smiling. In the background, a humorous, glowing, slightly transparent figure representing ''Jesus himself'' is depicted waving or smiling warmly. The setting is a sunny park with trees, a running path, and a bench. The tone is light-hearted and playful, with cartoon-style exaggerated expressions, emphasizing the irony and the joke about meeting medical professionals due to the risks of running at that age.'),
 (764, 'Mental Health Humor, Philosophy Humor', 'Sadness is rarely an illusion.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene featuring a sad-faced character standing in front of a large, whimsical magician''s hat from which colorful, sparkling illusions or magical swirls are emerging. The character looks puzzled and melancholic, with a small rain cloud hovering directly above their head, creating a contrast between the bright illusions and their real sadness. Around the character, there are faint translucent images of illusions or shiny magical objects floating in the air, but the character''s droopy posture and facial expression clearly show genuine sadness that stands apart from the illusions. The setting is simple with a plain background to emphasize the character. The style is lighthearted and humorous despite the serious theme, with exaggerated, rounded features and expressive eyes to highlight the emotional difference between illusion and actual sadness.'),
 (765, 'Humor, Mental Health Humor, Word Play', 'Schizophrenia: human version of cross-link files!', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon showing a person depicted as a computer file folder labeled ''Human Brain.'' This folder is shown trying to organize colorful sticky notes and small digital files visibly tangled and connected by chaotic, glowing lines labeled ''cross-links.'' The person looks slightly confused but curious, scratching their head while holding two files that are connected by a bright, jumping ''cross-link'' line. In the background, other folders labeled with various brain functions like ''Memory,'' ''Thoughts,'' and ''Emotions'' are also connected by similar glowing lines, some neatly and some tangled, with a sparkle effect to emphasize connections. The setting is a lighthearted, playful office or computer desktop environment emphasizing the concept of files and digital data organization rather than anything clinical or serious. The style is simple, cartoonish, and friendly, with exaggerated expressions for humor without depicting illness harshly or insensitively.'),
 (766, 'Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'Scrambo - the meanest word-tile game on the market!', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene inside a living room. On a small table sits a Scrabble-style word game with tiles scattered in a chaotic mess, some tiles even appearing to have angry faces or little frowns. The game box is prominently displayed with the label ''Scrambo'' in big, bold, playful letters. The subtitle on the box reads ''the meanest word-tile game on the market!'' Nearby, a frustrated player—exaggerated expression with furrowed brows and gritted teeth—is dramatically throwing their tiles up in the air in mock anger. Another player sits opposite, smirking mischievously while holding a tile, as if ready to unleash a ''mean'' word. The background is simple but cheerful, with a few cartoon-style speech bubbles showing silly words or letters clashing. The overall vibe is lighthearted and funny, capturing the chaos and competitive spirit of a family game night turned vicious, all in a playful way.'),
 (767, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'Seeing is believing - so you can close your eyes and be in Kansas.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing with their eyes closed, smiling peacefully, with a large thought bubble above their head. Inside the thought bubble is a colorful, whimsical depiction of Kansas, featuring iconic imagery like wide open fields, sunflowers, a flying tornado with a friendly face, and a small farm with a red barn. The person is casually dressed and standing in a simple, nondescript room. The caption or text on a sign nearby reads: ''Seeing is believing – so you can close your eyes and be in Kansas.'' The overall style is light-hearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the surreal, imaginative feel of ''being in Kansas'' while closing eyes.'),
 (768, 'Aging, Humor, Life', 'Seen it all, done it all, can''t remember most of it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring an older person sitting comfortably in a cozy living room armchair. The person has a relaxed, slightly amused expression and is surrounded by humorous visual cues indicating forgetfulness: empty thought bubbles above their head with question marks, a calendar with many crossed-out dates, and scattered items like photo albums, a pair of reading glasses, and a cup of tea on a side table. Behind them, a wall filled with framed photos showing different fun activities (like traveling, parties, sports) but the person looks puzzled or shrugging as if trying to recall. The overall style is lighthearted and warm, emphasizing the humor in having experienced many things but struggling to remember them clearly.'),
 (769, 'Humor, Movies, Word Play', 'Sequels we''ll never see: The Duplicate Bridge over the River Kwai', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing the original famous Bridge over the River Kwai with a cheeky twist. Draw two identical wooden bridges side by side stretching across a river labeled ''River Kwai.'' One bridge looks old-fashioned and war-themed, resembling the classic movie setting, complete with a few surprised or curious tourists taking photos. Right next to it, the second bridge is exactly the same in every detail, as if it’s a perfect duplicate, with a large sign overhead that says ''Duplicate Bridge over the River Kwai.'' Make both bridges colorful and a bit exaggerated, with comically large planks and rope railings. Include a small boat with puzzled people looking up at the two identical bridges, scratching their heads with question marks above their heads. The overall style should be lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions on the characters to emphasize the joke about a never-to-exist sequel involving duplication and the famous bridge.'),
 (770, 'Humor, Music Humor, Word Play', 'SFB: Song Fragment Buildup. Little bits of songs that you can''t get out of your head. Often the last song you heard on the radio before getting out of the car. Example: Day-O! Daylight''s comin'' an'' me wanna go home!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a car with a person sitting in the driver''s seat looking slightly annoyed but amused. Musical notes are floating around their head representing a catchy tune stuck in their mind. A small radio on the dashboard displays a song title or musical notes, indicating the source of the tune. The background through the car windows shows a simple street or parking lot, suggesting the person just got out of the car. Above the person, a speech bubble contains the text: “Day-O! Daylight''s comin'' an'' me wanna go home!” The overall style is light-hearted and colorful, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the feeling of a catchy song stuck in the head. The scene should evoke the common relatable experience of an earworm or a song fragment that won’t go away after leaving the car or radio environment. No people other than the driver, no violence or anything inappropriate.'),
 (771, 'History Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'Shakespeare invented the word ''assassination'' and ''bump''.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene with a playful medieval writer, styled like Shakespeare, sitting at a wooden desk cluttered with old scrolls and a quill pen. He has a jovial, slightly mischievous smile as he holds up two scrolls: one with the word ''assassination'' in an elegant, dramatic font, and another with the word ''bump'' in big, simple, cartoonish letters. The background shows a cozy Elizabethan study, with shelves of books and parchment. Nearby, a small animated speech bubble shows a tiny dagger next to the word ''assassination'' and a little comic bump (like a bump on the head) next to ''bump,'' emphasizing the contrast between the serious and silly words. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, focusing on the witty contrast of the two invented words by Shakespeare.'),
 (772, 'Humor, Life, Money Humor', 'Shopper''s bumper sticker: Broke but not broken.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing the rear end of a car with a large, colorful bumper sticker that reads ''Broke but not broken.'' Around the car, depict a cheerful shopper standing next to some shopping bags, looking optimistic despite an empty wallet visible in their hand or pocket. The background can be a simple parking lot outside a shopping mall with a few other cars and shoppers for context. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions on the shopper to highlight determination and good spirit despite financial strain. Include small humorous details like a cartoon wallet with a sad face or coins escaping from it, and maybe a few funny price tags floating around the bags to emphasize the ''broke'' theme without sadness.'),
 (773, 'Marriage Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'SHOTGUN WEDDING:  A case of wife or death.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a classic ''shotgun wedding.'' In the center, a nervous-looking groom in a tuxedo stands beside a cheerful bride in a wedding dress. Behind the groom, a large, slightly oversized cartoon shotgun is being held by a grinning father of the bride, pointing it comically over the groom''s shoulder but not menacingly—more like a playful warning. The setting is a simple wedding venue decorated with flowers, balloons, and a ''Just Married'' sign in the background. The groom appears caught between two exaggeratedly large objects: a heart-shaped wedding bouquet in one hand and a cartoonish skeleton or Grim Reaper figure with a scythe positioned on the other side, symbolizing ''death.'' The expressions should reflect humor and lighthearted tension to convey the joke''s pun: the groom chooses between marrying the wife or facing death. The style is colorful, exaggerated facial expressions and proportions typical of a funny comic strip, suitable for all ages.'),
 (774, 'Computers, Humor, Puns', 'Simple Analogies Used to Explain Computer Concepts to Laypeople: Disc caching is like Gin Rummy: you keep what you think you might need, except you can pick up as many cards as can fit in your hand.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters sitting at a small table playing Gin Rummy. One character is a friendly-looking computer with a smiling face on its monitor, holding a hand of playing cards. The other is a casual person looking slightly puzzled but intrigued. On the table, instead of normal cards, some cards are decorated with little icons representing files or digital documents. Above them is a speech bubble coming from the computer character that says: "Disc caching is like Gin Rummy—you keep what you think you might need, except you can pick up as many cards as can fit in your hand." The background is a cozy living room with a bookshelf containing a few computer textbooks and a small plant, emphasizing a lighthearted, educational vibe. The overall style should be bright, friendly, and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions to highlight the humor of the analogy.'),
 (775, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Smile, it''s the second best thing you can do with your lips.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person smiling widely in the foreground, showing shiny, prominent lips. Next to them, a large, colorful speech bubble says: ''Smile, it''s the second best thing you can do with your lips.'' Nearby, a pair of lips cartoonishly puckered up as if about to give a kiss, winking playfully. The background is simple and bright with a lighthearted, friendly atmosphere, using soft pastel colors. The characters are drawn with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize humor, and the style is clean, fun, and inviting without any complex backgrounds or distractions.'),
 (776, 'Food Humor, Puns', 'Smoking will kill you, and bacon will kill you, but smoking bacon will cure it', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful pig holding a partially cooked strip of bacon that is shaped like a large, crooked cigarette. The pig is smiling slyly as it smokes the bacon, with little puffs of smoke rising from the bacon-cigarette. Nearby, a classic old-fashioned cigarette lies extinguished on an ashtray, and a sizzling frying pan holds more bacon strips cooking. In the background, a vintage-style health warning poster reads, ''Smoking will kill you,'' and another sign says, ''Bacon will kill you.'' Above the pig, a thought bubble says, ''But smoking bacon will cure it!'' The setting is a cozy kitchen with a humorous, lighthearted atmosphere, bright colors, and exaggerated cartoon features on the pig. The scene emphasizes the pun and playful contradiction of the joke with a whimsical, fun tone.'),
 (777, 'Animals, Good Question!', 'Snails can sleep for 3 years without eating', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a snail comfortably asleep inside a tiny, cozy snail shell bed. The snail is wearing a cute sleeping cap and has a peaceful smile. Around the snail, there is a calendar on the wall with pages flying off rapidly, indicating the passage of several years. Beside the snail’s bed, a small alarm clock shows a huge time gap with years marked. There is no food nearby, emphasizing the joke about not eating. The background can be a simple garden with a few leaves and grass blades to set the outdoor scene. The overall tone is lighthearted and whimsical, with bright colors and exaggerated features to highlight the snail’s unusual long sleep habit.'),
 (778, 'Humor, Life', 'Some days you are the bug, other days you are the windshield.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a car speeding down a road with a large bug hitting its windshield. The bug looks surprised, its eyes wide open and legs spread out as if squished against the glass. On the other side of the scene, the same bug is depicted on a day when it’s the one driving a tiny bug-sized car, confidently crashing into a huge windshield-shaped wall labeled ''windshield.'' The background is simple with a sunny sky and a road, emphasizing the contrast between the bug being smashed and the bug doing the smashing. The art style is light-hearted, with exaggerated facial expressions on the bug and the car being cartoonish and fun, no violence or harm depicted, just comically illustrating the phrase ''some days you are the bug, other days you are the windshield.'''),
 (779, 'Animals, Exaggeration, Humor', 'Some lions mate over 50 times a day.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in an African savanna with a male lion looking astonished and overwhelmed, sitting on a large rock. Around him, several female lions are eagerly approaching or surrounding him, some with playful, expectant expressions. A cheeky speech bubble above the male lion reads, ''Some lions mate over 50 times a day!'' In the background, a comically tired lion nearby is lying flat on the ground with sweat drops and cartoon stars around his head, clearly exhausted. The sun shines brightly, highlighting the bustling nature of the scene. The art style is colorful, exaggerated, and light-hearted, emphasizing the humor of the lion''s predicament without any aggressive or sexual imagery.'),
 (780, 'Humor, Irony, Life', 'Some make it happen, some watch it happen, and some say, ''What happened?''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring three characters standing side by side with distinct expressions and actions. On the left, a confident person actively holding a large wrench or tool, clearly ''making it happen'' with a machine or project that is working perfectly. The middle character is casually sitting on a bench or leaning against a wall, watching the first person work with a relaxed, mildly interested look, representing ''watching it happen.'' The third character stands to the right, looking confused and scratching their head, with cartoon question marks floating above, clearly saying, ''What happened?'' The background is a simple workshop or outdoor setting with humorous small details like spilled coffee or scattered plans to add charm. The overall tone is lighthearted and exaggerated in classic cartoon style, with bright colors and expressive faces emphasizing the difference in attitudes toward action and observation.'),
 (781, 'Fantasy Humor, Relatable Humor', 'Some mornings I just don''t feel like slaying dragons.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a medieval knight waking up in bed looking tired and unmotivated. The knight is still wearing a sleepy expression with a soft, rumpled nightcap on his helmet. Around him, the room is decorated with classic dragon-slaying gear such as a shining sword, shield, and armor scattered on a chair and floor. Through a window, a dragon can be seen flying lazily outside, looking harmless and friendly rather than fierce. Include a bedside table with a mug of steaming coffee or tea and an alarm clock reading early morning hours. The overall vibe is cozy and relatable, with soft morning light coming in through the window. The image should be drawn in a lighthearted, colorful cartoon style emphasizing the knight’s humorous lack of enthusiasm for heroics this morning.'),
 (782, 'Computers, Humor, Nerd Humor', 'Some people really know how to have fun. But they''re probably not computer nerds.', NULL, 'A colorful, lighthearted cartoon scene showing two contrasting groups having fun. On the left, a small group of happy, lively people is outdoors playing frisbee, laughing, and enjoying bright sunshine. They wear casual, summer clothes and have wide smiles. On the right, a group of stereotypical ''computer nerds'' sits indoors in front of glowing computer screens filled with code and game graphics. They wear glasses, hoodies, and headphones, looking focused or excited but in a more subdued way. The background around them is a dimly lit room with tech gadgets and snacks scattered. The overall style is cheerful and exaggerated to emphasize the difference in energy levels and types of fun, without being mean-spirited. Include a humorous contrast in posture and expression between the two groups. The scene should look like a simple, friendly cartoon strip style, clear and visually playful.'),
 (783, 'Humor, Irony, Word Play', 'Some people wouldn''t recognize subtlety if it hit them on the head.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person obliviously standing in the middle of a comical situation illustrating ''subtlety'' hitting them on the head. The ''subtlety'' is depicted as a cartoonish, light and fluffy cloud or a gentle breeze personified with cute eyes and a smiling face, gently tapping the person''s head with a soft feather or small pillow. The person is wide-eyed and confused, perhaps scratching their head or looking around cluelessly. The background is simple with a park bench or a streetlamp to give context but keep focus on the interaction. Use exaggerated expressions to highlight the humor: the cloud has a playful and innocent look, while the person looks puzzled but unharmed. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with bright colors and rounded shapes to emphasize a non-threatening, funny tone.'),
 (784, 'Humor, Programming, Word Play', 'Some programming languages manage to absorb change but withstand progress.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a group of programming language characters personified as quirky robots or computer icons. One robot labeled ''Legacy Language'' looks worn-out, patched up with duct tape and bandages, symbolizing it absorbing changes but looking tired and old-fashioned. Another sleek, shiny robot labeled ''Modern Language'' is confidently walking forward with a futuristic vibe, carrying a briefcase labeled ''Progress.'' In the background, a puzzled crowd of smaller, neutral characters watches this interaction, representing programmers or users. The setting is a simple office space with code snippets on screens and a whiteboard showing arrows labeled ''Change'' pointing toward the Legacy Language robot, which tries to absorb these arrows, while arrows labeled ''Progress'' bounce off it, causing some comic confusion. Overall, the scene is lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions on the robots, emphasizing the joke''s play on adaptation to change but resistance to progress in programming languages.'),
 (785, 'Humor, Motivational', 'Some succeed because they are destined to. Most succeed because they are determined to.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene split into two halves side by side. On the left side, a character stands on a simple podium labeled ''Destiny,'' looking relaxed and content with a glowing aura or stars above their head, suggesting they are naturally fated to succeed. On the right side, another character is climbing a tall, steep mountain labeled ''Determination,'' sweating but smiling with effort, carrying a backpack full of tools like a rope and pickaxe. The background shows the mountain peak with a flag at the top that says ''Success.'' Both characters are cartoonish, friendly-looking, and dressed in casual clothes. The sky is bright and cheerful on both sides. The overall tone is optimistic and humorous, highlighting the contrast between destiny and determination in a lighthearted way.'),
 (786, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Someone stole my Scrabble game - I''m at a loss for words', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene inside a cheerful living room. In the center, show a person standing with a confused and frustrated expression, holding an empty Scrabble game box with nothing inside. Scattered around the floor are a few random Scrabble tiles, emphasizing that the game pieces are missing. Above the person’s head, include a visible thought bubble with quirky, jumbled letters floating inside, symbolizing ‘at a loss for words.’ Nearby, a suspicious cat or sneaky-looking cartoon thief with a bag labeled ''Scrabble tiles'' peeks around the corner to add a playful element. The background includes a cozy couch, bookshelf, and a small table with a Scrabble board visibly absent, highlighting the missing game. Use bright, vibrant colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor and light-heartedness of the situation.'),
 (787, 'Humor, Irony', 'Someone who thinks logically is a nice contrast to the real world.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a chaotic, exaggeratedly messy office or living room representing the ''real world.'' Papers, books, and random objects are scattered everywhere. In the middle stands a calm, neatly dressed character labeled ''Logical Thinker,'' depicted as serene and composed, holding a neatly stacked set of papers or a clipboard. Around them, cartoonish characters and objects behave wildly—one person frantically juggling phones and coffee cups, another tangled in headphones, and a cat knocking over a plant. The background features a clock spinning fast and a calendar with pages flying away to emphasize the chaos. The logical thinker’s calm demeanor and neat appearance stand out as a sharp and amusing contrast to the hectic, disorganized surroundings. All characters have exaggerated, comedic expressions to emphasize humor without any violence or negativity.'),
 (788, 'Love Humor, Money Humor, Puns', 'Someone with money to burn will always find a perfect match.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a wealthy-looking person with a sparkling crown and fancy clothes standing next to a bonfire made of money bills and coins literally burning in the fire. The rich person holds a box of oversized wooden matchsticks labeled ''Perfect Match'' with a big smile on their face, ready to light one. The background is cheerful and bright with a few gold coins floating in the air and little heart-shaped sparks rising from the fire, playfully suggesting both money being set aflame and the idea of finding a romantic or ideal match. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions and vibrant colors to emphasize the pun.'),
 (789, 'Humor, Relatable Humor', 'Sometimes I feel like I''m telling 6 foot tall jokes and everybody in the room is 5 foot 10 inches', NULL, 'A cartoon drawing of a person standing on a small wooden stool or ladder, looking confident and animated as if telling a joke to a group. The person appears taller than everyone else in the scene. Around them, a group of people stand or sit, all noticeably shorter—visibly about 5''10"—looking slightly puzzled or unimpressed, with some scratching their heads or glancing sideways. The setting is a casual comedy club or living room with a microphone stand nearby and a simple backdrop. The style is colorful and humorous, emphasizing the height difference exaggeration for comedic effect without being mean-spirited.'),
 (790, 'Humor, Relatable Humor', 'Sometimes I wake up Grumpy; Other times I let him sleep', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene split into two panels side-by-side. In the first panel, a person is waking up in bed early in the morning, eyes half-open with a big scowl on their face, clearly grumpy. The background shows a messy bedroom with a tired-looking alarm clock ringing loudly on the nightstand. In the second panel, the same person is seen asleep again under the covers, with a peaceful smile, completely relaxed. Above their head is a small cartoon ''Grumpy'' character (a tiny grumpy-faced figure with crossed arms) curled up and sleeping, complete with a little sleep bubble indicating Zzz. Use bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions for comic effect, emphasizing the mood difference between the two panels. The style should be lighthearted and cartoony, conveying humor without any harshness or negativity.'),
 (791, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Sometimes too much drink is not enough.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a lively bar. In the center, a cheerful, slightly disheveled character holds an overflowing glass of a colorful drink with bubbles and garnish. Around them, several empty glasses and bottles are scattered on the table, implying they''ve already had many drinks. The character looks both amused and frustrated, scratching their head with one hand while holding the drink with the other, as if saying, ''I still need more!'' The background shows fellow patrons enjoying themselves, some laughing, some watching the character with raised eyebrows. The bar has typical details: stools, a bartender wiping a glass, shelves lined with bottles, and funny small signs like ''Drink Responsibly'' with a wink emoji. The style is bright, cartoonish, and exaggerated to emphasize the humorous struggle of wanting more despite already having too much.'),
 (792, 'Computers, Humor, Puns', 'Sometimes user keys can be shifty.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a computer keyboard with a few keys literally sliding or shifting out of place, like small people or objects moving on a conveyor belt. The keys have little animated eyes and arms, some looking mischievous or surprised. The keyboard is on a desk with a computer monitor visible in the background. A frustrated but amused user is sitting at the desk, scratching their head or raising an eyebrow, looking at the shifting keys. The scene should be light, playful, and exaggerated, emphasizing the pun on ''shifty'' keys by making the keys appear physically shifty or mobile.'),
 (793, 'Humor, Social Commentary, Word Play', 'Sometimes, someone unexpected comes into your life out of nowhere, makes your heart race, and changes you forever. We call those people cops.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a surprised person on a city sidewalk, mid-stride, with a very exaggerated, wide-eyed, and heart-racing expression. Above their head should be a comic-style heart pounding symbol with motion lines to emphasize a racing heart. Suddenly, a friendly police officer unexpectedly appears out of nowhere, stepping onto the scene with a cheerful smile and a gesture like raising a hand in greeting or holding a ticket book. The setting is urban with a few simple street details: a streetlamp, a park bench, and a distant cityscape. The style is lighthearted and playful with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to show shock and sudden change. The overall mood is funny, capturing the surprise and impact the officer has on the person’s life as if they suddenly appeared like a love interest, but humorously it’s a cop instead.'),
 (794, 'Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'Sour grapes: the type of grapes used to make fine whines.', NULL, 'A whimsical cartoon scene featuring a fancy wine tasting event set outdoors with a vineyard in the background. On one side, a bunch of grape characters with sour, grumpy faces are gathered together labeled as ''Sour Grapes.'' Nearby, a sophisticated sommelier, wearing a classic wine taster outfit and monocle, is holding a wine glass filled with red wine while curiously sniffing it. A speech bubble from the sommelier says, ''Ah yes, made from the finest whines!'' The grapes look offended and sour, with exaggerated facial expressions such as frowns, scrunched noses, and crossed arms. Include a wine barrel and a banner saying ''Fine Whines Vineyard'' to emphasize the pun. The art style should be colorful, lighthearted, and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions for comedic effect, avoiding any violent, sexual, or political content.'),
 (795, 'Random', 'Spilling your guts is just exactly as charming as it sounds.', NULL, ''),
 (796, 'Humor, Pop Culture, Word Play', 'STAR: A performer who makes more than his or her agent.  SUPERSTAR: A performer who makes more than Guatemala.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a brightly lit stage, featuring a confident performer dressed in flashy, over-the-top superstar attire (sparkly jacket, sunglasses, exaggerated hair). The performer is holding a large bag of money with a dollar sign on it, smiling proudly. To the side, a small, somewhat grumpy-looking person wearing a business suit and holding a contract represents the agent, looking surprised or bewildered as they see the performer''s earnings. In the background, a small, simple outline or tiny map of Guatemala with a dollar sign next to it emphasizes the comparison. The stage has spotlights and a shiny star symbol overhead. The overall tone is lighthearted and comedic, using exaggerated expressions and cartoonish proportions to emphasize the joke without any violence or negativity.'),
 (797, 'Animals, Good Question!', 'Starfish haven''t got brains.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a starfish lying flat on a sandy ocean floor looking confused with wide, googly eyes. It''s surrounded by coral, shells, and small fish that are swimming around it, some shaking their heads or looking amused. Above the starfish, a little thought bubble shows a tiny empty brain outline or a question mark to emphasize the joke about it having no brain. The style should be light-hearted and colorful with exaggerated expressions to add humor, avoiding any aggression or negativity.'),
 (798, 'Humor, Irony', 'STATE-OF-THE-ART: Soon-to-be-obsolete.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a futuristic gadget labeled ''STATE-OF-THE-ART'' on a pedestal with a big spotlight shining on it, as if on display in a museum. The gadget looks sleek and shiny but is already covered in cobwebs and small dust clouds, humorously highlighting its obsolescence. Nearby, a confused-looking person (wearing casual clothes) scratches their head while holding a manual titled ''Instructions for the Future.'' The background features a sign that says ''Future Tech Museum'' with a small calendar showing the current year, emphasizing the irony. The overall style should be bright, colorful, and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions and light-hearted details like a small clock ticking fast to suggest time passing quickly. No violence, politics, or mature themes.'),
 (799, 'Humor, Relatable Humor, Word Play', 'STAY TUNED: I could say something brilliant at any moment.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a relaxed character sitting comfortably on a couch in a cozy living room. The character has a playful, slightly mischievous smile, and is holding a TV remote in one hand while a speech bubble above their head reads, ''STAY TUNED: I could say something brilliant at any moment.'' The TV in front of them displays a static or loading screen with the words ''Stay Tuned...'' The room includes classic cozy elements like a floor lamp, a small side table with a cup of coffee, and a quirky framed poster on the wall that says ''Brilliance Loading...''. The overall style is lighthearted and colorful with exaggerated cartoon expressions and rounded shapes to emphasize humor and anticipation without any aggression or negativity.'),
 (800, 'Humor, Language, Word Play', 'Stewardesses is the longest word typed with only the left hand.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a person sitting at a desk typing on a classic QWERTY keyboard. The person looks surprised and amused, pointing at the screen where the word ''Stewardesses'' is boldly displayed in large, colorful letters. Around the keyboard, only the left-hand side keys are highlighted or glowing to emphasize the joke. The setting is light and fun, with a bright office or home office background including a coffee mug and a small smiling airplane model on the desk to hint at the airline theme. The person''s right hand rests idly, while the left hand is actively typing. The overall style should be playful and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expression and clear visual focus on the keyboard and word on screen, reinforcing the idea that ''Stewardesses'' uses only the left hand keys while typing.'),
 (801, 'Humor, Life, Motivational', 'Strive always for your goals, but choose those goals with care. Every choice has a cost, and balance is the key.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a cheerful character standing on a tightrope stretched across a canyon. The character is wearing a determined expression and holding a balancing pole labeled ''Balance.'' On one side of the canyon is a treasure chest labeled ''Goals,'' glowing and enticing, while on the other side is a giant weight marked ''Costs.'' Below the tightrope are fluffy clouds and a bright, sunny sky. The scene emphasizes the theme of carefully balancing ambitions versus consequences in a lighthearted way, with exaggerated expressions and playful colors to keep the tone fun and positive.'),
 (802, 'Humor, Programming, Word Play', 'Structured Programming supports the law of the excluded muddle.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon showing a confused programmer sitting at a cluttered desk filled with open books and computer screens showing tangled, messy code. The programmer is scratching their head, looking puzzled. Above them, depict a playful sign or chalkboard that says ''Law of the Excluded Muddle'' instead of the usual ''Law of the Excluded Middle.'' Around them, add symbols representing structured programming, like neat flowcharts and simple code blocks, but tangled lines and question marks mixed in to emphasize confusion and muddle. The overall tone should be lighthearted and silly, capturing the irony of a logical programming concept becoming mixed up and perplexing.'),
 (803, 'Animals, Farming Humor, Puns', 'Studies show that cows produce more milk when the farmer talks to them. It''s a case of in one ear and out the udder.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a sunny farm in a green field with a red barn in the background. In the foreground, a friendly farmer, smiling and wearing overalls and a wide-brimmed hat, is leaning forward talking enthusiastically to a group of cows. The cows look happy and attentive, some with slight smiles. One cow in the center has oversized, exaggerated udders shaking slightly to emphasize milk production. To add humor, a speech bubble from the farmer says something like ''Good girl, keep it up!'' Above the scene, include a playful pun caption: ''In one ear and out the udder.'' The style should be bright, colorful, and cartoonish, with exaggerated features for both humans and cows to maximize the joke''s lightheartedness. No violent or inappropriate imagery, just a happy farm scene focused on the cows and the talking farmer.'),
 (804, 'Humor, School, Word Play', 'Study art and logic - learn to draw your own conclusions.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a student sitting at a traditional school desk. The student holds a pencil and a sketchpad, drawing a funny, exaggerated picture of a logical diagram (like a flowchart or Venn diagram) that is clearly labeled ''Conclusions.'' Around the student are two posters on the classroom wall: one labeled ''Art'' with paintbrushes and colorful strokes, and another labeled ''Logic'' with symbols such as syllogisms or math symbols. The student’s expression is sheepish but proud, suggesting they are literally ''drawing conclusions.'' The classroom setting is bright and playful, with a chalkboard in the background showing the phrase ''Study art and logic'' written neatly. The overall tone is lighthearted and clever, emphasizing the pun with visual elements combining art and logical reasoning.'),
 (805, 'Irony, Life, Relatable Humor', 'Success always occurs in private, and failure in full view.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene split into two panels side by side. On the left panel, a person is quietly celebrating alone in a cozy room, smiling modestly while sitting at a desk with a small trophy or certificate subtly displayed. The room is dimly lit with a single lamp, giving a private and calm vibe. On the right panel, the same person is in a busy public park or street, dramatically tripping over their own feet while juggling papers or objects, watched by a crowd of surprised and amused onlookers. People are pointing and laughing, some taking pictures with their phones. The contrast between the two scenes highlights the joke: quiet, private success vs. very public failure. Keep the characters cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions for humor and clearly different lighting for private vs. public settings. No violence or negativity, just a lighthearted and relatable depiction.'),
 (806, 'Food Humor, Life, Philosophy Humor', 'Success in life doesn''t depend on your face or fate; it depends on your taste.', NULL, 'A humorous, colorful cartoon scene depicting a whimsical character standing proudly in front of a large display of various desserts, gourmet foods, and artful dishes on plates. The character has an exaggeratedly expressive face showing delight, holding a fork with a tiny bite of food. Around the character are floating symbols representing ''face'' (a mirror showing an average face) and ''fate'' (a classic dice or a four-leaf clover), both crossed out or fading away. Instead, a huge, shining golden chef''s hat floats above the character''s head symbolizing ''taste'' as the key to success. The background is lighthearted with a kitchen or banquet setting to emphasize food and taste rather than looks or luck. The style should be cartoonish, bright, and cheerful with exaggerated, funny expressions to evoke humor without any violence or negativity.'),
 (807, 'Humor, Irony, Life', 'Success is a matter of luck; ask any failure.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon featuring two characters standing side by side, labeled ''Success'' and ''Failure.'' ''Success'' is depicted as a confident, well-dressed person holding a trophy or medal with a lucky rabbit''s foot hanging from their wrist. ''Failure'' is slouching, looking frustrated or bewildered, wearing worn-out clothes and holding a broken horseshoe. Both stand under a sky filled with cartoonish lucky symbols like four-leaf clovers, falling horseshoes, and shooting stars. A thought bubble above ''Failure'' reads, ''It’s all just luck…'' while ''Success'' looks smug, maybe shaking the rabbit’s foot. The background can be a simple park or plain with bright colors to keep the mood light and funny, emphasizing the irony of the quote. The style should be cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions to highlight the humor of blaming luck for success or failure, without any negativity towards either character.'),
 (808, 'Motivational, Puns', 'Success is not the result of spontaneous combustion. You must light yourself on fire.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a quirky character, perhaps a cheerful person wearing casual clothes, standing outdoors with a big smile. The person holds a giant matchstick, striking it against a big matchbox labeled ''Motivation.'' Flames subtly but comically start to flicker on the person''s feet or hands (clearly cartoon fire, not painful or scary). Around them, motivational posters or signs hang on a fence or wall, with slogans like ''Light Up Your Life!'' and ''Ignite Your Passion!'' The background shows a sunny day in a park or backyard, with cartoonish trees and a bench, creating a light-hearted and positive atmosphere. The character''s expression should be confident and funny, emphasizing the pun on ''light yourself on fire'' as an energetic metaphor for self-motivation rather than literal burning. Overall, the artwork should be vibrant, exaggerated, and playful to capture the clever wordplay of the joke.'),
 (809, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Suggestions Welcome:  They''re good for a lot of laughs', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy living room. In the center, a cheerful, somewhat quirky-looking character sits on a comfy armchair with a notebook or suggestion box labeled ''Suggestions'' on their lap. Around them are several laughing friends or family members, some pointing at the character while chuckling. On a nearby coffee table, there are a few playful items like funny hats, joke books, and a rubber chicken to hint at humor. The room has bright, colorful walls with framed comic strips or funny posters. The overall mood is lighthearted and fun, emphasizing the idea that suggestions (or the suggestion box) bring lots of laughter. The style is cartoonish with exaggerated, expressive faces and warm colors to enhance the comedic vibe.'),
 (810, 'Food Humor, Puns, Science', 'Support bacteria -- it''s the only culture some people have!', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy kitchen or science classroom. Center a cheerful, anthropomorphic bacterium character with big friendly eyes, a wide smile, and tiny arms giving a thumbs-up. Surround the bacterium with petri dishes labeled ''Culture'' with colorful bacterial colonies growing inside. Nearby, depict a few puzzled or unimpressed human characters, showing confused or blank expressions, highlighting that they lack ''culture.'' Include shelves with jars of yogurt, cheese, and other fermented foods to subtly emphasize the word ''culture.'' Bright colors and exaggerated, playful expressions should be used for a lighthearted effect without any negativity or harm. Make the overall tone fun and witty, visually reinforcing the pun about bacteria being a form of culture for some people.'),
 (811, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor', 'Tact is the art of making a point without making an enemy.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy living room. In the center, a well-dressed, friendly-looking character is speaking to another person who looks a bit surprised but not angry. The first character is holding a large, old-fashioned paintbrush labeled ''Tact'' and is gently painting a speech bubble above the second person''s head that contains the phrase ''making a point''. The second character has a small, cartoonish enemy (depicted as a tiny, grumpy cloud with arms crossed) trying to approach but is being stopped by an invisible barrier labeled ''without making an enemy''. The background includes a comfy sofa, a potted plant, and a framed motivational poster on the wall that says ''Speak Kindly''. The overall mood is light, friendly, and clever, with exaggerated facial expressions and bright colors to emphasize humor and warmth.'),
 (812, 'Humor, Language, Philosophy Humor', 'Tact: the unsaid part of what you are thinking.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters in a casual conversation. One character is speaking with a thought bubble above their head showing a blunt or rude comment. The other character listens with a polite smile but has a transparent bubble near their head labeled ''Tact'' that mutes or hides part of the thought bubble. The background is a simple living room or coffee shop setting with a few chairs and a table. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated, emphasizing the contrast between the harsh thought and the softened spoken words to represent tact as the unsaid part of what you are thinking.'),
 (813, 'Animals, Humor, Word Play', 'Take time to smell the roses and eventually you''ll inhale a bee.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene set in a sunny garden filled with blooming roses. In the foreground, a cheerful person is bending down with their nose very close to a bright red rose, enjoying the scent. Nearby, a comically large bee with wide eyes and little motion lines is zooming right toward the person''s nose. The person''s eyes are slightly wide, indicating surprise or imminent reaction. Surrounding elements include other flowers, a clear blue sky, and a few playful buzzing bees to emphasize the garden atmosphere. The overall tone is lighthearted and humorous, with exaggerated expressions and playful design to highlight the unexpected moment of inhaling a bee while smelling the flowers.'),
 (814, 'History Humor, Humor, Politics', 'Taxation with representation isn''t so hot, either.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a colonial-era character from the American Revolution period sitting at a simple wooden table. The character looks frustrated and is holding a scroll labeled ''Taxation Without Representation.'' Opposite him, a modern-day person in casual clothing sits at the same table holding a paper labeled ''Taxation With Representation,'' also looking unhappy but resigned. Above their heads, include speech bubbles: the colonial character saying, ''Taxation without representation is terrible!'' and the modern character replying, ''Taxation with representation isn''t so hot, either.'' The setting should exaggerate the contrast between the two eras by showing a colonial-style room on one side and a modern office-like setting on the other, both blending humorously. Keep the expressions exaggerated and cartoonish to emphasize frustration and irony. The overall scene should evoke humor about the woes of taxes across time without any negativity beyond mild grumbling.'),
 (815, 'Humor, Politics, Social Commentary', 'Taxes are not levied for the benefit of the taxed.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a confused, slightly frustrated taxpayer sitting at a cluttered desk covered in paperwork labeled ''Taxes.'' The taxpayer is holding a form and looking at a large, looming, shadowy figure in the background labeled ''Government'' or ''Tax Authority.'' The figure is happily counting money bags or throwing money into a giant vault, clearly benefiting from the taxes. The taxpayer’s speech bubble reads, ''Taxes are not levied for my benefit?!'' In the foreground, piles of money flow from the taxpayer’s desk toward the vault, emphasizing the one-sided benefit. The overall style should be lighthearted and exaggerated, with expressive faces and bright colors to emphasize humor without any aggression or political symbols.'),
 (816, 'Motivational, Philosophy Humor, School', 'Teachers aren''t the ''enemy.'' Other students aren''t the ''enemy.'' The only real ''enemy'' is what we believe we cannot accomplish.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon classroom scene. At the center, a confident student stands facing a large, friendly blackboard with the phrase ''The only real enemy is what we believe we cannot accomplish'' written boldly. Surrounding the student are smiling classmates who look supportive, and the teacher is giving a thumbs up, showing encouragement. Instead of traditional intimidation, the ''enemy'' is depicted as a silly, small, and goofy-looking shadow labeled ''Self-Doubt'' that is comically sneaking away, defeated. The classroom setting should be bright and optimistic with posters about learning and success on the walls. Keep the style playful and lighthearted, emphasizing the positive message that challenges come from within, not from others in the environment.'),
 (817, 'Humor, School, Word Play', 'Teachers have class.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a bright, cheerful classroom. In the center stands a smiling teacher with a confident pose, wearing glasses and holding a book titled ''Class.'' Around the teacher are cartoonish floating objects symbolizing ''class''—such as a little top hat, a monocle, and a fancy teacup—floating lightly in the air like magical icons. The chalkboard behind the teacher has the words ''Teachers have class'' written in playful, bold letters, with doodles of students clapping or giving thumbs-up. The room contains typical classroom elements: desks with notebooks, a globe, a clock on the wall, and colorful posters. The overall mood is lighthearted and witty, emphasizing the pun on ''class'' as both a group of students and having elegance or style. The cartoon style should be fun and exaggerated, with happy expressions and vibrant colors to capture the double meaning of the joke without any negativity or complexity.'),
 (818, 'Humor, Relatable Humor, Word Play', 'TELECRASTINATION (tel e kras tin ay'' shun) n. The act of always letting the phone ring at least twice before you pick it up, when you''re only six inches away.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy living room. A person is sitting comfortably on a couch, half-turned away from a ringing smartphone lying on a coffee table just six inches away. The phone screen shows incoming call with animated ringing lines or sound waves around it. The person has an exaggerated, amused expression, looking casually disinterested yet intentionally delaying picking up the call. Include a clock on the wall showing a couple of seconds passing, and maybe a thought bubble above the person reading: ''I''ll let it ring twice…'' The overall style should be light, colorful, and quirky with simple exaggerated features to highlight the playful procrastination of answering the phone.'),
 (819, 'Humor, Irony', 'Tell me what you need, and I''ll tell you how to get along without it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy living room. On the left, a person with a friendly, slightly sarcastic smile is leaning forward in a comfortable armchair, gesturing with one hand as if giving advice. On the right, another person stands with a puzzled expression, holding a shopping list titled ''What I need.'' The room has a simple setting: a small coffee table with a cup of tea, a bookshelf in the background, and a window showing a sunny day outside. Above the seated person, a speech bubble reads: ''Tell me what you need, and I''ll tell you how to get along without it.'' The overall style is light and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the sarcastic humor of the advice given in the joke.'),
 (820, 'Humor, Irony, Workplace', 'Tell your boss what you think of him, and the truth shall set you free.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in an office setting. Centered is an employee standing confidently in front of a boss’s desk. The employee has a cheeky, mischievous grin, mid-speech, clearly speaking their mind. The boss looks caught off guard with wide eyes, slightly startled but not angry. The office includes common items like a desk with papers, a computer, and a nameplate that reads ''Boss''. Nearby, a window shows a sunny sky, symbolizing the phrase ''the truth shall set you free.'' Add a small freedom bird flying outside the window as a visual pun. The style should be light, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the humor of telling the boss the truth setting someone free rather than resulting in trouble.'),
 (821, 'Humor, Programming, Puns', 'Testing can show the presence of bugs, but not their absence.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon featuring a quirky software tester in a casual office setting cluttered with computers and coding books. The tester is holding a magnifying glass up to a computer screen filled with visible cartoon bugs (small, colorful insects with funny faces) crawling over lines of code. The tester looks puzzled, scratching their head. In the background, a whiteboard has the phrase ''Testing can show the presence of bugs but not their absence'' written in playful letters. Around the room, small whimsical details like a coffee mug labeled ''Bug Hunter'' and sticky notes with code jokes add to the lighthearted tech atmosphere. The style is bright, colorful, and exaggerated for comedic effect, with the bugs looking more mischievous than scary, emphasizing the joke''s pun on software bugs rather than real insects.'),
 (822, 'Humor, Puns', 'Thank you for holding your breath while I smoke.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in a public place like a small elevator or a waiting room. There''s a person standing, holding their breath with puffed cheeks and cheeks turning slightly red, clearly struggling to keep from breathing. Nearby, another character is casually smoking a cigarette or a cigar, looking apologetic but relaxed. Include subtle smell lines (wavy lines) rising from the smoker to visually represent smoke. The background should be simple, with a clock on the wall and a few chairs to set the scene. Both characters should have exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the humor: the holder of breath looks uncomfortable but polite, while the smoker looks sheepish but amused. Make the style lighthearted and cartoonish, avoiding anything aggressive or unpleasant.'),
 (823, 'Humor, Life', 'Thank you for your attention. We now return to regular programming.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a vintage black-and-white TV set with rabbit ear antennas in the center. The TV screen displays the text ''Thank you for your attention. We now return to regular programming.'' The background is a cozy living room setting with colorful, slightly exaggerated furniture such as a comfy armchair, a side table with a lamp, and a curious cat or dog watching the TV. The overall mood is lighthearted and amusing, emphasizing the sudden transition from something important back to normal everyday TV shows. The style is simple and playful with expressive characters and slightly exaggerated proportions to bring out the comic effect of the announcement.'),
 (824, 'Humor, Relatable Humor', 'That must be wonderful! I don''t understand it at all.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters engaged in conversation. One person is speaking enthusiastically with a bright smile and wide-open eyes, perhaps holding a book or pointing to a complex chart or diagram. The other character looks utterly confused, scratching their head, eyebrows furrowed, with a puzzled expression. They might be holding their chin or shrugging. The background should be a simple indoor setting, like a cozy living room or a casual office, with minimal distractions. The contrast between enthusiasm and confusion should be emphasized, using exaggerated facial expressions and body language to highlight the humor of misunderstanding. Optional small speech bubbles can show a jumble of indecipherable symbols or words behind the speaker and question marks around the listener’s head to further convey confusion.'),
 (825, 'Humor, Puns, Science', 'The 2 most common elements in the universe are hydrogen and stupidity', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set in outer space. Show a colorful, whimsical depiction of the universe with stars, galaxies, and planets scattered in the background. In the center, depict two large, smiling, and cartoonish characters representing the elements mentioned: one as a bubbly, happy hydrogen atom with a big ''H'' on its body, and the other as a goofy, silly-looking character symbolizing ''stupidity''—for example, a funny creature with crossed eyes, a silly grin, and a little thought bubble showing a question mark or light bulb dimmed out. The hydrogen atom should look smart and scientific, wearing little glasses and maybe holding a tiny beaker, while the ''stupidity'' character contrasts by looking simple-minded and goofy. Both should be floating side by side in space, emphasizing they are the ''most common elements.'' The cartoon style should be light-hearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions to highlight the humor without any negative or offensive connotations.'),
 (826, 'Humor, Life', 'The amount of sleep required by the average person is just five minutes more.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a sleepy person trying to measure their sleep with a giant, exaggerated analog clock. The person, looking tired and disheveled with messy hair and pajamas, is lying in bed but has one eye slightly open, holding a giant alarm clock that clearly shows 5 minutes past an hour. The background depicts a cozy bedroom setting with a bedside table holding a lamp, a cup of coffee, and an eyelid-shaped pillow. A calendar on the wall humorously shows days passing by quickly, emphasizing the minimal sleep time. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with soft colors and exaggerated expressions to highlight the ridiculousness of needing ''just five minutes more'' of sleep. The humor focuses on the universal feeling of always wanting more sleep, despite how impossible that often is.'),
 (827, 'Animals, Cartoon, Humor', 'The ant always falls over on its right side when intoxicated.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon of a small ant standing on a tiny patch of ground or a leaf. The ant is shown in mid-fall, tipping dramatically to its right side with wide, exaggerated eyes and a silly grin, clearly looking intoxicated. Around its head, classic cartoon-style swirling stars or bubbles float to indicate dizziness. Nearby, a small bottle labeled with a comical ''ant-sized'' drink (such as a tiny bottle with a leaf or sugar cube icon) lies tipped over, spilling a few drops. The background is simple and bright, focusing on the ant''s funny predicament without clutter. The overall style is lighthearted, cute, and family-friendly, emphasizing the ant''s silly stumble as if it were a tiny cartoon character in a playful situation.'),
 (828, 'Animals, Good Question!, Humor', 'The average human eats eight spiders in their lifetime at night. (In this case I HOPE I am not average!)', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a person sleeping peacefully in bed at night, with a worried expression and wide-open eyes as if just having a nightmare. Above the bed, a humorous thought bubble shows eight tiny cartoon spiders sneaking toward the person, each spider comically tiptoeing with exaggerated sneaky poses. The bedroom is cozy and simple, with a lamp on a nightstand and a window showing a dark night sky with stars. The overall style is lighthearted and humorous, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the funny fear of eating spiders unknowingly during sleep.'),
 (829, 'Exaggeration, Humor, Workplace', 'The average office chair on wheels travels about eight miles per year.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a typical office cubicle space. The main focus is a slightly worn office chair with wheels, depicted as if it’s a small vehicle, complete with a tiny road under its wheels drawn on the office floor. The chair looks tired but determined, maybe with little cartoon eyes on the backrest, giving it personality. Around the chair, typical office items like a computer monitor, keyboard, coffee mug, stack of papers, and a potted plant are visible. To emphasize the joke, include a small wall poster or whiteboard nearby with a sarcastic graph or note reading ''Annual Distance Traveled: 8 Miles'' as if it’s a serious statistic. The overall art style is colorful and playful with exaggerated expressions and clean lines, giving a light-hearted and funny representation of how little these chairs actually move despite their mobility potential.'),
 (830, 'Good Question!, Humor, Word Play', 'The average person has one ovary and one testicle.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a diverse group of people standing in a line, each showing a comical, exaggerated body outline that highlights their reproductive organs. For each person, show one ovary clearly marked on one side and one testicle on the opposite side, like a quirky anatomy diagram. People should look puzzled or confused, glancing down at their own outline with exaggerated expressions. The background is simple, such as a friendly doctor''s office or classroom setting, with a large chart behind them titled ''Average Human Reproductive Organs'' showing one ovary and one testicle humorously circled. Use bright, cheerful colors and rounded shapes to keep it light and funny. Avoid any detailed or realistic anatomy; keep all features cartoonishly simplified and exaggerated for comedic effect. No violence or sensitive imagery, just fun confusion around a silly, false ''fact.'''),
 (831, 'Humor about Gender, Word Play', 'The average woman would rather have beauty than brains, because the average man can see better than he can think.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters: a man and a woman standing side by side. The woman is styled in a classic beauty look, with exaggeratedly perfect makeup, shining hair, and a confident smile. The man is depicted with cartoonishly large eyes that are humorously exaggerated to indicate strong visual perception; his thinking bubble above his head is small or nearly empty, implying limited thinking ability. The background is simple with soft pastel colors, emphasizing the characters. The woman might be holding a mirror or a beauty-related object, while the man wears glasses or squints with overly focused eyes. Both characters have exaggerated facial expressions to enhance the humor: the woman is proud and self-assured, the man is mildly clueless but visually attentive. No violence or negativity is shown, keeping the tone light and funny.'),
 (832, 'Irony, Philosophy Humor', 'The basis of optimism is sheer terror.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful-looking person standing on a cliff edge with an exaggeratedly terrified expression, eyes wide and hair standing on end. Behind them, dark storm clouds swirl ominously, but instead of looking worried, the person wears an overly bright smile, almost forced. Emphasize the contrast between their scared demeanor and their optimistic grin. Include a small speech bubble above their head that says, "This is great!" to highlight ironic optimism. The cliff is detailed with cracks and loose rocks to enhance the danger, but the overall style should be lighthearted and comical, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to maintain a funny and non-threatening tone.'),
 (833, 'Life, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'The best laid plans of mice and men are usually about equal.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small mouse and a man side by side, both looking frustrated but determined. The mouse is wearing tiny, old-fashioned overalls with a small blueprint rolled out in front of it, filled with complex little designs (like tiny traps or cheese wheels). The man, dressed in casual clothes, holds a similar-sized but much bigger blueprint showing a grand plan involving houses or machines. Both are sitting at a picnic table or simple drafting table outdoors, perhaps in a park, to emphasize equality despite size difference. Their expressions are comically serious as if their plans are equally complicated and likely to fail. Around them, subtle chaos like spilled coffee near the man, and a small fallen piece of cheese near the mouse suggests the plans might not work out. The background is bright and cheerful, reinforcing the light-hearted, ironic tone of the joke.'),
 (834, 'Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'The best prophet of the future is the past.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple room with a large crystal ball resting on a small round table covered by a purple cloth. Behind the table, a cheerful fortune teller wearing a colorful robe and a turban is dramatically pointing at the crystal ball. Inside the crystal ball, instead of mystical swirls or visions, there is a clear and detailed depiction of an old-fashioned scroll labeled ''The Past'' with an ancient quill pen on top. The fortune teller has a speech bubble that says, "The best prophet of the future is the past!" Around the room, funny little details include a calendar on the wall showing yesterday''s date, and a history book lying open beside the crystal ball. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions and bright colors, emphasizing the irony that to predict the future you just look at the past rather than magic or mystery.'),
 (835, 'Aging, Family, Humor', 'The best revenge is to live long enough to be a problem to your children.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing an elderly person sitting comfortably in a cozy living room, with a mischievous grin. The elderly person is surrounded by two grown-up children who look exasperated and slightly overwhelmed. One child is holding a phone and looking stressed, while the other is trying to tidy up but hesitates. Include typical home elements like a comfy armchair, a small table with a cup of tea, family photos on the wall, and a clock showing late afternoon. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the idea that the older person is still active and causing harmless trouble for their adult children.'),
 (836, 'Aging, Life, Philosophy Humor', 'The best thing about growing older is that it takes such a long time.', NULL, 'A cheerful elderly person with gray hair and glasses is sitting comfortably in a rocking chair on a porch during a sunny day. They have a relaxed smile and are holding a cup of tea. Around them, there are elements that symbolize the passage of time: an old-fashioned grandfather clock, a calendar with many pages flipped off, and a long winding path stretching into the distance, symbolizing the long journey of aging. The scene is drawn in a bright, colorful cartoon style with soft edges and exaggerated features to enhance the humor and lightheartedness of the message. The overall mood is calm and positive, emphasizing patience and the slow but steady nature of growing older.'),
 (837, 'Exaggeration, Humor, Life', 'The best things in life are free. The second best things are very expensive.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene split into two panels. The first panel shows a cheerful person standing outdoors with arms wide open, surrounded by simple pleasures like a bright sun, birds flying, flowers, and a smiling tree, emphasizing ''free'' things. The second panel contrasts this by showing the same person staring overwhelmed at a shopping cart overflowing with shiny, expensive items such as luxury gadgets, designer clothes, and fancy food, with a worried expression and dollar signs floating above their head. The setting should be lighthearted and colorful with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the punchline that the best things in life cost nothing but the next best things cost a lot.'),
 (838, 'Pop Culture, Religious Humor, Science Fiction Humor', 'The Bible has been translated into Klingon.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy study room filled with bookshelves stacked with various colorful Bibles. In the center, a big open book labeled ''The Bible'' is displayed on a lectern. Next to it, a smaller book with the Klingon script on its cover is being held up proudly by a cheerful character wearing a Star Trek uniform, featuring the iconic Starfleet badge. Around them, a few characters dressed as Klingons—complete with ridged foreheads and warrior costumes—are enthusiastically reading copies of the Bible in Klingon. The background should have a mix of traditional religious objects, like candles and crosses, juxtaposed with sci-fi elements such as a warp drive console or a starship window showing space. The characters’ expressions are amused and pleased, creating a quirky blend of religion and science fiction humor in a lighthearted cartoon style.'),
 (839, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor, Psychology Humor', 'The careful application of terror is also a form of communication.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in a living room setting. A person stands nervously with wide eyes and raised eyebrows, holding a pet cat that looks alarmed with its fur puffed up. Nearby, another person sits on a couch with a knowing smirk, holding a small remote control labeled ''Terror Device.'' The background features simple furniture like a sofa, a coffee table with a cup of coffee, and a couple of framed pictures on the wall. The expression on the smirking person''s face should clearly convey the idea that the ''terror'' they are applying is intentional and playful, emphasizing the joke that terror can be a way of communicating. The overall style should be lighthearted and exaggerated, with clean lines and bright colors to enhance the comedic effect without any menace or fear.'),
 (840, 'Irony, Philosophy Humor', 'The chief cause of problems is solutions.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a giant, exaggeratedly complicated Rube Goldberg machine labeled ''Solution Machine,'' with lots of gears, levers, and pipes. In the foreground, a frustrated-looking person in casual clothes, scratching their head while looking at the mess. Around the machine, small signs say ''Problem #1,'' ''Problem #2,'' and silly unintended side effects, like a bucket of water spilling or a toy robot malfunctioning. The background is a simple office or workshop with scattered tools and papers, emphasizing a chaotic but comical atmosphere. The style is lighthearted, bright colors, round shapes, and exaggerated expressions to capture the irony that solutions often cause more problems.'),
 (841, 'Facts, Good Question!, History Humor', 'The cigarette lighter was invented before the match.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters in an old-fashioned inventor''s workshop filled with quirky gadgets and tools. One character is holding a classic cigarette lighter with a big proud smile, presenting it as if it were a brilliant invention. The second character looks confused and holds a simple matchstick in their hand, scratching their head as if puzzled by the claim. Display a timeline or signpost behind them with ''Cigarette Lighter: 1823'' and ''Match: 1826'' to subtly emphasize the joke. Make the setting vintage with wooden tables, blueprints scattered around, and an old incandescent light bulb hanging from the ceiling. Both characters have exaggerated cartoonish features such as big eyes and expressive faces to highlight the humor. Keep colors bright and playful to maintain a lighthearted mood.'),
 (842, 'Computers, Humor, Programming', 'The computer is mightier than the pen, the sword, and usually, the programmer.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a quirky office or workspace. At the center is a large, classic desktop computer with an exaggeratedly big screen and keyboard, looking confident and almost regal. Next to it, a traditional pen with eyes and a smirk is standing upright on a desk, looking slightly annoyed or defeated. Nearby, a shiny sword with cartoonish eyes and a frown leans against the desk, looking irritated. In the foreground, a frustrated programmer slouches in a chair, rubbing their temples, wearing casual clothes and glasses, surrounded by scattered coffee cups and crumpled papers. The programmer looks tired and overwhelmed, while the computer appears to be smugly ''winning'' this silent battle. The background should be a simple office setting with humorous details like tech posters or scribbled notes. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke''s irony about computers being mightier than the pen, the sword, and the programmer themselves.'),
 (843, 'Puns, Word Play', 'The cost of feathers has risen.... now even down is up!', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cozy bedroom with a large, fluffy down comforter on a bed. The comforter looks unusually dense and expensive, with small price tags hanging from the feathers and the word ''Feathers'' prominently displayed on a sign next to it. To emphasize the joke, show an arrow pointing upward above the comforter with the words ''Down is UP!'' in big, playful letters. Include a puzzled character (could be a person with an exaggerated confused expression, scratching their head) standing beside the bed, looking at the comforter and a receipt or price tag showing a high price. The room should feel warm and inviting, with light-hearted colors and cartoon-style exaggeration, like puffed-up pillows and a small bird looking shocked or surprised nearby. Avoid any aggressive or negative imagery, focusing on the playful absurdity of ''down'' (feathers) being ''up'' (expensive).'),
 (844, 'Economics Humor, Life, Word Play', 'The cost of living hasn''t affected its popularity.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a lively marketplace stall labeled ''Cost of Living''. The stall is packed with colorful items like fresh fruit, vegetables, bread, and household goods, all with price tags. Around the stall, joyful cartoon people crowd happily, clearly unfazed and very interested. Above the stall, a big sign reads ''Cost of Living'' but there are also little balloons or stickers indicating ''Popular!'' and ''Loved by All''. The expressions on the people’s faces show excitement or delight, indicating that despite rising prices shown by exaggerated, comically high price tags, the popularity or interest in the market stall stays strong. The style should be light, cheerful, and whimsical to reflect the joke’s irony, emphasizing the contrast between the high cost and the continued popularity without any negativity or stress.'),
 (845, 'Facts, Humor, Travel Humor', 'The cruise liner, Queen Elizabeth II, moves only six inches for each gallon of diesel that it burns.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, classic cruise liner labeled ''Queen Elizabeth II'' prominently on its side. The ship should look massive and slightly exaggerated with multiple decks, smokestacks puffing out small clouds of smoke. Next to the ship, a huge, oversized diesel fuel gauge or fuel tank is shown, and a tiny measuring tape or ruler stretched exactly six inches along the water just in front of the ship''s bow. On the side, a small cartoon character (an engineer or ship captain with a surprised expression) is holding a gallon-sized fuel canister, looking incredulous as the ship creeps forward just a tiny distance. The scene is set on a calm ocean with gentle waves and a bright sunny sky, drawn in a colorful, light-hearted cartoon style emphasizing the slow movement versus the large fuel consumption in a playful, non-serious way.'),
 (846, 'Humor, Programming, Puns', 'The determined programmer can write a FORTRAN program in any language.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a programmer sitting confidently at a cluttered desk filled with multiple monitors, keyboards, and coffee mugs. The programmer has a focused and slightly smug expression, wearing casual techie clothes and glasses. Displayed on one monitor is code written in FORTRAN, but the surrounding screens show code snippets in various human languages (like English, French, Chinese characters, and Spanish) mixed with programming elements. A speech bubble above the programmer reads: "I can write FORTRAN in any language!" The background includes typical programmer items like sticky notes, a small plant, and a clock showing late hours. The overall style is light-hearted and exaggerated, emphasizing the programmer''s determination and skill humorously without any harshness or negativity.'),
 (847, 'Humor, Relatable Humor', 'The difference between antiques and junk is who''s running the garage sale.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a lively, colorful garage sale in a suburban driveway. On one side, an elderly individual with glasses and a proud smile is carefully displaying elegant, polished old items labeled as ''Antiques'' on a vintage tablecloth. These include a classic vase, an ornate clock, and an old-fashioned lamp. On the other side, a younger person with casual clothes and a slightly messy appearance is throwing a bunch of random, worn-out-looking items onto a folding table with a sign that says ''Junk''. Around them are a few confused buyers looking puzzled but curious. The background shows a cozy house and some balloons tied to the tables for a festive feel. The sky is bright and sunny to keep the tone light and friendly. The overall style is cartoonish with exaggerated expressions to enhance the humor of the difference being just ''who’s running the garage sale''.'),
 (848, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'The difference between genius and stupidity is that genius has its limits.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters side by side. On the left, a person labeled ''Genius'' has a large, glowing brain visible above their head, wearing glasses and a thoughtful expression. They are surrounded by books, math equations, or scientific symbols floating in the air, indicating intelligence and limits. On the right, a person labeled ''Stupidity'' looks confused or silly with a goofy, exaggerated facial expression, scratching their head with question marks circling above it, with an endless road or path stretching behind them to symbolize ''no limits.'' The background is light, with a simple classroom or office setting to keep a casual, friendly mood. The style should be colorful, whimsical, and exaggerated without any negativity, emphasizing the playful contrast between intelligence and foolishness in a light-hearted manner.'),
 (849, 'Humor, Word Play', 'The direct approach is the best approach.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting two characters in a casual conversation outdoors. One character is holding a large, comically oversized arrow pointed straight towards the other character, emphasizing the ''direct approach.'' The other character looks surprised but amused. The background is simple with a few trees and a park bench to set a casual, friendly environment. Both characters wear casual clothes and have exaggerated facial expressions to enhance the humor. The oversized arrow should look funny and exaggerated, almost like a cartoon prop, reinforcing the idea of being very direct. The style should be light-hearted and colorful to match the joke tone, with clean lines and expressive body language.'),
 (850, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'The dog''s kennel is not the place to keep a sausage.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene showing a cheerful doghouse (kennel) in a backyard. The doghouse is typical with a little arched entrance and a nameplate above it labeled ''Fido''. Inside the doghouse, instead of a dog, there is a plump, cartoon-style sausage lying comfortably on a small cushion, looking surprised or confused. Outside the kennel, a happy dog with a wagging tail looks at the sausage inside, tilting its head in curiosity. The background includes simple grass, a fence, and a bright sunny sky to give it a lighthearted and funny atmosphere. The style should be clear, bold lines, with playful expressions to emphasize the absurdity of putting a sausage inside a doghouse rather than a dog.'),
 (851, 'Humor, Motivational, Word Play', 'The door of opportunity won''t open unless you do some pushing!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, ornate door labeled ''Opportunity'' in big letters. The door is closed and slightly ajar, set in a bright and inviting hallway or entranceway. In front of the door stands a cheerful cartoon character with a friendly expression, using both hands to push against the door with visible effort. The character''s body is leaning forward slightly to emphasize the pushing action, and small sweat droplets or motion lines can show exertion. Behind the character, scattered thought bubbles or signs with motivational words like ''Push!'' or ''Try!'' add to the encouragement theme. The background is simple and lighthearted, with warm colors to keep the tone positive and funny but not intense. The overall style is playful, with exaggerated expressions and simple lines to enhance the joke''s message that the door (opportunity) only opens when you push (take action). No violent or political elements.'),
 (852, 'Humor, Life, Relatable Humor', 'The dream is the reward for finally getting to sleep.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a tired person in bed surrounded by sleep-related items. The person looks exhausted but joyful, already half-asleep with a smile, snuggled under a cozy blanket with a pillow. Above them, a dream bubble floats, showing a shining golden trophy with the word ''Dream'' on it as if it were a grand prize. The background includes a simple bedroom setting with a nightstand holding a lamp and an alarm clock showing late night hours. The overall tone is light and funny, emphasizing relief and reward after a struggle to fall asleep without any intense or negative imagery.'),
 (853, 'Random', 'The early bird may get the worm, but the second mouse gets the cheese. (Think about it some more.)', NULL, ''),
 (854, 'Exaggeration, Humor, Science', 'The earth is like a tiny grain of sand, only much, much heavier.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a giant hand holding a tiny, detailed grain of sand. Inside the grain of sand is a miniature Earth with recognizable continents and oceans. The Earth/grain looks small and delicate, but a comic-style weight scale next to the hand shows an exaggeratedly high weight, represented with a big, bold number and a sweating cartoon character struggling to hold it. The background is simple with a bright sky and a few clouds, emphasizing the contrast between the Earth and the grain of sand. The style is light-hearted and exaggerated, with cartoonish expressions to highlight the joke about the Earth being a tiny grain of sand, but much heavier than one would expect.'),
 (855, 'Humor, Programming', 'The effort required to correct a programming error increases with time.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a cluttered programmer''s workspace. On the left, a developer with exaggeratedly frazzled hair and wide eyes sits at a desk, staring at a computer screen showing a glowing red error message. Near the developer, a calendar on the wall shows days getting crossed off rapidly, emphasizing the passage of time. To the right, a large staircase or mountain labeled ''Effort'' rises steeply upward, with the programmer struggling to carry an increasingly heavy-looking error bug as they climb. The bug should look like a cartoonish beetle with a sad or mischievous face. The overall tone is lighthearted and cartoonish, with whimsical expressions and bright colors. The background includes coding symbols floating around to reinforce the programming context. No violence or inappropriate content, just a funny visual metaphor for how fixing bugs gets harder over time.'),
 (856, 'Good Question!, History Humor, Military Humor', 'The Eisenhower interstate system requires that one mile in every five must be straight.  These straight sections are usable as airstrips in times of war or other emergencies.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a long stretch of highway with a perfectly straight section highlighted, resembling an airstrip runway. The highway is labeled ''Eisenhower Interstate System.'' On one side of the road, there is a small vintage airplane parked on the straight section as if it had just landed or is ready to take off. A few cars are nearby, looking surprised or curious. The surrounding landscape should be simple and slightly exaggerated for comedic effect, with green fields and road signs indicating mile markers and a sign that reads ''1 mile straight - usable as airstrip.'' The style is colorful and lighthearted, emphasizing the absurdity and cleverness of highways doubling as emergency runways without any tension or danger.'),
 (857, 'Dark Humor, History Humor, Jobs', 'The electric chair was invented by a dentist.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a vintage dentist''s office with an old-fashioned wooden electric chair in the center, equipped with wires and electrodes attached to it. The dentist, wearing a white coat and a silly, exaggeratedly large dentist head mirror, stands beside the chair holding a giant electric drill and flashing a mischievous grin. Around the room, typical dental tools (mirror, pliers, toothbrush) are scattered casually, with a poster on the wall labeled ''Electric Chair: Dentists'' Greatest Invention.'' The style is bright and colorful with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke''s irony, making it clear and funny without any hint of violence or discomfort.'),
 (858, 'Good Question!, Philosophy Humor', 'The facts, although interesting, are irrelevant.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a classroom or lecture hall. In the center, a bored or unimpressed student with exaggeratedly crossed arms and a skeptical expression sits at a desk piled with books and papers labeled ''Facts.'' The teacher or lecturer at the front gestures towards a large blackboard filled with numerous detailed facts and scientific formulas written in neat handwriting. Around the student, funny little visual icons like question marks or an eye-roll symbol show disinterest. The overall style should be bright and colorful with clean lines and expressive, exaggerated facial features that highlight boredom and irrelevance. No violent or sensitive elements—just a lighthearted critique of how sometimes knowing facts doesn’t impact the bigger picture.'),
 (859, 'Humor, Life, Programming', 'The fastest algorithm can freqently be replaced by one that is almost as fast and much easier to understand.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple office or study room. On one side, a stressed-out programmer or computer scientist is sitting at a desk cluttered with complex code printouts, a coffee cup, and a laptop displaying tangled, hard-to-read code labeled ''Fastest Algorithm.'' They look frustrated and overwhelmed. On the other side, a relaxed, cheerful character holds a neatly organized, much simpler flowchart or code labeled ''Almost as Fast Algorithm,'' smiling confidently. The two characters face each other, highlighting the contrast between complexity and simplicity. The background has math symbols and algorithm diagrams floating whimsically in the air. The overall tone is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions emphasizing the struggle with complexity versus ease of understanding. Keep the colors bright and friendly, avoiding any technical jargon on screen other than the simple labels.'),
 (860, 'Animals, Humor, Science', 'The fingerprints of koala bears are virtually indistinguishable from those of humans, so much so that they could be confused at a crime scene.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a detective''s crime lab. In the foreground, a confused detective dressed in classic detective attire (trench coat, magnifying glass in hand) is examining a fingerprint on a glass slide under a microscope. On the lab table next to him, there is a sleepy, cute koala bear wearing tiny reading glasses and holding a magnifying glass as if trying to solve a mystery itself. The background shows a typical forensic wall with fingerprint charts pinned up and a whiteboard labeled ''CASE: Koala or Human?''. The koala should look innocent and slightly puzzled. The overall mood is lighthearted and funny, with exaggerated expressions on the detective and koala to emphasize the surprising similarity of their fingerprints. The style should be bright with clear cartoonish lines and comical facial features to highlight the joke without any realistic or dark elements.'),
 (861, 'Life, Relatable Humor', 'The first parking space you see will be the last parking space you see.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in a parking lot. In the foreground, a frustrated driver sits inside a small car, gripping the steering wheel tightly with a worried expression. The car is stopped just before the first available parking space, which is clearly open and empty. Behind the car, the parking lot is shown with dozens of cars tightly parked and no other open spots visible. Above the scene, a whimsical caption bubble reads: ''The first parking space you see will be the last parking space you see.'' The parking lot should have light humor style details like a ''No Parking'' sign on the far side, a distant clock tower or tree for background, and a little trickle of sweat on the driver''s forehead to show impatience. The style should be colorful, exaggerated cartoon with clear expressions emphasizing the irony of finding a spot early but knowing it''s the only one.'),
 (862, 'Humor, Life', 'The first three minutes of your life can be dangerous ... The last three can be pretty dodgy too!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a baby in a crib on the left side, looking freshly born with a surprised face, surrounded by three large, ticking clocks labeled ''First 3 minutes.'' On the right side, an elderly person with a mischievous smile is sitting in an armchair, wrapped in a blanket, with another set of three clocks labeled ''Last 3 minutes.'' Both sides are separated by a big, central clock with exaggerated, oversized hands. The background is light and cheerful with soft pastel colors. The baby wears a little bonnet and has a slightly frazzled look, while the elderly person looks relaxed but cheeky, holding a cup of tea. The style is playful, with exaggerated expressions and cartoonish lines to emphasize the humor about the potential dangers at the very beginning and end of life. No scary or dark imagery, just lighthearted and funny.'),
 (863, 'History Humor, Humor, Pop Culture', 'The first toilet ever seen on television was on ''Leave It To Beaver''.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set in a vintage 1950s living room with classic mid-century furniture and decor. Place a large, old-fashioned television set with big dials and rabbit ear antennas in the center. On the TV screen, show a cartoonishly exaggerated toilet bowl with water inside, making it obvious it’s a toilet. Add a small caricature of Beaver from the show "Leave It To Beaver" standing beside the TV, looking surprised or curious. Include details like the show''s logo or a retro TV screen border to emphasize the era. The overall tone should be light-hearted and nostalgic, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions for a funny and wholesome vibe. No violence or anything inappropriate should be included.'),
 (864, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'The future isn''t what it used to be... it never was.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a simple living room with a person sitting in an old-fashioned armchair, looking thoughtfully into the distance. Above their head is a classic thought bubble with a whimsical, blurry illustration of a futuristic city that is half-built and half-disintegrated, with uncertain shapes and question marks floating around it. The person looks a bit confused and slightly amused, with one eyebrow raised. Around them are some retro objects, like an old radio, a calendar on the wall showing a past year, and a clock with loose numbers falling off. The style is light-hearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions and rounded, soft lines for a classic cartoon feel. No violence or controversial elements present.'),
 (865, 'Life, Motivational, Philosophy Humor', 'The greatest use of life is to spend it on something that will outlast it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful person planting a large, vibrant tree labeled ''Life''s Legacy.'' The person is watering the tree with a watering can while smiling proudly. In the background, smaller trees and saplings are visible, representing things that outlast a single life. Above the scene, a sunny sky with a clock subtly blending into a sun symbolizes the passage of time. The style is lighthearted and colorful with exaggerated, friendly facial expressions and rounded shapes to emphasize positivity and longevity, avoiding any violence or negativity.'),
 (866, 'Dad, Humor, Shopping Jokes', 'The grocery store cashier asked dad ''do you want the milk in the bag'' He said ''No - just leave it in the carton''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a grocery store checkout aisle. Show a friendly, slightly bemused grocery store cashier standing behind the register, wearing a name tag and a standard cashier uniform. In front of the cashier is a typical middle-aged dad character holding a carton of milk. The dad has a deadpan or mildly confused expression, as if he’s not quite following the usual checkout routine. The milk carton should clearly be visible in his hand, and it should look like a typical milk carton with a label. The cashier has just asked, ''Do you want the milk in the bag?'' A speech bubble from the dad says, ''No – just leave it in the carton.'' Around them, add subtle grocery store details like a conveyor belt with a few items, shopping bags hanging on hooks, and shelves stocked with colorful products in the background. The mood is light, playful, and typical of a family-friendly cartoon gag. Use bright colors, clean lines, and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humor.'),
 (867, 'Humor, Word Play', 'The guy who coined the term ''coined the term'', coined the term ''coined the term''.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a quirky, slightly confused-looking man sitting at an old-fashioned desk cluttered with papers and a large, vintage dictionary opened in front of him. Above his head is a large, glowing light bulb indicating he has just had an idea. On the desk, there is a small plaque or nameplate that reads ''Mr. Wordsmith.'' Around him, in a playful visual effect like comic-style echo bubbles, the phrase ''coined the term'' is repeated multiple times, each bubble shaped like a speech balloon with little quotation marks. The background shows a cozy, book-filled study with a large bookshelf packed with thick books titled with various linguistic or phrase-related labels. The overall style is colorful, cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the man''s pride and slight bewilderment about the phrase he created. No other characters are present, keeping focus entirely on the man and his catchy phrase being ''coined.'''),
 (868, 'Food Humor, Puns, Relatable Humor, Steven Wright', 'The hardness of the butter is proportional to the softness of the bread.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon kitchen scene focusing on a loaf of bread and a butter stick on a counter. The loaf of bread looks soft and squishy, with a relaxed, happy facial expression and slightly sagging sides to emphasize softness. Beside it, a stick of butter appears very hard and solid, with a strained, determined facial expression, almost like it''s flexing muscles to show firmness. The butter could have little sweat drops, showing effort to remain hard. Above them or nearby, a simple balance scale tips to one side, with the bread on the soft side and the butter on the hard side, visually representing the proverb-like relationship between their textures. The background is a simple brightly colored kitchen setting with a toaster, a butter knife, and a plate nearby. Make sure the overall look is lighthearted, cheerful, and playful, with exaggerated cartoon features on the bread and butter to clearly convey the joke about their opposing textures.'),
 (869, 'Facts, Humor, Language', 'The Hawaiian alphabet has only twelve letters - a,e,h,i,k,l,m,n,o,p,u,w.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful teacher standing in front of a classroom blackboard. On the blackboard, the Hawaiian alphabet letters a, e, h, i, k, l, m, n, o, p, u, w are neatly written in large, playful letters. The teacher holds a pointer and smiles broadly while several cartoon students, with puzzled or curious expressions, look on. Around the classroom, decorations include a ukulele leaning against the teacher''s desk, a small palm tree in a pot near the window, and a wall poster showing a map of Hawaii with a bright sun and waves. The atmosphere is lighthearted and educational, with bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the joke''s fun fact nature. The style is simple, clean, and clearly cartoonish, suitable for family-friendly humor without any violence or negativity.'),
 (870, 'Facts, Geography, Humor', 'The highest point in Pennsylvania is lower than the lowest point in Colorado.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon map scene showing two states side by side: Pennsylvania on the left and Colorado on the right. Above Pennsylvania, a small hill labeled ''Highest Point in PA'' barely peeks above the ground, looking very tiny and unimpressive, with a cartoon character shrugging or scratching their head. Colorado has a large mountain labeled ''Lowest Point in CO'' towering over the hill in Pennsylvania. The mountain should look very tall and exaggerated compared to the small Pennsylvania hill. Add playful clouds around the mountain top and a cheerful sun shining. The overall style is bright, colorful, and exaggerated to highlight the surprising fact that Pennsylvania’s highest spot is lower than Colorado’s lowest, adding a subtle, amusing vibe to geography.'),
 (871, 'Good Question!, Science', 'The human heart creates enough pressure when it pumps out to the body to squirt blood 30 feet.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a cartoon human heart with exaggerated angry eyes and arms flexing muscles, standing on a small podium labeled ''World''s Strongest Pump.'' From its main artery, a dramatic, high-pressure red stream of blood shoots out like a powerful water fountain, arching in the air and stretching about 30 feet. Nearby, a few surprised cartoon characters (people or animals) react in astonishment, some shielding their eyes or holding umbrellas to avoid the ''blood spray.'' The background is a simple lab or anatomy classroom setting with a blackboard illustrating a heart diagram, emphasizing a playful educational tone.'),
 (872, 'Computers, Humor, Science', 'The human mind ordinarily operates at only ten percent of its capacity - the rest is overhead for the operating system.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a human brain depicted as a large, complex computer control center inside a person''s head. The brain is illustrated like an old-fashioned computer room with colorful buttons, screens, and blinking lights. Half of the brain area is bustling with tiny cartoon figures (representing the ''mind'') working energetically, while the other half is filled with a maze of cables, wires, and a bulky, slightly outdated-looking ''operating system'' machine labeled as ''OS Overhead.'' The person appears puzzled, with their head slightly open like a computer tower, showing the inner workings. Above the scene, a light, playful caption reads, "Only 10% mind power, 90% OS overhead." The style is whimsical and exaggerated with bright colors and friendly, simple characters to enhance the joke’s playful tone.'),
 (873, 'Motivational, Philosophy Humor', 'The important thing is not to stop questioning.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a curious young child and a friendly-looking adult sitting together at a kitchen table. The child eagerly holds a magnifying glass up to a cookie on a plate, examining it closely with wide eyes and raised eyebrows. The adult, wearing glasses and a slight smile, gestures encouragingly with one hand as if nurturing the child''s curiosity. On the table are scattered question marks floating above as if arising from their conversation. The background shows a cozy kitchen with a window letting in sunlight and a bookshelf filled with books and a small globe. The overall vibe is warm, lighthearted, and emphasizes the theme of continuous questioning and curiosity, with playful exaggerated expressions on both characters’ faces to enhance the humor and inspiration of the quote.'),
 (874, 'Cars Humor, Humor, Travel Humor', 'The journey of a thousand miles begins with a broken fan belt and a leaky tire.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a long, winding road stretching far into the background, implying a very long journey. In the foreground, there is a small, vintage car that looks old and a bit run-down. The car has a visibly broken fan belt flapping loosely and a flat, leaky tire with air slowly hissing out, illustrated with little wavy lines or drops of air. The driver, a frustrated yet comical character wearing a cap, is standing next to the car looking at both problems with exaggerated surprise or disbelief. The sky is clear, and there are roadside signs indicating "1000 miles to go". The overall mood is lighthearted and funny, with exaggerated cartoon expressions and bright colors to emphasize the misfortune at the very start of a long trip.'),
 (875, 'Humor, Life, Workplace', 'The learning curve is steep for the first n years, then flattens out. Typical quote from those with n years experience.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting two characters standing next to a large, exaggerated line graph on a whiteboard. The graph''s y-axis is labeled ''Learning'' and the x-axis is labeled ''Years of Experience.'' The graph starts with a very steep upward slope for the first segment labeled ''n years,'' then suddenly flattens out into a straight horizontal line. One character, wearing glasses and holding a pointer stick, is confidently explaining the graph to the other character, who looks skeptical or puzzled. Around them are office or classroom elements like a desk with a coffee cup, a stack of books titled ''Experience'' and ''Skills,'' and a clock showing time passing. The overall style is lighthearted with clear, bold cartoon lines, bright colors, and exaggerated facial expressions emphasizing the humor in the idea that after some ''n'' years, learning stops or plateaus completely.'),
 (876, 'Irony, Life, Philosophy Humor', 'The less you risk, the more you lose when you win.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a character standing at the edge of a gambling table or game board with a very cautious, nervous expression. The character is holding a small stack of chips or tokens close to their chest, hesitating to place a bet. On the opposite side of the table, a confident, playful dealer or another character is smiling knowingly, gesturing toward a big pile of chips or prizes labeled ''WIN''. Include thought bubbles above the cautious character showing images of ''risk'' as a cliff or a dice roll, and ''reward'' as a big treasure chest or jackpot. The setting should be bright and colorful with exaggerated features to emphasize the mental tension between risk and reward, but the style is light-hearted and cartoonish, without any gambling encouragement or negativity. There should be a clear contrast between the small risk taken and the large potential prize, visually reinforcing the joke’s message: the less you risk, the more you lose when you win.'),
 (877, 'Animals, Good Question!, Humor', 'The longest recorded flight of a chicken is thirteen seconds.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a surprised chicken mid-air, flapping its wings wildly as it makes a shaky flight lasting exactly thirteen seconds. Draw a cartoon stopwatch or clock in the corner showing thirteen seconds to emphasize the flight duration. The background should be a simple farmyard with a wooden fence, green grass, and a red barn in the distance. Add a small group of chickens watching with amazed or curious expressions. Include a lighthearted banner or scoreboard above that says “Longest Chicken Flight: 13 Seconds.” The style should be colorful, exaggerated, and playful to accentuate the joke''s absurdity without any harsh or scary elements.'),
 (878, 'Halloween, Movies, Pop Culture', 'The mask used by Michael Myers in the original ''Halloween'' was actually a Captain Kirk mask painted white.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring two masks side by side on a dark shelf in a spooky Halloween setting. On the left is a classic Michael Myers mask—plain, white, and expressionless, slightly eerie. On the right is a well-known Captain Kirk mask from Star Trek, recognizable by its distinctive facial features and hair, but painted entirely white to mimic the Michael Myers mask. Include a small paintbrush and white paint can nearby to suggest the repainting. The background should have subtle Halloween decorations like a jack-o''-lantern and cobwebs to set the mood but keep the tone light and funny, not scary. Maybe add a speech bubble from the Captain Kirk mask saying something cheeky like ''To boldly scare,'' playing on his famous catchphrase. The style should be colorful, simple lines, and exaggerated facial features to emphasize humor and contrast between the two iconic characters.'),
 (879, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor, Space Humor', 'The meek shall inherit the Earth. The rest of us shall go the the Stars!', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon split into two halves. On the left side, depict a meek-looking person—timid, small, with wide eyes—standing on green Earth, holding a little plant or flower, symbolizing inheriting the Earth peacefully. The Earth should be bright and cheerful, with a few trees and animals to show a hospitable environment. On the right side, show a group of confident, adventurous-looking people wearing space suits or casual space traveler outfits, happily boarding or floating around a large spaceship labeled ''Stars.'' The background is a starry, deep-space scene with twinkling stars, planets, and a shining spaceship ready to take off. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions showing calm contentment on the Earth side and excitement or ambition on the Stars side. Make sure the scene is clear, friendly, and humorous, emphasizing the contrast between the meek inheriting Earth and the others aiming for the stars, without any negative or aggressive elements.'),
 (880, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'The meek shall inherit the earth... if that''s o.k. with the rest of you.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set outdoors with a small group of diverse, exaggeratedly confident characters standing on a globe representing Earth. In the center, a very meek-looking character (timid posture, glasses, a book labeled ''Meekness 101'') is raising a hand hesitantly and looking worried. Surrounding this character are several louder, bolder characters — one with crossed arms and a skeptical expression, another pointing at the meek character with a smirk, and a third rolling their eyes or shrugging. The globe beneath them is colorful and detailed with continents and oceans, emphasizing ''the Earth.'' The style is lighthearted and playful, with expressive faces showing disbelief or annoyance. A speech bubble above the meek character says, "The meek shall inherit the earth... if that''s o.k. with the rest of you." The background is simple, perhaps with a few clouds or sun to keep focus on characters and the globe. The overall tone is comedic and ironic, highlighting the meek character’s uncertainty and the others’ resistance in a non-threatening, funny way.'),
 (881, 'Good Question!, Humor, Science', 'The moon may be smaller than Earth, but it''s further away.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing the Earth and the Moon personified as characters in a playful distance competition. Earth is drawn as a large, round, blue-and-green globe with a smug, confident face and arms crossed. The Moon is smaller, gray with crater features, looking slightly annoyed but determined, standing farther away on the right side of the image. Between them is a simple horizontal distance scale or measuring tape stretching across the scene, emphasizing the Moon is farther away. The background is a starry dark space with a whimsical feel. Both characters have exaggerated, friendly cartoon facial expressions to highlight the joke''s lighthearted nature. Include a small sign or speech bubble near Earth saying, "I’m bigger," and near the Moon "But I’m farther away!" The style should be clean, vibrant cartoon with bold outlines, making the concept clear and funny without any aggressive or intense elements.'),
 (882, 'Humor, Relatable', 'The more that you hate a song, the more difficult it is to get out of your head.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person with a frustrated expression, sitting at a desk or on a couch with music notes and a cartoonish, ugly-looking song symbol (like a speech bubble with a jagged musical note) floating above their head. The person''s head is slightly exaggerated and enlarged to emphasize the idea of the song being stuck inside. Around them, faint ghostly musical notes swirl uncontrollably, emphasizing the ''stuck'' effect. The person is holding their hands to their temples or trying to block their ears. The background is simple, with a light color and maybe a small clock indicating time passing to show the annoyance lasting. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated features and bright colors to make the frustration funny and relatable without any aggression or negativity.'),
 (883, 'Humor, Relatable, Weather Humor', 'The most delightful advantage of being bald - you can hear snowflakes.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set outside on a snowy winter day. In the center is a bald man with a big, friendly smile, his shiny scalp clearly visible. Snowflakes are gently falling around him, and several large, distinct snowflakes are shown close to his head, as if making a soft sound. The man has his eyes closed and a peaceful, delighted expression, with one hand cupped behind an ear to ''hear'' the snowflakes. Around him, a simple snowy landscape with a few bare trees and a light blue sky. The overall tone is lighthearted and whimsical, emphasizing the funny idea that being bald allows him to hear the delicate sound of snow falling. The style should be colorful and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions, no text needed in the image.'),
 (884, 'Motivational, Sports Humor, Word Play', 'The most important quality of a champion is the burning desire to be a champion.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a determined, energetic character standing on a winner''s podium labeled ''Champion.'' The character has flames comically rising from their head and shoulders to represent the ''burning desire.'' The character is wearing a gold medal and sports attire, striking a confident pose with clenched fists and a big smile. Around the podium are cheering cartoon spectators holding signs that say ''Go Champion!'' The background is a colorful stadium with bright lights, emphasizing a competitive sports atmosphere. The scene should be lighthearted and exaggerated in style to highlight the pun on ''burning desire,'' with the flames looking more like playful cartoon fire rather than anything dangerous.'),
 (885, 'Good Question!, School, Word Play', 'The name of all the continents end with the same letter that they start with.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a friendly, slightly puzzled teacher standing in front of a classroom blackboard. On the blackboard are the names of the continents: Africa, Asia, Europe, Antarctica, Australia, South America, and North America. The teacher is pointing to the words with a pointer, highlighting the first and last letter of each continent name. The last and first letters are circled in bright colors (for example, ''A'' circled in Africa and Asia, ''E'' in Europe). The students, a diverse group of children, look surprised and amused, with one scratching their head in confusion. The setting is a simple classroom with posters of a world map and a globe on a desk. The overall style is colorful, lighthearted, and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions showing curiosity and amusement.'),
 (886, 'Irony, Sports Humor', 'The object of golf is to play the least amount of golf.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a bright, sunny golf course with green rolling hills and a clear blue sky. In the foreground, depict a cheerful, slightly confused golfer in classic golf attire (polo shirt, cap, golf glove) holding a golf club upside down, looking at a scorecard with a puzzled expression. Around him, show several golf balls scattered very close to the tee, some barely hit. Nearby, a golf cart is parked, with a flagstick standing in a hole not far from the player. Add a thought bubble above the golfer’s head with a playful text saying, "The less I play, the better my score!" The overall vibe should be light and whimsical, emphasizing the ironic statement that in golf, doing the least amount of playing can be the goal. The style is cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions and bright colors to highlight the joke’s humor.'),
 (887, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'The only reason some people get lost in thought is because it''s unfamiliar territory.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing at the edge of a small cliff labeled ''Thought Territory.'' The person looks confused and lost, holding a map upside down with a question mark above their head. Behind them is a familiar, cozy-looking town labeled ''Reality,'' with smiling people going about their day. The landscape around the cliff is whimsical and abstract, with floating clouds shaped like various symbols representing ideas (light bulbs, question marks). The style is playful and exaggerated, with bright colors and clean lines to emphasize the humor of being ''lost in thought'' as if it''s a physical place one can get lost in.'),
 (888, 'Humor, Life, Relatable', 'The only substitute for good manners is fast reflexes.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two people sitting at a dinner table. One person has just made a rude or awkward comment, and the other person is depicted with wide eyes and a quick motion blur on their hand as they rapidly move to catch a flying object (like a thrown napkin or a small food item) coming at them. The setting is a typical dining room with plates, utensils, and a centerpiece like a vase or candle. Include exaggerated facial expressions to show surprise and quick reaction, emphasizing the idea that fast reflexes are compensating for a lack of manners. The style should be lighthearted and colorful, with clear, clean lines and playful exaggeration, suitable for a family-friendly cartoon strip or comic.'),
 (889, 'Facts, Humor, Word Play', 'The only ten-letter word you can create using the top line of letters on a typewriter keyboard is ''typewriter''.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a classic vintage typewriter prominently in the center. Above the typewriter, the top row of keys is clearly visible and exaggeratedly highlighted or glowing to emphasize the letters on the top row. A piece of paper is loaded in the typewriter, and the typed word ''typewriter'' is clearly printed on it in large, playful letters. Around the typewriter, scattered loose letters or keys are flying or floating, adding to the playful vibe. The background should be simple, maybe a desk or a retro office space to keep focus on the typewriter. The style should be colorful, lighthearted, and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions on the typewriter itself (like eyes on the front frame, smiling) to personify the device humorously.'),
 (890, 'Facts, Relatable, Sports Humor', 'The only two days of the year in which there are no professional sports games (MLB, NBA, NHL, or NFL) are the day before and the day after the Major League All-Star Game.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene focused on a large calendar hanging on a wall. The calendar is open to the month showing the Major League All-Star Game day highlighted brightly in the center. Around this day, the previous day and the following day are shown with big red X marks. Each of these marked days has little icons representing the four major sports leagues: a baseball for MLB, a basketball for NBA, a hockey puck with a stick for NHL, and a football for NFL. The previous and next day clearly have no sports icons, showing an empty schedule. Include small caricatures of fans looking puzzled or bored, with one holding a remote control and scratching their head humorously. Maybe add a TV screen in the background showing a countdown or ''No Games Today!'' message to emphasize the sports break. Use bright colors and exaggerated expressions to keep it lighthearted and funny, emphasizing the rarity of these two "no game" days flanking the All-Star Game day.'),
 (891, 'Humor, Relatable', 'The only way to amuse some people is to slip and fall on an icy pavement.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set on a snowy, icy pavement outside a city park. In the foreground, a person is slipping dramatically on a thin patch of ice, arms flailing in the air and eyes wide with surprise, about to fall backward. Nearby, a group of people are watching and laughing heartily, showing clearly amused expressions. One person might be holding a hot coffee cup spilling a little due to laughter. The environment should be simple with some snow-covered trees or benches in the background, emphasizing a cold, wintry day. Use bright, lively colors and exaggerated facial expressions and body poses to emphasize the humor and lighthearted tone of the moment.'),
 (892, 'Humor, Relatable, Workplace', 'The ''Oops'' attitude - get it done quick and bring it back if you have to.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a person working hurriedly at a cluttered desk with papers flying everywhere and a big clock showing time ticking down. The person looks slightly frazzled but determined, holding a wrench or some work tool in one hand and a half-finished project on the desk. Nearby, a speech bubble from the person says, ''Oops attitude - get it done quick and bring it back if you have to.'' In the background, a confused coworker or friend watches with raised eyebrows, holding a checklist or a manual. The scene conveys a funny ''rush now, fix later'' vibe in a lighthearted office or workshop setting, emphasizing quick, imperfect work rather than perfection.'),
 (893, 'Humor, Relatable', 'The opposite of talking isn''t listening. It''s waiting.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters sitting side by side. One character is animatedly talking, smiling and gesturing with their hands, clearly enthusiastic. The second character appears visibly bored, with droopy eyes and a half-smile, staring blankly ahead, holding a clock or tapping their fingers impatiently, symbolizing ''waiting.'' Between them is a speech bubble coming from the talker filled with lots of words, while the listener''s speech bubble is empty with just a small hourglass or clock icon representing impatience. The setting is casual, like a simple living room or coffee shop, with a small table and chairs. The overall tone is lighthearted and relatable, emphasizing the idea that the listener is just waiting their turn rather than actively listening.'),
 (894, 'Food Humor, Humor, Philosophy Humor', 'The optimist sees the donut; the pessimist sees the hole.', NULL, 'A lighthearted cartoon featuring two characters standing side by side, both looking at the same large donut on a simple table in front of them. The optimistic character is smiling broadly, eyes wide with delight, pointing excitedly at the whole donut. The pessimistic character frowns and squints, focusing on the donut’s empty center hole, with a thought bubble showing just the hole. The donut is oversized, with colorful sprinkles to make it visually appealing. The background is minimalistic, maybe a café or kitchen setting, to keep the focus on the characters’ contrasting expressions and the donut. The style is bright and cheerful, with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the humor in perspective difference, rendered in a clean, simple cartoon style without any violence or complexity.'),
 (895, 'Humor, Relatable, Workplace', 'The part you least suspect to be the problem is, and is usually the most expensive, AND they''re out of stock.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a brightly lit auto repair shop. A frustrated customer stands beside a car with its hood open, looking bewildered and scratching their head. The mechanic, wearing a slightly stained uniform and a name tag, points dramatically to a tiny, obscure car part (like a small sensor or bolt) on a workbench labeled ''The Culprit.'' Nearby, a large sign on a shelf reads ''Out of Stock'' with empty hooks and dusty boxes. The customer holds a long receipt with a ridiculously high price highlighted. Around them, exaggerated details include a calendar with circled days waiting for the part, a thought bubble above the customer showing a big question mark, and scattered tools emphasizing the chaos and confusion. The overall style is colorful, with exaggerated facial expressions and comedic proportions to emphasize the frustration and irony of the situation without any negativity.'),
 (896, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy Humor', 'The past is just a memory and the future is a guess. The point where they meet is the present, and it is the only place you exist.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing at the intersection of two winding roads labeled ''Past'' and ''Future.'' The road labeled ''Past'' fades into a cloudy, misty memory bubble with faint images of clocks and old photographs. The road labeled ''Future'' disappears into a foggy question mark-shaped cloud filled with question marks and crystal balls. At the crossroads where these two roads meet, the person stands on a small brightly lit platform labeled ''Present,'' looking puzzled but content. Around the person, show floating icons representing time like hourglasses, calendars, and clocks, but all with a playful, exaggerated cartoon style. The whole scene should be lighthearted and whimsical, with soft colors and simple shapes emphasizing the abstract concept of time in a fun way.'),
 (897, 'Food Humor, Irony, Puns', 'The perversity of nature is nowhere better demonstrated than by the fact that, when exposed to the same atmosphere, bread becomes hard while crackers become soft.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters: a cartoon loaf of bread and a cracker, both with expressive faces. The bread is standing on the left side, looking tough and hard, with a strong, rough texture and a grumpy expression. On the right side, the cracker appears sad and soft, drooping slightly with a wilted, softened look. Between them is a transparent glass dome marked ''Same Atmosphere'' showing they are exposed to the same air. The background is a simple kitchen counter, with a small open window letting air in. Add subtle visual cues like a tiny clock to suggest time passing and some crumbs around the bread and cracker. The overall style is colorful and playful, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the irony that bread hardens while crackers soften in the same conditions.'),
 (898, 'History Humor, Lawyer Humor, Word Play', 'The phrase ''rule of thumb'' is derived from and old English law which stated that you couldn''t beat your wife with anything wider than your thumb.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a confused looking medieval English judge in traditional robes and a curly white wig sitting on a high wooden bench inside a courtroom. The judge is holding an oversized cartoonish thumb ruler (like a ruler shaped as a giant thumb) up to a small, worried-looking man standing in front of him. The man is holding a wooden stick, narrowly avoiding it being crushed or measured by the giant thumb ruler. In the background, a scroll labeled ''Old English Law'' hangs on the stone wall. The courtroom setting is exaggerated with exaggerated wooden beams, an old-fashioned balance scale, and a quill and inkpot on the judge''s bench. The overall tone is light and silly, emphasizing the absurdity of measuring with thumbs in a legal context. No violence depicted, just confused faces and comically oversized thumb measuring tool.'),
 (899, 'Humor, Motivational, Quotes', 'The price of greatness is responsibility.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, muscular trophy character standing tall on a pedestal labeled ''Greatness''. The trophy has arms and legs and is holding a huge, heavy-looking clipboard labeled ''Responsibility''. It looks both proud and slightly overwhelmed. Around the base of the pedestal, scattered papers marked with tasks and duties fly about chaotically, emphasizing the burden. The background is a simple stage with curtains to highlight the ''award'' moment. The style is lighthearted with exaggerated expressions and bright, cheerful colors to keep the tone funny and uplifting.'),
 (900, 'Humor, Lawyer Humor, Philosophy Humor', 'The problem with any unwritten law is that you don''t know where to go to erase it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a confused character standing in front of an enormous, old-fashioned stone tablet labeled ''Unwritten Law.'' The tablet is blank but glowing slightly to emphasize the irony that it''s an unwritten law. The character, looking puzzled, is holding a giant eraser comically oversized for the tablet and searching around nervously for an eraser board or any place to rub off the law. Around the scene, there are whimsical elements like question marks floating above the character''s head and a signpost with directions like ''To the Law Library,'' ''Erase Here,'' and ''Unwritten Law Department'' all with arrows pointing in different, conflicting directions. The overall tone is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the character''s frustration and confusion.'),
 (901, 'Humor, Puns, Science, Steven Wright', 'The problem with the gene pool is that there is no lifeguard.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a gene pool literally depicted as a swimming pool labeled ''Gene Pool.'' The pool is filled with various cartoonish double-helix DNA strands swimming or floating around like people relaxing in a pool. There is no lifeguard chair or lifeguard present anywhere around the pool, emphasizing the joke. Around the poolside, goofy characters representing different genetic traits (like a character with oversized glasses, another with wild hair, and one with a quirky hat) are casually lounging or splashing. The background shows playful poolside details, such as a beach ball, a sun umbrella, and pool floaties in shapes referencing biology or genetics (like a microscope-shaped floatie). The art style is bright, cheerful, and exaggerated for comedic effect, with smiling DNA strands and relaxed atmosphere. The whole setup visually plays on the pun of a ''gene pool'' and the absence of a lifeguard in a swimming pool setting to communicate the joke clearly and humorously, without any offensive or inappropriate elements.'),
 (902, 'Computers, Humor, Irony', 'The program is absolutely right; therefore, the computer must be wrong.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a frustrated person sitting at a desk in front of an old-fashioned desktop computer with a classic CRT monitor. The computer screen displays a message saying: ''The program is absolutely right.'' The person looks confused and is scratching their head while pointing a finger at the screen, as if arguing with the computer. Around the desk, scattered papers and a coffee mug add to the office environment. The room looks like a typical home office, with a small wall clock and a plant on the windowsill. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated, with bright colors and expressive faces to emphasize the irony and humor of the statement that the computer must be wrong even though the program is right. The background is simple to keep focus on the interaction between the person and the computer.'),
 (903, 'Humor, Language, Word Play', 'The quantity of consonants in the English language is constant.  If omitted in one place, they turn up in another. When a Bostonian ''pahks'' his ''cah,'' the lost r''s migrate southwest, causing a Texan to ''warsh'' his car and invest in ''erl wells.''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene split into two panels side by side. On the left, depict a stereotypical Boston man with a thick accent, wearing a casual jacket, standing proudly next to his vintage car, labeled ''cah.'' He''s saying ''pahks my cah,'' emphasizing the missing ''r'' sounds. Thought bubbles or wavy lines illustrate the letter ''r''s flying out of Boston and heading southwest as small red letter ''R''s with tiny wings. On the right side, a cheerful Texan wearing a cowboy hat and boots is washing his car, shown with large soap bubbles. He says, ''warsh my car,'' emphasizing his added ''r''s and Southern accent. Near him, an ''erl wells'' oil well cartoonishly pumps oil in the shape of the letter ''R.'' The background can include subtle region markers or small map-like icons showing Boston in the northeast and Texas in the southwest. The overall style is light-hearted, colorful, and exaggerated to highlight the accents and the migration of the letter ''R''s in a charming, educational way.'),
 (904, 'Money Humor, Puns', 'The quickest way to double your money is to fold it in half and put it back in your pocket.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a person standing happily with a big grin, holding a folded dollar bill in one hand. The person is folding a single dollar bill neatly in half, clearly amused by their ''money doubling'' method. Nearby, their empty wallet or pocket is visible, open or extended, as they are about to put the folded bill inside. The background is simple and colorful, emphasizing the character and the dollar bill. There can be some light motion lines around the folded money to suggest the action of folding, and a small sparkle or shine on the bill to highlight its ''doubling.'' The style should be lighthearted and playful, capturing the clever but silly literal interpretation of ''doubling money.'''),
 (905, 'Good Question!, Humor, Science', 'The reason lightning doesn''t strike twice in the same place is that the same place isn''t there the second time.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small patch of ground after a lightning strike; the first panel depicts a cartoon lightning bolt striking a particular spot on a grassy field with a surprised expression on a nearby animal, such as a squirrel. The second panel shows the same spot but comically shifted and transformed—a tree fallen, a crater formed, or ground visibly moved—indicating the original spot is no longer there. Above the panels, include a whimsical caption or thought bubble with the joke text. The style should be bright, colorful, and exaggerated, emphasizing the playful impossibility of the ''same place'' existing twice due to the effects of the strike itself.'),
 (906, 'Humor, Political Humor, Technology Humor', 'The reason the government thinks you''re a number is because it''s just a machine.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a large, old-fashioned, bulky government machine with various blinking lights, levers, and a classic typewriter-style printout coming out the front. The machine has a simplistic, slightly anthropomorphic face with tired eyes, emphasizing it as just a cold, unfeeling device. Next to the machine stands an ordinary person looking confused or frustrated while holding up a sign with their name and a big digit ''7'' printed on it. The background is an office setting with filing cabinets and paperwork piled high, with a subtle joke atmosphere. The style should be colorful, lighthearted, and exaggerated in a cartoon style, focusing on the idea that the government processes people impersonally, as if they are just numbers for a machine.'),
 (907, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'The right side of the street should be wider than the left, since that''s the side that we drive on.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon of a simple street scene viewed from above, split down the middle. The right side of the street is exaggeratedly wide, with broad lanes, while the left side is very narrow, barely enough for a car. On the right side, several cars drive happily and confidently, maybe one car with a smiling face or eyes on the windshield to add personality. On the left side, a tiny car comically squeezed into a narrow lane or even trying to navigate a space too small for it, looking confused or frustrated. The street signs indicate that driving is on the right side. The background is light and colorful with simple buildings and trees lining both sides of the street. The overall style is playful and cartoonish with clean lines and bright colors emphasizing the absurdity of making one side wider just because we drive on it. Include a sun in the sky with a friendly face to add to the cheerful mood.'),
 (908, 'Good Question!, Humor, Travel Humor', 'The San Francisco Cable cars are the only mobile National Monuments.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a classic San Francisco cable car climbing a steep hill in the city. The cable car is drawn with exaggerated features, such as a proud, smiling face on its front, and wearing a small, cartoonish statue-like pedestal underneath it as if it is a monument. Around the cable car, tourists are taking photos and looking amazed, some with cameras and phones. In the background, iconic San Francisco landmarks like the Golden Gate Bridge and downtown skyscrapers are visible. A signpost near the cable car reads ''National Monument'' with an arrow pointing to the cable car. The overall art style is lighthearted and colorful, with playful expressions on the characters and a bright, sunny day to emphasize the joke about the cable car being a ''mobile'' monument.'),
 (909, 'Humor, Physical Comedy, Relatable Humor', 'The severity of the itch is proportional to the reach.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a person trying desperately to scratch an itch on their back. The person should be exaggeratedly stretching their arm and body in an awkward, almost impossible pose to reach the itchy spot. Their face should show a mix of frustration and determination. Include subtle visual humor like sweat drops or little red scratch marks appearing where they are trying to reach. The background can be simple, such as a plain room or outdoor setting, emphasizing the person’s struggle. Optionally, add a measuring tape or a graph next to the person showing a comical ''proportional relationship'' between the length of the reach and the intensity of the itch as a funny visual metaphor.'),
 (910, 'Animals, Dark Humor, Historical Humor', 'The sinking of the Titanic must have seemed like a miracle to the lobsters in the kitchen.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside the Titanic ship’s kitchen. In the foreground, a group of lively lobsters are inside a large kitchen pot, looking wide-eyed and surprised. Some lobsters wear little chef hats or have expressive faces showing relief and astonishment. Around them are typical kitchen items like pots, pans, and utensils scattered about. In the background, through a window, waves and the dark ocean are visible, with the Titanic tipping slightly to show it is sinking. The kitchen has a slightly chaotic atmosphere but in a lighthearted, funny way. The overall style is colorful and cartoonish, emphasizing the lobsters’ expressions as the focal point to highlight the joke’s punchline about their unlikely ''miracle'' escape from boiling in a sinking ship’s kitchen.'),
 (911, 'Food Humor, Puns, Science', 'The softness of the butter is inversely proportional to the softness of the bread.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon kitchen scene with a loaf of bread and a stick of butter on a counter. The bread looks very soft and fluffy, almost puffed up with a relaxed, sleepy expression on its face. The butter, by contrast, is rigid and firm, with a slightly annoyed or grumpy face, maybe even with a little sweat drop to emphasize it’s hard. Above the scene, a simple science chart or graph labeled "Softness Inverse Proportionality" shows a downward-sloping line connecting "Butter softness" on one axis and "Bread softness" on the other. The background is a bright kitchen with a table, some utensils, and a butter knife nearby. The overall style is light-hearted and cartoonish, using exaggerated facial expressions on the bread and butter to convey the joke visually without any violence, politics, or inappropriate content.'),
 (912, 'Irony, Motivational, Philosophy Humor, Steven Wright', 'The sooner you fall behind, the more time you''ll have to catch up.', NULL, 'Create a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person running on a winding race track. The runner looks both worried and slightly hopeful, glancing back over their shoulder with exaggerated wide eyes. Behind them, a humorous finish line is visible far in the distance. Several clocks and timers float in the air above the track, each showing different times, symbolizing the passing time. Nearby, a quirky, smiling tortoise wearing running shoes is casually strolling the path, representing the idea of slow progress. The track is lined with funny motivational signs saying things like ''Keep Up!'' and ''Catch Up Zone Ahead!'' The background is bright and lively with simple trees, a clear blue sky, and a few cartoon-style clouds. Ensure the expression and body language of the runner capture the irony with a mix of anxiety and optimism. The overall style is lighthearted and exaggerated, suitable for a clean and funny comic panel without any harsh or negative elements.'),
 (913, 'Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'The soul would have no rainbow had the eyes no tears.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a large pair of cartoonish eyes with exaggerated tear drops streaming down. From the tears, a colorful, vibrant rainbow arches upward and outward, filling the space above with bright, cheerful colors. The eyes look slightly sad but there is a subtle smile to add a lighthearted feel. The background is simple and light, perhaps with a few fluffy clouds around the rainbow to enhance the contrast. The overall tone is uplifting and whimsical, capturing the idea that tears (sadness) produce something beautiful (a rainbow) from within the soul, but presented in a playful and exaggerated style.'),
 (914, 'Humor, Political Humor, Relatable', 'The state of the world can be accurately gauged by the numbers of cars in the Pentagon parking lot on any given midnight.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set at midnight outside the Pentagon building, which is clearly labeled with a large sign reading ''PENTAGON'' on its facade. The background is dark with a moon and stars visible in the sky. The foreground shows a large, well-lit parking lot filled with cars, highlighting an excessive number of vehicles parked there at such an unusual hour. A couple of characters (maybe two friends or coworkers) stand at the edge of the parking lot looking surprised or puzzled while pointing at the sheer volume of parked cars. To add humor, one character could be holding a giant, exaggerated stopwatch or a world globe to symbolize ''gauging the state of the world.'' The overall style is light-hearted, colorful, and cartoonish with simple, exaggerated expressions to emphasize the witty commentary on world affairs and government activity at odd hours. No violence, political bias, or complex elements—just a funny, clear visual metaphor for the joke''s message about secretive or intense government involvement.'),
 (3222, 'Random', 'I''d be unstoppable if I could only get started.', NULL, NULL),
 (915, 'Anatomy Humor, Humor, Word Play', 'The strongest muscle in the body is the tongue.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring a human figure standing with an exaggeratedly oversized tongue stretching out from their mouth. The tongue should look muscular, with bold defined biceps-style muscles drawn on it, as if it’s a strong arm. The character should have a confident or proud expression, pointing at the tongue to emphasize its strength. Surround the figure with a few floating, simplified anatomical illustrations of other muscles (like an arm or leg muscle) looking smaller and less impressive in comparison to the tongue. Use bright, cheerful colors and keep the style playful and light-hearted without any aggressive or violent elements.'),
 (916, 'Christmas, Holiday Humor, Word Play', 'The sweater I got for Christmas was picking up lots of static electricity. I took it back and exchanged it and they gave me a different one free of charge.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy clothing store during Christmas time. In the center, a smiling customer holds up a brightly colored Christmas sweater with visible blue static sparks crackling around it. The sweater should look festive with holiday patterns like snowflakes or reindeer. The customer looks a bit surprised but amused. Next to them, a friendly store clerk is handing over another new sweater, identical but with no static electricity visible, looking cheerful and helpful. A small sign on the counter reads ''Holiday Sweater Exchange''. In the background, shelves display more sweaters and Christmas decorations like a small Christmas tree with twinkling lights. The overall tone is lighthearted and festive, with exaggerated, cartoon-style expressions to emphasize the joke about static electricity and the pun on ''free of charge''.'),
 (917, 'Humor, Motivational', 'The task ahead of us is never as great as the power behind us.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small group of people standing before a huge mountain labeled ''The Task'' which looks very tall and intimidating. Behind them is a giant, exaggeratedly large muscle arm symbolizing ''The Power'' supporting and lifting them up. The people look determined and hopeful, some with sweat on their brows, others flexing their arms confidently. The background is simple with a clear sky and some light clouds to keep focus on the metaphorical mountain and the powerful arm. Text above or below the image reads the joke: ''The task ahead of us is never as great as the power behind us.'' The overall tone is lighthearted and motivational, drawn in vibrant, colorful cartoon style with smiling faces and exaggerated expressions.'),
 (918, 'Humor, Life, Motivational', 'The time is right to make new friends.', NULL, 'A cheerful, colorful cartoon scene showing a friendly clock character with a big smiling face and arms, pointing at its watch face which displays the time as exactly 12:00. Surrounding the clock are diverse, happy cartoon characters representing different people—some waving, some shaking hands. The background is bright and welcoming, perhaps with a park setting including benches, trees, and flowers to suggest a social, pleasant atmosphere. The overall mood is upbeat and inviting, emphasizing the idea that now is a perfect moment to start new friendships. The style is simple, rounded, and playful, suitable for a lighthearted, humorous cartoon.'),
 (919, 'Irony, Relatable, Workplace', 'The trouble with being punctual is that nobody''s there to appreciate it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing alone in front of a closed door labeled ''Meeting Room'' with a clock on the wall clearly showing an early time (e.g., 8:00 am). The person looks confused and a bit disappointed, glancing around to see that the hallway and doorway are completely empty. Include small details like a watch on the person''s wrist and a calendar or notice board nearby indicating the meeting time is later. The setting is an office hallway with bright, simple colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the loneliness and irony of being the first and only one present.'),
 (920, 'Humor, Relatable', 'The trouble with doing something right the first time is that nobody appreciates how difficult it was.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a frustrated, tired person standing next to a perfectly completed project—a neatly assembled, complicated-looking puzzle or machine. The character has sweat drops on their forehead and is holding their hands up in an ''I did it!'' gesture, looking both proud and exhausted. Nearby, three other people are standing nonchalantly with blank or mildly indifferent expressions, completely ignoring the hard work that was just done. The background can be a simple room with a table where the project rests. Include small visual cues like a clock showing a long time passed, scattered tools or puzzle pieces around, and exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the contrast between the effort and the lack of appreciation. The overall color scheme should be light and playful, fitting a cartoon style with clear, bold outlines and simple shading.'),
 (921, 'Humor, Life, Philosophy Humor', 'The trouble with life is, you''re half way through it before you realize it''s a ''do it yourself'' thing.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a middle-aged person standing at a literal half-way point on a long, winding path labeled ''Life Journey.'' The character looks puzzled, holding an oversized instruction manual titled ''How to Live Your Life'' with a big question mark on the cover. Around the character, various life-related objects can be seen scattered: a toolbox with tools labeled ''choices,'' ''decisions,'' and ''effort,'' a calendar half-filled, a clock showing mid-day, and DIY project signs such as ''Build Your Dreams'' and ''Fix Your Future.'' The background should be bright and friendly, with whimsical elements like clouds shaped like light bulbs and thought bubbles. Everything should be drawn in a playful cartoon style with exaggerated expressions conveying surprise and realization. No violence or sensitive content, just a lighthearted and motivational tone emphasizing the idea of life being a self-driven project half-discovered too late.'),
 (922, 'Food Humor, Puns, Science', 'The Universe is made up mainly of interesting things. (More beer please!)', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person sitting at a bar counter, holding up a frothy beer mug. The bar background is filled with celestial-themed decorations such as stars, planets, and swirling galaxies, blending into the bar''s ambiance. Behind the bar, a bartender in a friendly pose is pouring another beer from a tap. Above the bar, a whimsical sign reads ''The Universe is made up mainly of interesting things.'' The person looks excited and slightly amused, as if making a lighthearted toast. The setting should feel lively and fun, with a mix of cosmic elements and a casual pub atmosphere, emphasizing the playful link between the universe and beer without any violent or inappropriate content.'),
 (923, 'Irony, Relatable, Workplace', 'The unwilling, led by the unqualified, doing the impossible for the ungrateful.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a small group of office workers struggling to carry a giant, oddly shaped, heavy object labeled ''Impossible Task.'' The workers look reluctant, with exaggerated expressions of exhaustion and frustration. Leading them is a boss figure confidently pointing forward but with a clueless, confused expression, wearing a suit slightly too big or crooked. Around them, other people (the ''ungrateful'') stand casually with crossed arms or indifferent faces, some taking selfies or checking phones, ignoring the effort happening. The setting is a typical bland office hallway with cubicles and motivational posters ironically saying ''Teamwork!'' and ''You Can Do It!''. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated emotions, bright colors, and simple line work to emphasize the humor of unwilling people being led by an unqualified leader to do impossible work for unappreciative onlookers.'),
 (924, 'Humor, Programming, Puns', 'The value of a program is proportional to the weight of its output.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a programmer sitting at a cluttered desk with a computer. The programmer looks puzzled and is staring at the printer next to the desk. The printer is comically overloaded and struggling to spit out a huge stack of printed paper that is so tall it almost reaches the ceiling. The papers are plain sheets with random code snippets and lines of text. Nearby, a scale is placed underneath the paper stack, clearly showing a large weight number on its display. In the background, a whiteboard with some programming sketches and lines of code hangs on the wall. The overall style should be lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions and an emphasis on the heavy output paper stack as the ''weight'' representing program value. No violence or offensive content.'),
 (925, 'Family, Humor, Relatable', 'The Wi-fi went down for five minutes, so I had to talk to my family. They seem like nice people.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a modern living room where a family of four is sitting awkwardly on a couch and chairs, looking at each other with shy or surprised expressions. In the background, a small Wi-Fi router is shown with a big red ''X'' or a disconnected symbol hovering over it to indicate the Wi-Fi is down. One family member (perhaps a parent) is nervously breaking the silence by saying something, while others glance at each other with hesitant smiles or raised eyebrows, as if rediscovering each other. Include a smartphone or tablet resting unused on the table to emphasize the lack of internet. The style is light-hearted and exaggerated, with clear facial expressions reflecting mild discomfort turning into amusement. The setting should feel cozy and familiar, like a typical contemporary family home, with humorous emphasis on the awkwardness of real-life conversation suddenly replacing screen time.'),
 (926, 'Humor, Language, Word Play', 'The word racecar and kayak are the same whether they are read left to right or right to left.', NULL, 'Draw a colorful cartoon scene showing two objects side by side on a simple white background. On the left, depict a shiny red racecar with cartoonish eyes on its windshield, smiling. On the right, show a bright blue kayak floating on a small pond with a friendly, slightly exaggerated face on its front tip. Above both, in large bold letters, write the words ''racecar'' and ''kayak'' respectively, each styled so they look symmetrical or mirrored from left to right. Include subtle arrows on each word pointing from left to right and right to left, emphasizing the palindrome nature. The overall style should be cheerful and simple, with thick outlines and bright colors to highlight the humorous idea that these words read the same forwards and backwards. No background details besides the pond under the kayak, and no people should be included.'),
 (927, 'Good Question!, Word Play', 'The word swims upside-down is still swims.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing the word "swims" written on a bright white pool float drifting in a clear blue swimming pool. The pool float is flipped upside-down in the water, with the letters still legible and spelled correctly as "swims" despite being inverted. Around the pool, a smiling cartoon character in sunglasses and a sunhat points at the float in surprise, admiring the quirky fact. Nearby, a small rubber duck floats, also upside-down but obviously a duck. The scene conveys lighthearted fun under a sunny sky with cartoon-style water ripples and sparkles to emphasize the pool setting.'),
 (928, 'Humor, Social Commentary, Word Play', 'The worst thing about censorship is XXXXXXXXXXXXXX.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a desk or computer, trying to write or speak the sentence: ''The worst thing about censorship is XXXXXXXXXXXXXX.'' The person looks frustrated and confused, scratching their head or shrugging, with a speech bubble or text box containing the line with the Xs clearly blocking out the rest of the sentence. Around the person, include visual symbols representing censorship, such as big red ''censored'' stamps, black bars covering words on papers, or a giant pair of scissors floating above ready to cut words. The background should be simple and lighthearted, emphasizing the absurdity and irony of being unable to express themselves fully due to censorship. Make the art style bright, colorful, and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions for humor but non-threatening and family-friendly overall.'),
 (929, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor, Relatable', 'The worst thing about the worst thing that could happen is that we know that the worst thing could happen.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting at a small table with a cup of coffee, looking puzzled and stressed. Their thought bubble should contain a dramatic swirling dark cloud labeled ''The Worst Thing'' with exaggerated lightning bolts and cartoonish eyes to personify the ''worst thing.'' Around the person, subtle smaller thought bubbles show different possible disasters, each increasingly absurd but all labeled ''worst thing.'' The background is a simple room with a calendar on the wall showing a marked day, emphasizing anticipation. The person''s expression is a mix of worry and irony, capturing the endless loop of worrying about the worst possible outcome. The art style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, with bright colors to keep the mood funny rather than gloomy.'),
 (930, 'Humor, Relatable', 'There are times my greatest achievement is keeping my mouth shut.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting in a cozy living room, looking proud and triumphant. The person is smiling with exaggerated satisfaction, maybe a little chest puffed out, and has their finger pressed gently against their lips in a ''shushing'' gesture. Around them are thought bubbles or floating icons like a trophy or medal that say ''Greatest Achievement.'' The setting should be light-hearted, with bright colors and simple, rounded shapes. Include a small clock on the wall to imply everyday life, and perhaps a couch with a pet (like a cat or dog) looking up curiously. The overall mood is playful and self-congratulatory without being boastful.'),
 (931, 'Puns, Science, Technology Humor', 'There are two major products to come out of Berkeley: LSD and UNIX. We don''t believe this to be a coincidence.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene set on a college campus labeled ''Berkeley.'' On one side, a whimsical scientist wearing round glasses and a lab coat is holding a large, swirling, psychedelic-looking molecule labeled ''LSD'' with a playful smile. On the other side, a quirky programmer with messy hair and thick glasses sits at an old-school computer terminal showing a UNIX command prompt on the screen. Between them, a large signpost points in two directions: one arrow toward a trippy, colorful, swirling background representing the psychedelic LSD culture, and the other toward a neatly organized server rack or computer stack symbolizing UNIX technology. In the background, iconic campus buildings with Berkeley banners should be visible. The style is bright and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions and funny details like floating binary numbers and colorful blobs around the scientist, and green command-line prompts glowing near the programmer. No violence or inappropriate content.'),
 (932, 'Gender Humor, Humor, Relatable', 'There are two theories to arguing with women. Neither one works.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a man and a woman sitting at a small round table, both with exaggerated puzzled expressions. The man is holding a tiny book titled ''How to Argue with Women'' with question marks floating above his head. The woman sits calmly across from him with a slight amused smirk, arms crossed. Between them on the table are two visibly torn or crumpled papers labeled ''Theory 1'' and ''Theory 2'' to symbolize failed strategies. The background is simple, with soft pastel colors, and a clock on the wall showing time passing to imply long, unproductive debates. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing confusion and humorous futility without disrespect.'),
 (933, 'Bathroom Humor, Word Play', 'There are two things you need to know about constipation: 1. There is no #2.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting awkwardly on a simple toilet seat in a bathroom. The person looks frustrated and slightly distressed, holding their stomach with one hand and looking at an empty toilet paper roll holder next to them. Above the toilet, a small sign humorously states: ''Things to Know About Constipation: 1. There is no #2.'' The bathroom should be simple and brightly colored to enhance the lighthearted mood, with a small plunger leaning against the wall and a small window showing a sunny day outside. The overall style should be exaggerated and cartoonish, capturing the awkwardness and humor of the situation without being crude or graphic.'),
 (934, 'Humor, Programming, Word Play', 'There are two ways to write error-free programs; only the third one works.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a programmer sitting at a cluttered desk with multiple computer screens. On one screen, a document titled ''Error-Free Programs'' is open, displaying two crossed-out methods labeled ''Method 1'' and ''Method 2'' with big red X marks. The programmer looks puzzled but amused, scratching their head. Above the desk, a thought bubble reads, ''There are two ways to write error-free programs; only the third one works.'' Nearby, an open notebook or whiteboard humorously shows a blank space or question marks where the ''third method'' should be, suggesting it’s unknown or mysterious. The environment includes typical programmer items like coffee mugs, code snippets on paper, and a small plant to add charm. The overall style is light and comical, emphasizing the irony and frustration programmers face with bugs and errors, in a non-threatening, funny way.'),
 (935, 'Humor, Life, Relatable', 'There comes a time when you should stop expecting other people to make a big deal about your birthday... around age 11.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene of a slightly awkward 11-year-old birthday kid standing in a modestly decorated living room. The kid looks mildly disappointed and holds a small, half-inflated balloon and a tiny cupcake with a single candle. Around the child, a few family members or friends stand casually, showing little excitement or attention toward the birthday. The decorations are simple: a small ''Happy Birthday'' banner that looks plain and a couple of sad-looking balloons floating at ceiling height. The background should suggest a normal home setting with a sofa, a table with minimal snacks, and a birthday card on the table. The overall mood is light and funny, capturing the moment where birthday expectations start to fizzle out at around age 11, making it a relatable and amusing scene without sadness or negativity.'),
 (936, 'Irony, Music Humor, Puns', 'There is a CD out entitled ''The Worst of Jefferson Airplane''. If you buy this, take it home, play it, and enjoy it, should you take it back and demand a refund?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy living room. In the center, a person stands holding a CD case titled ''The Worst of Jefferson Airplane'' with a puzzled but amused expression. The CD cover should have a playful, retro design featuring a cartoon airplane looking a bit distressed or crooked, hinting at the band''s name. Nearby, a stereo or record player is prominently displayed, playing music notes that visually look odd or twisted, to represent ''worst'' music. Include subtle visual cues like a thought bubble above the person''s head with a question mark and an ironic shrugging emoji or tiny refund receipt to show their dilemma. The room should feel lighthearted and colorful, with minimal background detail such as a comfy armchair, a small plant, and a poster of a classic rock band on the wall to set the tone. The style should be lively and exaggerated, emphasizing the joke’s irony about enjoying bad music and questioning a refund, without any harmful or negative imagery.'),
 (937, 'Humor, Life, Mental Health Humor', 'There is a fine line between ''hobby'' and ''mental illness.''', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person enthusiastically engaging in an unusual hobby that looks a bit eccentric. The person could be surrounded by an exaggeratedly cluttered workspace filled with quirky and odd items—like stacks of colorful, oddly shaped crafts, strange gadgets, wild plants, or piles of notes. The person wears a big, enthusiastic smile and holds a magnifying glass or a whimsical tool, clearly obsessed with their hobby. Nearby, a friend or family member looks on with a mix of amusement and bewilderment, maybe scratching their head or giving a hesitant thumbs-up. The background should be a cozy room or garage filled with creative chaos, highlighting the fine line between passion and eccentricity in a light-hearted, non-offensive way. Use bright, cheerful colors and expressive, cartoon-style characters to enhance the humor without suggesting anything negative or harmful.'),
 (938, 'Humor, Relatable, Workplace', 'There is absolutely no substitute for a genuine lack of preparation.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in an office or classroom environment. In the foreground, a person is sitting at a desk looking utterly frazzled and disorganized—papers scattered everywhere, a coffee cup tipped over, and a messy pile of books and notes around them. Their hair is wild and their expression shows panic and exhaustion. Behind them, a clock on the wall shows it''s late or just before a deadline. On the side, another character stands calmly, smiling knowingly with arms crossed, as if delivering the punchline. A speech bubble above this calm character contains the joke text: ''There is absolutely no substitute for a genuine lack of preparation.'' The overall tone is light-hearted and funny, with exaggerated facial expressions and clutter to highlight the chaos of being unprepared. The style is simple, bright, and cartoonish, emphasizing the contrast between calm acceptance and chaotic stress without any negativity or aggression.'),
 (939, 'Humor, Relatable, Workplace', 'There is always one more imbecile than you counted on.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a busy, chaotic office. At the center is a frustrated character (wearing casual office attire) looking surprised and slightly exasperated while counting on their fingers. Around them, several quirky, silly-looking coworkers act in absurd or goofy ways—one accidentally spills coffee, another typewrites nonsense, and a third is tangled in wires. In the background, a whiteboard or flip chart shows a neat list with a number, but an extra coworker stands behind it grinning mischievously, representing "one more imbecile" than expected. The office has simple desks, computers, coffee mugs, and scattered papers to emphasize the setting. The overall style is colorful and playful with exaggerated facial expressions and comically silly poses to highlight the joke''s meaning without any negativity.'),
 (940, 'Life, Motivational, Thanksgiving', 'There is always something for which to be thankful.', NULL, 'A cheerful cartoon scene set around a Thanksgiving dinner table. In the center, a large roasted turkey with steam rising, surrounded by classic side dishes like mashed potatoes, corn, and cranberry sauce. Around the table, a diverse group of smiling family members of varying ages, all holding hands or raising glasses in a toast. Above them, a warm glowing banner or speech bubble that reads, ''There is always something for which to be thankful.'' The background shows cozy home decorations like autumn leaves, pumpkins, and soft lighting to emphasize warmth and gratitude. The overall style is bright, colorful, and lighthearted, with exaggerated happy expressions to convey a joyful, grateful mood in cartoon form.'),
 (941, 'Life, Philosophy Humor, Relatable', 'There is much more to life than having everything.', NULL, 'Draw a simple, lighthearted cartoon scene featuring two characters sitting on a park bench under a tree. One character looks content and peaceful, admiring a small flower growing nearby, while the other character is surrounded by oversized bags and boxes labeled ''Everything.'' The character with the bags looks tired and overwhelmed, while the peaceful character smiles gently, enjoying the simplicity of life around them, such as birds, sunshine, and a butterfly. The backdrop is a sunny day in the park, with a few clouds and a sign that reads ''Life’s More Than Stuff.'' The style should be colorful, friendly, and whimsical, emphasizing the contrast between material abundance and simple joy in a non-judgmental, humorous way.'),
 (942, 'Humor, Star Wars', 'There is much Obi-Wan did not tell you.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a Star Wars-like desert landscape reminiscent of Tatooine. In the foreground, a confused-looking young Jedi, dressed in simple robes with a lightsaber hanging from his belt, scratches his head. Facing him is an older, mysterious Jedi master with a wise, knowing expression who is deliberately holding his finger over his lips as if keeping a secret. Around them, iconic Star Wars elements like twin suns in the sky and a small moisture farm in the background subtly enhance the scene. Above the characters, a speech bubble from the older Jedi reads, "There is much Obi-Wan did not tell you." The overall art style is colorful and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humor and mystique of hidden information, all drawn in a lighthearted cartoon format.'),
 (943, 'Mental Health Humor, Philosophy Humor, Relatable', 'There is no such thing as pure pleasure; some anxiety always goes with it.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person reclining on a comfy armchair with a content smile, holding a tray with a slice of cake and a steaming cup of tea. Around the person, subtle visual cues of anxiety are present: small cartoonish sweat drops, a tiny worried face hovering like a thought bubble above their head, or a small clock showing time ticking. The background should be cozy, like a living room with a bookshelf and a window showing a peaceful day outside. The overall vibe mixes comfort and slight tension to visually represent the idea that even in moments of pleasure, a bit of anxiety lingers. Use bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humorous contrast.'),
 (944, 'Life, Motivational, Workplace', 'There is nothing greater than the moment you realize that you''re free and the whole world is waiting to be explored. Quit your job and go!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a joyful person standing at the open door of an office cubicle. The person is mid-step, with one foot already outside, carrying a small suitcase or backpack, symbolizing readiness for adventure. The office is drab and gray, with a computer, stacks of paperwork, and a coffee mug on the desk. Outside the cubicle, a bright, vibrant outdoors scene bursts in through the doorway: green rolling hills, a clear blue sky with a shining sun, birds flying, and a winding path leading off into the distance. The person’s face expresses a mix of excitement and relief. Include a subtle calendar on the cubicle wall with crossed-out workdays, emphasizing the end of work, and tiny details like a clock showing quitting time. The overall style is colorful, light-hearted, and uplifting, capturing the freedom and thrill of leaving work to explore the world.'),
 (945, 'Food Humor, Irony, Relatable', 'There is something dishonest about putting bacon in a salad. You know? It''s kinda like smoking while you jog', 'Jim Gaffigan', 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person jogging in a park while holding a cigarette awkwardly in one hand, looking slightly guilty or confused. Nearby, there is a picnic table with a large, fresh green salad bowl. Inside the salad bowl are vibrant leafy greens along with strips of crispy bacon visibly mixed in. The jogger is glancing over at the salad, mirroring their conflicted expression. The background includes a clear, sunny day with trees and a few other park-goers who look pleasantly surprised or amused. The art style is light, colorful, and exaggerated to emphasize the absurdity of the juxtapositions—bacon in salad and smoking while jogging—without implying anything negative. The overall feel is playful and ironic, making the viewer smile at the ironic comparison between healthy and unhealthy choices combined in unexpected ways.'),
 (3214, 'Random', 'I wish I was deep instead of just macho.', NULL, NULL),
 (946, 'Exaggeration, Relatable', 'There must be hundreds of them.', 'Carl Sagan, age 8', 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing in front of a huge wall completely covered with dozens of identical small sticky notes or paper scraps. The person, with a confused or overwhelmed expression, is scratching their head or shrugging as they look at the wall. The sticky notes are arranged haphazardly but packed densely, emphasizing the idea of ''hundreds of them.'' The setting should be lighthearted and simple, possibly an office or a study room. Include a small desk with a lamp and a computer to hint at a workspace without overcrowding the image. The style should be exaggerated and playful, with big eyes and expressive body language to highlight the amusement and slight bewilderment of the character. Avoid any detailed background or anything violent, sexual, or political.'),
 (947, 'Humor, Irony, Philosophy Humor', 'There never was a good war or a bad peace.', NULL, 'A simple, humorous cartoon featuring two contrasting panels side by side. On the left panel, depict a chaotic, exaggerated battlefield scene showing confused soldiers scrambling around with silly expressions rather than intense fighting—no realistic violence. There are cartoon explosions made of colorful puffs of smoke and flying hats. On the right panel, show an overly peaceful, yet comically boring scene: a sleepy village with people napping in hammocks, reading newspapers, and having a dull conversation on a park bench, looking bored but content. Include a big, friendly dove with an olive branch flying above the peaceful scene. Above or between the two panels, have a speech bubble or banner with the text: ''There never was a good war or a bad peace.'' The overall style should be lighthearted, simple line art with bright colors and smiling or humorous facial expressions to reflect the irony in the statement without any negativity.'),
 (948, 'Math Humor, Puns', 'There''s a fine line between a numerator and a denominator. (and only a fraction of you will get this..)', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, hand-drawn blackboard filled with a simple fraction like 1/2 written in big chalk writing. On the top half of the fraction, a cheerful cartoon character labeled ''Numerator'' with a smiling face stands on the top line of the fraction bar, and on the bottom half, another cartoon character labeled ''Denominator'' looks similar but stands below the fraction line. Between them, a thin, clearly visible line acts as the fraction bar or ''fine line.'' The two characters look playful and friendly, maybe with tiny arms and legs. To the side, a cartoon audience (various diverse characters) reacting with puzzled or amused expressions. In the corner of the board, a small caption reads, ''Only a fraction of you will get this...'' The style should be bright, colorful, and light-hearted, clearly emphasizing the pun on ''a fine line'' and the math fraction theme without any complex background elements—just a classroom or simple setting to keep the focus on the fraction and characters.'),
 (949, 'Humor, Science, Word Play', 'There''s no future in time travel.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a slightly confused scientist standing next to a classic, comical time machine (think a quirky contraption with flashing lights, dials, and a big clock face). The scientist is scratching their head while holding a calendar showing the current date. A speech bubble above reads, "There''s no future in time travel." In the background, there is a long timeline displayed as a wavy line with past dates fading on the left and the present date marked clearly where the scientist stands. The timeline ends abruptly before reaching any ''future'' dates. The overall tone is lighthearted and silly, with exaggerated facial expression on the scientist emphasizing the ironic punchline.'),
 (950, 'Humor, Love Humor, Word Play', 'There''s so much to say but your eyes keep interrupting me.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters sitting across from each other at a small table. One character is trying to speak, with a speech bubble filled with many words trying to come out, but in front of their mouth, large, exaggerated cartoon eyes hover and cover the words, blocking the speech. The eyes should be big, bright, and animated with playful expressions, as if ''interrupting'' or ''talking over'' the person. The setting can be casual—a coffee shop or park bench—with a few simple background details like a coffee cup or tree. The overall tone is light and funny, emphasizing the playful interruption of the eyes to the speaker’s attempt to talk, visualizing the metaphor in the joke.'),
 (951, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'There''s too much blood in my caffeine system.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon of a person sitting wide-eyed and jittery at a kitchen table cluttered with multiple coffee cups and a big empty coffee pot. The character looks frazzled and wired, with sweat drops and shaky hands holding a coffee cup. Around them, little red droplets shaped like tiny blood cells bounce comically away from the coffee cups as if they''re being overwhelmed or pushed out. A thought bubble above the person reads, ''There''s too much blood in my caffeine system.'' The kitchen is bright and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions and vibrant colors to amplify the humor of someone who has had way too much caffeine and is confusing the body’s systems. Include humorous details like a ticking clock showing early morning and an overfilled coffee mug about to spill.'),
 (952, 'Humor, Word Play', 'They also surf who only stand on waves.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters at the beach. One character is energetically surfing on a big, dynamic ocean wave, confidently standing on a surfboard. The other character is casually standing upright on a smaller, tiny wave near the shore, holding the surfboard loosely or just standing on the water as if surfing, but with a relaxed, almost lazy expression. The waves are exaggerated and playful, with smiling faces on the water for added whimsy. The beach is sunny with a few palm trees in the background and some seagulls flying above. The style is colorful and lighthearted, emphasizing the contrast between the serious surfer and the laid-back ''stand-only'' surfer, highlighting the twist in the joke.'),
 (953, 'Humor, Nostalgia, Word Play', 'They don''t make nostalgia like they used to.', NULL, 'A colorful cartoon scene depicting an elderly person sitting on a cozy old-fashioned armchair, holding a dusty photo album with a smile. Surrounding them are nostalgic items: an old rotary phone, a vintage radio, a classic TV set showing a black-and-white show, and faded posters on the wall featuring retro styles. The character looks fondly at the album, with a thought bubble showing a faded scene from the past, like children playing outside with classic toys. The overall mood is warm and humorous, emphasizing fond memories. The scene is drawn in a lighthearted, cartoon style with exaggerated, friendly features on the character and slightly exaggerated proportions of the vintage items to enhance the nostalgic feel.'),
 (954, 'Humor, Physical Comedy, Relatable', 'They say dance like nobody is watching so I did, but someone was watching - they thought I was having a seizure and called an ambulance!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a living room. In the center, a person is enthusiastically dancing wildly with exaggerated, awkward movements, arms flailing and legs bent in odd angles. Their eyes are closed, completely absorbed in the dance, unaware of anything around them. Nearby, through a large window or an open door, a neighbor or passerby looks on with wide, concerned eyes, holding a phone to their ear as if calling an ambulance. The neighbor’s facial expression shows worry and confusion. The room is cozy and well-lit, with simple furniture like a couch, a coffee table with a small plant, and a framed picture on the wall. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with playful exaggeration to emphasize the awkward dancing and the misunderstanding. Speech or thought bubbles can be included if desired: the dancer thinking “Dance like nobody’s watching!” and the neighbor thinking “Is that a seizure?”'),
 (955, 'Humor, Music Humor, Word Play', 'They say if you play rap music backwards, you hear Satanic messages. And even worse - if you play it forwards, you hear rap music!', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene in a living room. A curious character with exaggerated surprised eyes is sitting on a cozy armchair wearing oversized headphones connected to a vintage-looking turntable playing a vinyl record labeled ''Rap Music.'' The character holds the record, which has a visible arrow indicating ''Play Backwards.'' Around their head are quirky musical notes and tiny flames shaped like tiny devils floating, suggesting ''Satanic messages.'' On the coffee table, there''s a speech bubble from another character, looking horrified and pointing at a large poster on the wall that says ''Rap Music'' with crazy, chaotic scribbles symbolizing unpleasant noise. The other character looks dismayed, covering their ears because the music is playing forward. The overall art style is bright and exaggerated, with cartoonish expressions and clear visual cues highlighting the joke''s punchline that playing rap forwards is worse than backwards. No violent or offensive elements present.'),
 (956, 'Irony, Life, Relatable', 'Things that come to those who wait are what''s left behind by those who got their first.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene with two characters standing side by side in a setting that looks like a group waiting in a line for something desirable, such as a food truck or amusement ride. The first character is happily walking away with a big plate of delicious food or a fun prize, smiling confidently and ignoring the second character. The second character is left behind looking disappointed and holding only a few scraps or an empty plate, symbolizing "what’s left behind." Include clear visual contrast: the first character is bright and fulfilled, while the second character appears duller and frustrated. Add a queue sign or a clock showing elapsed time to emphasize waiting. The overall tone is lighthearted and exaggerated to capture the irony of the phrase, without any violence or negativity. Make the style colorful and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions to enhance the humor of missing out because of waiting.'),
 (957, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'Things to do today: 1) Stop the arms race. 2) Floss.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a person standing in front of a large chalkboard or list board titled ''Things to do today.'' The board has two items: ''1) Stop the arms race'' and ''2) Floss.'' The person is scratching their head, looking both puzzled and amused, holding a large, comically oversized dental floss container in one hand. Behind them, faintly illustrated or as a background element, are two large muscular robot arms facing each other, as a silly representation of an ''arms race.'' The setting is a simple, bright room with a casual vibe, emphasizing the absurd contrast between the serious global issue and the mundane personal task. The style should be colorful and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions to highlight the humor in the juxtaposition of epic and trivial tasks.'),
 (958, 'Humor, Life, Motivational', 'Things turn out best for people who make the best of the way things turn out.', NULL, 'A cheerful cartoon scene with a smiling person standing at a crossroads in a simple countryside setting. The crossroads has two signposts: one pointing left labeled ''Plan A'' and the other pointing right labeled ''Plan B.'' The person is wearing casual clothes, has a positive expression, and is shrugging with open arms as if saying, ''Oh well!'' Around them are bright green grass, a few flowers, and a blue sky with fluffy clouds. In the background, a winding path continues beyond the signs, symbolizing the journey ahead regardless of the choice made. The overall tone is lighthearted and optimistic, drawn in a colorful, humorous cartoon style to emphasize making the best of whatever happens.'),
 (959, 'Comic Humor, Word Play', 'THINK! or THWIM!', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a superhero standing in a heroic pose on a city rooftop. The superhero looks confused, wearing a classic comic-style costume with a cape fluttering in the wind. Above the hero''s head are two large comic-style speech bubbles: one says ''THINK!'' in bold letters, and the other says ''THWIM!'' in action sound effect style lettering, emphasizing the sound of a web-shooting or teleportation move. The background displays a simple city skyline with a few buildings and a bright blue sky with fluffy clouds. The style is colorful and exaggerated, with the superhero having a slightly puzzled or unsure expression, hinting at the humorous confusion between thinking seriously and making a comic book sound effect. Emphasize the contrast between the thoughtful word and the whimsical sound effect, creating a visual pun in a lighthearted cartoon format.'),
 (960, 'Cars Humor, Humor, Puns', 'This car will never age - it won''t go over 40!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon of a car proudly parked in the center of the scene with a big, friendly smiling face on its windshield, as if it were a character. The car is small and boxy, clearly vintage, with exaggerated features like large eyes in place of headlights and a wide grinning bumper. Above the car is a large speedometer dial showing the needle stuck at 40 mph. Around the car, there are some subtle visual cues to indicate “aging” being stopped: a calendar with pages fluttering but staying on the same date, a cobweb nearby untouched, and an old-fashioned clock frozen in time. The background is a simple city street or driveway, bright and cheerful, emphasizing the car''s eternal youth due to its limited speed. The overall tone is lighthearted and cartoonish with bright colors and expressive lines that emphasize the joke’s pun about the car never aging because it never goes over 40 mph.'),
 (961, 'Food Humor, Word Play', 'This cookie is void where prohibited, licensed, or taxed.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large, oversized cookie sitting on a table with a serious official-looking stamp on it that reads ''Void Where Prohibited, Licensed, or Taxed'' as if it were legal fine print on a product. The cookie has a slightly perplexed but proud facial expression with cartoon eyes and a small smile. Around the cookie, place a few small signs that say ''Legal Notice,'' ''Tax Office,'' and ''License Required.'' In the background, an office clerk or government agent with glasses and a clipboard observes the cookie with a puzzled look. The setting is a simple, cheerful kitchen or a mix between a bakery and an office environment. The style is colorful, cartoonish, and exaggerated to emphasize the contrast between a tasty treat and legal jargon. No people look upset or angry—just amused and confused by the cookie’s unexpected legal status.'),
 (962, 'Humor, Relatable, Technology Humor', 'This has got to be the worst dream I''m ever having. I think I''m a computer...', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene of a person lying in bed asleep with a worried or confused expression on their face, eyes twitching under closed lids as if dreaming. Above the bed or near the person''s head, show a thought bubble filled with comical computer-related imagery: a desktop monitor displaying an error message or loading bar, a keyboard with some keys popping out, and maybe a mouse cursor floating around. The bedroom should be cozy but simple, with a nightstand holding an alarm clock and a small lamp. The overall style should be lighthearted and exaggerated, emphasizing the oddity and frustration of dreaming oneself as a computer rather than a pleasant or normal dream. Include soft colors and cartoonish proportions to enhance the humor and absurdity of the mental image.'),
 (963, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'This is a test as required by the FCC (Fortune Cookie Commision). Had this been a real cookie, it would have been much funnier.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene resembling a public service announcement broadcast setup. A cheerful fortune cookie mascot, anthropomorphized with big eyes and a wide smile, stands behind a podium labeled ''FCC - Fortune Cookie Commission''. The background features a simple banner with FCC initials and a few fortune cookies scattered around. The fortune cookie mascot holds a small paper scroll like a fortune message and speaks into an old-fashioned microphone. A speech bubble above the mascot reads: ''This is a test as required by the FCC (Fortune Cookie Commission). Had this been a real cookie, it would have been much funnier.'' The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions, bright colors, and a playful tone. No people or anything violent, just the cute cookie character delivering a mock official message.'),
 (964, 'Computers, Puns, Technology Humor', 'This is your computer:  01001000 01000001 01010000 01010000 01011001 00100000.  This is your computer on drugs: 01001000 01003001 01010300 01333000 31011001 33333333', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two side-by-side computer monitors on desks. The left monitor displays a screen filled with neat and clear binary code (strings of 0s and 1s) perfectly aligned and orderly. Above it is a friendly cartoon computer with a happy face and a thumbs-up gesture, radiating a calm and productive vibe. On the right, a second computer looks dazed, with droopy eyes, a wobbly smile, and crossed wires sticking out. Its screen is full of garbled, mixed-up strings of numbers and symbols resembling random code mixed with some illegible characters, as if the computer is malfunctioning or ''on drugs.'' Around this computer are humorous motion lines or swirls to emphasize its confused state. The background is a simple office setting with desks, keyboards, and mouse devices visible, with bright, cheerful colors to keep the cartoon light and funny. The caption or speech bubble could say: "This is your computer" above the first, and "This is your computer on drugs" above the second, to reinforce the joke visually without words dominating the scene.'),
 (965, 'Pop Culture, Puns, Technology Humor', 'This morning, Siri said, ''Don''t call me Shirley.'' I accidentally left my phone in Airplane! mode', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a kitchen table looking puzzled and holding a smartphone. The phone screen displays Siri’s speech bubble that reads, "Don''t call me Shirley." The person’s face shows a comical mix of confusion and surprise. Nearby on the table, an airplane mode icon on the phone screen is clearly visible. In the background, a small paper airplane toy rests on the table, adding a visual pun hinting at airplane mode. The setting is bright and cheerful, with exaggerated cartoon features to highlight the humor. Include playful details like small motion lines around the phone to suggest it just spoke, and a thought bubble above the person’s head with an airplane to reinforce the joke about airplane mode. The art style is light and fun, in bold colors, emphasizing the tech miscommunication theme with a witty nod to the classic “Don’t call me Shirley” line from the film Airplane!.'),
 (966, 'Humor, Irony, Word Play', 'Those who live by the sword, get shot by those who don''t.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two groups of people in a medieval-meets-modern setting. On one side, there are several knights in shining armor holding swords, looking confident and ready for battle. On the other side, a group of modern-day people dressed in casual clothes are holding guns, aiming playfully but carefully. The swordsmen have startled, worried expressions as they see the opponents with guns. The background could be a simple blend of a castle wall on one side and a contemporary cityscape behind the people with guns. Include a humorous street sign or banner above that reads, ''Those who live by the sword,'' and below it, another sign near the gun-holders saying, ''get shot by those who don’t.'' The overall color scheme should be bright and playful, with exaggerated, cartoon-style caricatures and expressions emphasizing the irony and humorous contrast between old and new weaponry.'),
 (967, 'Conspiracy Humor, Humor, Word Play', 'Three conspiracy theorists walk into a bar. That can''t just be a coincidence.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a lively bar with colorful decorations and a few patrons in the background. In the foreground, three distinct characters labeled or visually styled as ''conspiracy theorists'' enter through the door together. Each has exaggerated, stereotypical features: one wearing tinfoil hat, another holding a magnifying glass or notebook filled with scribbles and charts, and the third looking suspicious, scanning the room cautiously. The bartender is behind the counter, looking quizzical and slightly amused. Above their heads, speech bubbles or a thought bubble shows the phrase, ''That can''t just be a coincidence.'' The overall tone is light and funny, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to enhance the comedic effect.'),
 (968, 'Fantasy Humor, Relatable', 'Three guys stranded on a desert island find a magic lantern containing a genie, who grants them each one wish. The first guy wishes he was off the island and back home. The second guy wishes the same. The third guy says: ''I’m lonely. I wish my friends were back here.''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene on a small, sandy desert island with a few palm trees and a simple rock or two. Three men stand on the island looking a bit stranded and surprised. Near them lies an old, ornate magic lantern, from which a whimsical genie in a playful cloud of smoke is emerging. The first two men are happily disappearing in a sparkling swirl of magic, with joyful expressions as if they are being instantly transported back home. The third man, left behind and looking lonely and slightly confused, is surrounded by an empty space where his two friends once stood. His expression should be a mix of innocence and longing. The background shows a bright blue sky and a calm sea, emphasizing the isolation but keeping the tone light and funny. The style should be cartoony with exaggerated expressions and bright colors to highlight the humor and fantasy elements of the story.'),
 (969, 'Puns, Word Play', 'Time flies like an arrow, fruit flies like a banana.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene split into two parts. On the left side, depict a classic arrow flying swiftly through the air with motion lines, symbolizing the phrase ''Time flies like an arrow.'' The background shows a simple blue sky with a few clouds to emphasize speed and direction. On the right side, illustrate several small, cartoonish fruit flies with big eyes and wings happily gathering around and landing on a bright yellow banana that is lying on a wooden table. The fruit flies should look cheerful and animated, emphasizing the pun that these insects ''like a banana.'' The overall style should be light-hearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions on the flies and a clear visual contrast between the arrow in flight and the fruit flies interacting with the banana. Avoid any characters; focus on the arrow, the banana, and the flies to visually play on the dual meaning of the phrase.'),
 (970, 'Philosophy Humor, Science, Word Play', 'Time is nature''s way of keeping everything from happening at once.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon showing a whimsical, exaggerated clock with human-like features (big eyes, a smiling face) standing in the middle of a busy natural scene. Around the clock are various events from nature happening, but spaced out in time. On one side, a flower is blooming with a happy face; on another, a bird is flying; nearby, a tree is growing slowly with little cartoons of roots and leaves popping up. In the background, the sun is rising on one side and setting on the other, emphasizing the passage of time. The clock holds a sign or points to a speech bubble saying, ''Time keeps everything from happening at once!'' The overall style is playful and light, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions on the clock and natural elements to emphasize the humor in the idea of time controlling events in nature.'),
 (971, 'Dark Humor, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'Time is the best teacher; Unfortunately it kills all its students!', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring an old-fashioned teacher, personified as a whimsical clock with arms, legs, and a friendly face, standing in front of a classroom. The classroom has a blackboard with the phrase ''Time is the best teacher'' written on it. Surrounding the clock-teacher are cartoon students depicted as various smaller clocks or wristwatches, all looking a little worn out or sleepy, some with cartoon ''X'' eyes to humorously imply they are ''dead.'' The classroom setting is light-hearted and colorful, with desks, a globe, and school supplies scattered around. The overall tone is playful and funny, emphasizing the pun that though time teaches us, it also eventually leads to the end of all students. No dark or scary elements; keep the scene cheerful and silly to match the joke’s ironic humor.'),
 (972, 'Food Humor, Puns', 'Time-saving idea: pre-toasted bread - just heat and serve.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon kitchen scene featuring a loaf of pre-sliced bread labeled ''Pre-Toasted Bread'' sitting next to a regular toaster. The loaf has a smiling, confident face with steam rising from it, indicating it’s already toasted. A happy person, wearing an apron, is holding a plate with a perfectly toasted slice, looking pleasantly surprised. The toaster is unplugged and abandoned to the side, maybe with a small sign that says ''Not needed!''. The background is a bright, cheerful kitchen with a countertop, coffee mug, and a window showing morning sun rays. The overall style is playful and exaggerated with bold lines and vibrant colors, emphasizing the absurd convenience of the ''pre-toasted bread'' concept.'),
 (973, 'Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'To be Frank, I''d have to change my name.', NULL, 'A lighthearted cartoon scene featuring a person named Steve standing in front of a mirror, looking at his reflection. The mirror clearly shows his name tag on his shirt that reads ''Steve.'' A thought bubble above his head contains the text: ''To be Frank, I''d have to change my name.'' The background is simple, inside a cozy room with a dresser and a door visible. The character has a playful, slightly puzzled expression, and the overall style is colorful, cheerful, and exaggerated to emphasize the pun humor. No other people or complicated details, keeping the focus on the character and the pun about names.'),
 (974, 'Philosophy Humor, Quotes, Relatable', 'To be great is to be misunderstood.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing on a small stage or pedestal, looking proud but confused, with question marks and puzzled faces around them. The person is surrounded by various people who are reacting with funny expressions: some scratching their heads, some whispering to each other, and one person holding a dictionary upside down. Above the person on stage, a big speech bubble contains the phrase ''To be great is to be misunderstood.'' The background is colorful with simple shapes, and the style is lighthearted and exaggerated, focusing on the contrast between the confident individual and the baffled crowd. No violent or sensitive elements should be included.'),
 (975, 'Humor, Programming, Word Play', 'To be, or not to be, those are the parameters.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a confused Shakespeare character holding a large scroll or script with the famous line, but altered: ''To be, or not to be, those are the parameters.'' Shakespeare should be standing in a classic Elizabethan setting, perhaps in a dimly lit study or on a small stage with wooden floorboards. Around him, instead of the usual philosophical props, include some modern elements associated with programming or math – such as lines of code or parameter boxes floating in the air, question marks, and maybe a speech bubble with binary numbers or function arguments. Shakespeare’s facial expression should be puzzled but comedic, scratching his head or furrowing his brow. The overall style should be light, colorful, and exaggerated like a classic cartoon, capturing the playfully nerdy twist on the famous Shakespeare quote.'),
 (976, 'Motivational, Philosophy Humor', 'To believe you can is everything.', NULL, 'A cartoon scene showing a cheerful, eager character standing at the starting line of a race track labeled ''Life Challenge.'' The character is in mid-lean, ready to sprint, eyes bright with determination. Above their head is a glowing, large, inspirational thought bubble containing the phrase ''To believe you can is everything.'' Around the track are simple, encouraging signs like ''You got this!'' and ''Keep going!'' The background is bright and optimistic with a clear blue sky and a few fluffy clouds. The overall mood is motivational and light-hearted, drawn in a colorful, exaggerated cartoon style emphasizing positive energy and self-confidence.'),
 (977, 'Philosophy Humor, Relatable', 'To distinguish the real from the unreal, one must experience them both.', NULL, 'A whimsical cartoon scene split into two halves. On the left side, a cheerful person is holding a realistic-looking ice cream cone happily standing in a sunny park with trees, birds, and a bench. On the right side, the same person looks puzzled, now holding a melting, bizarre ice cream cone that looks unreal—perhaps with impossible shapes like floating scoops or glowing colors. The middle of the image shows a transparent mirror or glass dividing the two worlds, symbolizing the boundary between real and unreal. The person’s expression shifts from contentment on the real side to thoughtful curiosity on the unreal side. The overall style is lighthearted with bright colors and exaggerated, cartoonish features to emphasize the contrast and humorously illustrate the concept of distinguishing reality by experiencing both.'),
 (978, 'Animals, Puns, Word Play', 'To err is human, to moo bovine.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on a sunny green farm with a blue sky and fluffy white clouds. In the center, a cartoon cow stands upright like a human, with a comically thoughtful expression, holding a large book titled ''Human Mistakes'' in one hoof. Nearby, a confused-looking cartoon human wearing simple farmer clothes scratches his head. The cow is saying the phrase ''To err is human, to moo bovine'' in a speech bubble. Around them are classic farm elements: a red barn, a wooden fence, some hay bales, and a few other cows grazing or watching curiously. The style is colorful, lighthearted, and exaggerated with big eyes and friendly expressions to enhance the pun’s humor without any aggressive or negative tones.'),
 (979, 'Humor, Irony', 'To get maximum attention, it''s hard to beat a good, big mistake.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene depicting a person standing in the middle of a busy office or classroom with exaggerated, comedic expressions of surprise on everyone''s faces. The central character has a big, exaggerated facial expression of shock or realization, pointing to a giant, obvious mistake nearby, such as a massive, misspelled sign or a huge paper mess labeled ''Mistake.'' Around the character, other people stare wide-eyed or lean forward with curiosity, emphasizing the ''maximum attention'' concept. The setting is lighthearted with fun details like floating question marks, exclamation points, and cartoonish sweat drops to add humor. The style should be playful and exaggerated, making the mistake appear ridiculously large and the reactions overly dramatic, all done in a friendly, funny cartoon style without harsh lines or negativity.'),
 (980, 'Humor, Pop Culture, Science Fiction Humor', 'To hell with the Prime Directive - let''s kill something.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon-style scene set on the bridge of a starship, clearly inspired by classic sci-fi, with a diverse crew of colorful aliens and humans in futuristic uniforms. In the center, a captain with a confident, mischievous grin is dramatically throwing down a large, old-fashioned book titled ''Prime Directive'' onto a console. Around the captain, the crew reacts with surprised, shocked, or excited expressions. The background shows futuristic control panels, blinking lights, and viewscreens displaying outer space with distant planets and stars. Emphasize exaggerated cartoonish features and lively expressions to highlight the humor of breaking a well-known serious rule for a ridiculous reason. No violence should be depicted—just the playful mood of wanting to do something rebellious in a sci-fi setting.'),
 (981, 'Irony, Philosophy Humor', 'To laugh at men of sense is the privilege of fools.', NULL, 'A simple humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters: one clearly a wise, older man with glasses and a thoughtful expression, dressed in scholarly clothing, and the other a young foolish-looking character laughing exaggeratedly. The wise man stands calmly with a slight smirk, holding a book titled ''Sense & Wisdom.'' The fool wears a colorful jester hat and oversized shoes, giggling loudly with tears of laughter, pointing at the wise man. The background is minimalistic with a small podium labeled ''Privilege.'' The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions emphasizing the fool''s amusement and the wise man''s calm demeanor.'),
 (982, 'Food Humor, Puns', 'To me, ''drink responsibly'' means don''t spill it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a lively bar or party environment. In the center, a cheerful person is holding a glass of drink (could be beer, wine, or cocktail) with a big smile, focusing carefully on not spilling it. Nearby, drinks are precariously balanced, and someone in the background is accidentally spilling their drink, looking surprised or embarrassed. The setting includes a bar counter with bottles and glasses, colorful string lights, and a few other cartoon characters enjoying themselves. The overall style is lighthearted and exaggerated with bright colors and expressive faces to emphasize the punchline about ''drink responsibly'' meaning ''don''t spill it.'' No violence or inappropriate content should be depicted.'),
 (983, 'Humor, Relatable', 'To not see these messages all the time, close your eyes.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person sitting at a desk cluttered with a computer, smartphone, and several sticky notes with notifications or message icons on them. The person has a mildly frustrated but playful expression and is closing their eyes tightly, as if trying to escape the barrage of messages around them. Around their head, small cartoon message bubbles with exclamation marks, email icons, and chat symbols float in the air to represent constant notifications. The background shows a window with light coming in, and a clock on the wall indicating daytime. The overall style is bright and lighthearted, with exaggerated facial features and simple shapes to emphasize the comic mood without any aggression or negativity.'),
 (984, 'Humor, Word Play, Workplace', 'To steal ideas from one person is plagiarism, to steal from many is research.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a quirky, cluttered office or study room filled with books, papers, and quirky inventions. In the center, a character is comically holding a giant, overflowing net labeled ''Idea Catcher,'' capturing floating light bulbs (representing ideas) from several other characters around him who look surprised or annoyed. Each of these characters is standing by desks or chairs cluttered with papers and notebooks, some labeled ''Original Idea.'' The main character wears glasses and a mischievous grin, confidently sorting ideas into a big folder labeled ''Research.'' The background includes whimsical details like inspirational posters, a coffee mug, and a chalkboard with crossed-out copyrights and scribbled notes. The style should be colorful, exaggerated, and playful to highlight the witty contrast between plagiarism and research without any negativity.'),
 (985, 'Humor, Word Play', 'To the thief who took my anti-depressants - I hope you''re happy.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing next to an open medicine cabinet with an empty bottle labeled ''Anti-Depressants''. The person has a sarcastic, slightly annoyed expression and is shaking their fist upward. In the background, a shadowy, sneaky thief is tiptoeing away, sneaking off with a small sack or bag looking pleased and humming, clearly happy. The setting is a cozy, everyday bathroom with a sink, a mirror reflecting the frustrated owner, and some quirky details like a rubber duck and a towel rack. The overall tone is light and funny, emphasizing the irony of the statement with exaggerated facial expressions and body language in a cartoon style.'),
 (986, 'Humor, Programming, Technology Humor', 'To understand a program you must become one with the machine and the program.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person half-transformed into a robot sitting at a desk with a computer. The human side looks curious and slightly confused, while the robot side has mechanical features like a metal arm with wires and a screen for an eye. The computer screen shows lines of code. Around the desk, include scattered programming books and a coffee cup labeled ''Fuel.'' Have subtle steam or blinking lights around the person to emphasize the process of becoming ''one'' with the machine. The setting is a quirky, colorful office space with typical programmer items such as a keyboard, mouse, and sticky notes with funny reminders. The overall style should be lighthearted and whimsical, highlighting the funny idea of literally merging with a machine to understand a program better.'),
 (987, 'Irony, Life, Philosophy Humor', 'To win you sometimes have to concede.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene with two cartoon-styled characters sitting at a negotiation table. One character looks serious and determined, confidently pointing at a contract or chessboard labeled ''Victory.'' The other character is smiling slyly, holding a white flag or a small flag that reads ''I concede.'' Both characters are in a simple office or game room with a playful atmosphere, bright colors, and exaggerated expressions. The background should be minimal to keep the focus on the interaction and the concept of conceding as a form of winning. The overall tone is lighthearted and clever, emphasizing the irony of winning by giving up.'),
 (988, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'Total strangers need love too - and I''m stranger than most!', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a quirky, eccentric-looking character standing alone on a busy city street. The character should have a wide grin and be dressed in mismatched, colorful clothes to emphasize their oddball nature. Around this character, there are small groups of people clearly ignoring each other, highlighting the concept of strangers. Include subtle heart-shaped symbols floating above the character’s head to show their desire for love. The background should show everyday elements like street lamps, benches, and a few pedestrians walking by without paying attention. The overall style should be light-hearted and fun, with exaggerated expressions to convey the character’s self-aware and playful attitude about being “stranger than most.”'),
 (989, 'Humor, Science Fiction Humor, Word Play', 'Travel to the future in the blink of an eye!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a person standing in front of a large, old-fashioned clock face with exaggeratedly large eyes wide open, mid-blink. The clock’s hands are spinning rapidly, and around the person, there are small cartoonish futuristic elements like flying cars, robots, and holograms appearing as if they''ve popped up instantly. The character is frozen in the blink, with a surprised or puzzled expression, emphasizing the idea of ''traveling to the future'' literally by blinking. The background should be simple and colorful, playing up the contrast between the ordinary present time and the futuristic world. Include humorous details like a calendar flipping pages or a newspaper headline changing from ''Today'' to ''Future News.'' The style is light, playful, and suitable for all audiences, with round shapes and vibrant colors to keep the mood fun and whimsical.'),
 (990, 'Dark Humor, Life, Philosophy Humor', 'Treat each day as your last, one day you will be right.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful person waking up in bed with an exaggerated, bright morning sun shining through the window. The character is stretching widely with a big smile, wearing pajamas. Around the room are typical morning objects like an alarm clock, a coffee mug, and a calendar on the wall with the date circled in red. Above the character, a thought bubble displays the quote: ''Treat each day as your last, one day you will be right.'' The overall tone is light and optimistic but with a subtle twist of dark humor. The colors are bright and vibrant to emphasize the contrast between the lively morning and the underlying grim twist of the phrase. The art style is cartoonish with rounded shapes and expressive faces to highlight the joke''s ironic nature.'),
 (991, 'Education Humor, Exaggeration, Relatable', 'Trying to get an education here is like trying to take a drink from a fire hose.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a student sitting at a desk inside a classroom. The student looks overwhelmed, wide-eyed, and struggling to drink water from a gigantic fire hose that is blasting out a powerful stream of water directly at their open mouth. The water splashes everywhere, drenching the student and their books on the desk. The classroom background should include a chalkboard with some simple math or notes, a few scattered textbooks and papers flying from the impact of the water, and perhaps a small clock on the wall. The student wears casual school clothes and has exaggerated cartoon features expressing shock and being overloaded. The overall style is bright and goofy, emphasizing the absurdity of trying to ''drink'' from such an intense source, visually representing the phrase''s meaning about overwhelming education.'),
 (992, 'Humor, Irony, Relatable', 'Two can live as cheaply as one, for half as long.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two quirky characters sharing a single tiny, rundown apartment to cut costs. One character is lounging on a shabby couch looking relaxed and frugal, while the other is peeking from behind a door with a worried expression. The room should look cramped and old-fashioned, with minimal furniture such as a small table, a single lamp, and a bare light bulb hanging from the ceiling. A large calendar on the wall highlights the passage of time with pages flying off to emphasize the idea of short time. The atmosphere is lighthearted and kitschy, with exaggerated expressions to capture the humor about living cheaply but only for a short duration. Include small details like an empty wallet, a shared cup of instant noodles, and a clock showing time ticking fast to reinforce the joke’s theme of economy versus longevity. The style should be colorful, simple, and playful to enhance the cartoonish comedy of the scene.'),
 (993, 'Humor, Word Play', 'Two guys are fighting and one draws a line on the ground and says ''if you cross that line I''ll punch you''. <pause and look puzzled> uh, that was the punch line.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two guys standing face-to-face outdoors on a simple dirt or pavement ground with a clearly drawn straight line between them. One guy, with a serious but slightly puzzled expression, is drawing the line on the ground with a stick or finger. The other guy is standing just behind the line looking confused or thoughtful, scratching his head or raising an eyebrow. Above them, there''s a speech bubble from the first guy saying, ''If you cross that line I''ll punch you.'' The second guy then has a speech bubble with a pause or dots ''...uh, that was the punch line.'' The background is simple, emphasizing the focus on the characters, the line on the ground, and their comedic misunderstanding. The style is clean, bright, and cartoony with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the joke''s wordplay.'),
 (994, 'Crime Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'Two men broke into a drugstore and stole all the Viagra. The police are on the lookout for two hardened criminals.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set outside a small, colorful drugstore at night. Two cartoon men, looking sneaky but goofy rather than scary, are running away from the store carrying bags labeled ''Viagra'' in bold letters. One man should be taller and thinner, the other shorter and stockier, both with exaggerated expressions of mischief and excitement. Nearby, a police car with flashing lights is parked, and a couple of officers are looking around alertly, searching for the ''criminals.'' To add humor, show a wanted poster on a light pole featuring two muscular, tough-looking cartoon pills with stern faces, labeled ''Hardened Criminals.'' Make the style bright and playful with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the pun and the joke''s wordplay. Avoid dark or threatening tones; keep it lighthearted and funny.'),
 (995, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'Two rules for a very successful life:   1. Never tell everything that you know   2. (This space intentionally left blank)', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring a quirky, smiling character standing next to a large whiteboard or poster titled ''Two Rules for a Very Successful Life.'' The board shows: 1. ''Never tell everything that you know'' written clearly, and 2. ''(This space intentionally left blank)'' written below with a large empty space around it. The character is holding a marker and gesturing proudly towards the board, with a playful smirk or wink, suggesting they are in on a clever secret. Around the character, add a few lighthearted elements like a thinking bubble with an exaggerated secret (e.g., a treasure chest or a lightbulb with a lock), and a classroom or office background with subtle details like a small plant, a clock, or motivational posters, creating a friendly, humorous atmosphere. Use bright colors and simple cartoon styling to emphasize the joke''s irony and wit without any tension or negativity.'),
 (996, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'Two wrongs are only the beginning.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a series of two comic mistakes happening one after the other. The first part of the image depicts a character, looking puzzled, holding two incorrect items (for example, a broken map and a misspelled sign). The second part shows the same character making a second blunder based on the first one, like getting lost further or accidentally heading toward trouble, with exaggerated confused expressions and question marks above their head. The background can be a city street or a wilderness trail with signs pointing in conflicting or wrong directions, emphasizing the phrase ''two wrongs are only the beginning.'' The style should be colorful, playful, and emphasize the escalating nature of errors without implying any harm. Thought bubbles or caption boxes can be used to highlight the idea that one mistake leads to another.'),
 (997, 'Bad Puns, History Humor, Science', 'Two wrongs don''t make a right, but two Wrights did make an airplane.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two men labeled ''Wright Brothers'' standing proudly beside their vintage airplane. The airplane should be an early biplane with fabric wings and wooden propellers, styled like the Wright Flyer. The two men are smiling and dressed in early 1900s attire with caps and suspenders. Above them, a comic-style speech bubble or sign reads: ''Two wrongs don''t make a right, but two Wrights did make an airplane.'' The background is a simple open field with a clear sky. The overall mood should be lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the pun on the word ''Wright'' and the phrase ''make a right.'' No violent or political elements, just cheerful historical humor in a clean cartoon style.')
INSERT INTO @tmpJokes (JokeId, Categories, JokeTxt, Attribution, ImageTxt) VALUES
 (998, 'Humor, Language, Word Play', 'TYPEWRITER is the longest word that can be made using the letters only on one row of the keyboard.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a classic QWERTY keyboard viewed from above, emphasizing the top row of letters (QWERTYUIOP). Above the keyboard, a large, playful word bubble shows the word ''TYPEWRITER'' in big, colorful letters, clearly made up entirely from the top row keys. A cheerful cartoon character, perhaps a quirky writer or typist, is pointing excitedly at the keyboard with a big smile, wearing round glasses and a slightly exaggerated clicky typing finger. On the desk nearby, there are crumpled papers and a vintage typewriter (to humorously hint at the word''s meaning). The background is simple with pastel colors to keep focus on the keyboard and the character. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the cleverness of the fact that ''TYPEWRITER'' fits only on one keyboard row. Avoid any violent or political elements; focus on a fun, educational, and slightly nerdy vibe.'),
 (999, 'Humor, Life, Word Play', 'UNEMPLOYMENT ISN''T WORKING', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person lounging on a couch in casual, slightly rumpled clothes, looking completely relaxed with a content smile. Beside them is a coffee table cluttered with snacks, a remote control, and an empty coffee cup. Behind the couch, a calendar on the wall clearly shows a month with many days crossed out, indicating a long period of unemployment. The room has a messy, lived-in feel, with slippers kicked off near the couch and a sleeping cat curled up nearby. A thought bubble above the person reads ''Unemployment isn''t working,'' adding a clever visual pun. The overall style is lighthearted and colorful, emphasizing the irony and wordplay in a friendly, non-serious atmosphere.'),
 (1000, 'Humor, Relatable, Workplace', 'UNEMPLOYMENT: The usual alternative to overwork.', NULL, 'A simple cartoon scene depicting two contrasting sides to illustrate the joke about unemployment as an alternative to overwork. On the left side, draw a stressed-out worker slumped over a desk piled high with paperwork, clock showing late hours. The worker looks tired, with disheveled hair and dark circles under their eyes. On the right side, show the same character relaxed at home in casual clothes, lounging comfortably on a couch with feet up, watching TV or playing video games, looking content and carefree. Include a calendar on the wall with workdays crossed out on the left side and blank or relaxed symbols like smiley faces on the right. The overall style should be light, bright, and humorous, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize fatigue versus relaxation, in a clean, colorful cartoon format without any violence or political themes.'),
 (1001, 'Humor, Life, Motivational', 'Unless you try to do something beyond what you have already mastered, you will never grow.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing at the edge of a small cliff or stepping off a diving board labeled ''Comfort Zone.'' Behind them are various trophies and certificates on a shelf labeled ''What I Have Mastered.'' The person looks hesitant but determined, dressed in casual clothes with a small backpack labeled ''Growth.'' In the background, a bright sun is rising, symbolizing new opportunities. Nearby, a friendly cartoon character (a wise owl wearing glasses) points encouragingly toward a path leading uphill labeled ''New Challenges.'' The overall style is lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated expressions to convey cautious optimism and the idea of stepping beyond familiar limits to grow.'),
 (1002, 'Food Humor, Puns', 'Velveeta is so vegetarians can have Spam too.', NULL, 'Create a humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters at a picnic table in a sunny park. One character is a cheerful vegetarian holding a big, shiny block of Velveeta cheese labeled clearly. The other character is looking surprised, holding a can of Spam with a puzzled expression. On the table, place sliced Velveeta cheese arranged to look like slices of Spam. Include a picnic basket nearby with typical picnic food like bread, fruit, and utensils. Add a small sign or speech bubble from one character saying, ''Velveeta is so vegetarians can have Spam too.'' The style should be lighthearted and colorful, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the joke''s playful confusion about vegetarian substitutes. The overall tone is fun and silly, without any harshness or negativity.'),
 (1003, 'Puns, Shopping Jokes, Word Play', 'VENI, VIDI, VISA (We came, we saw, we went shopping)', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing three characters in ancient Roman-style clothing but with a modern twist. They are standing in front of a shopping mall entrance with big glass doors labeled ''VISA Shopping Center.'' One character holds shopping bags overflowing with various colorful items, another is looking excitedly at a store window, and the third is checking a credit card (with VISA logo). Behind them is a large billboard on the mall showing the phrase ''VENI, VIDI, VISA'' in bold letters, with a subtitle underneath: ''We came, we saw, we went shopping.'' The background has a mix of ancient Roman columns and modern retail store signs. The style is bright, exaggerated, and playful, emphasizing the pun on the famous Latin phrase and the VISA credit card brand.'),
 (1004, 'Humor, Star Wars', 'Very funny, Scotty.  Now beam down my clothes.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on the bridge of a starship with a cheerful, uniformed captain addressing a small, stout engineer named Scotty, who is standing next to a large, futuristic teleportation device. The captain is depicted with a playful smile, pointing toward an empty hanger or a clothes rack that is humorously floating in midair, indicating missing clothes. Scotty looks slightly puzzled or amused as he operates the teleportation controls. The background shows typical sci-fi elements like blinking consoles and a starry window view of outer space. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, capturing the joke about teleporting clothes rather than people.'),
 (1005, 'History Humor, Humor, Word Play', 'VIRGIN: A young innocent who in former times was sacrificed to the gods but who now merely lives in disgrace.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene divided into two panels. In the first panel, depict an ancient setting with a young, wide-eyed innocent person (labeled ''Virgin'') tied to a stone altar, surrounded by cartoonish angry gods with thunderbolts, dramatic fire, and gods looking displeased but not scary. The setting should be outdoors with temple columns and some tropical plants to suggest an ancient civilization. In the second panel, show the same young person in modern clothes, sitting alone on a park bench looking awkward and embarrassed, with people nearby whispering or giving side glances. Include modern urban elements like a city skyline, a lamppost, and a dog walker passing by. The style should be colorful, lighthearted, and exaggerated with big expressive eyes to emphasize innocence and shame without being mean. Add a caption under the panels reading: ''Virgin: A young innocent who in former times was sacrificed to the gods but who now merely lives in disgrace.'''),
 (1006, 'Humor, Life, Relatable', 'Vital papers will demonstrate their vitality by moving from where you left them to where you can''t find them.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a cluttered home office or study room. On a wooden desk, a person looks puzzled and frustrated, searching through scattered papers and folders. Several sheets of paper are shown with cartoonish, lively arms and legs, tiptoeing or sneaking away from the desk toward a dark, mysterious corner or behind a couch. The papers have playful, expressive faces showing mischief and vitality, as if they are alive and deliberately hiding themselves. The room includes typical office objects such as a lamp, a computer, a cup of coffee, and a wastebasket. The lighting is warm and inviting, emphasizing the comical struggle of finding important documents that seem to have a mind of their own. The overall style is lighthearted and exaggerated with bright colors, appealing to a wide audience in a cartoon format.'),
 (1007, 'Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'VUJA DE:  The strange feeling you get that nothing has ever happened before.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a confused person standing in the middle of a surreal landscape. The person has a puzzled expression, scratching their head with exaggerated confusion lines above their head. Around them, everyday objects like a coffee cup, clock, and calendar float in the air, but everything looks brand new and unfamiliar as if they''ve never been seen before. The background is whimsical and slightly surreal, with a twist on normal reality—trees with upside-down leaves and clocks with random numbers. A small caption near the person reads ''Vuja De: The strange feeling you get that nothing has ever happened before.'' The overall style is light-hearted, colorful, and cartoonish with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the oddity of the feeling.'),
 (1008, 'Relatable, Sleep Humor', 'Wake me in time for the weekend.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a person lying in bed with a cozy blanket, eyes closed, and a peaceful smile, clearly deep in sleep. The room is softly lit with a bedside lamp. On the nightstand next to the bed, there is an old-fashioned alarm clock showing some random weekday time. Above the sleeping person, a thought bubble contains the words, ''Wake me in time for the weekend.'' The wall behind the bed has a small calendar with the current day highlighted, emphasizing the wait for the weekend. The overall style is lighthearted and simple, with bright, cheerful colors and exaggerated expressions to convey the concept of longing to skip ahead in time. No other characters or complex background details are needed.'),
 (1009, 'Humor, Relatable', 'Waking a person unnecessarily should not be considered a capital crime. For a first offense, that is.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a sleepy person in bed, wearing pajamas and a nightcap, with heavy eyelids and a big yawn. Next to the bed, a mischievous character—depicted as a smiling person or cartoon animal—leans over, about to poke or shake the sleeper to wake them up. The bedroom should feel cozy, with a bedside table holding a lamp, an alarm clock showing an early morning time, and maybe a window showing dawn outside. The sleeping person looks annoyed or startled but not angry, emphasizing comedy rather than frustration. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated, with expressive faces and simple lines, capturing the silly idea of treating waking someone up as a serious crime. Include a small sign or thought bubble near the mischievous character that says something like "First offense" to link to the joke text humorously. The overall tone is playful and whimsical, without any aggressive or dark elements.'),
 (1010, 'Cartoon, Humor, Pop Culture', 'Walt Disney is in suspended animation.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Walt Disney inside a large, clear, futuristic glass tube or chamber labeled ''Suspended Animation.'' Walt is depicted with his iconic glasses, mustache, and neat suit, looking calm and peaceful as if simply resting. Around the chamber are whimsical Disney-themed decorations like Mickey Mouse ears, a small castle model, and animated sketches floating in the air, suggesting creativity in pause. Nearby, a quirky scientist in a lab coat with cartoonish gadgets looks on, scratching his head in mild confusion. A small sign on the chamber reads: ''Wake Me Up Before Tomorrowland!'' The style is bright, colorful, and exaggerated with soft lines, capturing a lighthearted, playful mood without any threatening imagery or dark tones.'),
 (1011, 'Humor, Language, Word Play', 'Wanna hear a word I just made up? Plagiarism', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon featuring a person standing on a small stage holding a microphone. The person looks enthusiastic and confident, as if about to share a joke or a fact. Above them, a large comic-style speech bubble reads: ''Wanna hear a word I just made up? Plagiarism.'' In the background, the audience looks puzzled or amused, some scratching their heads or whispering to each other. The setting is a simple comedy club or classroom with a spotlight on the speaker. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize the humor of the punchline about copying a word called plagiarism, which ironically means copying others'' work.'),
 (1012, 'Food Humor, Life, Relatable', 'Wanted: A 21-day diet that goes as fast as a 21-day vacation.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two split panels. On the left panel, a person excitedly packing a suitcase labeled ''21-day Vacation'' with sunglasses, a hat, flip-flops, and travel brochures scattered around. They have a big smile, and a calendar on the wall highlights 21 days marked off with bright colors. On the right panel, the same person is struggling at a kitchen table surrounded by vegetables, a salad bowl, a measuring scale, and a bottle of water. Their expression is tired and bored, glancing at a calendar also marked 21 days but dragging on with slow-moving clock hands above it. The contrast between the fast, happy anticipation of the vacation and the slow, arduous dieting journey is emphasized with exaggerated facial expressions and bright vs. dull colors. The whole scene should be drawn in a playful cartoon style with clear labels and visual humor to capture the joke about wanting a diet as fast and enjoyable as a vacation is.'),
 (1013, 'Philosophy Humor, War Humor, Word Play', 'War never decides who is right, only who is left.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a barren battlefield with a few scattered, tired-looking soldiers on both sides. The background shows damaged and abandoned flags, torn banners, and broken weapons strewn about. One soldier, standing in the center, looks puzzled and is holding a large sign with the words ''Who is right?'' on one side and ''Who is left?'' on the other. Another soldier nearby has an exaggeratedly confused expression, pointing to the ''Who is left?'' part of the sign. The atmosphere is light-hearted and comical, with no graphic violence, just a playful take on the wordplay. The scene uses bright colors and simple shapes to enhance the cartoon effect, with exaggerated facial expressions emphasizing the silliness of the pun.'),
 (1014, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'Warning: Dates in Calendar are closer than they appear.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a close-up of a traditional wall calendar. The calendar is open to a month with the days clearly visible. The numbers for each date seem to be comically squished or crowded together, almost overlapping, conveying the idea that the dates are physically closer to each other than usual. At the top of the calendar page, in big bold letters, is a warning sign that reads: ''Warning: Dates in Calendar are closer than they appear.'' In the background, a confused person or character with a raised eyebrow and wide eyes stares at the calendar, scratching their head as if puzzled by how tightly packed the dates are. The scene should have bright colors and exaggerated cartoonish expressions to enhance the humor and lightheartedness of the concept. The style is clean and simple with a focus on the calendar and the character''s reaction, capturing the joke’s play on words about the perception of dates approaching rapidly.'),
 (1015, 'Humor, Puns, Technology Humor', 'Warning: do not use your toaster as an alternate diskette reader.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene set in a cozy kitchen. On the left side, a confused, slightly frazzled person (gender-neutral) stands with a computer diskette in hand, staring at a toaster on the kitchen counter. The toaster has two slots on top, and instead of toast, a old-fashioned floppy disk (diskette) is halfway inserted into one slot, humorously ill-fitted. The toaster''s lever is halfway down, as if someone just tried to use it. Around the toaster, a few pieces of burnt toast with smoke rising comically form a small cloud above it. The background includes typical kitchen items: a coffee mug, a fruit bowl, and some cabinets. The person’s expression is exaggeratedly puzzled, with wide eyes and a raised eyebrow, capturing the confusion about using a toaster as a diskette reader. The overall style is bright, cartoonish, with slightly exaggerated proportions and simple, clean lines to emphasize the absurdity and humor of the situation. No text bubbles, just visual storytelling with a whimsical, lighthearted tone.'),
 (1016, 'Humor, Relatable, Weather Humor', 'Washing your car to make it rain doesn''t work.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene outside a suburban house on a sunny day, depicting a person enthusiastically washing their car with a big sponge and a bucket of soapy water. The car, shiny and wet, reflects the bright sun. Above, a clear blue sky with no clouds is visible, and a small, exaggerated cartoon sun wearing sunglasses beams down. The person looks hopeful but puzzled, glancing upward at the dry sky. Nearby, a calendar on the wall or post shows the date, emphasizing the moment. Include humorous details such as water splashing comically or a bird watching with a skeptical expression. The overall tone is light-hearted and playful, emphasizing the futility of the idea that washing a car could affect the weather.'),
 (1017, 'Money Humor, Workplace', 'Waste not; your budget will get cut next year.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene of an office budget meeting. Show a stressed-out office worker sitting at a desk covered with papers and a small calculator. The worker is looking worriedly at a big, scary budget chart on the wall with a downward arrow and the words ''Next Year Budget Cuts'' in bold. The scene has a large wastebasket overflowing with crumpled paper labeled ''Waste''. Add a speech bubble from the worker saying the joke: ''Waste not; your budget will get cut next year.'' The office environment should have a whiteboard and a clock showing late afternoon. Use bright colors and exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize humor and mild panic, avoiding anything violent or political.'),
 (1018, 'Mental Health Humor, Word Play', 'Watch out for Borderline psychotics - they tend to repeat things.  They tend to repeat things. Watch out for those borderline psychotics.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a quirky psychiatrist''s office. In the center, a cheerful psychiatrist with glasses and a clipboard is pointing nervously toward the office door. The door has a sign above it that reads ''Borderline Psychotic Waiting Room''. Outside the door, a slightly confused patient is pacing back and forth, repeating the same sentence twice with a speech bubble that loops over itself, saying: ''They tend to repeat things... They tend to repeat things.'' In the background, a wall chart titled ''Psychological Terms'' humorously highlights the word ''Borderline'' with a blinking light. The overall color palette is bright and lively, and all characters have exaggerated cartoon features for comedic effect. The scene should evoke a lighthearted, playful mood without any negativity or distress.'),
 (1019, 'Humor, Puns, Workplace', 'Watch out, buddy! You break it, you buy it! (Moral: Don''t Press Break.)', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a mischievous character about to press a big red button labeled ''BREAK'' on a large, old-fashioned machine. The setting is a workshop or a store with various gadgets around, some slightly cracked or broken. Another character stands beside him with an exaggerated worried expression, pointing a finger and shouting, ''Watch out, buddy! You break it, you buy it!'' The scene should be colorful and lighthearted, with cartoonish exaggerated facial expressions and body language showing the warning and impending trouble. The broken gadgets and the big red button are central elements, with a sign above the machine humorously reading ''Don''t Press Break!'''),
 (1020, 'Good Question!, Life, Philosophy Humor', 'Water is never truly yours - it’s just your turn to drink it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful person standing next to a large, clear water dispenser or water cooler with a big label that reads ''Water.'' The person is holding a glass of water and grinning broadly, as if proudly claiming the water. Around them, a subtle flow of water continues downstream or around a curved water pipe, visually indicating that the water is constantly moving or flowing elsewhere. In the background or as a small thought bubble above the person''s head, depict a clock or a line of people waiting to have their turn, suggesting the water is shared and only momentarily theirs. The style should be colorful and light-hearted, with exaggerated cartoon expressions to emphasize the joke’s theme that water is never permanently owned but just temporarily used. Include some simple elements like a river, a faucet dripping, or other containers to reinforce the idea of water''s ongoing flow and shared nature.'),
 (1021, 'Money Humor, Puns, Workplace', 'We all like praise, but a hike in our pay is the best kind of ways.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two colleagues standing side by side in an office break room. One person, dressed in casual business attire, is giving a thumbs-up and handing over a large paycheck with a big smile. The other person looks delighted, eyes wide and grinning, clearly preferring the paycheck over the verbal praise. Behind them, a whiteboard on the wall displays the words “Praise” with applause emojis and “Pay Raise” with dollar signs and upward arrows. The office setting includes a water cooler, a potted plant, and a coffee machine in the background. The characters have exaggerated facial expressions, emphasizing the joy over the pay raise, with a subtle humorous tone highlighting the pun “hike in pay” sounding like a “hike” walk in nature but referring to money increase instead.'),
 (1022, 'Life, Philosophy Humor', 'We are always the same age inside.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters, one elderly person and one child, standing side by side inside a giant transparent birthday cake decorated with colorful candles. Both characters have the same vibrant, youthful expression and wide, excited eyes as if they feel equally young on the inside. The elderly person is wearing glasses and slightly wrinkled clothes, while the child is dressed in casual, bright clothing. Around them are festive decorations like balloons and streamers. The background is simple and cheerful, emphasizing the contrast between their outward appearances and their shared inner youthfulness. The style is playful and exaggerated to highlight the joke’s message visually, with thought bubbles above each character showing a smaller version of themselves happily playing or dancing.'),
 (1023, 'Humor, Life, Relatable', 'We are born naked, wet and hungry.  Then things get worse.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a newborn baby lying on a changing table, looking a bit distressed. The baby is naked, with a little puddle of water around them to emphasize being wet, and a tiny milk bottle nearby to suggest hunger. Above the baby, a whimsical thought bubble shows a cartoonish downward spiral representing ''things getting worse,'' with funny mishaps: a diaper exploding, a crying toddler, spilled food, and messy toys. The background is a cozy nursery with pastel colors, a mobile hanging from the ceiling, and a tired-looking parent peeking in with a bemused expression. The overall tone is lighthearted and exaggerated to capture the humor in the statement without any harshness or negativity.'),
 (1024, 'Humor, Word Play, Workplace', 'We do precision guesswork.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene in an office setting featuring a group of professionals in lab coats and glasses standing around a large conference table covered with blueprints, rulers, calculators, and computers. They have confused, uncertain facial expressions as they try to measure something, but comically, their measuring tools are all wildly inaccurate or absurd (e.g., a ruler bent like a snake, a calculator displaying random symbols, a giant protractor mismatched to the drawing). One person is scratching their head, another is shrugging, and a third is marking a blueprint with a big question mark. In the background, a whiteboard says in large letters: ''PRECISION GUESSWORK'' with a wavy underline, emphasizing the ironic nature of the phrase. The overall tone is light and fun, with exaggerated expressions reflecting the contradiction between ''precision'' and ''guesswork.'' The style is simple, colorful, and playful, evoking classic cartoon humor without any harsh or negative elements.'),
 (1025, 'Absurd Humor, Food Humor', 'We don''t make sense, but we do like pizza.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two whimsical characters standing side by side. One character is a quirky, abstract shape with mismatched eyes and limbs, symbolizing the idea of ''not making sense.'' The other character, more normal in shape but happily holding a large, cheesy pizza with various toppings. Both characters have big smiles and relaxed poses, emphasizing their positive attitude despite confusion. The background is simple with a casual setting, like a brightly colored kitchen or a park with a picnic blanket and a pizza box open nearby. Include playful details such as floating question marks around the quirky character and little hearts or sparkles around the pizza-loving character. The overall tone is lighthearted, cheerfully embracing silliness and the joy of pizza.'),
 (1026, 'Irony, Motivational, Workplace', 'We have done so much for so long with so little, we can now do anything with nothing.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon of a tired but determined office worker sitting at a cluttered desk piled high with old, broken gadgets and empty coffee cups. The worker is smiling wryly, holding up empty hands as if proudly showing they have nothing. In the background, show a barely functioning, outdated computer with a flickering screen. Include motivational posters on the wall with irony, such as one reading ''Do More With Less'' and another saying ''Innovation from Nothing.'' The overall tone should be light and playful, emphasizing the idea of making do with very little but having a can-do attitude.'),
 (1027, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'We have enough youth, how about a fountain of SMART?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a park with a whimsical, sparkling fountain labeled ''Fountain of SMART'' in large, playful letters. Nearby, a group of diverse teenagers hang out looking playful and carefree, representing ''youth.'' An older, wise-looking figure (such as a professor or a cartoonish elder with glasses and a book) stands beside the fountain, holding a scroll or clipboard that says ''Intelligence Requests'' with an exaggerated hopeful expression. The background includes green grass, trees, and a clear blue sky, with some birds or butterflies to add lightness. The fountain should have sparkling water shooting up in a fun, exaggerated way, perhaps with little light bulbs or brains floating in the water to symbolize intelligence. The overall tone is lighthearted and clever, with characters drawn in a friendly, cartoon style with expressive faces to emphasize the joke’s ironic longing for more smarts rather than more youth.'),
 (1028, 'Pirates, Technology Humor, Travel Humor', 'We really used to print out pages from MapQuest and travel like pirates.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two modern-day travelers on a small boat dressed as pirates with eyepatches and pirate hats. One pirate is holding a big printed-out paper map with the MapQuest logo clearly visible, looking confused while trying to navigate. The other pirate is looking at a smartphone or GPS device, appearing amused or skeptical. The boat is whimsically decorated with a pirate flag, and the background shows a simple ocean with a tiny island in the distance. The overall tone is lighthearted, capturing the anachronism of using old-fashioned printed directions like pirates relying on treasure maps, contrasted with modern navigation technology.'),
 (1029, 'Art Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'We were state-of-the-art, but the art moved to a different state.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene featuring a modern, sleek art gallery labeled ''State-of-the-Art Gallery''. The gallery looks very high-tech and polished with shiny floors, digital screens, and contemporary sculptures. In front of the gallery is a large map of the United States with the gallery located in one state (e.g., California). From the gallery, various pieces of framed artwork, sculptures, and paintings are shown physically moving off the gallery walls and out of the building, animated with happy faces or tiny legs as if they are walking or floating. These artworks are heading towards another state on the map (e.g., New York), where a new bustling art scene is depicted with another gallery labeled ''New Art State'', with excited people admiring the incoming art. The overall mood is playful, with exaggerated expressions on the art pieces and a sunny background. The style is bright and cartoonish with clear labels on the buildings and map for clarity, emphasizing the pun that ''the art moved to a different state,'' both geographically and conceptually.'),
 (1030, 'Nature Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'Weeds always grow like weeds.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a suburban backyard garden. In the foreground, there is a patch of various garden plants with a few big, scraggly weeds growing tall and wild among them. The weeds are personified with silly faces and exaggerated features like wild, unkempt leaves and crooked stems, looking proud and mischievous. A gardener with a slightly puzzled or bemused expression is standing to the side, holding a watering can, looking at the weeds almost admiringly. Behind the gardener, a small sign stuck in the ground reads ''Garden''. The overall style should be lighthearted, colorful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the weeds’ uncontrolled and unruly growth as if they are happily doing exactly what weeds do best. No harmful or aggressive elements, just playful chaos of nature overruling human intent.'),
 (1031, 'History Humor, Puns, Science', 'Wernher von Braun settled for a V-2 when he coulda had a V-8.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing Wernher von Braun, an early rocket scientist, dressed in mid-20th-century attire with a rocket blueprint in one hand, standing next to a large rocket labeled ''V-2''. Nearby, there is a sleek, shiny red V-8 engine car with a confused or wistful expression on its face, symbolizing the missed opportunity. Von Braun looks contemplative, glancing between the rocket and the car. The background is a simple rocket launch pad with smoke or steam puffs, and a signpost humorously pointing in two directions: one labeled ''Rocket Science'' toward the V-2, and the other labeled ''Luxury Cars'' toward the V-8. The overall style is light-hearted and exaggerated in classic cartoon format, with expressive faces and bright colors to emphasize the pun about the V-2 rocket and V-8 car engine.'),
 (1032, 'Pop Culture, Puns, Science Fiction Humor', 'We''ve replaced the Dilithium with new Folgers Crystals!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set on the bridge of a starship reminiscent of classic sci-fi shows. The captain, wearing a futuristic uniform with a confused but amused expression, is holding a small coffee jar labeled ''Folgers Crystals'' in one hand and pointing to a glowing, futuristic ''Dilithium Crystal'' power core next to a coffee machine on the console. Around him, colorful control panels and blinking lights typical of a spaceship bridge are visible. A crew member nearby is nervously holding a steaming coffee cup, looking hopeful. Above the scene, a whimsical thought bubble shows a spaceship zooming powered by coffee steam instead of energy beams, emphasizing the joke’s play on replacing a vital power source with coffee crystals. The style is bright, exaggerated, and cartoonish, capturing light-hearted sci-fi parody without any violence or political elements.'),
 (1033, 'Absurd Humor, Food Humor, Puns', 'What a concept - boneless spare ribs!', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene at a backyard barbecue or picnic setting. In the center, show a large plate labeled ''Boneless Spare Ribs'' piled high with ribs, but the ribs look funny—each rib is a cartoon rib bone with a cute, exaggerated meat portion that is comically missing its bone in the center. Nearby, have a surprised cartoon character (could be a cheerful grill master or a picnic guest) with wide eyes and an open mouth, holding a rib in one hand and scratching their head with the other as if puzzled and amazed by the idea of ''boneless spare ribs.'' Include a barbecue grill in the background with smoke wafting lightly, and casual picnic elements like a checkered tablecloth, condiment bottles, and a bottle of barbecue sauce labeled ''Sauce.'' The overall style is colorful, lighthearted, and exaggerated for humor, not realistic. No violence or inappropriate content.'),
 (1034, 'Humor, Pop Culture, Puns', 'What are terminators called when they retire? Exterminators', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a group of Terminator-style robots in a retirement home setting. The robots have a metallic, humanoid appearance with glowing red eyes, but instead of looking menacing, they appear relaxed and cheerful, engaging in leisure activities like playing cards or knitting. One robot is wearing reading glasses and holding a newspaper with the headline ''Retirement Tips for Terminators.'' Another robot is reclining in a rocking chair with a cup of tea. In the background, include a sign that says ''Exterminators Retirement Community.'' The overall mood should be lighthearted and funny, emphasizing the pun ''Exterminators'' by showing these tough robots now taking it easy in retirement. Use bright, cartoonish colors and exaggerated expressions to enhance the comedic effect.'),
 (1035, 'Absurd Humor, Philosophy Humor, Relatable', 'What can''t affect you isn''t really there. But that doesn''t mean what isn''t really there can''t affect you.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting calmly on a park bench, eyes closed, smiling peacefully. Around them, faint translucent ghost-like shapes (representing ''things that can''t affect you'' because they''re not really there) float harmlessly, looking silly and harmless. However, one of these ghostly shapes is shown momentarily casting a visible shadow or ripple that subtly causes the person to sneeze or twitch, highlighting the contradiction. The background is a simple park setting with trees and a clear sky, and the overall tone is light and whimsical rather than spooky. The characters and ghosts should be colorful and exaggerated with friendly, non-threatening expressions to emphasize humor and irony without any sense of danger or fear.'),
 (1036, 'Animals, Puns, Word Play', 'What did the fish say when he hit a wall? Dam.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a surprised fish swimming underwater right in front of a large, cartoonish brick wall labeled ''DAM'' to clarify it''s a dam wall. The fish has wide eyes and its mouth open as if speaking or shocked. Bubbles rise from the fish''s mouth to emphasize speech. The underwater environment includes simple aquatic elements like seaweed, small rocks, and water plants to set the scene. The style is lighthearted and colorful with exaggerated expressions to enhance the joke''s punchline.'),
 (3218, 'Random', 'I won''t rise to the occasion, but I''ll slide over to it.', NULL, NULL),
 (1037, 'Animals, History Humor, Word Play', 'What do Atilla the Hun and Winnie the Pooh have in common?  Their middle name!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene split into two halves. On the left side, a caricature of Atilla the Hun is shown — wearing a traditional Hun warrior helmet with horns, fur clothing, and holding a small battle axe. He looks puzzled as he holds a name tag or scroll that says ''Atilla H. Hun.'' On the right side, Winnie the Pooh is standing, looking similarly puzzled and holding a honey pot labeled ''Pooh H. Bear.'' Both characters have exaggerated confused expressions, glancing at each other''s name tags or scrolls to emphasize the joke about their shared middle name initial ''H.'' The background is lighthearted with bright colors and simple shapes to keep it playful, and a big question mark floats above both characters to highlight the joke''s theme. No violence or intimidating features, just goofy and friendly cartoon vibes.'),
 (1038, 'Animals, Puns, Word Play', 'What do cows like to read? Cattle-logs', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a friendly cow sitting comfortably in an armchair, wearing reading glasses, and holding a book titled ''Cattle-logs'' with a cover that shows a cartoon log and a cow. Around the cow, add a cozy living room setting with a small side table holding a cup of tea and a lamp. In the background, a bookshelf contains other animal-themed books. The cow has a delighted expression as it reads. The overall style is colorful, lighthearted, and playful to emphasize the pun on ''cattle'' and ''catalogs.'' The focus is on the cow enjoying its reading, reinforcing the joke visually without any other characters or complicated elements.'),
 (1039, 'Absurd Humor, Farmers Humor, School', 'What do they call 100 John Deeres circling a McDonald''s in Iowa? Prom night.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a large group of exactly 100 green John Deere tractors forming a perfect circle around a bright, classic McDonald''s restaurant with its golden arches clearly visible. The setting is a small Iowa town with flat farmland visible in the background. The tractors are all similar, each with visible brand logos and big wheels, parked close together to form the ''circle.'' Inside the circle, a few teenagers dressed up for prom—wearing tuxedos and prom dresses—are standing awkwardly beside the diners or peeking outside. The setting is daytime with a simple blue sky, and the overall mood is light and comical, highlighting the contrast between farm equipment and a traditional high school event. The style should be cartoonish with exaggerated expressions on the teenagers’ faces showing surprise or embarrassment, and the tractors have a subtle, almost personified look to enhance humor.'),
 (1040, 'Puns, Word Play', 'What do you call a line of men waiting for a hair cut? A barber queue', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene of a barber shop exterior with a long line of men waiting patiently for their turn. The men should look similar but distinct in hairstyle and clothing to add variety, some with funny exaggerated hairdos like wild curly hair, bald spots, or comb-overs. The line stretches from the barber shop door, with a red and white barber pole spinning nearby. A small sign on the door reads "Barber Shop." One man at the front is sitting in the barber''s chair getting a haircut with scissors in the barber’s hand, smiling cheerfully. The overall mood is lighthearted and silly, emphasizing the play on words between "barber queue" and "barbecue." Use bright colors and simple, cartoonish lines to keep the image playful and inviting.'),
 (1041, 'Animals, Puns, Winter Humor', 'What do you call a snowman with a 6-pack? The abdominal snowman', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful snowman standing outdoors in a snowy winter setting. The snowman should have classic features: a carrot nose, coal eyes and buttons, a scarf, and a top hat. However, instead of a round belly, the midsection of the snowman clearly shows defined six-pack abs made of snow. The snowman poses proudly with its twig arms flexed, showing off its muscular ''abdominal'' area. Around the snowman, gentle snowflakes fall from the sky, and a few evergreen trees dusted with snow are in the background. The overall tone is light, playful, and funny, emphasizing the pun ''abdominal snowman.'' The art style should be cartoonish and exaggerated to highlight the joke without any aggressive or dark elements.'),
 (1042, 'Food Humor, Friends, Word Play', 'What do you call friends you go out to eat with? Taste buds', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing a lively group of friends sitting around a restaurant table, happily eating and laughing together. Each person should be depicted with a big, exaggerated smile and enjoying their food. On the table, include plates with various dishes like pizza, salad, and burgers to emphasize the eating scenario. Above them or nearby, floating with a slight glow, are several large, comical taste buds drawn as cute little characters with friendly faces and arms, mingling happily with the human friends like part of the group. The background should be a warm, cozy restaurant setting with light decorations and a few other diners in the background. The overall tone is cheerful and playful, with exaggerated, cartoonish expressions to highlight the joke’s pun on "taste buds" as both friends and literal taste buds on the tongue.'),
 (1043, 'Humor, Life, Relatable', 'What do you expect of a day that starts by getting out of bed?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene depicting a groggy person just waking up and reluctantly getting out of bed. The bedroom is a typical messy room with an unmade bed, a nightstand with a ringing alarm clock, and coffee mug on it. The person wears pajamas and slippers, rubbing their eyes with a tired, slightly annoyed expression. A calendar or wall clock shows early morning time. Around the character, subtle humorous details such as a sleepy, droopy-eyed pet (like a cat or dog) watching in sympathy, a slightly tilted picture frame, and an open window letting in bright sunlight exaggerate the idea of a difficult start to the day. The overall vibe is lighthearted and cartoonish, emphasizing the common experience of struggling with mornings that ''start by getting out of bed.'' The style should be colorful, exaggerated, and friendly, evoking relatable morning blues without negativity.'),
 (1044, 'Animals, Puns, Word Play', 'What do you get when you cross a bee and a sheep? A bah-humbug.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a quirky hybrid animal with the body of a fluffy white sheep, complete with wool, and the distinct yellow and black stripes of a bee. The creature has delicate bee wings fluttering on its back and large bee antennae on its head, but it’s standing on sheep-like legs. It is standing in a green meadow under a bright sunny sky with cartoon flowers around. The sheep-bee hybrid is making a grumpy or annoyed face, with a visible speech bubble above it that says ''Bah-humbug'' in a playful comic font. Nearby, a simple wooden signpost labeled ''Pun Meadow'' adds a lighthearted touch. The style should be colorful, clean, and charmingly exaggerated to emphasize the humor of the pun, with rounded shapes and friendly expressions typical of a children''s cartoon.'),
 (1045, 'Humor, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'What do you get when you cross a Mafia don with a deconstructionist?  Somebody who makes you an offer you can''t understand.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon featuring two main characters combining traits of a Mafia don and a deconstructionist philosopher. On one side, depict a classic Mafia don: a portly man wearing a pinstriped suit, fedora hat tilted, with a cigar in his mouth and a stern expression. On the other side, show an academic-looking man with glasses, messy hair, and holding a thick book labeled ''Deconstruction Theory.'' Between them, show a confused person scratching their head, wearing casual clothes, surrounded by question marks and speech bubbles with fragmented, complex words and confusing symbols. The setting should look like a dimly-lit office with a desk and an old-fashioned rotary phone. Include a large sign on the wall that says, ''An Offer You Can’t Understand'' in bold letters. The style should be lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated features to emphasize confusion and humor, avoiding any violent or threatening imagery.'),
 (1046, 'Animals, Humor, Word Play', 'What do you get when you cross a polar bear with a seal? A polar bear.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a snowy Arctic landscape under a bright, clear sky. In the center, a large polar bear is standing looking confused or puzzled. Next to it, a cute, smiling seal is lying on the ice. Between them, a comically simple ''crossed'' sign—a big plus symbol or an ''X''—is drawn, suggesting a mashup. The caption below reads: ''What do you get when you cross a polar bear with a seal? A polar bear.'' The style is lighthearted and playful with exaggerated expressions on the polar bear and seal, emphasizing the joke''s punchline that the result is just a polar bear anyway. Include small details like ice chunks, snow mounds, and maybe a few distant snowy mountains to set the Arctic scene creatively but simply.'),
 (1047, 'Animals, Puns, Winter Humor', 'What do you get when you cross a snowman and a shark? Frostbite!', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a large snowman with classic features: a carrot nose, coal eyes and buttons, stick arms, and a scarf. Above or next to the snowman, draw a friendly-looking shark wearing a winter hat and a scarf as well, swimming in icy blue water or snow. To illustrate the joke''s punchline ''Frostbite,'' show the snowman''s hand or one of its stick arms clearly bitten by the shark, but keep the expression comedic and light-hearted rather than scary—maybe the snowman looks surprised but amused. Include snowy landscape elements like snowflakes falling, a few snow-covered trees, and a chilly atmosphere with visible breath clouds to emphasize the cold. The tone should be bright, playful, and cartoonish to enhance the pun-based humor.'),
 (1048, 'Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'What does a house wear? Address', NULL, 'Draw a funny cartoon scene showing a simple house standing upright like a person. The house should have eyes and a smiling face on the front, making it look friendly and alive. Instead of clothes, it is wearing a big, colorful name tag or badge with the word ''Address'' clearly printed on it, hanging around its ''neck'' area like a necklace or lanyard. Around the house, include a few street signs or a mailbox to emphasize the idea of an address. The background should be a cute neighborhood with other houses but without characters or people to keep focus on the main house figure. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated features, like the house’s windows acting as eyes and a door as the mouth to add humor to the concept that a house ''wears'' an address like an outfit.'),
 (1049, 'Absurd Humor, Art Humor, Philosophy Humor', 'What garlic is to food, insanity is to art.', NULL, 'Draw a colorful, humorous cartoon scene split into two parts side-by-side. On the left, depict a steaming dish of food (like a pasta plate) with exaggerated, cartoonish garlic bulbs floating around it, emphasizing how essential garlic is to food. On the right, show a wild, eccentric artist in a messy art studio surrounded by crazy, surreal paintings, splashes of paint, and quirky art tools flying around. The artist looks delightfully ''insane'' or wildly inspired, with a playful expression and maybe wild hair. Include whimsical details like a paintbrush swirling through the air or a canvas with a bizarre image, to highlight the connection between insanity and art. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions, no harsh lines or serious tones.'),
 (1050, 'Animals, Farmers Humor, Puns', 'What happened to the cow that jumped over the barbed wire fence? Udder destruction.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a startled cow mid-jump over a rusty barbed wire fence. The cow has wide, expressive eyes and exaggerated motion lines to emphasize the jump. Its udder is visibly stretched or exaggerated to highlight the pun. Below or next to the fence, the ground is slightly disturbed to suggest impact or ''destruction.'' The background is a simple farm setting with a few tufts of grass and a blue sky with fluffy clouds. The overall tone is light-hearted, colorful, and comical, focusing on the pun ''udder destruction'' without any injury shown. The cow appears more surprised than hurt, emphasizing the joke rather than any real harm.'),
 (1051, 'Halloween, Humor, Puns', 'What happens if you don''t pay your exorcist? You get re-possessed', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set inside a spooky, slightly messy haunted house. In the center, a surprised person is halfway faded and ghostly, showing they are being ''re-possessed'' by a ghost or spirit. Nearby, an exorcist character with a cross necklace, holding a big unpaid invoice labeled ''Unpaid Bill'', looks annoyed but playful. Ghostly wisps swirl around the person and the exorcist. In the background, typical haunted house elements such as cobwebs, a creaky old chair, a flickering candle, and a hovering spirit add to the spooky, comical vibe. The style should be colorful and lighthearted, emphasizing the pun on ''re-possessed'' without being scary.'),
 (1052, 'Absurd Humor, Music Humor, Relatable', 'What happens when you play a Country & Western album backwards? Your spouse comes back, your pickup truck starts, you get out of jail and you sober up.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene centered around a vintage record player with a Country & Western album spinning backwards. Nearby, show a joyful person with a big smile reunited with their happy spouse who is arriving with open arms. Include a classic pickup truck with its headlights on and smoke coming from the exhaust, indicating it just started. In the background, add a simple jail cell door swinging open with cartoon hands waving goodbye. Also show the same person holding a clear water bottle or coffee cup, looking alert and refreshed to represent sobering up. The overall atmosphere is lighthearted and positive, using bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the absurdity of these unlikely good events happening simultaneously. Keep the style playful and cartoonish with clean lines and simple backgrounds so all elements stand out clearly as part of the joke''s visual punchline.'),
 (1053, 'Animals, Humor, Relatable', 'What if the dog only brings the ball back because he thinks I like throwing it?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in a park holding a tennis ball, with a dog sitting nearby looking slightly puzzled. The dog has a thought bubble that shows the dog thinking about the human happily throwing the ball, but with a question mark, as if wondering whether the human actually enjoys the game. The person looks excited and ready to throw the ball again. Include trees, a bench, and a frisbee on the grass to give a playful outdoor vibe. The style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the dog''s curiosity and the human''s joy.'),
 (1054, 'Food Humor, Puns', 'What is the opposite of LadyFingers? Mentos', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene featuring two anthropomorphized characters standing side by side. On the left, a tall, elegant ''Lady Finger'' biscuit character wears a fancy dress and a pearl necklace, smiling gently and waving a delicate hand. The biscuit should look long, slender, and golden brown, resembling the actual ladyfinger cookie. On the right, a pack of Mentos candies is personified as a cheerful, bubbly character with a big grin and shiny, round candy pieces visible through the clear pack. The Mentos character wears a playful hat or bowtie for added personality. Both characters stand on a simple flat surface with a softly colored background, possibly kitchen-themed or pastel-colored to emphasize playfulness. Above them, in a whimsical speech bubble or banner, the joke is written: ''What is the opposite of LadyFingers? Mentos.'' The tone is lighthearted and cute, with exaggerated, friendly expressions and soft outlines, perfectly suited for a cartoon comic panel or humorous greeting card style.'),
 (1055, 'Philosophy Humor, Science, Word Play', 'What is wanted is not the will-to-believe, but the wish-to-find-out,  which are exact opposites.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters in a cozy library or study room. One character is holding a bright light bulb above their head, representing the ''wish-to-find-out,'' with an eager and curious expression. They are surrounded by open books, magnifying glasses, and scientific tools like a microscope and test tubes. The other character stands opposite, with their arms crossed, wearing a thought bubble with a heart symbol inside it, symbolizing the ''will-to-believe'' and looking confidently stubborn. Between them floats a signpost with arrows pointing in opposite directions labeled ''Will-to-Believe'' and ''Wish-to-Find-Out.'' The background includes shelves filled with books and curious objects, such as a globe and a telescope, adding to the theme of inquiry versus belief. The style is light-hearted and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions to emphasize their opposing stances in a friendly, non-serious debate.'),
 (1056, 'Absurd Humor, Environmental Humor, Philosophy Humor', 'What philosophical question will replace ''If a tree falls in the forest...'' when all the forests have been cut down?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a completely barren landscape where a dense, lush forest once stood. In the foreground, a thoughtful-looking philosopher character with a beard and glasses, wearing a classic philosopher''s robe, strokes his chin while looking at a single, small tree stump. Above his head is a whimsical thought bubble with a question mark and a fading old tree falling sound effect. The background shows dull tree stumps, some with tiny sad faces, and distant hills with no trees at all. Near the philosopher, a sign reads ''Welcome to the Forest of the Future.'' The overall mood is lighthearted and ironic, emphasizing the missing forest while humorously pondering philosophy in a world without trees. The style should be simple, colorful, and exaggerated with clean lines typical of a cartoon strip, emphasizing expression and the irony of the scenario without any violence or negativity.'),
 (1057, 'Humor, Riddles, Word Play', 'What starts with E, ends with E, and has only one letter in it?  An envelope!', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing a large, friendly-looking envelope standing upright with a big smile and wide cartoon eyes. The envelope should have human-like arms and hands, one hand holding a small letter (a tiny paper with a visible letter symbol) prominently in front of it. Around the envelope, little animated letter symbols (like ''A'', ''B'', ''C'') float playfully. The background is simple and cheerful, like a light blue sky with a few white clouds. To the side, a puzzled cartoon character (person) scratches their head, looking at the envelope with a questioning expression. A speech bubble above the person says, "What starts with E, ends with E, and has only one letter in it?" while the envelope seems to be playfully presenting the answer. The overall tone is light, clean, and whimsical, suitable for all ages.'),
 (1058, 'Humor, Jobs', 'What was Bob the Builder called after he retired? Bob', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing an older man named Bob the Builder, wearing a faded yellow hard hat pushed back on his head and casual clothes instead of work gear. He is sitting comfortably on a porch rocking chair with a cup of tea or coffee in hand, smiling contentedly. Around him are retired worker items: a small toolbox closed and put aside, a pair of worn-out work boots beside the chair, and a calendar on the wall behind him marked ''Retired!''. The setting is a cozy home outdoors with a garden in the background. Above Bob’s head is a simple speech bubble that says, ''They just call me Bob now.'' The overall tone is lighthearted and ironic, emphasizing that after retirement, he no longer has a special job title—he''s simply Bob. The style is colorful, exaggerated, and cartoonish to enhance the joke’s simplicity and charm without any violent, sexual, or political elements.'),
 (1059, 'Halloween, Puns, School', 'What was the witch''s favorite subject in school? Spelling', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a friendly, classic witch sitting at a wooden school desk in a classroom. The witch is wearing a traditional tall pointy hat and has a big grin on her face. On the desk in front of her is an open book titled ''Spelling''. In the background, a chalkboard shows letters and words written neatly, with magical sparkles around the word ''Spelling''. Other students at desks (non-witch children or cartoon animals) look amused or curious. The classroom has whimsical Halloween-themed decorations like a small black cat perched on a shelf and a broomstick leaning against the wall. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with bright, cheerful colors emphasizing the pun on ''Spelling'' as both a school subject and magical spell casting.'),
 (1060, 'Humor, Life, Motivational', 'What you can be is more important than what you have been.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters in a cozy living room setting. On the left, a slightly scruffy but cheerful person is proudly looking forward, wearing casual, slightly mismatched clothes and holding a medal labeled ''Future Potential.'' On the right, a dusty old photo frame sits on a small table, featuring the same person but looking tired and worn out, wearing outdated clothes. Between them floats a large, glowing speech bubble stating, ''What you can be is more important than what you have been.'' The background includes a comfy armchair, a small bookshelf with a few quirky books, and a potted plant. The style is colorful and exaggerated with big eyes and expressive faces to highlight the hopeful, forward-looking humor of the message.'),
 (1061, 'Absurd Humor, Philosophy Humor, Word Play', 'What you cannot avoid, Welcome.', NULL, 'A lighthearted cartoon scene featuring a big, friendly anthropomorphic obstacle with a smiling face standing firmly in the middle of a busy street. The obstacle is shaped like a large, colorful roadblock or traffic cone with exaggerated eyes and a welcoming grin. Around it, cartoon people dressed in everyday clothes are humorously trying to walk past but are gently being stopped or guided by the obstacle. One person has a confused expression, another is shrugging, while a third is cheerfully waving at the obstacle. The background shows a sunny, cheerful urban setting with simple buildings and trees. A whimsical speech bubble emerges from the obstacle, saying, ''What you cannot avoid, Welcome.'' The overall style is bright and playful with bold outlines and exaggerated expressions to emphasize the humorous tone.'),
 (1062, 'Humor, Language, Philosophy Humor', 'What you''re saying is too vague to be inconsistent.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two characters having a conversation. One character, looking slightly confused and holding a speech bubble with vague, scribbled lines representing unclear speech, is saying something indistinct. The other character looks puzzled with a raised eyebrow and scratchs their head, responding with the line: ''What you''re saying is too vague to be inconsistent.'' The setting is a simple indoor room with a casual, friendly atmosphere, such as a couch or a coffee table between them. The style is light, playful, with exaggerated facial expressions emphasizing confusion and bemusement. The focus is on their interaction and the speech bubbles to convey the joke about vagueness and inconsistency in communication.'),
 (1063, 'Absurd Humor, Humor, Relatable', 'Whatever it is, I didn''t do it.', NULL, 'Create a humorous cartoon scene featuring a mischievous-looking character, who is an ordinary person — perhaps a child or a casually dressed adult — standing in the middle of a room that looks slightly chaotic. The room should have a few obvious signs of trouble: a broken vase on the floor, a spilled cup of juice, and a torn book on a table. The character has an innocent, wide-eyed expression and is shrugging their shoulders with palms up in a classic ''I didn''t do it'' pose. Around the character, perhaps a couple of other cartoon characters (like a parent or a pet) look on with skeptical or surprised expressions. The overall tone is light, playful, and non-threatening, emphasizing the humor in the denial despite obvious evidence. Use bright, simple colors and exaggerated expressions to enhance the comedic effect.'),
 (1064, 'Irony, Shopping Jokes', 'Whatever you spend a fortune on today will be on sale tomorrow.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a brightly colored, busy shopping mall. The main focus is a frustrated shopper standing in front of a large store window, looking at an expensive item like a flashy gadget or designer handbag with a price tag labeled ''Full Price $999''. The shopper has a comically exaggerated sad expression, scratching their head or holding their empty wallet. Behind them, a store employee cheerfully points to a big sign outside the store that says ''Sale Tomorrow! 50% OFF'' in bold, colorful letters with little stars and arrows. Add a calendar on the wall showing today''s date with an arrow pointing to tomorrow''s date, marked with a big red circle and a ''SALE'' sticker. Include some humorous small details like a confused pet dog dragging a shopping bag, or a price tag slipping off the item to emphasize the joke. The overall style should be playful and exaggerated with bright colors and clear, expressive characters to highlight the irony that what you buy expensive today drops in price just tomorrow.'),
 (1065, 'Board Games, Country Humor, Puns', 'What''s Canada''s favorite board game? Sorry', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a cheerful Canadian family sitting around a table playing the board game ''Sorry!''. The family members are wearing cozy winter clothing with visible maple leaf logos on sweaters or hats to emphasize Canadian identity. The board game ''Sorry!'' is sprawled out in the middle with colorful pawns and cards visible. One family member holds up a card that says ''Sorry!'' with a playful smile. In the background, a window shows a snowy landscape with a Canadian flag flying outside. The atmosphere is warm and friendly, highlighting the pun on ''Sorry'' being a common Canadian stereotype. Add lighthearted expressions and a cozy, inviting home environment with wooden furniture and a steaming mug of hot chocolate nearby.'),
 (1066, 'Humor, Language, Puns', 'What''s the difference between a cat and a complex sentence? A cat has claws at the end of its paws. A complex sentence has a pause at the end of its clause.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two side-by-side panels. In the left panel, a cute, slightly mischievous cartoon cat sits proudly with its tail curled around its paws. The cat''s paws show exaggerated, sharp, shiny claws extended. In the right panel, a giant book or paper scroll is open, labeled ''Complex Sentence.'' At the end of the sentence is a large, visible comma or semicolon, personified as a small pause symbol with sleepy eyes and a relaxed pose. Above the panels is a playful title that reads, ''What''s the difference between a cat and a complex sentence?'' The background should be light and simple, with soft colors and a friendly cartoon style. The focus is on the contrast between the physical claws of the cat and the punctuation mark representing the pause in the sentence, emphasizing the wordplay visually and humorously.'),
 (1067, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Word Play', 'What''s the difference between a hippo and a zippo? One is really heavy, and the other is a little lighter.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two main objects side by side on a simple white or light-colored background. On the left, draw a large, cute, and chubby hippopotamus with a friendly and slightly puzzled expression. It should be clearly heavy and bulky, sitting or standing solidly on the ground. On the right, illustrate a small, shiny Zippo-style lighter with the lid open and a small flame flickering. The lighter should look tiny compared to the hippo, emphasizing the size and weight difference. Between them, add a light-hearted caption or speech bubble with the joke text: ''What''s the difference between a hippo and a zippo? One is really heavy, and the other is a little lighter.'' Make the style bright and colorful with exaggerated, rounded cartoon features to enhance the playful mood.'),
 (1068, 'Objects Humor, Puns, Word Play', 'What''s the difference between a tuna, a piano, and a jar of glue? You can tuna piano, but you can''t piano a tuna (what about the glue?) I knew you''d get stuck there', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene split into three panels side by side. The first panel shows a cheerful person holding a large tuna fish, looking confused but trying to ''tune'' it with a giant old-fashioned piano tuning hammer. The second panel depicts the same person next to a grand piano, tuning the instrument with a smile, clearly focused and happy. The third panel shows the person staring perplexedly at a jar of glue on a table, scratching their head, with a small speech bubble containing a question mark. Around the jar are sticky notes or little cartoon squiggles showing the person ''stuck'' in thought. The background is simple and clean with light colors, emphasizing the playful confusion between the words and objects. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated typical cartoon, with expressive faces and clear labeling or signposts on each object to enhance clarity and humor.'),
 (1069, 'Animals, Food Humor, Puns', 'What''s the difference between deer nuts and beer nuts? Beer nuts are $1.49 and deer nuts are under a buck.', NULL, 'A colorful and humorous cartoon scene split into two halves side-by-side. On the left side, depict a cheerful deer standing casually in a forest clearing, with a small pile of cartoonish acorns or nuts labeled ''Deer Nuts'' on the ground next to it. A small price tag attached to the nuts clearly shows ''Under $1''. The deer should have a humorous smile, giving a playful vibe. On the right side, show a bright, eye-catching grocery store shelf stocked with a can or bowl of classic crunchy peanuts labeled ''Beer Nuts,'' with a clear price tag showing ''$1.49''. The scene should emphasize the contrast between the natural setting and the grocery store aisle, with clear and exaggerated price tags to highlight the pun. Keep the art style light, simple, and cartoonish, with friendly characters and bold text for the labels and prices. No people are required, just the deer and the grocery item as main subjects.'),
 (1070, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'What''s the difference between ignorance and apathy? I don''t know and I don''t care', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters standing side by side. The first character looks confused, scratching their head with a questioning expression, symbolizing ''ignorance.'' The second character stands next to them, arms crossed and wearing a bored or indifferent face, symbolizing ''apathy.'' Above their heads is a simple caption with the joke text: ''What''s the difference between ignorance and apathy? I don''t know and I don''t care.'' The background is plain or minimal to keep focus on the characters and the text. The style is bright, colorful, and exaggerated with cartoonish facial expressions for clear humor, avoiding any harsh lines or details. The characters can be casually dressed and set in a neutral indoor or outdoor environment, such as a park bench or sidewalk, emphasizing the universal nature of the joke.'),
 (1071, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'What''s the difference between snowmen and snowwomen? Snow balls', NULL, 'A cheerful, colorful cartoon scene showing two snowmen and two snowwomen standing side by side in a snowy landscape with pine trees and a bright blue sky. The snowmen have traditional features like carrot noses, coal eyes and buttons, and stick arms. The snowwomen are similarly styled but with cute winter accessories like scarves and earmuffs. In front of the snowmen, the artist should draw two large shiny snowballs (round snow spheres) clearly labeled or emphasized humorously. The snowwomen have no snowballs visible to show the joke''s punchline visually. The characters have friendly, smiling faces, and the overall art style is lighthearted and playful but clearly cartoonish and easily recognizable. Include some snowflakes falling gently around them to enhance the winter vibe. No backgrounds or elements that imply anything violent, sexual, or political.'),
 (1072, 'Humor, Word Play', 'What''s the least spoken language in the world? Sign language', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two characters standing side by side in a simple park-like setting with a few trees and a bench. One character is speaking excitedly with a speech bubble containing question marks, representing the question, ''What''s the least spoken language in the world?'' The other character is responding with a large smile and hands raised mid-sign, clearly using sign language. Above them, a floating thought bubble shows a comical depiction of the word ''SILENCE'' in big letters with little ''sound waves'' fading away to emphasize that sign language isn''t spoken aloud. The characters should be drawn with exaggerated expressions to emphasize the joke: the first character looks curious and puzzled, while the second is confident and cheerful. The art style should be colorful, simple, and playful, with bold lines, suited for a lighthearted cartoon comic strip. No violent, sexual, or political elements. Background details minimal but enough to suggest a casual everyday environment.'),
 (1073, 'Humor, Word Play', 'What''s the number one rule of vegan fight club? Tell everybody', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a group of quirky animals and a few humans gathered together in a lighthearted ''fight club'' setting. There is a big banner overhead that reads ''Vegan Fight Club.'' The characters include a friendly cow, a carrot with boxing gloves, a lettuce leaf, a tofu block with a headband, and a few smiling humans in workout clothes. Everyone is standing around chatting and laughing in a bright, cheerful gym or community hall with mats on the floor. In the center, a person with a megaphone is enthusiastically announcing, "Remember: Rule number one – tell everybody!" The overall mood is playful and ironic, capturing the idea that vegan fight club is about outspoken openness instead of secrecy. The style is colorful, exaggerated, and cartoonish with expressive faces and body language that emphasize humor and approachability.'),
 (1074, 'Humor, Word Play', 'What''s the tallest building in the world? The library - it has the most stories.', NULL, 'A colorful, humorous cartoon scene showing a very tall building shaped like a classic library: large, with big windows and a sign that says ''Library'' at the top. The building has multiple visible floors stacked high, each floor is represented as an open book shelf lined with oversized books labeled as ''Story 1'', ''Story 2'', etc. Sitting on top of the building is a cheerful librarian character holding an oversized book and waving. The sky is bright and clear with a few light, fluffy clouds. Nearby, a few small, modern skyscrapers look up in amazement, looking tiny compared to the towering library. Include a playful banner or caption at the bottom that says, ''The tallest building – it has the most stories!'' The overall tone should be lighthearted and whimsical, in a bright cartoon style with exaggerated proportions and expressive characters.'),
 (1075, 'History Humor, School, Word Play', 'What''s the worst thing about ancient history class? The teachers tend to Babylon.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a colorful ancient history classroom. The classroom has stone walls decorated with hieroglyphics and ancient artifacts like a small pyramid, a clay pot, and scrolls on shelves. Several students with exaggerated, confused expressions sit at desks looking at an animated teacher who is dressed like an ancient Babylonian with a typical beard, a striped robe, and a tall, tiered hat. The teacher is shown yawning widely, leaning back in his chair, clearly bored or sleepy. Behind him, a chalkboard or stone tablet displays the phrase ''Babylon'' with doodles of zzz''s floating above to emphasize his boredom or tendency to nod off. The scene should have bright and cheerful colors with slightly exaggerated cartoonish proportions to enhance the humor without any violence or politics. Include speech bubbles or cartoon-style text showing the pun: ''Teachers tend to Babylon,'' to highlight the joke visually in the scene.'),
 (1076, 'Absurd Humor, Puns', 'What''s worse than a box full of snakes? A box that''s SUPPOSED to be full of snakes', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two large, open boxes placed side by side on a wooden table. The first box is overflowing with cartoonish, colorful snakes that look lively and slightly mischievous, with some slithering out of the box. The second box is also open but completely empty, with a big label on it reading ''Snakes Inside'' in bold letters. A confused character, drawn in a funny, exaggerated style—maybe a person with wide eyes and scratching their head—stands between the two boxes, clearly puzzled and disappointed that the box supposed to have snakes contains nothing. The background is simple, maybe a backyard or a warehouse setting, keeping focus on the boxes and the character. The overall style is light and playful with bright colors and expressive faces to emphasize the joke’s irony.'),
 (1077, 'Absurd Humor, Humor, Social Commentary', 'When a bunch of bizarre people get together, how do you think we appear to them, if at all?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing two groups of quirky, eccentric-looking people facing each other. On one side, a group of very strange, oddball characters with exaggerated features (wild hairstyles, mismatched clothes, silly expressions) looking puzzled and whispering among themselves. On the other side, another distinct group of equally bizarre and colorful characters mirroring their confusion and curiosity. Between them, a translucent, ghostly outline representing how they might see each other—faint, blurry, and hard to distinguish, as if they barely perceive one another clearly or at all. The background is simple and bright, with exaggerated facial expressions of confusion and curiosity to enhance the comic effect. Include humorous elements like question marks or thought bubbles above their heads to emphasize their mutual bewilderment and the theme of mutual perception.'),
 (1078, 'Absurd Humor, Animals, Food Humor', 'When a cat is dropped, it always lands on its feet, and when toast is dropped, it always lands with the buttered side facing down.  I propose to strap buttered toast to the back of a cat; the two will hover, spinning inches above the ground.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a fluffy cat mid-air, with a slice of buttered toast strapped comically to its back using a loose, quirky strap or harness. The cat''s body is slightly tilted, feet splayed as if trying to land, while the toast is oriented butter-side down. The background is simple, with a few motion lines to suggest the cat-toast combination is hovering and spinning just above a living room floor. Nearby, a surprised person with wide eyes and an open mouth watches the hovering cat-toast contraption. Include small humor details like a tipped-over butter dish or a clock on the wall showing the humorous moment, keeping the colors bright and the style lighthearted and cartoonish without any violence or distress.'),
 (1079, 'Absurd Humor, Cartoon, Technology Humor', 'When a computer has the desire to travel somewhere by itself, we''re going to be in trouble.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person sitting at a desk with a desktop computer that has anthropomorphic features: a happy, determined expression on its screen with cartoon eyes and a small mouth. The computer has little arms and legs, is standing up, and holding a suitcase and a travel map, ready to leave. Around the computer are typical office items like a keyboard, mouse, papers, and a coffee mug. The person looks surprised and worried, leaning back slightly in their chair. The setting is a simple, colorful home office with a window showing a sunny day outside. The vibe is light-hearted and comedic, emphasizing the absurd idea of a computer wanting to travel by itself.'),
 (1080, 'Animals, Humor, Science', 'When a male fish is ready to spawn, it blows bubbles.', NULL, 'A colorful underwater cartoon scene featuring a cheerful male fish puffing out a big bubble from its mouth. The fish should have exaggerated, expressive eyes looking proud and maybe a little shy. Around the fish, include smaller bubbles rising upwards to emphasize the blowing action. Add some seaweed, coral, and a couple of curious smaller fish watching the bubble-blowing fish in amusement or surprise. Keep the style lighthearted and humorous, with bright colors and rounded shapes, capturing a friendly ocean environment without any threatening or scary elements.'),
 (1081, 'Humor, Math Humor, School', 'When aiming for the common denominator, be prepared for the occasional division by zero.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a classroom or math lecture hall. At the front, a friendly-looking teacher stands next to a large blackboard filled with mathematical symbols and equations. The teacher is pointing at an equation labeled ''common denominator'' that humorously shows a fraction with a denominator of zero, causing a big, comical ''ERROR'' or ''DIVISION BY ZERO'' sign to flash above it. The teacher has a slightly surprised or worried expression, scratching their head. In the foreground, a few students sit at desks with puzzled or amused faces, some raising their eyebrows or whispering to each other. The classroom has typical school elements like desks, chairs, and a clock on the wall. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the math joke in a cartoon style with exaggerated expressions and clean, simple lines, avoiding any negativity or complexity.'),
 (1082, 'Random', 'When all other means of communication fail, try words.', NULL, 'Cartoon scene: a small chaotic rooftop or park clearing where every nonverbal method of communication has hilariously failed. Center foreground: a calm, slightly exasperated person holding a giant, literal white speech bubble sign that reads in bold block letters: “WORDS.” Their posture is triumphant but sheepish. Around them in a semi-circle are other characters, each showing a failed attempt:- Left: someone waving two semaphore flags frantically while a confused pigeon sits on their head, holding a tiny “Nope” sign.- Next: a person with a smoking campfire sending “smoke signals” — puffs form question marks and one tiny cloud shaped like a phone with an “X.”- Center-left: a broken megaphone cracked open with cartoonish sparking, a smartphone with a gigantic red “NO SIGNAL” bubble.- Center-right: a person trying elaborate sign language, but the listener has tangled headphones and a puzzled face.- Far right: someone tapping Morse code on a tin can, with musical notes turning into squiggly lines.Background: simple city skyline or park, bright colors, exaggerated expressions (confusion, frustration, relief). Add small caption banner at top: “When all other means fail…” Humorous, clean, friendly cartoon style.'),
 (1083, 'Absurd Humor, Puns, Workplace', 'When companies ship styrofoam, what do they pack it in?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a shipping warehouse with a puzzled-looking cartoon box character standing beside a giant shipping crate. The crate is humorously overflowing with white, puffy, cloud-like pieces of styrofoam shaped like tiny boxes, with some pieces stacked haphazardly inside and some floating outside the crate as if they were being packed. The box character has wide eyes and a comical expression of confusion. In the background, there’s a simple conveyor belt with various packaging materials (bubble wrap, tape rolls, cardboard boxes), emphasizing the shipping context. The scene has bright, cheerful colors and exaggerated facial expressions to keep the mood light and funny. The overall vibe is playful and cartoonish, focusing on the funny paradox of styrofoam needing packaging itself.'),
 (1084, 'Good Question!, Humor, Pop Culture', 'When confronted by a seemingly difficult problem, it is easier solved by reducing it to the question ''How would the Lone Ranger have handled this?''', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a frustrated person sitting at a cluttered desk filled with papers, books, and a complicated-looking problem on a whiteboard behind them. The person scratches their head thoughtfully while imagining a heroic figure dressed as the Lone Ranger, complete with a white cowboy hat, mask, bandana, and horseback, confidently tipping his hat and holding a clever solution note or tool. The background has subtle details like a clock, a coffee mug, and a small toy horse on the desk. The style is lighthearted and exaggerated, with bright colors and expressive faces emphasizing the contrast between the overwhelmed problem-solver and the calm, confident Lone Ranger inspiration floating in a thought bubble above.'),
 (1085, 'Humor, Life, Relatable, Steven Wright', 'When everything is coming your way, you''re in the wrong lane.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon of a car on a two-lane road. The car is in the left lane, and multiple objects are flying or rolling directly toward the car from behind and ahead: a flying football, a rolling tire, a bouncing basketball, a dropped ice cream cone, and a paper airplane. The driver looks surprised and confused. On the right lane, another car calmly drives forward with no objects coming its way. The setting is a bright, simple countryside road with clear lane markings. The scene conveys the idea of ''everything coming your way'' but showing that the driver is in the wrong lane by visualizing all kinds of things headed toward them in traffic. The overall style should be lighthearted, colorful, and cartoonish with exaggerated expressions and motion lines to show the incoming objects.'),
 (1086, 'Humor, Irony, Life', 'When faced with a crisis, take the inevitable and turn it around to make it look like a conscious decision.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person in the middle of a chaotic situation, such as a small room where something clearly went wrong (like a spilled cup of coffee, papers flying everywhere, or a broken object). The person stands confidently and proudly holding a large sign or a speech bubble saying, ''I totally meant for this to happen!'' Their expression is smug and calm, as if they have a clever plan. Around them, friends or colleagues look surprised or confused, glancing at the mess but unsure whether the person’s explanation is true. The style is light-hearted and exaggerated, with bright colors and rounded shapes to emphasize the humor and avoid any serious or negative tone.'),
 (1087, 'Absurd Humor, Food Humor, Puns', 'When Heinz ketchup leaves the bottle, it travels at a rate of 25 miles per year.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a nearly empty bottle of Heinz ketchup on a kitchen table. From the small opening at the bottle''s top, a thin, slow-moving red ketchup ''road'' or ''trail'' extends outward. Along this trail, small cartoon-style speed indicators appear, like a tiny road sign that reads "25 mph" but corrected humorously to "25 miles per year" in big, playful lettering. Nearby, an amused cartoon character with glasses and a measuring tape or stopwatch is observing the ketchup trail as if timing the slow movement. The background is a simple kitchen setting with a plate, fork, and other condiment bottles, emphasizing the slow drip of ketchup in a lighthearted and exaggerated way. The overall tone is gentle and funny, highlighting the joke about how slowly ketchup actually comes out of the bottle.'),
 (1088, 'Humor, Life, Relatable', 'When I am right nobody remembers... When I am wrong nobody forgets!', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in the middle with two thought bubbles above their head. One thought bubble to the left shows the person confidently giving a correct answer, but people around them are uninterested or distracted, looking away or checking their phones. The other thought bubble to the right shows the same person looking embarrassed or regretful after making a mistake, while a crowd around him points fingers, laughs, or holds up signs that say ''Never Forget!'' and ''Oops!''. The background is a simple setting like a park or office to keep focus on the characters. The person should be drawn in a lighthearted and relatable way, with exaggerated facial expressions for humor. Include diverse people in the crowd to represent bystanders. The style should be bright, colorful, and typical of friendly cartoon humor, without any harshness or negativity.'),
 (1089, 'Direction Jokes, Humor, Relatable', 'When I ask for directions, please don''t use words like ''east.''', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set outdoors at a road intersection or a simple street corner. Show a confused-looking person, maybe holding a map upside down, standing next to a quirky, overly enthusiastic local giving directions. The local should be animatedly pointing in a general direction with one hand while holding a compass labeled with cardinal points (N, E, S, W) in the other hand. Surround them with simple street signs, one labeled ''East'' prominently, to highlight the confusion. The confused person could have a thought bubble with symbols like question marks and arrows going in all directions. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, with exaggerated facial expressions to emphasize confusion and frustration, without any harsh or negative imagery.'),
 (1090, 'Humor, Relatable, Workplace', 'When I look around at all the turmoil and strife, the power struggles and wars and injustice, I can''t help but think ...  Why do I keep working here?', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon office scene with a stressed-out employee sitting at a cluttered desk covered in paperwork, a computer, and a coffee mug. Around them, depict subtle chaotic elements symbolizing turmoil: coworkers arguing in the background, a bulletin board with pinned headlines like ''Power Struggles,'' ''Wars,'' and ''Injustice.'' Include a clock on the wall showing late hours and an overflowing trash bin to emphasize workplace overwhelm. The employee should have a weary, puzzled expression, scratching their head, clearly questioning why they remain in this hectic environment. The style should be playful and exaggerated, with bright colors and expressive facial features to enhance the comic tone without any violence or harshness.'),
 (1091, 'Humor, Relatable, Time Humor', 'When I say, ''The other day'', I could be referring to any time between yesterday and 15 years ago.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing with a confused and slightly exaggerated pondering expression, holding a calendar in one hand and pointing to an imaginary timeline with the other. The timeline above their head stretches from a date labeled ''Yesterday'' on the left, gradually extending all the way to ''15 Years Ago'' on the right, marked with playful icons like a smartphone for recent times and floppy disks for the past. Around the person, small thought bubbles contain small, funny memories or objects scattered along the timeline to emphasize the wide range of possible times ''the other day'' could refer to. The background is simple and colorful, with clock faces and calendar pages swirling humorously to highlight the confusion about time. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish with exaggerated features and lively expressions to convey the joke visually without any violence, politics, or adult themes.'),
 (1092, 'Humor, Word Play', 'When I''m around Hispanics, I say ''Mucho'' all the time - it means a lot to them.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a smiling person standing in the center, casually chatting with a diverse group of friendly Hispanic people around them. The person is cheerfully saying the word ''Mucho'', with comic-style speech bubbles showing this word repeatedly. The Hispanic group looks amused and pleased, with warm, friendly expressions. The background is simple and colorful, perhaps with festive decorations like colorful papel picado banners to subtly hint at a Hispanic cultural setting. Include subtle visual cues such as a taco stand or maracas nearby to set the tone without stereotypes. The overall style is lighthearted and exaggerated, with clear, bold lines and bright colors to emphasize the fun and wordplay of the joke, avoiding any caricature or offense.'),
 (1093, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'When I''m not in my right mind, my left mind gets pretty crowded.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a human brain split into two sides labeled ''Right Mind'' and ''Left Mind.'' The ''Right Mind'' side is empty or very sparse, looking calm and quiet. The ''Left Mind'' side is overcrowded with little cartoon characters or tiny people pushing and shoving, trying to fit in, with some comically squeezed into small spaces. The brain has a friendly face with raised eyebrows, looking slightly overwhelmed but amused. The background is simple and colorful, emphasizing the contrast between the empty and crowded sides. Add visual elements like small thought bubbles or symbols (like lightbulbs or question marks) above the left side to show busy thinking. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, drawn in a bright, friendly cartoon style suitable for all ages.'),
 (1094, 'Absurd Humor, Pun, Relatable', 'When one door closes and another door opens, you are probably in prison.', NULL, 'A cartoon-style prison hallway featuring two large metal doors. One door is shown closing with a heavy slam, complete with motion lines and a ''clang'' sound effect. Another identical door nearby is ajar, slightly open with a bright light shining through, suggesting entrance or exit. Inside the hallway, a confused prisoner wearing classic striped prison clothes and a ball-and-chain attached to his ankle looks back and forth between the doors with a puzzled expression. The walls are plain and gray, with a small barred window casting shadows. A simple bench and a water fountain near the closed door add to the setting. The overall style should be humorous and lighthearted, with exaggerated facial expressions and clean, bold lines typical of comic strips.'),
 (1095, 'Animals, Humor, Nature Humor', 'When opossums are playing ''possum, they are not ''playing.''  They actually pass out from sheer terror.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene showing two opossums in a forest setting. One opossum is standing upright with wide, scared eyes and sweat drops flying off its head to indicate terror. The other opossum is lying on the ground with eyes closed, limp body, and tongue sticking out slightly, mimicking ''playing possum'' (pretending to be dead). Include a few trees, bushes, and maybe an annoyed squirrel or bird watching the scene, looking confused or unimpressed. Use exaggerated facial expressions for humor and make the overall tone lighthearted and playful. Bright colors and simple cartoon style recommended to emphasize the comedic effect of the opossums'' misunderstanding of “playing possum.” Avoid any violent or dark elements.'),
 (1096, 'Bad Puns, Humor, Word Play', 'When puns are outlawed, only outlaws will be punished.', NULL, 'Draw a playful cartoon scene set in a Wild West style town with a humorous twist. In the foreground, show two exaggeratedly outlawish characters wearing classic cowboy hats, boots, and bandanas over their faces. One outlaw is holding a large scroll that says ''Pun Laws'' with a red seal that reads ''Outlawed!''. Another character, a sheriff with a comically large badge labeled ''Pun Enforcement'', looks serious but confused, holding a giant mallet labeled ''Punisher''. Around them, a few amused townsfolk peek from behind buildings, some snickering or covering their mouths, clearly enjoying the pun chaos. Add a wooden signpost in the background saying ''Welcome to Punville'' with a bullet hole, and a wanted poster on a wall that features a smiling face with ''Wanted for Puns''. The overall style should be bright, colorful, and exaggerated, emphasizing the pun-themed humor without any violence, just a lighthearted comic setting.'),
 (1097, 'Humor, Relatable', 'When someone asks what I did over the weekend, I squint and ask, ''Why, what did you hear?''', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring a person standing casually in a living room setting. The character has a playful, mischievous smile and is slightly squinting their eyes as if suspicious or teasing. Their body language should convey a sense of slyness, with one eyebrow raised and a slight lean forward. Include a thought bubble with a stylized ear or sound waves emerging to hint at overhearing gossip. Surround the character with subtle weekend-related items like a couch, a coffee mug, maybe a weekend newspaper or a TV remote nearby to set the casual weekend vibe. The colors should be bright and cheerful to match the lighthearted tone of the joke. Avoid complex backgrounds; keep the focus on the character''s facial expression and gesture conveying their funny, cheeky response to the question, ''What did you hear?''.'),
 (1098, 'Humor, Relatable', 'When someone says, ''That''s a good question'', you can bet that the question will be better than the answer.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene set in a casual office or classroom. In the foreground, a confident person is raising their hand with a big smile and a speech bubble that says, ''That''s a good question!'' Behind a desk, a teacher or presenter looks slightly nervous or puzzled, scratching their head as if unsure how to answer. Around them, several cartoon thought bubbles show exaggerated, complex questions with question marks, while the answer bubble from the presenter is small, simple, and unimpressive. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with bright colors and exaggerated expressions to emphasize that while the question is exciting, the answer disappoints in comparison. Include typical office or classroom items like a whiteboard, papers, and a water cooler in the background for context, and make the characters cartoonish with rounded features and expressive faces to heighten the humor without any harshness or negativity.'),
 (1099, 'Absurd Humor, Animals, Word Play', 'When the chips are down, the buffalo is empty.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a large buffalo standing next to a bowl or small basket labeled ''Chips.'' The chips bowl is completely empty. The buffalo looks puzzled or slightly sad, as if surprised by the empty chips bowl. The setting is simple, with a plain background and maybe a small picnic table holding the chips bowl beside the buffalo. The buffalo should have exaggerated features - big eyes and a gentle, friendly expression to add to the humor. Include scattered poker chips or snack chips around to imply ''chips'' in both senses, and a small sign or thought bubble near the buffalo that hints at confusion or disappointment. The style is colorful, fun, and cartoonish without any harsh lines or dark tones.'),
 (1100, 'Puns, Relatable, Technology Humor', 'When the inventor of USB dies, they''re going to lower him into the grave, raise him up, turn him over, then put him back in.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene of a graveyard with a tombstone labeled ''Inventor of USB.'' A group of funny-looking cartoon gravediggers (wearing simple hats and gloves) are lowering a coffin into the grave with ropes and pulleys. Next to the grave, the same gravediggers are shown lifting the coffin back up slightly, turning it 180 degrees in the air (with a comical exaggerated turning motion), and then carefully placing it back down. One gravedigger is scratching his head in confusion, while another holds a USB drive and points at the coffin as if explaining something. The sky is bright and clear with a few fluffy clouds, and there are some flowers and small bushes around the grave. The overall style is colorful, playful, and cartoonish, emphasizing the absurdity of the repeated raising, turning, and re-lowering of the coffin, mimicking the well-known fussiness of USB plugs needing to be turned before plugging in properly.'),
 (1101, 'Humor, Puns', 'When the missionaries visited the tribe of cannibals, they got their first taste of religion', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a group of friendly missionaries visiting a tribe of cannibals in a tropical jungle clearing. The missionaries, dressed in typical explorer or missionary clothing with hats and backpacks, appear nervous but polite. Nearby, a tribal chief and several tribe members with traditional colorful attire and feathered headdresses look at them curiously. The focus is on a large cooking pot over a fire, with a cartoonish speech bubble from the chief saying, ''Here, try the religion!'' Inside the pot, instead of anything scary, there are floating symbolic religious items like a small cross, a Bible, and a pair of glasses, humorously implying the ''taste of religion.'' The background includes palm trees, jungle plants, and a bright blue sky. The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, with exaggerated expressions on all characters to emphasize the joke''s pun on ''taste of religion.'''),
 (1102, 'Humor, Relatable, Word Play', 'When there''s a will, I want to be in it.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a cheerful person holding a legal document titled ''Last Will and Testament.'' The person is smiling broadly and pointing at the document. Nearby, a group of people—family members or friends—look surprised or confused. In the background, a judge or lawyer sits at a desk, looking amused. The setting is a bright, simple office with a few plants and framed certificates on the walls. A playful sign on the wall reads ''Estate Planning Made Fun!'' The overall style is colorful and cartoonish, emphasizing the pun on the word ''will'' with lighthearted expressions and exaggerated features without any dark or morbid elements.'),
 (1103, 'Humor, Relatable', 'When you ask me what I am doing today, and I say ''nothing,'' it does not mean I am free. It means I am doing nothing.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person lounging comfortably on a couch at home, wearing casual clothes like sweatpants and a t-shirt. The person has a relaxed, slightly guilty expression while scrolling on a phone or tablet. Around them are items that suggest laziness rather than availability: a messy stack of unopened mail, a coffee cup with steam rising, a half-eaten snack, and a clock on the wall indicating early afternoon. The speech bubble above the person says, "I''m doing nothing," while a nearby phone shows an incoming call or message asking, "Are you free today?" The overall style is lighthearted and playful, emphasizing the idea that doing "nothing" is an activity in itself. The background is a simple living room setting with a plant on a small table and a window letting in daylight.'),
 (1104, 'Absurd Humor, Nature Humor, Workplace', 'When you''re up to your hips in alligators, you forget the original project was to drain the swamp.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene set in a swamp with murky water up to a man''s hips. The man looks overwhelmed and frazzled, half-submerged among a comically large number of friendly-looking alligators that surround him, some poking their heads out of the water near his arms and legs. The man wears casual outdoor clothing—shorts and a shirt—stained with mud, holding a simple, dripping bucket labeled ''Swamp Drain Project'' loosely in one hand, forgotten. In the background, the swamp is dense with exaggerated reeds, cattails, and a funny sign stuck in the mud that reads ''Drain the Swamp!'' The overall tone is light and silly, with exaggerated expressions on the man and cartoonish, slightly goofy alligators to emphasize the man''s distraction and predicament. Bright colors and clear lines define the characters and setting in a playful style suitable for family-friendly cartoons.'),
 (1105, 'Irony, Marriage Humor, Relationship Humor', 'Whenever you meet a man who would make a good husband, you will usually find that he does already.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two women standing at a party or social gathering. One woman is whispering or talking to the other with a knowing smile, while the other woman looks surprised or thoughtfully nodding. In the background, show a few men mingling; one man stands out, depicted as a charming, well-dressed gentleman with a wedding ring clearly visible on his finger. The setting should be bright and cheerful with typical party decorations like balloons or streamers. Emphasize the irony with a subtle visual cue: a small thought bubble from the surprised woman imagining a single man looking lonely or out of place. The style should be lighthearted and playful, using exaggerated facial expressions for comedic effect, with no violent or sensitive content.'),
 (1106, 'Humor, Lawyer Humor, Word Play', 'Where there''s a will, there''s a probate.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a cluttered lawyer''s office. On the left, an elderly person with a mischievous smile is signing a large, official-looking document labeled ''Last Will and Testament.'' On the right, a stern-looking probate judge in robes is holding a big rubber stamp with the word ''PROBATE'' on it, ready to stamp another document. In the center, a long scroll-like paper flows from the will to the judge''s desk, visually connecting the two characters, symbolizing the legal process. The office is filled with law books, a gavel on the desk, a clock showing late afternoon, and a potted plant with droopy leaves to add humor. Both characters have exaggerated, cartoonish expressions to emphasize the joke’s play on words. The background wall features a framed diploma and a humorous motivational poster saying "Where there''s a will, there''s a probate." The overall tone is lighthearted and playful, suitable for a legal pun without any dark or serious undertones.'),
 (1107, 'Philosophy Humor, Quotes, Relatable', 'Wherever you go, there you are.', NULL, 'A simple, humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in the middle of a small town square or park. The person looks mildly confused but calm. Around the person, on signposts, walls, and shop windows, there are identical directional signs or sticky notes all stating ''You Are Here.'' The background includes a few buildings, trees, and a bench. The character is scratching their head in a funny way as if realizing no matter where they move, the signs keep pointing to ''You Are Here.'' The mood is light-hearted and whimsical, with bright colors and exaggerated cartoon expressions highlighting the irony of the phrase.'),
 (1108, 'Animals, Bad Puns, Food Humor', 'Which day do chickens hate the most? Friday', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring a group of chickens standing in a farmyard. The central chicken has an exaggeratedly annoyed or frustrated expression, possibly crossing its wings or shaking its feathers in displeasure. Around them, a colorful calendar is prominently displayed, with the day ''Friday'' circled or marked in bright red, emphasizing its significance. Other days on the calendar are visible but less emphasized. The background includes a classic red barn, green grass, a few haystacks, and a bright blue sky with a smiling sun to enhance the cheerful yet funny mood. The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with bold lines and bright colors typical of cartoons, making the chicken''s dislike for Friday clear and funny without any hostility or negativity.'),
 (1109, 'Humor, Puns', 'Which is the non-smoking lifeboat?', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a lifeboat floating on calm seas near a large ship. The lifeboat is labeled clearly, and next to it stands a cheerful anthropomorphic cigarette with a sad or disappointed face, looking at the lifeboat. The lifeboat itself is wearing a big no-smoking sign (a cigarette crossed out) on its side. In the background, a few seagulls fly with speech bubbles, one pointing to the lifeboat and announcing, “This one doesn’t smoke!” The overall style is lighthearted and playful, with bright, vivid colors and exaggerated, friendly character designs for the cigarette and lifeboat. The scene should feel like a classic cartoon, with expressive faces and simple ocean waves underneath.'),
 (1110, 'Humor, Irony, Life', 'While money can''t buy happiness, it certainly lets you choose your own form of misery.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing a person standing in front of a large display board titled ''Choose Your Misery.'' The board is divided into sections, each labeled with different types of typical stressful situations or problems, such as ''Work Stress,'' ''Health Issues,'' ''Relationship Drama,'' ''Bills & Expenses,'' and ''Traffic Jam.'' The person is holding a big bag of money and looking thoughtfully at the options, with a slight smirk on their face. Around the character, little symbolic icons represent each misery type—like a dripping faucet for bills, a ringing phone for work stress, a broken heart for relationships, a traffic cone for traffic jams, and a pill bottle for health issues. The background is bright and cartoonish, with exaggerated expressions on the person’s face to emphasize the ironic twist of having money only to pick the kind of unhappiness they want. The scene should evoke a lighthearted, ironic feel without being dark or gloomy.'),
 (1111, 'Humor, Relatable, Science', 'Who me? I just wander from room to room. It might look like I am doing nothing, but at a cellular level I am quite busy.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene inside a cozy, slightly messy home showing a person casually wandering from one room to another with a nonchalant expression. The person is depicted in mid-step between a living room and a kitchen, wearing comfortable clothes and slippers. Around them, several rooms are visible through open doorways. To visualize the ''cellular activity,'' the person''s body is semi-transparent, revealing a colorful, exaggerated cartoon view of busy, animated cells inside—some running on tiny treadmills, others lifting weights, and a few using computers. The cells have happy, determined faces, emphasizing their ''busyness.'' The background is lighthearted and warm, with simple furniture like a couch, a small table with a cup of coffee, and a few houseplants. No violent, sexual, or political elements are included, and the style is bright, simple, and playful to bring out the contrast between external stillness and internal energy.'),
 (1112, 'Humor, Relatable, Workplace', 'Whoever decided beards are unprofessional probably couldn''t grow one.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene featuring two men in a simple office setting. On the left, a clean-shaven man dressed in a suit and tie looks somewhat uncomfortable or annoyed, holding a clipboard labeled ''Professionalism Standards.'' On the right, a confident man with a thick, well-groomed beard wearing casual office attire (a button-up shirt and jeans) leans back in his chair with a smug smile. Behind them is a whiteboard showing a checklist with ''Beard = Unprofessional?'' with a big red X next to it. The background includes typical office elements like a desk with a computer, a coffee mug that has a small beard logo, and a potted plant. The overall style is lighthearted and cartoonish, emphasizing the contrast between the two men’s appearances and attitudes about beards in a professional environment. The expressions and body language clearly communicate the joke’s punchline — the clean-shaven man’s probable inability to grow a beard, contrasted with the bearded man’s pride and relaxed demeanor.'),
 (1113, 'Good Question!, Humor, Puns', 'Whoever invented air conditioning must have been really cool', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon showing a cheerful inventor from the past, wearing old-fashioned clothing and round glasses, standing proudly next to a large, whimsical air conditioning machine. The machine looks a bit exaggerated with big vents blowing out icy cold air, shown with frosty effects and snowflakes. The inventor is surrounded by a few happy, relaxed people cooling off, wearing summer clothes and enjoying the breeze. The background is a sunny outdoor scene with a bright sun and a thermometer showing high temperatures, contrasting with the cold air coming from the machine. The overall tone is lighthearted and fun, with exaggerated, friendly expressions on the characters'' faces to emphasize the joke about the inventor being ''really cool.'''),
 (1114, 'Animals, Love Humor, Relatable', 'Whoever said you can''t buy happiness forgot about little puppies.', NULL, 'A colorful, cheerful cartoon scene featuring a smiling person kneeling on a grassy park lawn, holding a small, adorable fluffy puppy in their arms. The puppy looks happy, wagging its tail enthusiastically. Around them, little hearts and sparkle icons float in the air to emphasize joy and happiness. Nearby, a simple park bench, a tree with green leaves, and a bright blue sky with a shining sun create a lighthearted, warm atmosphere. The person’s face expresses delight and contentment, showing that the puppy is the source of their happiness. The cartoon style is playful and cute, with exaggerated expressions and rounded, soft shapes to enhance the uplifting mood.'),
 (1115, 'Humor, Relatable', 'Whoever snores loudest falls asleep first.', NULL, 'A humorous cartoon scene showing two people in a bedroom at night. Both are lying in separate beds side by side, clearly ready to sleep. One person is wide awake with a big smile, eyes open, looking amused. The other person is already asleep, mouth wide open, exaggeratedly snoring with large comic-style ''Zzz'' symbols emerging. The snore lines are visually loud and almost filling the room, while the awake person appears relaxed and amused. Include little details like a bedside lamp, a clock showing nighttime hours, and a window with a moon outside for context. The overall style should be lighthearted and simple, with exaggerated facial expressions and sound effects to bring out the joke''s punchline about snoring indicating who falls asleep first.'),
 (1116, 'Humor, Pop Culture, Star Wars', 'Why did Star Wars 4,5,6 come before 1,2,3? Because in charge of scheduling, Yoda was.', NULL, 'Draw a humorous cartoon scene featuring Yoda sitting behind a large, cluttered office desk labeled ''Scheduling Department.'' Yoda is wearing oversized round glasses and looking thoughtfully at a big calendar that shows movie release schedules. The calendar humorously lists Star Wars episodes with ''4, 5, 6'' scheduled in the earlier months and ''1, 2, 3'' booked later. In the background, posters of Star Wars movies (episodes 1-6) hang on the wall with the numbers out of order. Yoda holds a pen in one hand and scratches his head with the other in a puzzled and funny manner. Add a small sign on the desk saying ''Master Scheduler Yoda.'' The style should be colorful, cartoony, and lighthearted, emphasizing Yoda''s quirky personality and the joke about his confusing, backwards speech affecting movie release order. Include subtle Star Wars themed items like a lightsaber leaning against the desk and a small spaceship model on the shelf behind him to enhance the setting.'),
 (1117, 'Random', 'Why did the Jedi kill his master? To get to the other side!', NULL, NULL),
