 (1127, 'Random', 'Why Yawning Is Contagious:  You yawn to equalize the pressure on your eardrums. This pressure change outside your eardrums unbalances other people''s ear pressures, so they must yawn to even it out.', NULL, NULL),
 (1128, 'Random', 'WILY''S LAW: n. The only known exception to Newton''s Law of Gravity, Wily''s Law states that an animal or person can suspend himself in midair provided (a) he is in a cartoon, and (b) he doesn''t look down and realize he is no longer on solid ground.', NULL, NULL),
 (1129, 'Random', 'Wisdom is knowing what to do with what you know.', NULL, NULL),
 (1130, 'Random', 'With all the talk of adding Puerto Rico as the 51st state, I feel like we should add two more to be 53 - a prime number. You know how it goes - ''One nation, indivisible''', NULL, NULL),
 (1131, 'Random', 'Without adventure, civilization is in full decay.', NULL, NULL),
 (1132, 'Random', 'Women blink nearly twice as much as men.', NULL, NULL),
 (1133, 'Random', 'Work would be okay but it takes such a big chunk out of your day.', NULL, NULL),
 (1134, 'Random', 'Would you believe...the pyramids in Egypt contain enough stone and mortar to construct a wall ten feet high and five feet wide running from New York City to Los Angeles.', NULL, NULL),
 (1135, 'Random', 'X-CHROMOSOME: A genetic double-cross that empowers women with the ability to bear children and reserves for men the right to be color-blind hemophiliacs.', NULL, NULL),
 (1136, 'Random', 'Yesterday a clown held the door open for me. I thought it was a nice jester.', NULL, NULL),
 (1137, 'Random', 'You always find something in the last place you look.', NULL, NULL),
 (1138, 'Random', 'You are familiar with ''school of fish'' and ''pride of lions'', but what about a ''knot of toads'', an ''exaltation of larks'', and  a ''murder of crows''?', NULL, NULL),
 (1139, 'Random', 'You are more likely to be killed by a Champagne cork than by a poisonous spider.', NULL, NULL),
 (1140, 'Random', 'You are validating my inherant mistrust of strangers.', NULL, NULL),
 (1141, 'Random', 'You can fool some of the people all of the time, and all of the people some of the time, but you can make a fool of yourself anytime.', NULL, NULL),
 (1142, 'Random', 'You can get ANYWHERE in ten minutes if you drive fast enough.', NULL, NULL),
 (1143, 'Random', 'You can never lose a homing pigeon. If it doesn''t come back, it was just a pigeon.', NULL, NULL),
